title: Lives No Longer Ours
synopsis: Directed by Paul Sanderson. With Paul Sanderson, Sterling Walbrook, Robert Bennett, Cliff Jenkins. In 1650 an adventurer returns to his castle to take down his deceased wife's portrait, but his long first night back is filled with revelations about her death. At dawn a swordfight with his prospective brother-in-law finally forces him into coming to terms with his loss.

title: On the Road
synopsis: Directed by Walter Salles. With Sam Riley, Garrett Hedlund, Kristen Stewart, Amy Adams. Young writer Sal Paradise has his life shaken by the arrival of free-spirited Dean Moriarty and his girl, Marylou. As they travel across the country, they encounter a mix of people who each impact their journey indelibly.

title: Nappily Ever After
synopsis: Directed by Haifaa Al-Mansour. With Sanaa Lathan, Ricky Whittle, Lyriq Bent, Lynn Whitfield. Violet Jones tired of waiting for her longtime boyfriend to propose, breaks up with him. But old feelings, and heaps of jealousy, no doubt, arise when he promptly begins dating another woman.

title: Anderson's Cross
synopsis: Directed by Jerome Elston Scott. With Michael Warren, Joanna Cassidy, Joyce Guy, Bill Moseley. Nick Anderson, Kevin Daniels, and Tracey Green do everything together. They are the best of friends, and yet they couldn't be more different. Neighbors from adolescence, they finish each other's thoughts and sentences, joys and pains, happiness and tears. Using Nick's house as their own members only clubhouse, they escape into their own world of contentment. Yet the inevitable intrusion of others tests their stability in ways never imagined.

title: The Giver
synopsis: Directed by Phillip Noyce. With Jeff Bridges, Meryl Streep, Brenton Thwaites, Alexander Skarsgård. In a seemingly perfect community, without war, pain, suffering, differences or choice, a young boy is chosen to learn from an elderly man about the true pain and pleasure of the "real" world.

title: Cargo, les hommes perdus.
synopsis: Directed by Léon Desclozeaux. With Aurélien Recoing, Sukanya Kongkawong, David La Haye, Alain Moussay.

title: Milenge Milenge
synopsis: Directed by Satish Kaushik. With Kareena Kapoor, Shahid Kapoor, Aarti Chhabria, Delnaaz Irani. Hoping that destiny will re-unite them, a couple, on the verge of getting married, attempt to locate each other.

title: Before We Go
synopsis: Directed by Chris Evans. With Chris Evans, Alice Eve, Emma Fitzpatrick, John Cullum. Two strangers stuck in Manhattan for the night grow into each other's most trusted confidants when an evening of unexpected adventure forces them to confront their fears and take control of their lives.

title: The History of Love
synopsis: Directed by Radu Mihaileanu. With Gemma Arterton, Derek Jacobi, Sophie Nélisse, Elliott Gould. The story of a long-lost book that mysteriously reappears and connects an old man searching for his son with a girl seeking a cure for her mother's loneliness.

title: Surviving in L.A.
synopsis: Directed by Abbi Lake O'Neill. With Abbi Lake O'Neill, Jay Huguley, Robert Walden, Ken Kercheval. Kate McCarthy, a former teen sitcom star who trashed her life through drug abuse, is forced to live, fresh out of rehab, on the one remaining piece of property, her business manager, Charlie has kept out of foreclosure - a run-down apartment building in east L.A. With her one remaining trendy friend, Claire, who's still an addict and trapped in a loveless marriage, they are both contemptuous of her new tenants. Walter, is a failed screenwriter, Suzanne, is a nurse trying to keep her teenage son, Jerome away from gangs, Carlos, is an overachieving physics major, Sam is a homeless man living on her front lawn and Mark, her divorced building manager, is getting his veterinarian degree from UCLA. Kate is in total isolation until her dog is wounded during a random drive by shooting. It's then that Mark jumps into action and with grudging support and brutal honesty helps Kate to get back on her feet.

title: A Bird of the Air
synopsis: Directed by Margaret Whitton. With Rachel Nichols, Jackson Hurst, Anjanette Comer, Linda Emond. A man in search of his past, and a woman who lives in the moment, are brought together when they pursue the origins of a stray parrot in this comedic and romantic drama.

title: Blunt Movie
synopsis: Directed by Jason Bunch. With Angie Everhart, Dennis Rodman, Pat Morita, Michael Winslow. Sketch comedy in the tradition of "Kentucky Fried Movie". Several TV commercial and movie parodies, sex, politics and crazy-humor sketches.

title: Hall Pass
synopsis: Directed by Bobby Farrelly, Peter Farrelly. With Owen Wilson, Jason Sudeikis, Jenna Fischer, Christina Applegate. Rick and Fred, two husbands who are having difficulty in their marriages, are given a Hall Pass by their wives

title: Bandage
synopsis: Directed by Takeshi Kobayashi. With Jin Akanishi, Kie Kitano, Kengo Kôra, Ayumi Ito. Four boys have their friendship and musical talents tested in the ever changing worlds of the music industry and real life in 1990s Japan.

title: Barry Munday
synopsis: Directed by Chris D'Arienzo. With Patrick Wilson, Judy Greer, Chloë Sevigny, Jean Smart. Barry Munday wakes up after being attacked to realize that he's missing his family jewels. To make matters worse, he learns he's facing a paternity lawsuit filed by a woman he can't remember having sex with.

title: Something Borrowed
synopsis: Directed by Luke Greenfield. With Ginnifer Goodwin, Kate Hudson, Colin Egglesfield, John Krasinski. Friendships are tested and secrets come to the surface when terminally single Rachel falls for Dex, her best friend Darcy's fiancé.

title: Tulip Fever
synopsis: Directed by Justin Chadwick. With Alicia Vikander, Dane DeHaan, Jack O'Connell, Holliday Grainger. An artist falls for a young married woman while he's commissioned to paint her portrait during the Tulip mania of seventeenth century Amsterdam.

title: Bad Blood
synopsis: Directed by Conrad Janis. With Piper Laurie, Conrad Janis, Bret Anthony, Cori Bright. 9 college students on road trip get waylaid and wind up in deep trouble.

title: Love & Other Drugs
synopsis: Directed by Edward Zwick. With Jake Gyllenhaal, Anne Hathaway, Oliver Platt, Hank Azaria. In 1990s Pittsburgh, a medicine peddler starts a relationship with a young woman suffering from Parkinson's disease.

title: Syrup
synopsis: Directed by Aram Rappaport. With Juan Luis Acevedo, Kirstie Alley, Jolene Andersen, Max Barry. A slacker hatches a million-dollar idea. But, in order to see it through, he has to learn to trust his attractive corporate counterpart. Based on Max Barry's novel.

title: What's Your Number?
synopsis: Directed by Mark Mylod. With Anna Faris, Chris Evans, Ari Graynor, Blythe Danner. A woman looks back at the past nineteen men she's had relationships with in her life and wonders if one of them might be her one true love.

title: She's Out of His Mind
synopsis: Directed by Emmett Loverde. With Bill Mendieta, Tom Schanley, Jennifer Siebel Newsom, Genevieve Zweig. A young man learns to let go of worn-out dreams in order to make room for new love.

title: Night Catches Us
synopsis: Directed by Tanya Hamilton. With Anthony Mackie, Jamara Griffin, Sadiq Afif, Shango Rich. In 1976, complex political and emotional forces are set in motion when a young man returns to the race-torn Philadelphia neighborhood where he came of age during the Black Power movement.

title: Elliot Loves
synopsis: Directed by Terracino. With Antoni Porowski, Robin de Jesus, Alfredo Narciso, Elena Goode. Two stages of a Dominican-American's life; first as a boy trying to bond with his young mother, then a 21-year-old looking for love in New York City.

title: The First Grader
synopsis: Directed by Justin Chadwick. With Naomie Harris, Oliver Litondo, Tony Kgoroge, Alfred Munyua. The story of an 84 year-old Kenyan villager and ex Mau Mau veteran who fights for his right to go to school for the first time to get the education he could never afford.

title: It's Kind of a Funny Story
synopsis: Directed by Anna Boden, Ryan Fleck. With Keir Gilchrist, Dana DeVestern, Lauren Graham, Jim Gaffigan. A clinically-depressed teenager gets a new start after he checks himself into an adult psychiatric ward.

title: Belle Du Seigneur
synopsis: Directed by Glenio Bonder. With Jonathan Rhys Meyers, Natalia Vodianova, Ed Stoppard, Marianne Faithfull. English-language adaptation of Albert Cohen's epic Swiss tale of a tortured love affair between a high-ranking Jewish official and the protestant wife of one of his employees.

title: The Danish Girl
synopsis: Directed by Tom Hooper. With Alicia Vikander, Eddie Redmayne, Tusse Silberg, Adrian Schiller. A fictitious love story loosely inspired by the lives of Danish artists Lili Elbe and Gerda Wegener. Lili and Gerda's marriage and work evolve as they navigate Lili's groundbreaking journey as a transgender pioneer.

title: Dirt Music
synopsis: Directed by Gregor Jordan. With Kelly Macdonald, Garrett Hedlund, Badger, Jacob Clayton. The stunning landscape of Western Australia is the backdrop for an impassioned tale of love and grief in Gregor Jordan's adaptation of the acclaimed novel by Tim Winton.

title: Take Me Home Tonight
synopsis: Directed by Michael Dowse. With Topher Grace, Anna Faris, Dan Fogler, Teresa Palmer. Four years after graduation, an awkward high school genius uses his sister's boyfriend's Labor Day party as the perfect opportunity to make his move on his high school crush.

title: She's Out of My League
synopsis: Directed by Jim Field Smith. With Jay Baruchel, Alice Eve, T.J. Miller, Mike Vogel. An average Joe meets the perfect woman, but his lack of confidence and the influence of his friends and family begin to pick away at the relationship.

title: Flipped
synopsis: Directed by Rob Reiner. With Madeline Carroll, Callan McAuliffe, Rebecca De Mornay, Anthony Edwards. Two eighth-graders start to have feelings for each other despite being total opposites.

title: Valentine's Day
synopsis: Directed by Garry Marshall. With Jessica Alba, Kathy Bates, Jessica Biel, Bradley Cooper. Intertwining couples and singles in Los Angeles break-up and make-up based on the pressures and expectations of Valentine's Day.

title: Manhattan Minutiae
synopsis: Directed by Steve Becker. With Chris Elwood, Linda Shing, Eddie Daniels, Jenni Pulos. A rock & roll romantic comedy set in NYC about the pursuit of love, passion, and the meaning of life, all punctuated by an original, pulsating soundtrack and live performances by the all girl group MaxiTit.

title: Approaching Midnight
synopsis: Directed by Sam Logan Khaleghi. With Jana Kramer, Sam Logan Khaleghi, Brandon T. Jackson, Mia Serafino. US Army Staff Sergeant Wesley Kent returns from the war abroad and must now fight the threat of corruption and deception in his hometown at all personal costs.

title: The Kids Are All Right
synopsis: Directed by Lisa Cholodenko. With Julianne Moore, Annette Bening, Mark Ruffalo, Mia Wasikowska. Two children conceived by artificial insemination bring their biological father into their non-traditional family life.

title: Jack & Diane
synopsis: Directed by Bradley Rust Gray. With Juno Temple, Jackson Ning, Samantha Ives, Anika Jennie Ji. Diane's feelings for Jack -- the girl she met over the summer -- begin to manifest themselves in terrifying ways when she learns that her friend will soon be moving away.

title: Jackson Arms
synopsis: Directed by Nitram Nosirrag. With Matthew O. Sloan, Kim Jiang Dubaniewicz, Luona Wang, Jeff Bredt. A bad-boy bachelor falls for his nemesis and downstairs neighbor, a conservative chinese-american acupuncturist. Just as he becomes more family-oriented, an offensive bet he made about her is revealed, and he must scramble amidst a colorful array of characters to win back her heart. Cinematography by oscar nominee james laxton (moonlight). Shot for under $100,000 in oakland california.

title: Letting Go
synopsis: Directed by Jake Torem. With Jake Torem, Shirly Brener, Luca Bercovici, Greg Baker. Unlucky in love, strangled at work, and tormented at home, Joel Slater is desperately searching for a way to juggle his life. But sometimes, the secret to happiness begins with letting go.

title: Jewtopia
synopsis: Directed by Bryan Fogel. With Austin Abrams, Tom Arnold, Brennan Bailey, Wilmer Calderon. A romantic comedy centered on a gentile who pretends to be Jewish in order to win the affection of his love interest.

title: Eat Pray Love
synopsis: Directed by Ryan Murphy. With Julia Roberts, I. Gusti Ayu Puspawati, Hadi Subiyanto, Billy Crudup. A married woman realizes how unhappy her marriage really is, and that her life needs to go in a different direction. After a painful divorce, she takes off on a round-the-world journey to "find herself".

title: AIR: The Musical
synopsis: The Musical

title: The Switch
synopsis: Directed by Josh Gordon, Will Speck. With Jason Bateman, Victor Pagan, Jennifer Aniston, Jeff Goldblum. Seven years after the fact, a man comes to the realization that he was the sperm donor for his best friend's boy.

title: Movin' In
synopsis: Directed by Griff Furst. With Alex Yves, Griff Furst, Christy Carlson Romano, Estelle Harris. A comedy about a young man from Switzerland who travels to Los Angeles to escape his dead-end life and to reconnect with a female pen pal with whom he has lost touch. Everything falls apart when the pen pal turns out to be a complete fraud and he is reunited with an old friend (a real trouble magnet) who keeps pulling him into the most awkward situations. The story takes unexpected turns when the two - somewhere between moving into an old folks home, going to auditions, and dealing with a phony agent and a group of gangsters - fall for the same girl.

title: The Happy Housewife
synopsis: Directed by Antoinette Beumer. With Carice van Houten, Marcel Hensema, Isis Cabolet, Waldemar Torenstra. After giving birth to her first child, a happily-married woman sees her picture-perfect life spiral out of control.

title: The Devil's Flower
synopsis: Directed by Ekaterina Grokhovskaya. With Marina Golub, Andrey Kharitonov, Olga Khokhlova, Sergey Krapiva.

title: The House of Sun
synopsis: Directed by Garik Sukachyov. With Svetlana Ivanova, Stanislav Ryadinskiy, Darya Moroz, Ivan Stebunov. A young woman (Svetlana Ivanova) meets a hippie leader and finds trouble.

title: L'imbroglio nel lenzuolo
synopsis: Directed by Alfonso Arau. With Geraldine Chaplin, Maria Grazia Cucinotta, Anne Parillaud, Miguel Ángel Silvestre. 1905, the cinematograph has reached Southern Italy, and casts fear among the people to whom it seems a devilish trick. They call it "o 'imbroglie din t'o lenzuolo" - "The Trick in the Sheet", as white sheets were used for screening.

title: Little Fockers
synopsis: Directed by Paul Weitz. With Robert De Niro, Ben Stiller, Owen Wilson, Dustin Hoffman. Family-patriarch Jack Byrnes wants to appoint a successor. Does his son-in-law, the male nurse Greg Focker, have what it takes?

title: Hitchcock
synopsis: Directed by Sacha Gervasi. With Anthony Hopkins, Helen Mirren, Scarlett Johansson, Danny Huston. The relationship between Alfred Hitchcock and his wife Alma Reville during the filming of Психо (1960) in 1959 is explored.

title: Chooriyan
synopsis: Directed by Sukhwant Dhadda. With Vinod Khanna, Sudhanshu Pandey, Mohnish Behl, Vikas Bhalla. Chooriyan is the story of Simran (Gracy Singh), an orphan who has always dreamt of being a part of a family. Her dream finally comes true when Army Office Aman (Sudanshu Pandde) asks her to marry him and she lives happily as part of Aman's family. Aman and Simran cherish every moment before he returns back to his army duty. Before he leaves, Simran makes a vow to him that while he is away, she will always take care of his family as her own. She looks after her invalid father-in-law (Parikshat Sahni) and dotes on her two loving brother-in-laws (Vikas Bhalla and Manish). Aman informs Simran of his plans to come back home on an official visit. Fate has other plans for them. She is informed of Aman's fatal accident on his way home. Her world is shattered as the deep red of the Mehendi that still decorating her hands turns into a deadly shade of white. However, Simran is determined to take care of the family. Despite financial hardships, her two brother-in-laws get married to their respective girlfriends. These wives start to create a rift in the family causing the foundation of the family to crack. Simran and her father-in-law are completely ostracized from the family. With the help of their family friend Besant Singh (Vinod Khanna), Simran starts to regain all that she had lost. Does Simran have the strength to reunite her family? Will she be able to fulfil her promise to her husband or regain all that she lost?

title: Four
synopsis: Directed by Joshua Sanchez. With E.J. Bonilla, Emory Cohen, Aja Naomi King, Wendell Pierce. On a hot 4th of July night, sparks fly between four people as they test the limits and possibilities of their own freedom.

title: Multiple Sarcasms
synopsis: Directed by Brooks Branch. With Timothy Hutton, Mira Sorvino, Dana Delany, Mario Van Peebles. NYC, 1979

title: A Flat
synopsis: Directed by Hemant Madhukar. With Jimmy Shergill, Sanjay Suri, Hazel Croney, Kaveri Jha. A spate of unexpected events jolted Rahul as soon as he landed from U.S. Now, Rahul finds himself trapped in his own flat, completely cut off from the world. The only companion he has is a ghost, a ghost that will not let go of him.

title: Dear John
synopsis: Directed by Lasse Hallström. With Channing Tatum, Amanda Seyfried, Richard Jenkins, Henry Thomas. A romantic drama about a soldier who falls for a conservative college student while he's home on leave.

title: The Significant Other
synopsis: Directed by Shalene Portman. With Brittany Joyner, Donny Boaz, Stephanie Young, Morgana Shaw. When operating a Bed and Breakfast it's better to be married? Or is it? Clara will find that her fictitious husband may cost her the love of her life. Her first guest, Rick, is gorgeous, sweet and single but he thinks she's married. Clara doesn't know how to tell him that she's not really married, and after running into her "husband" with his male lover, Rick doesn't know how to tell her that her husband is gay and cheating on her. The Significant Other is hysterical romp where love checks in and sanity checks out.

title: A Christmas Prince: The Royal Baby
synopsis: Королевское дитя

title: Life Mein Twist Hai
synopsis: Directed by Dinesh Soni. With Sahil Akhtar, Sahil Akhtar, Govind Mishra, Michelle Shah.

title: The Forgotten
synopsis: Directed by Daria Onyshchenko. With Maryna Koshkina, Vasiliy Kukharskiy, Danylo Kamenskyi, Serhiy Smiyan. A Ukrainian language schoolteacher and a rebellious teenage student, both from the eastern city of Luhansk, fall for each other during the tumultuous time of the city's occupation by pro-Russian separatists.

title: Kader Postasi
synopsis: Directed by Çigdem Bozali, Elif Akarsu Polat. With Boncuk Yilmaz, Benian Dönmez, Sahin Ergüney, Rana Kayaçan. The separation from her first love makes Zeynep into a lonesome woman; trying to find her lost love in letters she writes to prison inmates, she is led to one sentenced to life in prison.

title: My Secret Billionaire
synopsis: Directed by Fraydun Manocherian, Fred Manocherian. With Victor Alfieri, Ione Skye, Gerry Bamman, Ivo Velon. Hilarity ensues when a handsome businessman goes undercover in New York City as a "Homeless Billionaire."

title: Ispade Rajavum Idhaya Raniyum
synopsis: Directed by Ranjit Jeyakodi. With Harish Kalyan, Shilpa Manjunath, Ma ka Pa Anand, Makapa Anand. The relationship between a guy and a girl becomes complicated when the latter gets tired of the former's impatient behaviour.

title: The Protector
synopsis: Directed by Tosca Musk. With Emma Catherine Rigby, Rachel Allinson, David Bamber, Louise Bangay. Based on the novel by best selling author, Jodi Ellen Malpas.

title: Sweet Face
synopsis: Directed by Kayode Kasum. With Andrianna Adebiyi, Ademola Adedoyin, Twitch Badmus, Manual Coker. ....is a narrative that takes place over the life span of a married couple, their adorable love story starting from how they meet as youths, become friends, their courtship, their marriage and the difficulties they encounter.. they can't imagine their lives without each other until the hiccups and road bumps life throws at them. they struggle to get through the rough patch as they hope their marriage survives the pressure.

title: Love Aaj Kal
synopsis: Directed by Imtiaz Ali. With Kartik Aaryan, Sara Ali Khan, Randeep Hooda, Sonu Saini. When professional ambitions clash with personal feelings for a modern-day couple, a love story from a bygone era may offer some wisdom.

title: Simple Passion
synopsis: Directed by Danielle Arbid. With Laetitia Dosch, Sergei Polunin, Lou-Teymour Thion, Caroline Ducey. A mother falls into an addictive relationship with a Russian diplomat, with whom she has nothing in common.

title: Ringolevio
synopsis: Directed by Kristin Peterson Kaszubowski. With Nicole Velasco Lockard, Meredith Johnston, Joshua Koopman, Cory Hardin. Ada, a reserved young woman with a passion for entomology, travels north to meet her girlfriend's family, but struggles to find common ground.

title: Stay
synopsis: Directed by Hellene Alabi-Williams. With Hellene Alabi-Williams, Neils Williams, Sagirah Young, Anthony Brady. An American one-hit wonder finds love in a Nigerian gospel singer.

title: Premay Namaha
synopsis: Directed by Jagdish Keshav Vatharkar. With Devendra Chaugule, Narendra Desai, Prakash Dhotre, Roopali Krishnarao.

title: Rangeela Raybaa
synopsis: Directed by Kedar Shinde. With Alhad Arvind Andore, Tushar Bhaskar, Kishore Chougule, Mayur Dalvi. Rayaba, an aimless guy who fails in 12th-grade exams, falls in love with Shraddha, a state topper and the daughter of a health quality inspector. After a lot of wooing, Rayaba manages to win Shraddha's heart and when her father comes to know about their relationship he agrees for their marriage but on the condition that Rayba passes the test put by him. Whilst attempting to pass the test, Shraddha's father creates several hindrances and every time clears a level he is faced with a bigger challenge.

title: Spandan What is Relationship
synopsis: Directed by Shailesh Narayan Kulkarni. With Shailesh Narayan Kulkarni, Prasann Pawar, Vaishali Shah. Spandan is an emotional roller coaster that has elements of laughter, joy, and tears. It showcases how in the modern day the increased usage of social networking platforms has affected the family relationships and how it has created a sense of void among the family members.

title: Zvyozdy svetyat vsem
synopsis: Directed by Aleksandr Kananovich. With Ilya Kapanets, Kostya Kapskiy, Andrey Karako, Evelina Sakuro.

title: Shao nv tian shi
synopsis: Directed by Zhenhao Zhao. With Wenting Hao, Fangxi Shen, Haoyu Wang.

title: Premak Basaat
synopsis: Directed by Rupak Sharar. With Rajeev Jha, S.C. Mishra, Ashutosh Sagar, Rupak Sharar.

title: Luxor
synopsis: Directed by Zeina Durra. With Andrea Riseborough, Michael Landes, Shereen Reda, Karim Saleh. When British aid worker Hana returns to the ancient city of Luxor, she meets former lover Sultan. As she wanders, haunted by the familiar place, she struggles to reconcile the choices of the past with the uncertainty of the present.

title: El verano que vivimos
synopsis: Directed by Carlos Sedes. With Blanca Suárez, Javier Rey, Pablo Molinero, María Pedraza. Isabel is a journalism student who is in the journal of a Galician coastal town for her work placement. During her stay, she finds an anonymous obituary dedicated to Lucía. It tells a love, friendship and treason story in 1958.

title: Odd Love
synopsis: Directed by Julian Berger. With Julian Berger, Isabella Dake, Rachael Gula, Hudson Klass. After graduating high school, Quinn realizes he has one last chance to tell his long-time crush, Audrey, how he really feels.

title: Between Maybes
synopsis: Directed by Jason Paul Laxamana. With Gerald Anderson, Julia Barretto, Yayo Aguila, Christian Vasquez. While on vacation in Japan, a Filipina actress meets a young Filipino man.

title: Gail's New Boyfriend
synopsis: Directed by Jim Mendrinos. With Jordan Paige Aanrud, Aria Avilia, Benny Benowitz, Laura Bolivar. New Media Comedy presents the most unusual love story of all time. Gail is human. Her new boyfriend is not. Can a woman and a ventriloquist's dummy find true love in NYC? Check out Amanda Nicholas and her co-star "Jack" as they give you a taste of the RomCom as you've never seen it before!

title: James & Pat & Dave
synopsis: Directed by Theodore Boborol. With Ronnie Alonte, Loisa Andalio, Donny Pangilinan, Awra Briguela. It follows Pat Reyes who is a hardworking hostel manager and online vegetable seller who trains her boss' hardheaded and exiled grandson as a hostel employee.

title: Angel Sign
synopsis: Directed by Kamila Andini, Masatsugu Asahi, Tsukasa Hôjô, Nonzee Nimibutr, Ken Ochiai, Ham Tran. With Abigail, Neennara Boonbithipaisit, Dean Fujioka, Phiphob Kamolketsophon. Two musician lovers dream of composing a melody that will move the world.

title: My Second Year in College
synopsis: Directed by Rasoul Sadrameli. With Soha Niasti, Fereshte Arastouie, Ali Mosaffa, Pedram Sharifi. Mahtab and Ava are classmates in their second year of college studying engineering. The story begin when they and other classmates go on a trip to Esfahan.

title: Jaddi Sardar
synopsis: Directed by Manbhavan Singh. With Guggu Gill, Sippy Gill, Dilpreet Dhillon, Sawan Rupowali. After a misunderstanding among their parents, two brothers turn against one another.

title: Goa Girls
synopsis: Directed by Krishna Prasad. With Navya, Ranjith, Vaidehi. Goa Girls is about Priya who is married to a millionaire and has an illegal affair with her PA Aravind. To lead a happy life they plan to kill Priya's husband. Twist in the tale arises when Priya herself gets killed. Finding the killer and the motive behind it forms the rest of the story.

title: Mantan Manten
synopsis: Directed by Farishad I. Latjuba. With Atiqah Hasiholan, Arifin Putra, Tutie Kirana, Tio Pakusadewo. A wealthy woman is betrayed and all her wealth is gone. Her marriage plan is also in danger. But, she still has a villa as her only hope. To take the villa back, she had to become an assistant to a traditional bride shaman.

title: Stealing Belmondo
synopsis: With Anna Bondareva, Aleksandr Pankratov-Chyornyy, Sergey Zhuravel, Vladimir Mishchanchuk. The writer is on the wave of success, as he is approaching a creative stagnation. Trying to escape from his crisis, he makes a bet with the publisher that in 3 months, he'll finish his new novel. He surely wants the woman he loves back.

title: Eigaban Futari ecchi: Rabu agein
synopsis: Rabu agein

title: Last Fool Show
synopsis: Directed by Eduardo W. Roy Jr.. With Arci Muñoz, JM de Guzman, Snooky Serna, Bibeth Orteza. After several box-office flops, an independent filmmaker is encouraged to make a commercial romantic comedy that mirrors her own relationship.

title: Classic Again
synopsis: Directed by Thatchaphong Suphasri. With Thitipoom Techaapaikhun, Ranchrawee Uakoolwarawat, Gee Sutthirak Subvijitra, Tong Samitpong Sakulpongchai. In a love triangle that miraculously mirrors her mother's romance years ago, a young woman lets her heart lead.

title: Taxi, What's Your Name?
synopsis: Directed by Tuan Vu Dinh, Duc Thinh. With Truong Giang, Angela Phuong Trinh, Khanh Hien, Isidi Shahini. After a missed flight, an absent-minded scientist must catch a cab to make his marriage proposal but a stern driver veers him further off-course.

title: Manmadhudu 2
synopsis: Directed by Rahul Ravindran. With Nagarjuna Akkineni, Rakul Preet Singh, Vennela Kishore, Rao Ramesh. Under pressure to marry, a perennial bachelor hires a much younger woman to act as his fiancée, but her bond with his family throws his plan for a loop.

title: Single & Ready
synopsis: Directed by David C. Snyder. With Bre'Ana Nix, LaToy Fowler, Alexander Cantrell, David C. Snyder. When Latanya gets dumped by her boyfriend thru a text message, her wacky roommate persuades her to try online dating in this interracial dramedy from Executive Producer Johnny Swirl.

title: Verano no miente
synopsis: Directed by Ernesto Santisteban. With Pilar Tordera, Juan Carlos Rey de Castro, Pamela Sánchez, Nando Romero. In a countryside house located in the Ecuadorean Andes Mountains lives Christine, a paralytic old woman who has decided to be isolated from the world. In that place, she found refuge in old memories of her first love, Manuel. Years after getting married and widowed from another man, Christine and her daughter, Julia, decide to put together a plan in order to reunite two young people at their countryside house. Christine's drive is for them to fall in love, so she can relive love through their eyes. Consequently, Julia meets Angie, a literature student, and Santiago, an artist dedicated to restoring religious art. Christine is not even close to imagining the amazing journey that awaits her with both of them. As the story goes on, more peculiar characters join them on this unpredictable voyage. For instance, Su, an eccentric girl; Don Curador, an art professor; and, an old man from Luxembourg.

title: Pansamantagal
synopsis: Directed by Joven Tan. With Gelli de Belen, Bayani Agbayani, Chacha, Ronnie Lazaro.

title: 49 Days 2
synopsis: Directed by Nhat Trung, Vo Thanh Hoa. With Ngo Kien Huy, Hari Won, Viet Huong, Mac Van Khoa.

title: Until You
synopsis: Directed by Tuan Vu Dinh. With Tran Thanh, Nguy Thien An, Will, Lilly Nguyen. A magical encounter leaves a young woman with a dog that must help her romance a pop star in order to transform back into a human.

title: Healing Mate
synopsis: Directed by Sin Jong-Geol. With Hye-Kyeong Jin.

title: Wild Grass
synopsis: Directed by Xu Zhanxiong. With Ye Gao, Johnny Huang, Sichun Ma, Vivienne Tien. In the 1990s, the two girls and a boy who first entered the society tested the incredible destiny they experienced in the pursuit of a new life. In the flourishing 1990s, they rose up with the dream and they survived.

title: Killing Sarai
synopsis: Directed by Matías Moltrasio. With William Levy, Dalisa Alegria, Mónica Ayos, Ettore D'Alessandro. Victor (William Levy) has a deep secret - he is a cold-blooded assassin. Smooth talking and seductive, Victor was raised to do one thing only, which is to kill for money. When he is sent to the home of a brutal drug lord to collect payment for his most recent hit, he encounters the beautiful Sarai (Alicia Sanz), who has been forced to spend the last 9 years of her life with the drug lord. After Victor leaves the compound, Sarai seizes her chance at freedom by hiding out in Victor's car. But things don't go as planned and instead of being transported back to her home, she finds herself free from one dangerous man only to be caught in the clutches of another. While on the run from the vengeful drug lord and his brutal henchmen, Victor's conscience catches up with him as he risks all that he stood for to protect his captive. In the end, the power Sarai unknowingly holds over Victor and their undeniable attraction may be what places her right in the arms of a killer.

title: Amalu
synopsis: Directed by L. Ravi Kumar. With Kavya, Bhanu Prakash. It is about the things that happen due to alcohol addiction. Raghuram joins army and gets killed by enemy army. His father then gets addicted to alcohol to kill his pain. But Raghuram shocks everyone as he returns home safe. His father then continues his rest of life spending with alcohol.

title: The Call of Destiny
synopsis: Directed by Ta Huy Cuong. With Huy Khanh, Van Phuong, Hieu Hien, Dj Oxy.

title: Chandigarh Amritsar Chandigarh
synopsis: Directed by Karaan Guliani. With Dilpreet Dhillon, Gippy Grewal, Ankit Kumar, Sargun Mehta. While on her way from Chandigarh to Amritsar to sabotage her own wedding, a woman encounters a stranger who spends the day with her despite their obvious differences.

title: Auerhaus
synopsis: Directed by Neele Leana Vollmar. With Piet Fuchs, Damian Hardung, Sabine Holzloehner, Greta Hubert. Four troubled friends who despite the feeling that they live standardized lives share a flat under the sceptical looks of their neighbours.

title: Vinara sodara veera kumara
synopsis: Directed by Sateesh Chandra Nadella. With Priyanka Jain, Priyanka Jain, Jhansi, Jhansi. Ramana falls in love with Sulochana but their relationship fails to materialize due to which he decides to end his life. He then meets a soul that communicates with him to make him realize the importance of life over love.

title: The Secret of the River
synopsis: Directed by Rui Zhang. With Peng Chi, Qingxiang Wang, Nannan Xu, Guo'er Zhangyang. Shi Guiqing, who raised her daughter alone, suddenly passed away. When her daughter Shi Xiaowei picked up her belongings, she found a group photo which showed some clues to set her on the way to find her father.

title: Tausiyah Cinta
synopsis: Directed by Humar Hadi. With Rendy Herpy, Irwansyah, Ressa Rere, Hamas Syahid.

title: War of the Youth: Love Reload
synopsis: Love Reload

title: Impossible to Imagine
synopsis: Directed by Felicity Tillack. With Yukiko Ito, William Yagi, Kazuya Moriyama. The story of a traditional, Kyoto woman who runs a failing, kimono business and the biracial entrepreneur who comes to help keep it solvent. Along the way they fall in love but his need for change clashes with her desire for the world to stay the same.

title: Street Stall
synopsis: Directed by Kweon-Hyi Choi-Yool. With Chae-dam Lee, Jae-Wook Choi, Hong-je Kim, Soo-Hyeon Go.

title: Mamo, ya lotchyka lyublyu
synopsis: Directed by Aleksandr Ignatusha. With Darya Botsmanova, Yana Glushchenko, Lyubava Greshnova, Mikhail Kukuyuk.

title: Stranded
synopsis: Directed by Ice Idanan. With Jessy Mendiola, Arjo Atayde, Miko Raval, Gretchen Ho. It follows a career-oriented girl whose priorities have always been clear for her, even if it compromises the things she really wants to do. When a typhoon worsens while she's at work, she finds herself trapped inside the building with a food delivery guy, whose background is also more complicated than he looks. While stranded, the two learns more about each other's lives, and soon will also learn some things about themselves and their feelings.

title: The Twins
synopsis: Directed by Jin-seong Kim. With Duling Chen, Haoran Liu, Rui Zhao. A mystery melodrama which deals with the bizarre incidents that unfold in a mountain cabinet.

title: One on One
synopsis: With Yoon Se-na.

title: To Her
synopsis: With Yoo Ji-won, Hanna, Kim Jong-sin.

title: Younger Sister-in-law
synopsis: With Kim Seon-I. Ga-eun, who is traveling alone after breaking up with her boyfriend, happens to stop by her cousin Ga-young's house. Ga-eun and Ga-young, who have been like her real sisters when they were young.

title: Dil Sada Luteya Gaya
synopsis: Directed by Hardeep Badowal. With Rhythm Arora, Patel Ashmit, Rana Jung Bahadur, Jonita Doda. A Rom Com revolving around Angad (Ashmit Patel) who is forced by his two Fathers by whom he was adopted to get married to the girl of their choices. On the contrary two best friends (Jividha Aastha) and (Pooja Tandon) fall for Angad and he plans to take both of them to his house and who so ever wins the Fathers heart, Angad will marry her. Drama unfolds in an emotional climax. Screenplay & Dialogue Writer

title: Dhumas
synopsis: Directed by Shivaji Doltande. With Sakshi Chaudhary, Krutika Gaikwad, Bharat Ganeshpure, Vishal Nikam. Dhumas is a Marathi movie starring Vishal Nikkam, Krutika Gaikwad, Gopichand Padalkar in prominent roles. It is a drama directed by Shivaji Doltade.

title: Bhetali Tu Punha
synopsis: Directed by Chandrakant Kanse, Ajit Sable. With Pooja Sawant, Vaibhav Tatwawadi. Two youngsters meet each other, one falls in love the other doesn't; and then they meet again.

title: Cocoon
synopsis: Directed by Leonie Krippendorff. With Lena Urzendowsky, Jella Haase, Lena Klenke, Elina Vildanova. Nora from Berlin struggles with growing up and her own identity. Her sister and her best friend are only interested in fashion and social media. Nora tries to do the same, but it does not make her happy. Then she meets Romy.

title: Always a Bridesmaid
synopsis: Directed by Trey Haley. With Javicia Leslie, Jordan Calloway, Yvette Nicole Brown, Michelle Mitchenor. Corina is stuck being everyone's bridesmaid. Deciding to no longer be a lady-in-waiting, she bravely re-enters the dating scene. Will she always be a bridesmaid or could the love of her life be right around the corner?

title: Rose and Tulip
synopsis: Directed by Teruo Noguchi. With Hwang Chan-sung, Eri Fuse, Hyunri, Jun-Ho Lee. An acclaimed painter travels to Japan for an exhibition where he takes advantage of his free time to enjoy a Japanese bath or onsen. However, there is more to it than that. He is told that the owner of the bath has a false work of his. He meets a look-alike at the bath and the situation lends itself to what comes next.

title: Up to You
synopsis: Directed by Hideo Jôjô. With Yukihira Aika, Yûki Ashida, Yamane Chiharu, Katsuya Maiguma. There is a man who has many sex slaves. Another man offers his wife as a sex slave to him and the slave owner agrees. He adds the man's wife to his stable. Alas, the husband comes to reverse his decision and takes his wife back. The reversal of the arrangement causes trauma.

title: Fishing and Fishermen's Conversations
synopsis: Directed by Milan Trenc. With Rade Serbedzija, Leon Lucev, Bojan Brajcic, Romina Tonkovic. A nobleman poet embarks on a boat trip with two local fishermen. As they hop the bucolic islands, he recalls his youthful tragic love and his artistic impotence while the uneasy relationship with common fishermen evolves..

title: Schmetterlinge
synopsis: Directed by Sebastian Jobst. With Jannis Hain, Daphne Heil, Sebastian Jobst.

title: A Rock N' Roll Heart
synopsis: Directed by Travis Greer. With Travis Greer, Sommer Branham, Jill K. Allen, James Lantiegne. A dog walker by day and writer by night searches for love and fame in a society distracted by technology.

title: Odessa
synopsis: Directed by Valeriy Todorovskiy, Irina Tretyakova. With Evgeniy Tsyganov, Leonid Yarmolnik, Irina Rozanova, Kseniya Rappoport. Odessa, August 1970. A heat wave. The city is full of tourists. Boris and his eight-year-old son Valeri arrive from Moscow to visit his pensioner in-laws, Grigori and Raisa. Their daughters, Mira and Lora and their husbands, Arik and Volodya respectively and children are also there on vacation. His wife is the middle daughter and would come later. It is a Jewish family. Arik is a slobber and Volodya a quiet drunk. Something doesn't smell like love. On the day of their arrival, Odessa declares a quarantine due to a cholera outbreak, and the city is closed off. Boris is a true international journalist and a real import, metropolitan little thing. He drives women and girls in Odessa crazy with his metropolitan gloss. Having come for a few days, the son-in-law is plunged into a world changed by serious danger. Family secrets will be disclosed, improbable events happen, and a great forbidden love starts.

title: The Perfect Secret
synopsis: Directed by Bora Dagtekin. With Wotan Wilke Möhring, Jessica Schwarz, Elyas M'Barek, Karoline Herfurth. Seven friends--three women and four men--meet for dinner. Everyone must put their cell phones on the table. No matter what message comes in, anyone can read it and listen to the phone calls. However, this leads to a lot of chaos.

title: Foreign Love
synopsis: Directed by Eboni Adams, Ben Chiadika. With Kc Ejelonu, James Akingbade, Maura Antas, Brittney Ayona Clemons. An American college student and a brilliant Nigeria girl fall in love and must work to bridge their cultural differences in order to defy the odds and stay together.

title: No Storybook Love
synopsis: Directed by James Slorf. With Gareth Root, Miko Coffey, Evan Judway, Shelby Daeffler. Oliver is a boy who knows what he has, but not what he wants. Samantha is a girl who knows what she wants, but not what she has. When the two of them break up, both are devastated. Oliver knows that he wants nothing more than to "win her back," but how can he do that when he was the one who caused the breakup in the first place? He'll try his best with a little help and advice, from storybook characters that only he can see. As Don Quixote, Maid Marian, and others try to get him back on his feet, Oliver must answer a question for himself

title: Holiday Heist
synopsis: Directed by Roger M. Bobb. With Chaley Rose, Tobias Truvillion, Phillip Edward Van Lear, Lucien Cambric. A man released from prison is torn between a life of crime and a fresh start with a woman he meets while scoping out a potential heist

title: Hello, Love, Goodbye
synopsis: Directed by Cathy Garcia-Molina. With Kathryn Bernardo, Alden Richards, Maymay Entrata, Maricel Laxa. A bartender romances a domestic helper despite the fact that she is moving to Canada.

title: Single 2
synopsis: Directed by Raditya Dika. With Raditya Dika, Annisa Rawles, Yoga Arizona, Ridwan Remin. Ebi is going towards 30 years old and still single. Now, Ebi is determined that before his 30th birthday he must release his single status. He must have a girlfriend. Even though he doesn't know how to do it at all.

title: Liberation
synopsis: Directed by Danial Hajibarat. With Arash Soleimani, Aram Yousefinia, Bijan Ganjali, Danial Hajibarat. Arsalan has huge problem with his father and he wants to tell his fiance (Raha). But he looses his chance to ... At this time Raha accepted the propose offer of other man, without telling Arsalan And also Arsalan find out something about his father at home that lead to...

title: National Theater Live: Cyrano de Bergerac
synopsis: Directed by Jamie Lloyd, Tony Grech-Smith. With James McAvoy, Anita-Joy Uwajeh, Eben Figueiredo, Michele Austin. An intense, raw and deep revival of Rostand's Cyrano de Bergerac by the Jamie Lloyd Company.

title: The Cursed
synopsis: Directed by Joel Bender. With Louis Mandylor, Brad Thornton, Costas Mandylor, Francesca Cecil. A supernatural thriller set in a cozy Tennessee town where Sheriff Jimmy Muldoon and younger brother, Deputy Lloyd Muldoon, have a firm grasp of law and order until a stranger, Denny White, comes to town and horrible things begin to happen. - James Clark, Southern Standard

title: Prime of Your Life
synopsis: Directed by Kelly L. King. With Ryan Donowho, Brett Rice, Jim R. Coleman, Nicole Abisinio. A 20-something slacker girl meets a handsome rebel at her best friend's funeral. She partners up with him and through a series of cons, finds her path to independence and love.

title: Prem Amar 2
synopsis: Directed by Bidula Bhattacharjee. With Eyasin Arafat, Rakibul Hasan Mahmud, Faysal Mia, Shoud Bin Nahin. Prem Amar 2 is the love story of two young souls Apurba (Pujja Cherry Roy) and Joy (Adrit Roy) who meet each other in college and fall in love. Incidentally, they turn out to be neighbours as well. Thus, begins an innocent love story that grows inside the college and blooms in the terrace.

title: Christmas Coupon
synopsis: Directed by Daniel Knudsen. With Courtney Mathews, Aaron Noble, Robert Laenen, Sheena Monnin. Alison Grant begins teaching ice skating students on a friend's frozen pond after being fired from her rink job. On the first day of class her old high school sweetheart and now famous hockey player, Ivan Hall, unexpectedly shows up when he brings his niece for her skating lessons. While an initially cold reunion ensues, eventually Alison warms up to Ivan again. Dove Family Approved for all ages.

title: Fair Haven
synopsis: Directed by Samantha Nolte. With Bobby McGruther, Amandalyn McLellan, Brian McGurk, Bailey Smart-Zimmerman. After being gone for eleven years, a burnt out hardcore vocalist returns to his small, New Jersey hometown, in the wake of his father's death during the holidays.

title: E Ee
synopsis: Directed by Ram Ganapati Rao, Ram Ganpati Rao. With Neirah Sham, Naira Shah, Sudhakar, Krishna Bhagavan. E Ee is about Siddhu (Neiraj Sham,) who hates women. Hasini (Naira Shah,) who detests men, joins Siddhu's company and trouble starts brewing, as the two don't get along. On a company trip, Siddhu and Hasini get into a heated argument and Siddhu insults all women. This is overheard by a Swami, who curses them both. Siddhu's and Hasini's souls are interchanged. Does this bring the two closer?

title: Belle Douleur
synopsis: Directed by Joji Alonso. With Mylene Dizon, Marlon Rivera, Jenny Jamora, Vlad Del Rosario. Belle Douleur tells the story of a woman's journey of finding happiness as she breaks free from the confines of society that shackles women.

title: Finding You
synopsis: Directed by Easy Ferrer. With Jerome Ponce, Jane Oineza, Barbie Imperial, Sue Ramirez. Nel never forgets, literally. His condition called Hyperthymesia makes him remember everything in the past, and he uses it for his work as a journalist. He is plunged into an enigmatic journey when one day, his social media account pops up throwback posts he supposedly wrote about a girl who apparently broke his heart. Philippines Tagalog movie.

title: Man & Wife
synopsis: Directed by Laurice Guillen. With Gabby Concepcion, Jodi Sta. Maria, Amy Austria, Liza Lorena. Carding and Luisa are a married couple torn between their love for each other and issues of their respective families.

title: My Best Summer
synopsis: Directed by Disa Zhang. With Arthur Chen, Haha He, Kara Wai, Huimin Tao. Geng Geng was an ordinary girl before her entry to the best high school in the province by chance. She doesn't like her life there until she meets Yu Huai, her seatmate--their names make up the phrase "Geng geng yu huai", which means "Unforgettable memories".

title: Jee Chahta Hai
synopsis: Directed by Ganesh Mehta. With Tarun Anand, Priyanka Burman, Sachin Sharma, Kavita Tiwari. Story of a man whose college love marries his brother and then he slowly falls in love with the younger sister of his now brothers wife.

title: The Love Between Us
synopsis: Directed by Christian Igbinovia. With Ikenna Alily, Carl Allen Jr., Raz Ayer, Joseph Benjamin. This is the story of a young, immigrant couple, whose love is tested by real life struggles and challenges on a foreign soil.

title: Atlantics
synopsis: Directed by Mati Diop. With Mame Bineta Sane, Amadou Mbow, Traore, Nicole Sougou. In a popular suburb of Dakar, workers on the construction site of a futuristic tower, without pay for months, decide to leave the country by the ocean for a better future. Among them is Souleiman, the lover of Ada, promised to another.

title: Adoring
synopsis: Directed by Larry Yang. With William Chan, Wallace Chung, Yi Ding, Bu Fanfan. Star-studded holiday ensemble comedy about pets and their owners lives.

title: Ichigo no uta
synopsis: Directed by Shintarô Sugawara. With Yûtarô Furutachi, Shizuka Ishibashi, Emi Wakui, Ken Mitsuishi. Kota is employed at a frozen food factory and plant. his school-mate and friend Shinji died while leaping to the aid of Sennichi for whom they both had admiration. It was a sacrifice and a dismal moment at the same time. Ten years have passed and it should all be in the rear view mirror now, but then Kota and Snnichi run into one another.

title: Kiss Me at the Stroke of Midnight
synopsis: Directed by Takehiko Shinjô. With Ryôta Katayose, Kanna Hashimoto, Gordon Maeda, Alissa Yagi. A stern young girl who yearns for romance, finds herself involved with a celebrity whose image reveals a hidden persona.

title: Little Love Song
synopsis: Directed by Kôjirô Hashimoto. With Katrina Bourdo, Leigh Carmichael, Tomiko Claire, Kazuhiko Kanayama. Inspired by a hit song by Mongol800, there is a small town in Okinawa where the US occupation forces are stationed and have fenced off their base. A popular high school band is scouted by a Tokyo-based record company. The band is involved in a car accident, however, shattering many hopes. The band receives a demo tape from a girl who lives on the navy base. They are reinvigorated.

title: Certified Copy
synopsis: Directed by Abbas Kiarostami. With Juliette Binoche, William Shimell, Jean-Claude Carrière, Agathe Natanson. In Tuscany to promote his latest book, a middle-aged British writer meets a French woman who leads him to the village of Lucignano. While there, a chance question reveals something deeper.

title: Love in America
synopsis: Directed by John Shike. With Nabil Shike. When a well educated Muslim Pakistani can not find a job in Pakistan, he migrates to the United States for work and falls in love with a young lady from the Hindu religion. Due to conflicting religions, the marriage is not allowed by the families, however Love prevails in the end.

title: Mogra Phulaalaa
synopsis: Directed by Shrabani Deodhar. With Dipti Bhagawat, Madhuri Bharti, Sanyogita Bhave, Umesh Damle. A Very uniquely blended love story of different kind which revolves around a boy who so deeply involved in family matters, that he has crossed his age of marriage. Until one day when he falls in love with a very strong and independent women and realises his love for her as they belong to two different world.

title: Yeo-ja, nam-ja
synopsis: Directed by Ji-na Kang, Woo Moon-gi, Yeon-Shick Shin. With Baro, Mi-yeon Lee. A collected-works compilation featuring three short films, "Geu-ge a-ni-go/Not That", "Hear My Song", "Seul-peun ssin/Sad Song", by contemporary South Korean filmmakers and produced by fashion magazine W Korea on its 10th year anniversary.

title: The Perfect Mistress III.
synopsis: Directed by Magdolna Cecília Eröss. With Ileana Toma, Andrea Ivett Eröss, László Székely-Benczédi, Veaceslav Grosu.

title: Love in Suspenders
synopsis: Directed by Yohanan Weller. With Yehuda Barkan, Nitza Shaul, Shlomo Bar-Aba, Gabi Amrani. Tami is a widow in her 60s and Beno is a widower in his 70s. They are both still suffering from the loss of their loved ones, but disregarding their differences in lifestyle and personality, they eventually fall in love.

title: Edakkad Battalion 06
synopsis: Directed by Swapnesh K. Nair. With Tovino Thomas, Samyuktha Menon, Shalu Rahim, Karthik Vishnu. Shafeek's father wanted him to become a chef, but he chose to serve his country instead. On his annual leave from work, Shafeek, now a young soldier, must deal with his family, his bride to be and a gang involved in illegal activities.

title: As I Am
synopsis: Directed by Anthony Bawn. With Andre Myers, Jerimiyah Dunbar, Rodney Chester, Tom McLaren. A story of a young man running from the truth about his childhood returns in order to correct his past but ends up discovering a side of himself that he suppressed.

title: Dwelling in the Fuchun Mountains
synopsis: Directed by Xiaogang Gu. With Zhenyang Dong, Hongjun Du, Wei Mu, Luqi Peng. A feature film shot over the course of two years intended to capture the changing of the seasons along the river in a town in the Fuyang district of Hangzhou city.

title: Sick, Sick, Sick
synopsis: Directed by Alice Furtado. With Sílvia Buarque, Luiza Kosovski, Lourenço Mutarelli, Ismar Tirelli Neto. An introspective young girl falls for the new boy in class, an outcast who is also a hemophiliac.

title: You Deserve a Lover
synopsis: Directed by Hafsia Herzi. With Hafsia Herzi, Djanis Bouzyani, Jérémie Laheurte, Anthony Bajon. After Rémi's infidelity, Lila has a hard time dealing with their break-up. One day, he announces that he will travel alone to Bolivia to try to understand his mistakes.

title: A Fight for the Good Guy
synopsis: Directed by Monique Teagle. With TiAunna Alsup, Frank Fjay Bateman Jr., Sunni Brown, Eric Coleman. Local barber find himself having to choose between a long-term relationship or the unexpected relationship he encounters with one of his clients.

title: Burning Ghost
synopsis: Directed by Stéphane Batut. With Thimotée Robart, Judith Chemla, Saadia Bentaïeb, Djolof Mbengue. In the streets of Paris, Juste collects the last memory of people only he can see, before helping them into the afterlife. Juste is a ghost. But one day Agathe recognizes him. She knew him when he was alive.

title: Timelife
synopsis: Directed by Hamid Benamra. With Stephanie Benamra, Mohamed Malas, Marie-Christine Darah, Sébastien Benoist. A poet chooses to give birth alone at home surrounded by characters pregnant with their dreams. The narrative takes root in each moment of reality. The truth extracted from context is fictionalized. A way of staging life.

title: The Bare Necessity
synopsis: Directed by Erwan Le Duc. With Swann Arlaud, Maud Wyler, Fanny Ardant, Nicolas Maury. Captain Pierre Perdrix's life has been turned upside down since the enigmatic Juliette Webb burst into his life. Her presence alone will force his tight-knit family to redefine their boundaries and finally begin to fully live their lives.

title: Love Me, Love Me Not
synopsis: Directed by Takahiro Miki. With Minami Hamabe, Yûki Furukawa, Takumi Kitamura, Eiji Akaso. The love affairs of four schoolkids

title: My First Summer
synopsis: Directed by Katie Found. With Arthur Angel, Markella Kavenagh, Steve Mouzakis, Maiah Stewardson. Isolated Claudia hides away on a remote property after her mother's death. Shocked when spirited local teen Grace appears in her garden, the pair find support and love in each other.

title: Sparks
synopsis: Directed by Ryan Lesica, Donovan Russo. With Nidhi Subbaiah, Michael Brueno. A broken couple inevitably question the meaning of their relationship while on a drive.

title: Rok Sako To Rok Lo
synopsis: Directed by Kashif Saleem. With Mehmood Aslam, Hina Dilpazir, Kinza Hashmi, Jawed Sheikh.

title: Still Today
synopsis: Directed by Tommy Walton. With Teri Wyble, Carlos Aviles, Hunter Burke, Mark Ashworth. After being left at the altar, Pete's groomsman give him a wedding gift he'll never forget. An escort. Maybe it's the Lunar Eclipse, maybe it's fate, but after a magical night in the city maybe this girl is what Pete needed all along.

title: Huway Hum Jin Kay Liye Barbaad
synopsis: Directed by Mohammad Iftikhar Iffi. With Rubina Ashraf, Aijaz Aslam, Sara Bhatti, Behroze Sabzwari. When Anju falls obsessively in love with Hashim, little does she know that he is actually a Jin. 'Huway Hum Jin Kay Liye Barbaad' is a supernatural romantic comedy about an unexpected otherworldly love affair.

title: Feminin
synopsis: Directed by Mani Nouri. With Fereshteh Alousi, Nastaran Parsaian, Fatemeh Neyshabouri. Nothing behind, no where to go and stuck in a house with unknown people... This is a story of middle eastern immigrants on their way to Europe. Three generations of women, three different life-styles and philosophy in a home that doesnt really belong to any of them. The house, more than anything else, symbolizes the current situation in Iran, feeling trapped and surounded by corruption, lies, pretence and the only thing unifying them all, a wish for a better future.

title: Abbas Abbas Send Help!
synopsis: Directed by Mani Nouri. This is an independent film made in Iran, due to its subject it is banned from theaters in its country of origin. This long feature is created in black and white, it is POV of the main character of the movie, through his eyes (camera) we come to understand the pain he is suffering and also the changes in Iranian modern society.

title: Always Miss You
synopsis: Qian ren

title: Love, Weddings & Other Disasters
synopsis: Directed by Dennis Dugan. With Maggie Grace, Diane Keaton, Jeremy Irons, Jesse McCartney. It is a multi-story romantic comedy about the people who work on weddings to create the perfect day for a loving couple - while their own relationships are outlandish, odd, crazy and far from perfect.

title: Spring, Again
synopsis: Directed by Jung Yong-ju. With Chung-Ah Lee, Jong-Hyun Hong, Park Kyung-hye, Park Ji-bin. Lee Cheon Ah, a woman who committed suicide following her daughter's death, but instead doesn't die. Hong Jong Hyun is a mysterious man who wants to commit suicide and meets Cheon Ah at a suicide site.

title: 2 Weeks in Lagos
synopsis:
Directed by Kathryn Fasegha. With Toyin Abraham, Bambo Adebowale, Lawal Aramide, Ayanlola Ayankunle. "2 Weeks in Lagos" is a turbulent and thrilling journey into the lives of Ejikeme and Lola. Their lives collide when Ejikeme an investment banker comes home from the United States with Lola's brother Charlie to invest in Nigerian businesses. It is love at first sight for them and as they embark on a journey of discovering this new love, they have to contend with the political ambitions of Ejikeme's mother who is planning a marriage between him and the only daughter of Otunba Ayodeji, a political juggernaut who is considering Ejikeme's father as his running mate for the Nigerian Presidency. His mother's actions create a rift between Ejikeme and Lola that pits their families against one another with almost deadly results. Ejike's mother is a driven social butterfly with just one aim in mind, make her husband President and become the First Lady. Lola's mother is a psychologist with a cool temperament but she is pushed too far when her daughter is threatened. As the love story of Ejikeme and Lola unfolds, viewers will laugh, cry and root for true love all at once.

In "2 Weeks in Lagos" we witness the impact of superstitions on the Nigerian mind when a father tries to kill his young daughter who he has accused of being a demon child (Ogbanje in the local parlance), claiming she is the reason for his depressed business and his wife's sickness that had been going on since she was born. When he is stopped from doing this by Lola and her tailor Madam Eloho, he dumps the child on Madam Eloho and leaves without a backward glance. In Madam Eloho, the elasticity of the Nigerian psyche in dealing with difficulties is fully displayed as she takes on the child without giving it any though and declares that "God will help us" when Lola questions her about being able to provide for the child.

"2 Weeks in Lagos" captures the excitement and vibrancy of everyday life in Lagos and reflects the complexity of life in Lagos, a dynamic city where anything is possible in 2 Weeks. Through out the story, Nigerian traditions are explored in an authentic manner that is exciting, educative and poignant; biblical truths about mercy, love, and forgiveness are explored and naturally woven into the day-to-day lives of the protagonists in a truthful and respectful manner reflecting the deep faith of the typical Nigerian. From the crippling infamous Lagos traffic, to the daily hustle that makes up life on the streets of Lagos and a visit to the local street food vendors (Bukkas) serving up the best in local delicacies, "2 Weeks in Lagos will keep viewers glued to the screen from beginning to end.

title: Women at the Peak

title: Growing Pains
synopsis: Directed by Danny Pang. With Jiao Xu, Xia Hu, Nuo Lu, Leehom Wang. Hunan province, southern China, the present day. Senior high-school student Xia Yuanyuan (Jiao Xu), 17, dreams in class about manga characters, her only real interest apart from Taiwan American singer Leehom Wang, whom she's idolised all her life. Her parents divorced when she was young and she's been raised by her paternal grandmother, who indulges her. Always bottom of the class, she has the university entrance exam in three months' time and is constantly berated by her martinet class teacher Gu (Hao Ju). After a row one day with him, she storms out and goes to the beach with biker/hippie friend Luo Tao (Nuo Lu), who is a member of the same manga-cosplay group. They both rail against the conformist world. Following his collapse after Xia Yuanyuan's walkout, Gu is ordered to rest and younger replacement teacher Li Mi (Charlene Choi) takes over. Xia Yuanyuan again walks out when she finds the words "student trash" written on her desk. Li Mi finds out what happened from nerdy student Gu Mingyao (Xia Hu), who's known Xia Yuanyuan since primary school and is her only real friend in class. He, however, is under intense pressure from his father to pass the entrance exam and study science and engineering at a good university. Luo Tao takes Xia Yuanyuan to a bar to relax when both of them should be at the cosplay group's rehearsal; fellow member Lisha, who likes Luo Tao, blames everything on Xia Yuanyuan. To bring the competitive class together, Li Mi pairs the students off at desks; Gu Mingyao offers to sit with Xia Yuanyuan and she starts to take more of an interest in studying, which further annoys ambitious class head Lin Wei (Jingzi Shi) who secretly fancies Gu Mingyao. Also jealous of the time that Xu Jiao now spends with Gu Mingyao is Luo Tao, who warns him off. But Gu Mingyao denies he is Xia Yuanyuan's boyfriend, just as Xia Yuanyuan denies she is Luo Tao's girlfriend.
