synopsis: Directed by Shunsuke Shinada. With Miyu Andô, Mitsuhiro Fujiwara, Yuriko Hirooka, Manami Iida. A sentient period goes around harassing women at their time of the month.

title: Andy Kindler: I Wish I Was Bitter
synopsis: I Wish I Was Bitter

title: Ghost Hustlers
synopsis: Directed by Javan Garza. With Joseph Bishop, Stephen Braun, Preston Caldwell, Jesse Fryery. A group of paranormal investigators inspect a so called 'haunted' theater, but get more than they bargained for.

title: Rock 4
synopsis: Directed by Mamat Khalid. With Sharwani Ns, Hazama Azmi, Adam John, Bulan Terry. New rock band RIMBA BARA 2 embarks on a journey to revive the legacy of RIMBA BARA with the help of their manager Dio (former RIMBA BARA roadie).

title: Millennium Bugs
synopsis: Directed by Alejandro Montoya Marín. With Braden Anderson, Chad Brummett, Joseph Conway, Daniel Cruz. Set in the last week of 1999, best friends Kelly and Miguel find themselves on the cusp of their future. Kelly has been floating through life after her parent's death. Drowning herself in alcohol and drugs. When her inheritance money runs out, Kelly is slapped with the realities of her actions. Her best friend Miguel is torn between his immigrant parent's expectations and his dream to become a comedian. The pressure to pursue his dreams while defying the sacrifices his parents made for him pushes Miguel to the brink. Together, Kelly and Miguel along the rest of the world find themselves wondering what's next.

title: Asuang
synopsis: Directed by Raynier Brizuela. With Alwyn Uytingco, Chai Fonacier, Brenda Mage, Toni Almazan. "Asuang", the God of Sins, was once a ruthless and fickle God of Bicol, but now he is a loner and a loser who has no place in the world that is overrun by sinful human beings. He resorted to social media to regain his former glory and fame but to no avail. On his track to retirement, he was approached by the Seers to help them stop Armageddon. Along with a group of sinful misfits, Asuang will go on a quest, against his nature, to help mankind - Or so he think he will.

title: Lat Mat 4: Nha Co Khach
synopsis: Nha Co Khach

title: Bau Na Vichaar
synopsis: Directed by Hrutul Patel. With Bhatt Bhushan, Janki Bodiwala, Shraddhaben Chaudhari, Sonali Lele Desai. Getting selected in final 8 teams of a reality show specially for entrepreneurs, Varun an unaware over thinker , seeks to win the show to prove his unique start up idea's worth to his father by solving civil war amongst his best friend/business partners and saving them from fear of failure, confusion, insecurity and negative thinking,with help of Dadu, while unknowingly tackling a traitor amongst his team.

title: Frank & Fearless
synopsis: Directed by Gray Hofmeyr. With Leon Schuster, Thembalethu Ntuli, Kenneth Nkosi, Khanyi Mbau. The killing of Reini's mother by poachers sets these four on an ill-advised, sometimes funny, and deeply moving journey through the wild African bush to an equally-wild African city. Their purpose

title: On a Magical Night
synopsis: Directed by Christophe Honoré. With Chiara Mastroianni, Benjamin Biolay, Vincent Lacoste, Kolia Abiteboul. After 20 years of marriage, Maria decides to leave. She moves to the room 212 of the hotel opposite her marital home. From there, Maria can scrutinize her apartment, her husband, her wedding. She wonders if she has made the right decision.

title: You Tell Me
synopsis: Directed by Michael Fetter Nathansky. With Walid Al-Atiyat, Gisa Flake, Christina Große, Patrick Heinrich. Due to an unexplicable act the destinies of three people collapse and dissolve into a dramaturgical dance about victims, offenders and the truth that lays between the lies.

title: Mat Tudung
synopsis: Directed by Wan Hafiz. With Fizz Fairuz, Nelydia Senrose, Rosnah Mat Aris, Harun Salim Bachik. "Mat Tudung" follows a Casanova by the name of Johari, a former Mat Rempit who has fallen in love at first sight with Zizie. Zizie is unlike any girl Johari has ever met as the hijab wearing beauty is known to give guys the cold shoulder. Unwilling to give up on his dream girl, Johari dresses up as a hijab wearing girl, Johanna, the 'sister' of Johari in order to get close to Zizie.

title: Zygote
synopsis: Directed by Cameron B. Smith. With Emily Gomez, Arianna Tysinger, Cameron B. Smith, Hal Cosec. Amber has a doctor's appointment.

title: The Show Might Go On
synopsis: Directed by Byron Hatfield. With Noah Applebaum, Chris Bashen, Andrew Bentley, Karisa Bruin.

title: Rise To Stand-Up
synopsis: Directed by Cameron B. Smith. With Cameron B. Smith, Timmy Sherrill, Zack Burk, Lew Morgante. Cameron Smith pursues the challenge of becoming a stand-up comedian for his high school senior project.

title: This Jelly Doughnut Feeling
synopsis: Directed by Sebastian Spangenberg. With Angelo Konzett, Maria C. Liedhegener, Marco Jorge Rudolph, Kim Sophie Scheele.

title: I Need You Dead!
synopsis: Directed by Rocko Zevenbergen. With Estevan Muñoz, Sean Arlo, Ada Hurtado, Lloyd Kaufman. After a moment of total teenage angst, a young punk finds himself at odds with a psychedelic monster of his own creation.

title: Rampaat
synopsis: Directed by Ravi Jadhav. With Kushal Badrike, Abhinay Berde, Priya Arun Berde, Ankush Chaudhari. We all dream differently. But there are some dreams that are larger - than - life, that have no limits and yet we continue to chase those dreams regardless of it's relativity to the real life. One of such larger - than - life dreams that have mesmerized countless youngsters today is the dream of 'Stardom'!. And In this age where everything is instant and fleeting the youth today expect the same from their dreams. They want it right away, super-fast viz. Rampaat !! Mumbai being the 'city of dreams' the youth from various villages, cities, every nook, and cranny in India arrive in Mumbai to pursue this dream. But is that all it takes? Or does it require immense dedication, hard work and seeking the right direction to achieve this dream? This is what Rampaat portrays. With the dream of Instant stardom, earning quick money and making their parents proud - Mithun from Solapur and Munni from Kolhapur come to Mumbai and that's when the bittersweet struggle of their journey to achieving their dreams begin. This amusing journey teaches them to work harder and hustle for an 'All time hit' rather than a 'One-time hit ' Telling the youth their own story in an upbeat manner along with rhythmic music, the fast-moving story does justice to its title. Rampaat is the 70 mm projection of and for the young ambitious dreamers today.

title: Cult
synopsis: Directed by Luke Ibbetson. With Neil Allen, James Barnes, Anthony Bullinger, Tim Cartwright. A documentary crew travel to a remote village in England to capture the lives of notorious cult 'Friends at the End'.

title: Miss
synopsis: Directed by Ruben Alves. With Alexandre Wetter, Pascale Arbillot, Isabelle Nanty, Thibault de Montalembert. A young man seeking his gender identity decides to take part in the Miss France beauty pageant.

title: Chhalawa
synopsis: Directed by Wajahat Rauf. With Mehwish Hayat, Umer Aalam, Zara Noor Abbas, Mehmood Aslam. Zoya plans to escape from her father's haveli so that she can be with Sameer. But Chaudhry sb has shut down all communications. It will be a tough exit without wifi, facebook, Instagram and well, a phone connection.

title: Scare Me
synopsis: Directed by Josh Ruben. With Josh Ruben, Aya Cash, Chris Redd, Rebecca Drysdale. During a power outage, two strangers tell scary stories. The more Fred and Fanny commit to their tales, the more the stories come to life in their Catskills cabin. The horrors of reality manifest when Fred confronts his ultimate fear.

title: Aatpadi Nights
synopsis: Directed by Nitin Supekar. With Subodh Bhave, Jatin Inamdar, Yogesh Iratkar, Chhaya Kadam. There is an important place for matrimonial in Indian society. After marriage, the first night of honeymoon is must there along with great excitement and nervousness too. 'Aatpadi Nights' tells us about the excitement, nervousness and the ignorance of the first night of marriage. Vasant Khatmode (Vashya) is the hero of the film who is also very excited but he has doubts as other grooms, due to lack of knowledge of the first night of the Honeymoon. He loves very much of his becoming wife and he is very excited and nervous for a honeymoon. Due to this phobia, he goes to his friends to clear the doubts about the first night. The friends give advice and the drama of the story is started here - senseless advice given by friends and the ignorance put Vashya into great trouble. Alimentally the first night of the honeymoon in his life goes bitterly horrible and terrible. After that night Vashya's life is changed and the private issue becomes public. This is what the spicy and the interesting story of 'Aatpadi Nights'.

title: Jakkanna
synopsis: Directed by Krishna Akella. With Master Atharvan, Chaitanya, Harsha Chemudu, Mannara Chopra. The movie is about an attempt by Sunil the protagonist to repay a kindness earns him the wrath of a ruthless gangster Kabir Duhan Singh the antagonist who's wish is to continue his all illegal proceedings.

title: Dhaght Ali
synopsis: Directed by Abdulaziz Hashshad. With Amr Abdulaziz, Sabri Abdulmonem, Wael Abul-Suood, Ayten Amer. An electrical engineer gets electrocuted causing him to become a source of electricity to all around him, which then falls in love with a girl he electrocuted while facing the attempts of officials trying to benefit from his new gift.

title: Die Abenteuer des Tiberius von Hadern
synopsis: Directed by Axel Loh. With Christine Kendel, Axel Loh, Andreas Muth, Nadine Neumann. "The Adventures of Tiberius von Hadern" is a funny silent movie with mysterious witches and quirky types in black and white. Scotland in 1520

title: Na bank sie uda
synopsis: Directed by Szymon Jakubowski. With Adam Ferency, Lech Dyblik, Marian Dziedziel, Maciej Stuhr. General prosecutor is asking young police computer expert for help in bank robbery case where three elderly gentlemen have been red handed inside the vault. From the footage collect from Bank camera it looks that bank robbers had some technical support from outside and the algorithm used to open the vault is very similar to released seven years before by our young police expert. Now the heat is on him. Force to run to avoid arrest he needs to solve the case to clear his name.

title: Honesty Weekend

Their therapist prescribes a weekend of total honesty - the same weekend they're going to the country with close friends for a blowout good time.

title: Ryan Cownie: I Can't Die
synopsis: I Can't Die

title: Boucan
synopsis: Directed by Antonin Schopfer, Thomas Szczepanski. With Antonin Schopfer, Michel Schopfer, Thomas Szczepanski, Béatrice Bellato. Antonin pays a visit to his father whom he hasn't seen for fifteen years. He asks a friend and cameraman to accompany him because he wants to make a documentary of the encounter. Very quickly, everything gets out of control

title: Pink Thief
synopsis: Directed by Mustafa Ozgun. With Xingtong Yao, Laura Weissbecker, Grégory Pierre, Gauthier Roubichou.

title: S.O.N.S. (Sons of Nanay Sabel)
synopsis: Directed by Dado C. Lumibao. With AiAi Delas Alas, James Brando, Jon Gutierrez, Bosx1ne.

title: Beer Conversations
synopsis: Directed by Ryan Willer. With Brian Harrison Mack, Hailey Graves Tucker, Jared Price, Dan Franklin. Sixteen different mini stories each involving two people discussing life's issues over a cold one.

title: Krocken
synopsis: Directed by Lena Koppel. With Siw Erixon, Magdalena in de Betou, Jacob Koppel, Andrea Ung Malmberg.

title: Premier de la classe
synopsis: Directed by Stéphane Ben Lahcene. With Mutamba Kalonji, Pascal N'Zonzi, Michèle Laroque, Fatsah Bouyahmed. Abu, 14, is his father's pride. Unlike his three brothers, he is the "top of his class". Well, that's what he would have you believe. In truth, Abu is, above all, the king of lies and fake school grades. When the first meeting of parents and teachers arrives, he is going to stage the biggest lie of his life

title: Tout nous sourit
synopsis: Directed by Mélissa Drigeard, Ibrahim Hamdan. With Elsa Zylberstein, Stéphane De Groodt, Guy Marchand, Anne Benoît. The members of an apparently happy couple, each with their respective lovers, have the same idea

title: My Dog Stupid
synopsis: Directed by Yvan Attal. With Yvan Attal, Charlotte Gainsbourg, Eric Ruf, Pascale Arbillot. Henri is a middle-aged writer in crisis. Just at a time when he assesses of his life, an enormous gray dog, impolite and smelly, sneaks into Henri's house.

title: Foosballers
synopsis: Directed by Joe Heslinga. With Todd Loffredo, Tony Spredeman, Ryan Moore, Robert Mares. Through an ensemble cast, FOOSBALLERS not only uncovers a forgotten piece of sports history, it follows 6 of the best table soccer players in the world as they prepare for The Tornado World Championships.

title: Daddy, Be with Me
synopsis: Directed by Bao Mi. With Qian Yu, Yilin Huang, Jiro Wang, Li-Chun Lee. Zhang Shengli left his wife and daughter fifteen years ago and went to Hong Kong to strive for a successful life. Now Zhang is rich and the daughter Ni Xiaoman plans to take reprisal for the fifteen-years-abandon.

title: Hip Hip Hurray
synopsis: Directed by Shriprasad Pawar, Ramesh Sharma. With Vijay Chavan, Mangesh Desai, Smita Gondkar, Avinash Narkar. 'Hip Hip Hurray' is a story about good friends Kushal and Chatur. Both are from middle class backgrounds and looking for jobs and money making enterprise. Kushal starts a new business everyday and gets over with it soon much to his family's ire. Chatur is from a family of priests, but he is not interested in the family tradition. Both of them are in love with two college girls from rich families.

title: Bad Dog and Superhero
synopsis: Directed by Kenneth Hughes. With Sita Acevedo, Mark Bate, Rich Bianco, Robert W. Boelio. It is a Butch Cassidy and the Sundance Kid with a kick in the ass from Shakespeare and Dr. Suess musings. It is a Rosencrantz and Gildenstern with a Southpark twist. It is 2 Romeo's that meet one Juliet; the 2 Romeos live in a Willy-Wonka-World attempting to repair Juliet's (and everyone else they meet) tragic world of reality.

title: Chasing Molly
synopsis: Directed by Josh Sutherland. With Adinda Catherine, Shelley Pack, Jim Cashman, Kurt Angle. Molly, a paranormal con artist who cleans people of their valuables instead of their demons, accidentally rips off a drug kingpin. She now has to save her kidnapped partner and herself while battling through the underbelly of Los Angeles.

title: Giraffraud
synopsis: Directed by Michael Papich. With Kaley Morrison, Rena MacMonegle, Faneal Godbold, Alex Bradford Cobb. An underachieving woman gets fired from her job at a bank but uncovers international fraud in the process. To keep herself out of prison, she pretends to be in on the scheme and learns that everyone fakes it until they make it.

title: Portrait of My Love

title: Ingawood
synopsis: Directed by Tessa Hall, Cami McCullough. With Jacob Figueroa, Justin Grant, Tessa Hall, Chase Johnson. Two foreign test tube babies and their journey in Hollywood.

title: Bellezonismo
synopsis: Directed by Jordi Arencón. With Armando del Río, Miguel Cazorla, Elvia Herrera, Yanet Garcia. Two rally drivers get lost during a competition and end up stranded in a Beauty Technification Center in the middle of nowhere.

title: My Wonderful Wanda
synopsis: Directed by Bettina Oberli. With Agnieszka Grochowska, Marthe Keller, André Jung, Birgit Minichmayr. Wanda, a Polish woman, takes care of 70-year-old Joseph in his family villa on the lake. She is always there for him and also helps his wife Elsa. The work is poorly paid, but Wanda needs the money for her family.

title: A Brother's Love
synopsis: Directed by Monia Chokri. With Anne-Élisabeth Bossé, Patrick Hivon, Evelyne Brochu, Sasson Gabay. Sophia, an unemployed academic, is forced to change the way she thinks and lives her life when Karim, her beloved brother, falls in love.

title: MO
synopsis: Directed by Adam Swegarden. With Dave Davis, Monique, Ivan Pavletic, Adam Swegarden. MO a English Bulldog sets off on a cross country adventure of a lifetime.

title: Fjols til fjells
synopsis: Directed by Petter Holmsen. With Herbert Nordrum, Nader Khademi, Bjørnar Bruun, Bente Kvile Buflod. title: The Prom

synopsis: Directed by Robert Redford. With James McAvoy, Robin Wright, Kevin Kline, Evan Rachel Wood. Mary Surratt is the lone female charged as a co-conspirator in the assassination trial of Abraham Lincoln. As the whole nation turns against her, she is forced to rely on her reluctant lawyer to uncover the truth and save her life.

title: Back Roads
synopsis: Directed by Alex Pettyfer. With Juliette Lewis, Jennifer Morrison, Robert Patrick, Nicola Peltz Beckham. In 1993, Harley's dad is shot dead and his mom goes to prison. He has to earn money and look after his 3 kid sisters. No college. Over 2 years, family secrets are slowly revealed. Will a good therapist be enough?

title: El Padrino II: Border Intrusion
synopsis: Border Intrusion

title: Blood of Hatred
synopsis: Directed by Sylvain Jouannet. With Christelle Dumas, Rémi Lucas, July Morel, Aurélien Meunier. On a spring morning, a young girl's body is found at Conleau Beach in Vannes. The police easily identify the victim as Lauren Coulon, a popular high school student who was declared MIA a few days ago. Alongside the police investigation, her family and friends decide to investigate on their own. What nobody knows at the moment is that the Lauren Coulon case will permit to unearth several dark family secrets that had been hidden for more than a decade.

title: 919 Lakeview Drive
synopsis: Directed by Sandy Sai. With Sri Chilukuri, Asif Khan, Kartik Garimella, Abhinay Rao. Brothers Vicky and Nandu wanting to pay off an old debt, plan to steal the crown jewel of diamonds The French Blue . They mistakenly break into the wrong house and must now fight for their lives after making a shocking discovery about their new victim.

title: Vellai Pookal
synopsis: Directed by Vivek Elangovan. With Vivek, Charlie, Pooja Devariya, Dev. A retired cop from India while on a trip to USA solves a series of clueless crimes in his neighborhood, relying only on his power of reasoning.

title: Calling
synopsis: Directed by Yu Zhang, Quan Cui. With Na Cao, Yi Nuo Li, Guo Wei, Luo Xi. This film tells the story of a middle-aged real estate tycoon - Jianguo Wang - suffering from a dual personality disorder exacerbated by extreme work and private life pressures. One day, he receives a call from a stranger. The stranger is able to mysteriously control Wang's car door from a distance. If Wang has a hope of opening the door, he must obey the stranger's increasingly bizarre orders. Based on the stranger's puzzling clues, Wang sees himself divorced from his beautiful but demanding wife Min, his lover Ling-Ling is murdered by a man donning a black coat in a hotel suite, and Wang's Real Estate empire collapses around him. In tantalizing morsels, the stranger continues to reveal the things Wang has done in the past. Finally, the stranger gives him a pill and Wang falls into a coma. After several minutes, in a darkened room the mobile rings again. Wang is standing in an unlit room with a menacing grin - dialing himself .

title: Cortex
synopsis: Directed by Moritz Bleibtreu. With Moritz Bleibtreu, Nadja Uhl, Emily Kusche, Jannis Niewöhner. Hagen develops disturbing nightmares and soon can no longer distinguish between dream and reality.

title: Cocaine. Gangster. Talk.
synopsis: Directed by Al Carretta. With Al Carretta, Clare Scott, Luke Dalton, Paul Bridger. The true identity of 'Carl Hart' is the mystery no government department can unravel. After 19 years the purpose of his operation becomes apparent as his true motive is revealed.

title: Justice Judgment
synopsis: Directed by Sungmo 'Sunghyun' Cho. With Sungmo 'Sunghyun' Cho. One righteous and innocent man who studied law get angered by injustice and find the concealed truth of major company which runs illegal prostitution business and that company's connection with corrupt public prosecution power.

title: Badri vs. Madhumathi
synopsis: With Aravind Bolar, Akanksha Gandhi, Jahagir, Prathapawan. Badri is an army officer who falls in love with Madhumathi and wants to confess his love for her. However, before he can do that, his friend runs away with his girlfriend, and he has to worry about saving his friend from the girl's father. Just when things seem to settle down, Badri is called back for a surgical strike to fight against terrorism.

title: Naanu Nammudugi Kharchgond Mafia
synopsis: Directed by Amar Saalva. With Ashwini, Shraddha Benagi, Amar Saalva, Shyam Sundar.

title: Blood on Her Name
synopsis: Directed by Matthew Pope. With Bethany Anne Lind, Will Patton, Elisabeth Röhm, Jared Ivers. A woman's panicked decision to cover up an accidental killing spins out of control when her conscience demands she return the dead man's body to his family.

title: MacGuffin
synopsis: Directed by Nick Hernandez. With Rene Cuadrado, Ariel Lopez, Nick Hernandez, Denise Lopez.

title: Fall Nights in China Grove
synopsis: Directed by Horace Priester. With Aleks Kapett, Brook Sill, Ken Jackson, Gerald Proctor. After backstabbing his criminal brother, 17-year-old Cullen stumbles upon a group of teens, with secrets of their own, that give him a taste of the youth he has missed. He soon learns that his whereabouts are not as hidden as he believes.

title: Our Godfather
synopsis: Directed by Mark Franchetti, Andrew Meier. With Tommaso Buscetta, Paul Castellano, Thomas Bilotti, Rudy Giuliani. OUR GODFATHER is a feature-length documentary about Tommaso Buscetta, the first high-ranking Italian mafia boss ever to turn against Cosa Nostra. Buscetta helped convict more than 400 Mafiosi. He became the Mob's most wanted man in the world - and 11 members of his family were killed. "He was the most important, protected and endangered witness in US criminal history" The film tells - for the first time- the Buscetta story with exclusive access to his family, which is breaking its silence after 30 years in hiding.

title: Whatever It Takes The Movie: When Blood Runs Cold
synopsis: When Blood Runs Cold

title: The Guilty Ones
synopsis: Directed by Yu Wang. With Qianyuan Wang, Jia Song, Yuanzheng Feng, Jiuxiao Li. BAI's daughter was kidnapped and died accidentally ten years ago, officer CHEN promised her to catch the criminal but retired without any result. Now LI's granddaughter was kidnapped and the modus operandi looks just same as the case ten years ago. BAI and CHEN reunite to investigate the case to catch the criminal.

title: Midnight Party
synopsis: With Rania Youssef. Young woman invite her friends to her villa and when all of them arrive she locks them inside and starts questioning them about betraying her trust.

title: Griekwastad
synopsis: Directed by Jozua Malherbe. With Arnold Vosloo, Alex van Dyk, Jane de Wet, Tim Theron. In 2012, Deon Steenkamp was murdered along with his wife Christelle and their teenage daughter Marthella on their farm Naauwhoek. GRIEKWASTAD, based on the bestselling true-crime novel by Jacques Steenkamp, tells the tale of the search to find the truth about these murders, however difficult and upsetting it might be.

title: Blindfire
synopsis: Directed by Michael Nell. With Brian Geraghty, Sharon Leal, Bethany Joy Lenz, Jim Beaver. Lives are left in pieces after a white cop responds to a hostage call and kills the Black suspect, only to learn he may have been set up; facing trial, he must find the person responsible while examining his own accountability.

title: Dhilakani
synopsis: Directed by Hussain Munawwaru. With Mohamed Faisal, Hassan Manik, Mohamed Manik, Niuma Mohamed. DHILAKANI is about one man's tumultuous journey to seek vengeance, his undoing and his eventual redemption from an unlikeliest of sources.

title: A mano disarmata
synopsis: Directed by Claudio Bonivento. With Claudia Gerini, Francesco Venditti, Francesco Pannofino, Mirko Frezza. The story of Federica Angeli, reporter of the daily newspaper "La Repubblica" that investigates the Roman underworld, challenging threats and dangers.

title: Servants of War
synopsis: Directed by Mariusz Gawrys. With Piotr Stramowski, Maria Kania, Pawel Królikowski, Karolina Czarnecka. A well-known doctor, Professor Jerzy Abramski, is murdered. The case is handled by Commissioner Wojciech Samborski ("Sambor") and Junior Officer Marta Zadara. They both assume that behind the professor's murder there is his lover, and she is responsible. However her sudden death changes everything. The "Helpful Hand" Foundation, founded by Professor Amramski attracts the attention of the police. The police investigation is hampered by the fact that Sambor and Marta are hiding their relationships from others. Gradually they discover a tangle of corruption, lucrative modern form of trade of human organs and attempts to sell sensitive information about soldiers DNA. In the end they would have to decide what's more important their relationship or interior security.

title: Child 44
synopsis: Directed by Daniel Espinosa. With Xavier Atkins, Mark Lewis Jones, Tom Hardy, Joel Kinnaman. A disgraced member of the Russian military police investigates a series of child murders during the Stalin-era Soviet Union.

title: The Quarry
synopsis: Directed by Scott Teems. With Bruno Bichir, Shea Whigham, Catalina Sandino Moreno, Anna Watt. A drifter (Shea Whigham) kills a traveling preacher and takes his place at a small-town church, but the police chief (Michael Shannon) suspects foul play.

title: Donna di rispetto
synopsis: Directed by Enzo Acri. With Mariangela De Rosa, Peppe De Rosa, Enzo Lucarelli, Angelo Sepe.

title: Alva
synopsis: Directed by Ico Costa. With Henrique Bonacho. After committing a crime, Henrique, a man in his thirties, hides in the forest.

title: Chop Chop
synopsis: Directed by Rony Patel. With Atala Arce, Jake B. Taylor, David Harper, Mikael Mattsson. A night of chaos ensues when a murderous psychopath targets a loving young couple who might be harboring a secret of their own.

title: Ready for War
synopsis: Directed by Andrew Renzi. Andrew Renzi's sheds light on the lives of three of the estimated thousands of immigrants who volunteer for service in the American military, yet find themselves deported from the US once their tours of duty are over.

title: No Man's Truth
synopsis: Directed by Marina Libik. With Coral Bhamra, Chirag Saluja, Gaurav Kamble, Divya Sharma. The peace of a middle-class family is shattered by the suicide of the elder daughter just a month after she is admitted to college. Coral, her younger sister, replaces her in the college to find out the circumstances her sister's death.

title: Drowsy City
synopsis: Directed by Dung Luong Dinh. A young man who works as a slaughterman is forced to take revenge on three strangers that brutally attack his simple life.

title: Forensic
synopsis: Directed by Anas Khan, Akhil Paul. With Tovino Thomas, Mamta Mohandas, Saiju Kurup, Reba Monica John. Samuel uses his forensic skills and discovers breakthroughs in a serial killing case as further victims are added to the list. Shikha teams up with Samuel and uncovers evidence that might lead to the killer's identity.

title: Desire Game
synopsis: Directed by Tao Guo. With Tao Guo, Zifeng Zhang, Chao Jiang, Ting Mei. Set in 2020. After the death of his daughter, a leading figure in intelligent technology industry hides himself far from the madding crowd and stays with intelligent robots. He inexplicably becomes a murder fugitive when an accident happens, and falls into a trap step by step.

title: Sargana
synopsis: Directed by Yogesh Bharadwaj. With Shatakshi Gupta, Bobby Kumar, Rakesh Kumar, Vishwajeet Pradhan.

title: Blackwell
synopsis: Directed by Bones Harrison. With Jessica Quartel, Bones Harrison, Philip Richard Black, Dave 'Scruffy' Funk. One twin comes back from jail, while the other has lost herself. It all plays out on one strange farm.

title: Mirage
synopsis: Directed by Christophe Beaucourt. With Charles Sereis, Jérémie Haïk, Taga Addams, Plex. A desperate photographer who suffers from a degenerative eye disease and a husband who wants to kill his dying wife, plot to recover her life insurance.

title: Summer of Changsha
synopsis: Directed by Feng Zu. With Feng Zu, Lu Huang, Minghao Chen, Qianru Zhang. A detective investigating a bizarre murder case begins to fall in love with a surgeon he has met while trying to solve the crime.

title: The Council
synopsis: Directed by JayTee Thompson. With Brandon Michael Thomas, JayTee Thompson, Kendon Tillis, Darryl Griffin. In an era of crime, drugs and violence, the streets of South Central Los Angeles walk in fear as the gangs, police and criminals take over. Four heroic men take matters into their own hands and bring a nightmare on the streets that they can't wake up from. No justice, no peace and if peace is far out of reach, so will the idea of being a law abiding citizen. The criminals leaned in the ear of the city and said a storm is coming, The Council leaned back and whispered..."WE ARE THE STORM!"

title: Three Days and a Life
synopsis: Directed by Nicolas Boukhrief. With Sandrine Bonnaire, Pablo Pauly, Charles Berling, Philippe Torreton. Christmas 1999, in a peaceful little village in the Ardennes. The life of a young boy named Antoine will soon be devastated by three tragic events

title: The Voice of Sin
synopsis: Directed by Nobuhiro Doi. With Shun Oguri, Gen Hoshino, Yutaka Matsushige, Kanji Furutachi. A newspaper reporter is working on an investigative piece regarding an unsolved mystery dating back thirty years. there was gangsterism and extortion at play. As part of his work the man comes across a riddle of a cassette tape. Alsmost at the same time a man in Kyoto comes across a cassette among his father's belongings. He hears himself.

title: Bedaad
synopsis: Directed by Anil Sharma. A bitter truth of society is "What actually exist is not visible and whereas which is not visible does appear. Behind every successful person, there is someone, so is with Psycho, who is not psychic by his/her choice. The movie " BEDAAD" is an attempt to smash the mask of the faces of such people.

title: Luca
synopsis: Directed by Horatiu Malaele. With István Téglás, Andi Vasluianu, Madalina Craiu, Rodica Mandache. He wanted to become Someone, and he became somebody else.

title: Ghostmist Island
synopsis: With Jinshang Huang, Jiancheng Wang.

title: Vinci Da
synopsis: Directed by Srijit Mukherji. With Anirban Bhattacharya, Ritwick Chakraborty, Rudranil Ghosh, Gautam Moitra. A gifted make-up artist gets entangled up in a world of crime with a psychopathic vigilante.

title: M.I.S.T.E.R (Made It Surviving Through Extreme Reality)
synopsis: Directed by Todd Lucky Johnson. With Darryle Jermaine, Brittany Mirabile, Hasheem Rivers, Torey Waters. M.I.S.T.E.R is a Crime/Drama about a gangster who is considering changing his life. While serving the remainder of his time on a parole violation, he begins writing a fictitious book about himself. Subsequently, to being released from prison he begins the process of getting his novel published. Based on a true story about love, loyalty, deception and betrayal.

title: Mrs. Serial Killer
synopsis: Directed by Shirish Kunder. With Jacqueline Fernandez, Manoj Bajpayee, Mohit Raina, Zayn Marie Khan. When a doctor gets jailed for a string of shocking murders, his loyal wife sets out to commit a copycat crime to prove his innocence.

title: Kingshighway
synopsis: Directed by Clayne Crawford. With Clayne Crawford, Lina Esco, Burt Young, Edward Furlong. A young man visits a bar and falls for the waitress whose family turns out to be tied to Italian mob. The head henchman doesn't like him, so things heat up, even though the don likes him. Then stolen diamonds enter the picture.

title: The Witness
synopsis: Directed by Jun'ichi Mori. With Riho Yoshioka, Mahiro Takasugi, Kôdai Asaka, Jun Kunimura. There is an accident. A young man dies and a young woman loses her eyesight and becomes blind. She was about to become a cop, but that vocation is not to be. Opportunity to do policing work comes to pass several years when the woman is in minor accident and hears a girl. Cusrious and investigating she meets a boy. She senses something dangerous a foot.

title: I'm Your Woman
synopsis: Directed by Julia Hart. With Rachel Brosnahan, Marsha Stephanie Blake, Arinzé Kene, Jameson Charles. In this 1970s set crime drama, a woman is forced to go on the run after her husband betrays his partners, sending her and her baby on a dangerous journey.

title: Ghost
synopsis: Directed by Anthony Z. James. With Anthony Mark Streeter, Nathan Hamilton, Russell Barnett, Emmy Happisburgh. On the first day of freedom, a grizzled ex-con must reconnect with his troubled son before his violent past catches up with them.

title: The Bag Girls
synopsis: Directed by Wil Lewis, Howard Patterson. With Crystal The Doll, Malik Walls, James Darnell, Leah Envy. Twenty-seven-year-old Deandrea Smith, wife of prominent business owner Walter Smith, deals with his treacherous actions causing her to become destitute and enraged with revenge. Deandrea confides in her best friend, Nola, an exotic dancer, and they recruit two more women, Crystal, a religious single mother, and Daisy, a street thug, to help them execute a plan to steal $50,000 from Walter. After the successful theft from Walter, the group decides to try their fortune at bigger spoils and come up with a plan to rob Nola's place of employment, the strip club, dubbing themselves, The Bag Girls. Gaining notoriety, The Bag Girls are hired to do a job that's way over their head when they're put up against the Cuban mafia.

title: The Pardon
synopsis: Directed by Tom Anton. With Jaime King, Leigh Whannell, T.J. Thyne, John Hawkes. With all the picturesque glamour of the 1940s, "The Pardon" recounts the unlikely true story of Toni Jo Henry. A grisly murder leads to a series of sensational trials in which she pleads her innocence; she was executed in Louisiana, 1942.

title: Antigone
synopsis: Directed by Sophie Deraspe. With Nahéma Ricci, Rawad El-Zein, Antoine DesRochers, Nesrine Argoub. A modern adaptation of the classic Greek tragedy which falls within a social realism. To the law of men, the young Antigone apposes her own sets of values.

title: The Guilt I
synopsis: With Suo He, Xinmin Li, Hang Yin, Yanmanzi Zhu.

title: The Guilt II
synopsis: With Suo He, Xinmin Li, Hang Yin, Yanmanzi Zhu.

title: The Guilt III
synopsis: With Suo He, Xinmin Li, Hang Yin, Yanmanzi Zhu.

title: The Promised Land
synopsis: Directed by Takahisa Zeze. With Gô Ayano, Akira Emoto, Shizuka Ishibashi, Reiko Kataoka. A girl is kidnapped and the perpetrator roams freely. When a similar case occurs along the same road and in similar circumstances a suspect is identified leading to the accused running away and going into hiding. Another year on and another man falls into suspicion. It is too much to bear and a burden to carry, but with suspicion all around and no culprits apprehended the situation is somewhat understandable.

title: Exit Point
synopsis: Directed by David Mondin. With Ray Morales, Marlon Marrero, Nelson Nieves, Henry Gonzalez. A smalltime mobster's no-hassle heist turns out to be the money and drugs of a rival leader. 22-year-old Ian Martinez escapes the United States in an attempt to move his life forward through higher education but is lured into unlawful activity by predatory gang members.

title: Active Shooter
synopsis: Directed by Robert Bryce Milburn. With Michael Aaron Milligan, Catherine Dyer, Joshua Mikel, Andrea Andrade. Held up in an office restroom during an active shooter situation, three women find their trust tested when they start looking for holes in a fellow victim's story.

title: Innocent Day
synopsis: Directed by Chen Xu. With Haohui Zhou.

title: Cop and Rookie
synopsis: Directed by Sam Sudama. With Matthew Silva, Meagan, Paul, Sam Sudama.

title: Il codice del babbuino
synopsis: Directed by Davide Alfonsi, Denis Malagnino. With Denis Malagnino, Stefano Miconi Proietti, Tiberio Suma, Marco Pocetta.

title: Modelar
synopsis: Directed by Petr Zelenka. With Krystof Hádek, Jirí Mádl, Veronika Khek Kubarová, Richard Stanke. Droneman is about Chemist and Fly Navigator Pavel and his friend Bussinessman and free time Rapper Plech. Pavel has strong sense of justice and wishes to fix wrongs with the World while Plech dreams about Big money and secure life. Their common passion are Drones since School. Pavel returns from Foreign and meets again with Plech and together they use Drones to start Bussiness. They monitor Power Stations, wear luxury handbags at the show or spray the Petrin Tower from the air. Their clients even include Presidential candidate. Everything changes when one of them decides to misuse Drones.

title: Das dunkle Paradies
synopsis: Directed by Catalina Molina. With Stefanie Reinsperger, Manuel Rubey, Andrea Wenzl, Wolfgang Rauh. The Salzburg police duo Heilmayr and Merana is looking for the murderer of a noble call girl.

title: Black Hand
synopsis: Directed by Hamed Niki. With Marcel Zadé, Dan Vaida, Kristof Gillese, Scott Harlow. When a wealthy entrepreneur dies in an accident, a journalist and a veteran detective team up to uncover the truth. Not everything is as it seems as the trail leads them to a criminal organization.

title: Trikonam
synopsis: Directed by M.S. Raaja Rajeshwaran. With Dhananjay Gandotra, Sridhar Kuppurao, Madhu Lokanath, M.S. Raaja Rajeshwaran.

title: Cute Devil
synopsis: Directed by Hisayasu Satô. With Lisa Akikawa, Kumiko Akiyoshi, Ai Kobayashi, Hiroyuki Watanabe. As a result of an illicit affair between a man and his employee results in the man having his genitals cut off in front of the woman by the woman's husband.

title: White Nights
synopsis: With Sheng Wang, Yun Xing.

title: Hemelrijken
synopsis: Directed by Stanley Kolk. With Jennifer Welts, Esmée van Kampen, Fred Goessens, Maarten Heijmans. When Kelly is released from prison, her sister Samantha tries hard to keep her on the right track. But then Kelly's ex-boyfriend Eddy gets back into her life.

title: Magic Mountains
synopsis: Directed by Urszula Antoniak. With Marcin Dorocinski, Hannah Hoekstra, Maria Maj, Thomas Ryckewaert. A successful writer asks his ex, who left him, to climb one last time in the mountains together. Only then he can really let her go.

title: Lynn + Lucy
synopsis: Directed by Fyzal Boulifa. With Roxanne Scrimshaw, Nichola Burley, Kacey Ainsworth, Jennifer Lee Moon. Lynn and Lucy are lifelong best friends, their relationship as intense as any romance. Neither has ventured far from where they grew up. Lynn, who married her first boyfriend and whose daughter is fast growing up, is delighted when the charismatic, volatile Lucy has her first baby boy. Lucy, however, does not react to being a mother as Lynn expects. Soon, they find their friendship is tested in extreme circumstances.

title: My First Client
synopsis: Directed by Kyu-sung Jang. With Dong-hwi Lee, Seon Yu, Choi Myung-bin, Lee Joo Won. A rookie lawyer blinded by success, meets a 10 year old girl as his first client, who insists she killed her younger brother.

title: Qaranliq
synopsis: Directed by Kenan Zeynalov. With Lale Huseynzade, Ramiz Melikov, Gülsad Baxsiyeva, Murad Ismayil. Nuray lost Farid two months ago. She makes her mind to write a new love story. So, she wants to use Firuza's diary. Firuza was mysteriously murdered 34 years ago. When reading the diary Nuray finds out that one sheet of the diary is missing.

title: The Art of Political Murder
synopsis: Directed by Paul W. Taylor. With Jack Palladino, Celvin Galindo, Francisco Goldman, Arturo Aguilar. An investigation into the truth behind the murder of Guatemalan Bishop, Juan Gerardi, who was killed in 1998 just days after trying to hold the country's military accountable for the atrocities committed during its civil war.

title: Die Unsterbliche Partie - The Immortal Game
synopsis: Directed by Sem Gray. With Massoud Baygan, Curse, Sascha Koal, Michael Fuchs. Kian Pyâdah is a taxi driver who makes a disturbing discovery during his night shift. He gets a mysterious call, which places him deep in criminal activity.

title: Mr. Jasoos
synopsis: Directed by Kalp Trivedi. With Kalpesh Patel, Bhakti Rathore, Ketankumar Sagar. Based On Kanu Bhagdev's Novel "JASOOS", Mr. Jasoos revels around a murder which has more than 3 suspects and each has a strong motive for doing this murder. Find Out How Vijay Mane AKA Mr. Jasoos solves complicated case in the film.

title: Article 15
synopsis: Directed by Anubhav Sinha. With Ayushmann Khurrana, Nassar, Manoj Pahwa, Kumud Mishra. In the rural heartlands of India, an upright police officer sets out on a crusade against violent caste-based crimes and discrimination.

title: Bandishala
synopsis: Directed by Milind Lele. With Mukta Barve, Pravin Tarde, Sharad Ponkshe, Madhav Abhynkar. Madhavi Sawant is a resilient police officer who tries to root out the corrupt administration in the prisons. However, she makes powerful enemies who plot a gang rape against her. The harrowing incident leaves a strong Madhavi, broken. The film attempts to bring out the discrimination and crimes against women to the forefront through Madhavi's story.

title: The Precious and the Damned
synopsis: Directed by Nathan Karimi. With Seth Ferranti, Skully Shemwell, Kyle A. Lee, Jackie Kelly.

title: Destinies
synopsis: Directed by Pu Zhang. With Jin Gao, Yang Li, Yu Li, Tat-Wah Lok.

title: Diamond Anxiety
synopsis: Directed by Junzhao Lin. With Ran Fu, Bo Zhan Ju, Yanqi Lu, Fei Yu. Diamond ring cursed by the devil in the hands of common clerk from jewelry store.

title: Le scandalose
synopsis: Directed by Gianfranco Giagni. With Sonia Bergamasco, Daniela Di Giusto, Claudio Santamaria. A docu-noir about thirty years of female murder, documenting the evolution of crime committed by women, in a series of emblematic milestone cases from the early 1940s to the 1970s, using all the material available on the murderers, the victims, the investigations, the trials and, a fundamental issue, the media impact of the crimes and the people involved. An exploration without prejudice about the differences and specificities in the murders observed in the past, but which with time and the profound transformation of society, now seem to vindicate those who say "Women kill for the same reasons as men, and often with the same pain".

title: El Sonido de los Tulipanes
synopsis: Directed by Alberto Masliah. With Pablo Rago, Calu Rivero, Gerardo Romano, Iván Masliah. A journalist plunges into the after-crisis world of Buenos Aires full of violence and ambitions of power, when trying to find the true reasons for his father's death.

title: Dead Hand
synopsis: Directed by Thomas J Armstrong. With Trenton Hudson, Burton Kennedy, Jacqueline Mackey, Bryan McCallum. A man is detained under suspicion of a plot that an unnamed Government agency tries to unfold.

title: Victim(s)
synopsis: Directed by Layla Zhuqing Ji. With Xianjun Fu, Kahoe Hon, Wilson Hsu, Wilson Hsu. When both the victim's mother and the murderer's mother find out about the unknown sides of their sons, they have some tough decisions to make in this "We Media Era." What we see may be the facts, but not necessarily the truth.

title: Diksoochi
synopsis: Directed by Dilip Kumar Salvadi. With Chandni Bhagwanani, Sammeta Gandhi, Dilip Kumar Salvadi, Arun Savvana. A man sets out to solve the mystery surrounding a tragic incident that happened in 1975.

title: Magamuni
synopsis: Directed by Santhakumar. With Arya, Indhuja Ravichandran, Mahima Nambiar, G.M. Sundar. Two long-separated brothers end up in life-threatening situations. How do their lives intersect and what happens next?

title: Stand Up
synopsis: Directed by Vidhu Vincent. With Rajisha Vijayan, Nimisha Sajayan, Arjun Ashokan, Jolly Chirayath. Diya and Keerthi are friends. Keerthi is an aspiring Stand Up comedian and she is trying to find some opportunities for her shows. a becomes a regular presence in the friend's gatherings and through which she get introduced to 's brother Amal and his friends Jeevan and Sujith. Diya and Amal become lovers eventually. This changes everything for everybody in the

title: No Place
synopsis: Directed by Peter Matsoukas. With Benjamin Madrid, Afton Shepard, Forba Shepherd, Ric Payne. Mac travels the country looking for the next hustle. After he wraps up business with his Midwest fixer Les, she turns him on to a big score in Indianapolis with a local bar owner. He finds out it involves his old flame Evelyn and soon discovers that his past has caught up with him and he may not make it out alive.

title: Vo Gian Dao
synopsis: Directed by Tran Viet Anh. With Le Binh, Huynh Anh Lê, Xuan Nghi, Vo My Phuong.

title: Go Back
synopsis: Directed by Eun-young Seo. With Park Ha-Sun, Ha Yoon-kyung, So-Hyun Gam. Jiwon, highly motivated new policewoman, meets Osun, a mysterious lady, and Jiwon gets interested in her. Osun is a social worker and she has strong attachment to abused children and tries to help them, but the wall of harsh reality is too high. On a hot summer day, the message from a kidnapper was spread by media and this case becomes a national concern immediately. And Jiwon doubts correlation between this case and Osun. Suddenly, when a death case occurs in police region and the daughter of the dead, Bora, disappears, Jiwon gets to know that Bora was the abused child who was under responsibility of Osun. When Jiwon realizes that Bora and Osun disappeared together, Jiwon decides to find Osun.

title: The Dark Knight: The Ballad of the N Word
synopsis: The Ballad of the N Word

title: The Mummy Rebirth
synopsis: Перерождение

title: That Trafficker
synopsis: Directed by Bodrul Ahmed, Abir Mahafuz. With Trent Pfauser, Tokkyo Faison, Johnathan C. Williams, William J. Adamo.

title: The Old Town Girls
synopsis: Directed by Yu Shen. With Regina Wan, Gengxi Li, Jue Huang, Binlong Pan. High school girl living with her father and stepmother is visited by her biological mother, who left her soon after birth. They gradually reconcile, but the mother has a heavy debt.

title: Damned Gold
synopsis: Directed by Tsogiin Khuselbaatar. With Adilbishiin Adiltsetseg, Tomorbaataryn Anar, Dambarentsengiin Khurelkhuu, Tsegmidiin Tserenbold. Khuder must navigate the worlds of organized crime and the supernatural after escaping from a mental institution.

title: A Demon Called Desolation
synopsis: Directed by Diego Mauricio Alvarez. With Diego Mauricio Alvarez. An ex-Disney animator must to finish a silent film script in order to save his soul.

title: Rodeukil
synopsis: Directed by Soo Sung Lee. With Oh Kwang-rok, Cheol-min Lee, Won Ho Shin, Lee Ye-Eun. 'Human makes the way to hell without sin.' Ogwang, a real estate agent is on his way to the countryside for real property development. His journey becomes more and more strange, and eventually leads to accidents. And after a while, he meet Chang's family and each family memebr looks very familiar to him. Jang's family seems to be kind and saved him from ther accident...but later turns into serious misery to him. Ogwang runs away from the situation, but he has no choice to come back repeatdly. That's how Ogwang comes back from his dream. And Ogwang receives the last phone call... What will happen to Ogwang?

title: The Set Up
synopsis: Directed by Niyi Akinmolayan. With Sunny Ajaero, Dakore Akande, Uzor Arukwe, Ayoola Ayolola. A former drug smuggler and a confidence artist gets more than she bargains for when she is hired by a down on his luck businessman to assist with his scheme to marry a wealthy heiress. Things quickly take a turn for the worse as she realises that there is more to the scheme than meets the eye.

title: The Stronghold
synopsis: Directed by Cédric Jimenez. With Gilles Lellouche, Karim Leklou, François Civil, Adèle Exarchopoulos. A police brigade working in the dangerous northern neighborhoods of Marseille, where the level of crime is higher than anywhere else in France.

title: Macabro
synopsis: Directed by Marcos Prado. With Renato Góes, Amanda Grimaldi, Guilherme Ferraz, Diego Francisco. Based on the true story of the "Necrophil Brothers", two young brothers who were accused of brutal murders in the 90's, in Brazil.

title: Fischertag
synopsis: Directed by Thomas Pfaus. With Wolfi Anders, Ela Dollinger, Jo Dollinger, Sandra Grotz.

title: Serious Serial Killers
synopsis: Directed by Tim Rogers. With Sam Amirante, Robert Beattie, David Berkowitz, Barry Boschelli. Take a tour with us as we learn about some of the most violent serial killers to ever walk the earth including BTK, Jeffrey Dahmer, John Wayne Gacy, Ted Bundy, Son of Sam and more.

title: Only the Animals
synopsis: Directed by Dominik Moll. With Denis Ménochet, Laure Calamy, Damien Bonnard, Nadia Tereszkiewicz. A woman disappeared. After a snowstorm, her car is discovered on a road to a small remote village. While the police don't know where to start, five people are linked to the disappearance. Each one with his or her own secret.

title: The Bull
synopsis: Directed by Boris Akopov. With Yuriy Borisov, Stasya Miloslavskaya, Aleksandr Samsonov, Aleksandr Levin. 1997. Russia is finding it tough in the wake of the USSR, a fact reflected in local criminal gangs. Bull is leader of one such. He ends up at the police station, where he s asked pull off a risky mob-job in return of imprisonment.

title: The 12th Suspect
synopsis: Directed by Myoung-Sung Ko. With Kim Sang-kyung, Heo Sung-tae, Kim Dong-young, Ji-Soon Jung. A military detective investigating the murder of a poet in the immediate aftermath of the Korean War.

title: Fanfare
synopsis: Directed by Donku Lee. With Hwa-Young Im, Jong-hwan Park, Yeon-woo Nam, Seung-Won Lee. J, the mysterious woman, may well just be a phenomenon rather than an actual person. A minimal society squeezed within a tight space--this is the stage to express the director's perspective towards intertwined human interactions and current affairs.

title: Peitruss
synopsis: Directed by Max Jacoby. With Peri Baumeister, Maarten Heijmans, Jules Werner, Anouk Wagener. Since she's started a passionate new relationship with the handsome and mysterious Joakim, life is smiling back at Lara again. Her marriage to detective Toni is but a distant memory. But when he accuses Joakim of having committed a series of unsolved murders in Luxembourg City's Peitruss Valley, Lara's world is thrown upside down. While trying to prove his innocence, she starts to wonder how well she really knows the one she loves.

title: Verdict
synopsis: Directed by Raymund Ribay Gutierrez. With Max Eigenmann, Kristoffer King, Jordhen Suan, Rene Durian. Battered wife Joy stands up for justice against her alcoholic husband Dante in a turmoil process of the justice system.

title: Animal Security
synopsis: Directed by Guillaume Falardeau. With Mathieu Dufresne, Marc Fournier, Jean Drolet, Iani Bédard. Following a happy reunion between a young girl and her lost pet, a young enthusiastic wannabe detective creates his own pet detective agency. Tracking him day-to-day with a camera, a friend documents the detective's peculiar career choice, and soon finds himself a partner to his investigations.

title: A Risky Revenge
synopsis: Directed by Paul Ruven. With Max Croes, Golda de Leon, Gonny Gaakeer, Jenny Hsia. A Chinese detective writer has a risky plan to help women revenge their unpunished rapists. #MeToo? Let's take action. Inspired by Hitchcock's "Strangers on a train" (perfect alibi) and Michael Mann's "Collateral" (cab to "justice").

title: Mai arrendersi
synopsis: Directed by Gianluca Ciotta. With Rosario Bonaccorsi, Gianluca Ciotta, Leonardo Costa, Piero Giugno.

title: Whisper of Silent Body
synopsis: Directed by Yanwei Huang, Hai-shu Li. With Dai Si Daisy, Juan Du, Le Geng, Shao-Wen Hao. Forensic pathologist Qin works with his assistant and the police captain to resolve the backlog of cases.

title: Limbo
synopsis: Directed by Tim Dünschede. With Elisa Schlott, Tilman Strauss, Martin Semmelrogge, Mathias Herrmann. 90 minutes, one take

title: Inhale-Exhale
synopsis: Directed by Dito Tsintsadze. With Salome Demuria, Camilla Borghesani, Natalia Gabisonia, Lasha Kabanashvili. Irina, a 43-year-old doctor is returning home from prison for a crime her family knows she did not commit. Once home, things don't go at all as expected. a dark and haunting study of people's unreasoning hatred of those who are different.

title: Hydra
synopsis: Directed by Kensuke Sonomura. With Masanori Mimoto, Miu, Tasuku Nagase, Takaya Aoyagi. Hydra - a small bar in the middle of Tokyo. There's Takashi, standoffish guy working where he hides his another identity of a highly skilled hit man now has to face a brutal killing game that he has been pointed as a target.

title: Poker: Niebezpieczne miasto
synopsis: Niebezpieczne miasto

title: Solid Gold
synopsis: Directed by Jacek Bromski. With Janusz Gajos, Andrzej Seweryn, Marta Nieradkiewicz, Olgierd Lukaszewicz. Kaja Miller is a police officer that is abducted and abused on one of her missions. Eight years later she meets her former boss Nowicki, who takes her to Gdynia with the task of exposing a large criminal circuit.

title: Voice of Silence
synopsis: Directed by Hong Eui-jeong. With Yoo Ah-in, Yoo Jae-myung, Moon Seung-ah, Lee Ka-eun. Two men work for a criminal organization to clean up the aftermath messes. One day, they receive an unexpected order.

title: The Adversary
synopsis: Directed by Brandon Kyle. With Brandon Kyle, Joan James Muixi, Carlos Barbouth, Nick Checket. After a campaign manager witnesses the murder of her high profile client, she finds herself in protective custody and on the run with someone from her past.

title: Asuren II
synopsis: Directed by Rajaram Mohan. With Vishnu Jith, Jijin Nath, Twinkle Raj, Aravind Vijayakumar.

title: Carmen Vidal Mujer Detective
synopsis: Directed by Eva Dans. With Eva Dans, Roberto Suárez, Luciano Demarco, Leonor Courtoisie. Carmen Vidal is a private detective addicted to pizza, beer and marijuana who fights against a criminal Senator to avenge the death of her colleague, in a modern film noir about self-improvement.

title: The Arsonist
synopsis: Directed by Morgan O'Callaghan. With George Everett-Button, Jonny Brookes, Nathan Hoad, Seán Doherty. Detective Harvey Price (George Everett-Button) has been transferred over to a new unit, where he is to befriend his new and intelligent partner Alexander Boston (Jonny Brookes), together, both Alex and Harvey must put their differences to the side so they can tackle a new threat, with very limited help from the corrupt police service they work for. Price is to be challenged both mentally and physically when he is face to face with his cities newest and greatest wanted criminal, known as The Arsonist.

title: Hei bai wu jian
synopsis: Directed by Nuo Si. With Renee Dai, Tony Ho, Chirs Leung, Simon Lui.

title: Xiong di: Yi zi dang tou
synopsis: Yi zi dang tou

title: ECCO
synopsis: Directed by Ben Medina. With Lathrop Walker, Tabitha Bastien, Helena Grace Donald, Michael Winters. Michael vows to hunt down his origin for his family's chance at a new life.

title: Long Live the King
synopsis: Directed by Yoon-Seong Kang. With Rae-won Kim, Jin-ah Won, Jin Seon-kyu, Gwi-hwa Choi. Jang Se Chool is the boss of a gang. He has been in love with Kang So Hyun for the past 3 years, even though she constantly rejects him and tries to push him away. Having had enough, she tells him that she can't be with him because she wants to be the first lady of Korea.

title: Snatch Up
synopsis: Directed by Joon-Hyeong Heo. With Kim Dae-Gon, Kwang-ryul Jun, Oh Jung-se, Mu-Yeol Kim. In this Korean action comedy, seven people including a cop, a killer, gangsters and a delivery man all try to get their hands on a gun and a golf bag filled with cash.

title: Lost Bullet
synopsis: Directed by Guillaume Pierret. With Alban Lenoir, Nicolas Duvauchelle, Ramzy Bedia, Stéfi Celma. A small time delinquent, turned police mechanic for a go fast task force, is forced to defend his innocence when his mentor is killed by dirty cops.

title: Aesop's Game
synopsis: Directed by Naoya Asanuma, Yûya Nakaizumi, Shin'ichirô Ueda. With Guama, Hiroe Igeta, Ruka Ishikawa, Yôta Kawase. Shy and self conscious Miwa attends university, goes home, studies and converses with her turtle. Saori in contrast is an entitled daughter of a rich and somewhat idolized family. Koyuzu is in the family business conducting shady business out of their offices. The agency gets even on behalf of customers. The three become entangled in life and are set against one another, which in their cases is not a simple matter.

title: Maanaya
synopsis: Directed by Anju Dhananjaya. With Wasantha Kumarawila, Upeksha Swarnamali, Pavithra Wickramasinghe, Dilip Manohara. Where gangsters set forth in terrorizing a wealthy family and where a street hoodlum eventually comes to the rescue.

title: Extracurricular
synopsis: Directed by Ivan-Goran Vitez. With Milivoj Beader, Zeljko Königsknecht, Anita Matic Delic, Marko Cindric. The recently divorced father of a nine-year-old, furious his daughter can't spend her birthday with him, bursts into her classroom with a birthday cake and a rifle. A hostage crisis ensues, and the mayor of the town in which the events take place will try to use the situation to gain advantage ahead of the elections, stopping at nothing. The son of a young policeman is in the same class, and before the events unfold, he'll have to answer a question as well.

title: DSP Dev
synopsis: Directed by Mandeep Benipal. With Dev Kharoud, Manav Vij, Aman Dhaliwal, Mehreen Pirzada. Honest police officer, Dev, tries to fight the corrupt system prevalent in Daulatpura because of a powerful criminal. He vows to end the tyrant's hooliganisms and bring peace to the town.

title: Rendez-vous
synopsis: Directed by Pablo Olmos Arrayales. With Antonio Alcantara, Italo Maximiliano Concha Veloz, Aaron Gomez, Markin López. Shot in one single take with no cuts, Rendez-vous is an original Mexican thriller about a couple who meet online.

title: 45 25: #KusursuzCinayet
synopsis: #KusursuzCinayet

title: Deathwell
synopsis: Directed by Ethan Allen. With Mina Tobias, Dakota Kieras, Benjamin J. Welch, Ethan Allen. Unsuspecting citizens become enemies of the state in this pre-apocalyptic noir.

title: Mayar Jonjal
synopsis: Directed by Indranil Roychowdhury. With Kamalika Banerjee, Paran Banerjee, Bratya Basu, Ritwick Chakraborty. A petty criminal who loves a whore and wants to run away with her savings meets a laid-off factory worker who is desperate to stop his wife from working as a housemaid.

title: Danny. Legend. God.
synopsis: Directed by Yavor Petkov. With Dimo Alexiev, Kate Nichols, James Ryan Babson, Valentina Aleksandrova. A city councillor hijacks a documentary team and takes them on a wild and dangerous ride into his ruthless world of corruption.

title: Homicide Watch
synopsis: Directed by Villa Mane. With Jameel Gordon, Villa Mane, Randy Scott, Str8 Dropp tha Prophet. Perry returns to Alabama so he can reconcile with his brother. He quickly finds out it was a mistake.

title: Caliche Run
synopsis: Directed by Morgan Howard. With William Treptow, Josh Blake, Hunter Barker, Brandon Walston. Having served seven years in prison following a failed heist, Gregg Garland is hell-bent on tracking down the man responsible for his downfall.

title: February
synopsis: Directed by Joong-Hyun Kim. With Minkyung Jo, Ju-won Lee, Si-wan Park, Young-bin Park. Min-kyung, who is preparing for civil service examinations while listening to a thief lecture. her struggling urban survival season.

title: Gold Coast Lounge
synopsis: Directed by Pascal Aka. With Pascal Aka, Raquel Ammah, Fred Nii Amugi, Adjetey Anang. An Afro-noir film taking place in the heart of Ghana. A crime family have to clean up their act before the government shuts down their private lounge.

title: Revenge Ride
synopsis: Directed by Melanie Aitkenhead. With Serinda Swan, Diego Boneta, Jake Lockett, Pollyanna McIntosh. Maggie (Serinda Swan) is a tough and ruthless member of the all-female Dark Moon biker gang led by the merciless Trigga (Pollyanna McIntosh). After Maggie's cousin (Vanessa Dubasso) is drugged at a party, the gang rides out for revenge.

title: Clean Sheets
synopsis: Directed by Jake S. Weisman. With Sally Anderson, Shirley Blazen, Dakota Loesch, Veronica Sinclair. Low-level con artists, Bebe and Buzz, raise hell on Bebe's birthday.

title: The Blue Elephant 2
synopsis: Directed by Marwan Hamed. With Karim Abdel Aziz, Nilli Karim, Hind Sabri, Eyad Nassar. A meeting with a new inmate in the psychiatric hospital flips Dr. Yehia's life upside down, he prophesies that the death of his entire family is only three days away.

title: Corruptissima
synopsis: Directed by Andrew Koblick. With Joseph Camilleri, Johnny Gilligan, Andrew Koblick, Douglas Lippi. John Kember former aid to recently murdered Councilman Charles is fired and takes files and other documents with him that will incriminate Developer (and double agent) Ivan Pukowski. Pukowski hires security expert Mario to get the documents. Neither Mario or Kember realize they are caught up in an explosive international scandal that could implicate the POTUS and the British Prime Minister. MI6 agents Percilla Dumprey and Clive Mittlecoat must make sure the documents don't end up in the wrong hands but can't agree on whose hands.

title: Lootcase
synopsis: Directed by Rajesh Krishnan. With Kunal Khemu, Rasika Dugal, Vijay Raaz, Ranvir Shorey. Nandan Kumar comes across a suitcase and discovers it is full of cash. He takes the suitcase and soon finds himself being chased by a notorious gangster, an honest cop and a minister, who want the suitcase at any cost.

title: Ya ne takoy. Ya ne takaya
synopsis: Directed by Ruslan Paushu. With Anna Churina, Kristina Babushkina, Renata Piotrovski, Philippe Reinhardt. Three friends - Vera, Lyuba and Nadia meet in a country house to celebrate Nadia's engagement, but during the celebration they learn that their beloved men use the services of the same prostitute. And it seems that the female ideal world is destroyed forever. Desperate, the girls decide to call a homeowner under the guise of clients, and the bachelorette party takes on a completely unexpected turn.

title: Narco Soldiers
synopsis: Directed by Felix Limardo. With Rafael Amaya, Carolina Guerra, Octavio Pisano, Ricardo Chavira. Narco Soldiers is a timely, action-packed crime thriller that explores the resurgence of the Caribbean drug routes and one couple's violent, Bonnie and Clyde-style rise to power.

title: Amir & Loqman Pergi ke Laut
synopsis: Directed by Mamat Khalid. With Shuib Sepah, Syuk Raja Lawak, Sofi Jikan, Zarina Anjolie. Amir and Loqman, two lowly criminals who are just not cut out for the life of crime, resort to trying their hands at robbing money changers upon learning that they must pay a whopping RM30,000 to exit the 'Brotherhood' they once so badly wanted to join. They now want only one thing - to set up a cafe by the sea and to spend the rest of their days serving drink to beautiful foreigners. They are oblivious to the fact that the Brotherhood are being hunted and viciously killed by three mysterious assassins. Will Amir and Loqman manage to escape the Brotherhood - alive?

title: Queen of the Trap House
synopsis: Directed by Jeff Profitt. With Kelsey Delemar, Jeff Profitt, Charles W Harris III, Hassan Goines. Kionna is a young woman with a bright future, who has fallen in love with a local drug dealer named Tyreek. When Tyreek is locked up, after one of his trap houses are raided by police, he asks Kionna for a huge favor. Tyreek asks Kionna to take over his drug empire until he gets out of jail. Kionna reluctantly agrees to take over and steps into her new position as Queen of the Trap House.

title: The Call
synopsis: Directed by Chung-Hyun Lee. With Park Shin-Hye, Jeon Jong-seo, Kim Sung-ryung, Lee El. Two people live in different times. Seo-Yeon lives in the present and Young-Sook lives in the past. One phone call connects the two, and their lives are changed irrevocably.

title: The Beast
synopsis: Directed by Jung-Ho Lee. With Lee Sung-min, Yoo Jae-myung, Daniel Choi, Kim Dae-Gon. A criminal action movie about two detectives in conflict who solve a murder that shakes up the Korean peninsula.

title: Who Killed Garrett Phillips?
synopsis: Directed by Liz Garbus. With Oral Hillary, Brian Phillips, Tyler Rodrigues. The documentary examines and chronicles the years following the 2011 murder of 12-year-old Garrett Phillips and the subsequent trial of Clarkson University soccer coach Oral "Nick" Hillary.

title: Rounds
synopsis: Directed by Stephan Komandarev. With Ivan Barnev, Assen Blatechki, Ovanes Torosian, Stoyan Doychev. Three police patrol-vehicles, six policemen, city of Sofia in the night, between 9th and 10th of November 2019.

title: Red Snow
synopsis: Directed by Sayaka Kai. With Masatoshi Nagase, Nahana, Arata Iura, Yui Natsukawa. Thirty years after a boy's disappearance, a journalist revives interest in the case, which in turn compels the victim's brother to look for this woman's daughter in the snowy hinterlands of northern Japan.

title: Totgeschwiegen
synopsis: Directed by Franziska Schlotterer. With Claudia Michelsen, Laura Tonke, Katharina M. Schubert, Godehard Giese.

title: Smith
synopsis: Directed by Jaron Lockridge. With Michael LaCour, Buzz Blackburn, Grae Marino, Bianca McMillian. Underwhelmed by corporate assignments, a private detective is approached by a client with the type of investigation he's longed for.

title: Deception of the Novelist
synopsis: Bi zhong you zui

title: Evaru
synopsis: Directed by Venkat Ramji. With Adivi Sesh, Regina Cassandra, Naveen Chandra, Murali Sharma. Sub-inspector Vikram Vasudev is entrusted with the task of investigating the murder of a high ranking officer who was killed by his alleged rape victim. When he delves deeper into the case he uncovers some surprising facts.

title: Mina-anud
synopsis: Directed by Kerwin Go. With Raven Lorenz Eusebio, Rino Gutierrez, Vince Aaron Guimeroy, Ernamae Rosita. Paradise is upturned when 3 tons of cocaine wash up on the peaceful shores of a fishing village. Two local surfers must decide if the lure of a richer tomorrow is really worth risking family and freedom.

title: Vita segreta di Maria Capasso
synopsis: Directed by Salvatore Piscicelli. With Luisa Ranieri, Daniele Russo, Luca Saccoia, Antonio De Matteo. After becoming a widow with three children, Maria accepts the help of Genaro, the rich owner of a car dealership. She is willing to do anything for her family.

title: 1 Time
synopsis: Directed by Kevin Stagger. With David Balderrama, Doug Bitter, Michael Champ Jr., Ray W. Colbert Jr.. Hilarity ensues when two friends, Chino and Eddie, pretend to be cops and end up in a world of trouble when they mess with the wrong drug dealer.

title: Between Wars
synopsis: Directed by Tom Phillips. With Michael Imperioli, Julie Stackhouse, Hollis Sherman-Pepe, Dominic Chianese Jr.. BETWEEN WARS takes an intimate look at the struggle of re-entering civilian life post combat. It follows Veteran Marine Franny Malloy of the Bronx as he struggles with integrating himself back into civilian life post combat in Afghanistan.

title: Marriage
synopsis: Directed by Keke Lowery Jones, Theo Jones. With Malika Edwards, Brandon Jefferson, Paris Lindsay, Sanya Mills. Mr. and Mrs. Spencer were set to enjoy a romantic evening in celebration of their anniversary. However, the evening had other plans for them as it took a turn down homicidal mystery lane. Tune in to find out what happens and to find out who killed Alex.

title: Hamza's suitcase
synopsis: Directed by Akram Farouk. With Hasan Abdulfattah, Youssef Ahmed, Inas Ali, Fares Bakr. Four crime partners devise a plan to get their hands on 3 millions dollars; when the operation is done, they trust the money to one of them; they disappear for 2 months to meet again and divide the money but when they meet after two months, their friend does not show up.

title: Stockholm
synopsis: Directed by Mario Savanco. With Damian Grassi, Malena Otta, Fernando D'Assero, Elivia Dugatto. Desperation and debt causes a man to kidnap a little girl for her ransom. It is a bold and dangerous move, but does he have what it takes to see it through to the end? Does he have it in him to do the unthinkable if necessary?

title: The Forest of Love
synopsis: Directed by Sion Sono. With Kippei Shîna, Shinnosuke Mitsushima, Kyoko Hinami, Eri Kamataki. A small group of student filmmakers and a shy young girl with strict parents are simultaneously manipulated, seduced and abused by an older man. They follow his bidding, even when murder is involved.

title: Operation Undercover 2: Poisonous Dragon
synopsis: Poisonous Dragon

title: Paradise Next
synopsis: Directed by Yoshihiro Hanno. With Satoshi Tsumabuki, Etsushi Toyokawa, Nikki Hsieh, Kaiser Chuang. Three drifting souls meet by chance on an island in high summer and keep each other company. Facing their inner demons and a mysterious killer, can they truly redeem themselves through love and find the paradise in their hearts?

title: Psy 3: W imie zasad
synopsis: Во имя правил

title: Above the Sky
synopsis: Directed by Oksana Karas. With Aleksey Agranovich, Filipp Avdeev, Anastasiya Bogatyreva, Grigoriy Chaban. A young girl spends the summer in a country resort under the watchful eyes of her mother. There, her attention is attracted by a guy whose past is shrouded in mystery.

title: Mafia: Chapter 1
synopsis: Directed by Karthick Naren. With Arun Vijay, Prasanna, Priya Bhavani Shankar, Praveen. A narcotics officer engages in a cat-and-mouse chase to capture a powerful criminal kingpin not knowing that it could have a connection to the truth in his past.

title: Identity (Pehchaan)
synopsis: Directed by Sani Usman. With Salma Agha, Shafqat Cheema. The feature film Identity is a fact-based story centered on the inner feelings of different human beings. The story deals with the tension between desire, carnal feelings, culture. Inspired by real events, this is the story of an open-minded teenage British girl who moves from a very liberal, open English society, to an infamous red-light area in Pakistan. Here, she ends up finding her true origin. In the UK she has qualified as a lawyer and loves to dance, as she has been taught at a private dance academy. She has never traveled to her parents' homeland. She decides to travel thereafter her parents have already flown abroad. She plans a very short stay, due to work commitments in the UK but, unexpectedly, the situation changes during her visit to local village area in Punjab. After arriving in Punjab, and meeting with a school teacher, who comes to teach the area , She feels a sense of lust towards him. She is very liberal and has secret friendships with different people - later including a brother of well-known business personality who invites her to attend a party. She get involves in a murder mystery of young boy. let see what happens next on British Big Screen.

title: Behind Closed Doors
synopsis: Directed by P.A. Carter. In 2008, 13-year-old Aarushi Talwar, and her family's servant, Hemraj Banjade, were found dead in their home in Noida, India. More than a decade later, the case remains unsolved.

title: Inside
synopsis: Directed by Electra Gustafsson. With Sophia Wulsin, Omar Khan, Max Macgibbon, Alex Henrique. An intelligent, reclusive girl joins an inner circle of friends who share a dark secret - they are professional robbers. She must decide between her future or her loyalty to her friends as a detective is closing in on the case.

title: Four Stories of St. Julian
synopsis: Directed by Shane Thueson. With Ky Evans, David Alan Graf, Nicholl Hiren, Tommie St. Cyr. Four strangers become trapped in the elevator of St. Julian-a decrepit, inner-city building. One of the four is an assassin.

title: Transit
synopsis: Directed by Antonio Negret. With Jim Caviezel, Diora Baird, James Frain, Elisabeth Röhm. A gang of bank robbers hide their loot in the car of a family going camping. They chase down the family to kill them and get the loot back, but run into a fight.

title: Wanton
synopsis: Directed by Jaimin Bal. With Aryan Neeraaj Anand, Vipin Bhardwaj, Pooja Chauhan, Varsha Choudhary. On a fateful night, the lives of three friends descend into chaos after one of them commits a gruesome crime in a nightclub.

title: The Flannagans
synopsis: Directed by Jeff Canarsie. With Michael A McGrath, Jeff Canarsie, Elio Forcina, Sean Lynch. Malcom Flannagan, the last of The Westies, tries to keep a firm grip on his crime family.

title: Faking A Murderer
synopsis: Directed by Stuart Stone. With Adam Rodness, Stuart Stone, Josh Cruddas, Phillip Jarrett. In search of their next hit series, two filmmakers embark on an investigation to find a man they believe to be a serial killer. Are they in over their heads? Yes.

title: Eclipses
synopsis: Directed by Fadhel Jaziri. With Ali Jaziri, Yasmine Bouabid, Mohamed Driss, Sarra Hannachi. Hind, a popular television show producer and star presenter, falls in love with Lassaad, a police commissioner who was investigating a murder of a building contractor. in the process, they discover a network of Jihadist smugglers to Syria.

title: Xira
synopsis: Directed by Ashutosh Raj Shrestha. With Namrata Shrestha, Pramod Agrahari, Samrat Magar, Srijana Regmi. Xira is a story about a woman who chose an unconventional path for vengeance. It shows the journey of a mixed-martial arts (MMA) athlete in search of justice for those she loved and lost.

title: The Culprit
synopsis: Directed by Jung-Wook Ko. With Soo-Yeon Han, Jang Hyuk-jin, Hee-tae Jeong, Hyun-Sook Jun. "The Culprit" is about a man named Yeong-hoon who tracks his wife's killer and the tale of his search for justice.

title: Entre El Poder y La Calle
synopsis: Directed by Larry Moreta. With Larry Moreta, Keila Rodríguez Infante, Julio C. Rodríguez, Víctor del Rosario. A corrupt Governor (Mártires Castro) shows himself off as an efficient public server during the day, but at night is the head of a violent and criminal gang of mercenaries. Due to the acts of violence, three detective and special unit cops Kiloa Infante (Larry Moreta), Gutiérrez (Víctor del Rosario) and Bravo (Marcos Sánchez) are sent from the country's capital in order to solve the situation. Rapidly the investigators suspect who is the responsible of the issue and the Governor ignites a bloody counterattack that includes killing Alexa (Keila R. Infante), who happens to be Kiloa's love interest. Soon both cops and criminals face each other putting to the test how ends a life between power and corruption.

title: The Division
synopsis: Directed by Vicente Amorim. With Erom Cordeiro, Thelmo Fernandes, Vanessa Gerbelli, Bruce Gomlevsky. In the 90s, Rio de Janeiro was shaken by a wave of kidnappings. Security forces call controversial agents to help save the city from thugs and also from the police itself.

title: Durj

She also has a crush on the crime reporter Adithya (Thumindu Dodantenna), whose help she seeks for research material on accidents on the flyover. She finds that each day some motorists move the concrete blocks that partition the road just to take a quick U-turn and avoid the traffic. They don't move them back and the blocks are left to lie randomly on the road leading to many accidents. A beggar sitting on the flyover notes down the vehicle numbers of bikers who violate the rule to take the U-turn. Then he gives the list to Raveena. She obtains the details of the culprits using her contact in the traffic department, with the intention of confronting them for their "short-cut" and writing an article for the paper. Her attempt to meet the first person on the list goes in vain. Later the same day, the police take her into custody and accuse her of killing the same person she wanted to meet. She is shocked and tells her side of the story. Though the senior police officer rejects it, sub-inspector Ranga (Hemal Ranasinghe), finds it believable and does some investigation. It is revealed that all the persons Raveena has on her list have committed suicide. They also noticed that they have committed suicide the same day they took the wrong "u-turn". Raveena and Ranga find another number has been noted by the beggar which is to be delivered to Raveena the next day. The duo trace the address and try to rescue the man, a lawyer (Rana Madhav) , who has taken the u-turn on the same day. As nothing seems suspicious, both leave only to encounter the very death of the lawyer whom they came to rescue.

title: The Secret Safari
synopsis: Directed by Tom Zubrycki. A dramatized documentary showing how volunteers from England and Holland drove trucks full of hidden guns and ammunition overland across Africa to supply the African National Congress in their fight against the Apartheid government. Forty tons were transported under the seats of unsuspecting tourists on Africa Hinterland Expeditions between 1987 and 1993. No-one was ever caught and the mission remained one of the ANC's deepest secrets until 2001. The simple but ingenious technique of hiding the weapons was made more effective by the cover of the white tourists and the European drivers. In the 'Secret Safari' the filmmakers found the original tourists and reveal the most unusual holiday secret to very different responses.
