When a woman Vitele Webb (Mari) a writer is involved in three different abusive relationships, over a 13 year span learns that love can be found in an unlikely source. How many times does he have to hit you in order for you to realize that love isn't suppose to hurt. Mari is dealing with abuse from a physical, mental and emotional stand point. This story base loosely on true encounters will have you in tears. Mari searching for answers and praying to God to release her from the torment. Mari has to go through the storm to regain her faith, each one of her abuser, brought a different type of pain. Aiden, a man full of ANGER played by Willie Taylor Izzy, a man full of INSECURITY played by Rodney Staton Marcus, a man full of MANIPULATION played by Reggie Gaskins Nosy Liz played by Dee Armstrong brings the laughter after the pain, and becomes the hero who see and hears everything. Her faith in God brings the story of survival to another level. Jesus loves you and so do I. A.I.M this drama filled production bringing awareness to abuse. And when a mother is like mommy dearest bringing forth secrets from the past that will explain why a mothers love was never felt. Drea Kelly ( Mother Rose) delivers an astonishing performance of redemption, with secrets from her past becoming a shocking revelation to Mari, explains a lot of why the sense of disconnect was felt. If you know anyone dealing with abuse, get them the support they need. Angry Insecure Men tells of a story felt by many survivors. The production based off the novel "Angry Insecure Men" written by Angel Terron.

title: Rock and a Hard Place
synopsis: Directed by Jay Espinal. With Thomas Watts.

title: Journey of Unity
synopsis: Directed by Lawrence Doc Hollywod McMichael. With Kimberly Bailey, Tamika Bailey, Joshua Bolden, Carolyn Davenport.

title: On the Nanniwan Frontier
synopsis: Directed by Diana Pang. With Ta Ji, Diana Pang, Shuai Ren, Ren Shuai.

title: Get Real
synopsis: Directed by Darby Christensen. With Kali Holman, Peter King, Abigail Knoettgen, Reed Madden. Set in the 1980s, David is an aloof nerd who meets an unlikely group of friends

title: Terrolun and Lunlun
synopsis: Directed by Hiroyuki Miyagawa. With Maiko Kawakami, Amane Okayama, Rina Ono.

title: Arrhythmia
synopsis: Directed by Gibran Bazan. With Fernando Sarfatti, Valentina Buzzurro, Salvatore Nocera, Patrizia Schiavo. A man who followed the beating of his heart.

title: Stars Await Us
synopsis: Directed by Dalei Zhang. With Hai-Qing, Jing Dong Liang. Released from prison on New Year's Eve, Ma Biao returns to a freezing border town between China and Russia. He searches for former lover Karinna, but unwittingly gets dragged again into a gangland conflict from years ago.

title: Send Me to the Clouds
synopsis: Directed by Congcong Teng. With Chen Yao, Jiuxiao Li, Xinming Yang, Yufang Wu. Diagnosed with ovarian cancer, a 29-year-old journalist who longs for true love ends up writing the biography for an entrepreneur's father, which leads her to embark on an existential journey.

title: Sudba
synopsis: Directed by Zhanna Issabayeva. Azat, is a 19-year-old villager who comes to a big city of Almaty to work in the construction team of his elder brother. In the city there will be the "crossroad of fate" which determines how things will unfold in Azat's life.

title: The Sacred Arrow
synopsis: Directed by Pema Tseden. With Deji, Duobujie, Dunzhu Renqing. Set in the Qinghai province. Two Tibetan villages keep friendship from generation to generation. Now two young man will compete in an upcoming archery contest.

title: Love Song 1980
synopsis: Directed by Feng Mei. With Xian Li, Jessie Li, Yanlu Yang, Mai Zi. Love Song 1980 tells a story of love and hatred between several young men and women in the 1980s. It covers family relationships, friendship, love and three-dimensional characters with touching stories.

title: Super Me
synopsis: Directed by Chong Zhang. With Talu Wang, Jia Song, Kevin Lee, Gang Wu. A young scriptwriter starts bringing valuable objects back from his short nightmares of being chased by a demon. Selling them makes him rich.

title: Vermelha
synopsis: Directed by Getúlio Ribeiro. With Emerson Alves, Jonatas Borges, Maurício Cruz, Maria Divina.

title: Over Again
synopsis: Directed by Ming Hua. With Hao Chen, Zhiyong Ding, Yuexi Gai, Yuzhe Gan. The story follows two childhood friends as they go back in time to try and prevent the suicide of their other best friend.

title: Sunray
synopsis: Directed by Natalie Spence. With Patrick Anthony, Robert Ball, Lisa Banks, Travis Bryant. A soldier is haunted by ghosts of the past as he wrestles with those of the present.

title: Bad Class
synopsis: Directed by Han Dong-ho. Ji-eun has a bad impression of men due to bad experiences with her father but her mom Hyeon-ah convinces her into getting tuition from an art student. Jeong-woo is surprised at how cold she is towards him but at the same time, there's tension between the two.

title: L'autre
synopsis: Directed by Charlotte Dauphin. With Astrid Bergès-Frisbey, James Thierrée, Anouk Grinberg, Jean-Louis Martinelli. An intimate portrait of a woman's mental confrontation and drifting between dream and reality after experiencing loss.

title: Finky
synopsis: Directed by Dathaí Keane. With Dara Devaney, Ned Dennehy, Diarmuid de Faoite, Fionnuala Gygax. A young musician with a tragic past is crippled in a car accident and given a chance at redemption when he is recruited by a violent, avant-garde circus.

title: You Mean Everything to Me
synopsis: Directed by Bryan Wizemann. With Morgan Saylor, Ben Rosenfield, Lindsay Burdge, Bene Coopersmith. Cassandra falls hard and fast for Nathan, a local DJ. As his coercive control increases and his demands grow darker, she must decide what her own freedom is worth.

title: Omar and Us
synopsis: Directed by Mehmet Bahadir Er, Maryna Er Gorbach. With Cem Bender, Taj Sher Yakub, Menderes Samancilar, Hala Alsayasneh. Ismet is a Turkish soldier, who was on duty at the border as a Commander of the Coast Guard and recently got retired. Now as a civilian, he struggles to communicate with his family and people surrounding him. His only son abandoned him and left to the U.S.

title: Chernobyl: Zona otchuzhdeniya
synopsis: Зона отчуждения. Финал

title: Chasing a broken heart
synopsis: Directed by Pierre Nicolas. With Marion Ossent, Zack Zublena.

title: Illegal Woman
synopsis: Directed by Ramon Térmens. With Daniel Faraldo, Isak Férriz, Yolanda Sey, Montse Germán. The life of an immigration lawyer changes radically when his new client appears dead in suspicious circumstances inside a CIE (immigration detention center).

title: One Night
synopsis: Directed by Kazuya Shiraishi. With Yôsuke Asari, Hanae Kan, Mayu Matsuoka, Megumi. A mother and her three children find their fate thrown into chaos by an incident that happened one night. The family members each go their separate ways but reunite after 15 years and struggle to restore their family bonds.

title: Taste of Life
synopsis: Directed by Yu-Shan Huang. With Hsiao-hsuan Chen, Duncan Lai, Yvonne Yao, Danni Liang. Different styles of dining can also be portrayed as different types of life. Restaurant hostess, Liu Fen-Fang, prepares a feast for the new opening of her restaurant. Deep in her heart, however, she also experiences her most bitter moment. Her family is shattered when she hears news of her husband's affair. Fen-Fang considers marriage as her forever refuge. She never expects to face such crisis. She alone must continue to persist. The couple, seemingly in harmony, but at odds, are managing restaurants together at the same time. Fen-Fang's good friend, Yi-Rong, helps manage the restaurant.Restaurant's customers, a mainland General and a local councilman, are in opposition. From refusing to give in to becoming in-laws, everyone stages their taste of life. This urban implication of the multiple aspects of life, people with prestige and beauty, hidden struggles and temptation, are all portrayed through dining.

title: Nadhoo Khan
synopsis: Directed by Imran Sheikh. With Singh. Balli, Vaneesa Bansal, Gurpreet Bhangu, Harinder Bhullar. A man tries to heed his grandfather's advice to stay away from women while pursuing his dream of becoming a wrestler.

title: Undga
synopsis: Directed by Vikrant Nandkumar Warde. With Mayur Bachhav, Shivani Baokar, Jyoti Bavdhankar, Sharvari Gaikawad. A studious boy Vijya and mischievous troublemaker Ganya become best friends and continue on their unique paths until the dynamics of their friendship is changed by Meera's entry into their world.

title: Vremeto e nashe
synopsis: Directed by Petar Popzlatev. With Itschak Fintzi, Irini Jambonas, Elena Telbis, Ruscen Vidinliev. During a turmoil period in Bulgaria, after the communist regime fell, the writer Martin Sestrimski receives a dangerous file about himself from his friend Boyan Tilev - a DS (National Security Service) agent.

title: Love Sick Diaries
synopsis: Directed by Mike Ahuja. With Chris Vent, Maggie Hai-Uyen, James Russo, West Liang. A film that attempts to reconstruct the expected, while taking you on a journey through the heart of a young man battling his addiction of love, life, and obsession. This is a sick and twisted love story that tackles the "Love is blind" theme in a whole new innovative fashion.

title: La rivoluzione
synopsis: Directed by Joseph Troia. With Paolo Marco Caterino, Vittorio Nastri, Giulia Schiavo. Two boys and a girl perform a violent act in the name of the ideals they believe in, but a tragic accident will challenge their convictions.

title: Sem Raiz
synopsis: Directed by Renan Rovida. With Carlota Joaquina, Renan Rovida, Maria Tereza Urias, Deborah Hathner.

title: Fingertips of an Angel
synopsis: Directed by Mohsen Aghalar. With Mahchehreh Khalili, Arash Mashverat. A couple is driving along a country road. The man would like to pull over and rest for a while; the beautiful landscape reminds him of God. As they arrive in the city at midnight, they realize that their car has run out of gas. Since the woman needs the car the next morning, the man decides to go and look for a petrol station to fill the car up; so his dreamlike night journey begins, taking him back to where he started.

title: Karma ke Rati
synopsis: Directed by Jayanta Nath. With Aimee Baruah, Rajkumar, Podmaraag Goswami, Rimpi Das. It is a story of an ideal teacher who leads a few youths and through education inspires them to fight against corrupt politicians by joining the administration and police force.

title: Darah Panas
synopsis: Directed by Arjin Uppal. With Sharnaaz Ahmad, Nur Fathia, Adam Corrie, Sofi Jikan. Syahana is a very religious girl who has a dream of becoming a Muslim model due to the influences of modeling videos on social media. Syahana then seeks for help from Fandi, a guy she met on the Internet who claims that he can help Syahana achieve her dreams. When her father and brother object to her decisions, she runs away to Kuala Lumpur to meet Fandi alone. Upon reaching Kuala Lumpur, she finds out she has been tricked and Fandi is bringing her into the world of prostitution instead of modeling.

title: In a New York Minute
synopsis: Directed by Ximan Li. With Celia Au, Amy Chang, Yi Liu, Ludi Lin. In A New York Minute follows three strangers as they accidentally discover the solution to their problems lies in a single pregnancy test. Amy is haunted by a past breakup that has manifested into an eating disorder. Angel is caught between a loveless marriage to an American business man and a passionate affair with a Chinese writer. Nina moonlights as an escort in order to support herself.

title: Double Twisting Double Back
synopsis: Directed by Joseph Abello. With Tony Labrusca, Mon Confiado, Juancho Miguel Besana, Ella Mae McCoy. A year ago, Badger was one of the best gymnasts in the Philippines. He wanted to be the very best, until his reckless best friend sabotaged his athletic career. Now, Badger is miserably working as a distributor, selling alcoholic beverages to the managers of bars and supermarkets. To his delight, Badger receives a new opportunity to pursue his quest to be the best Filipino gymnast. He immediately resigns from his job. His reckless best friend, who fulfills his desires through this job, gets pissed and vows to stop Badger's dream once again.

title: Common Creed
synopsis: Directed by Logan Kyngston. With Hakeem Sharif, Steven P. Hamm, LaToy Fowler, Devonte M. Hodges. Based on true events that happened in Cleveland, Ohio during the heroin and opioid epidemic. The epidemic has caused destruction and havoc in the city. A Cleveland Police detective starts an investigation to put an end to the biggest drug rings ever to exist. Meanwhile, a local rapper has showcased phenomenal talent and success with his music but associates himself with the biggest drug traffickers in Ohio. His association will unravel the beginning of his misfortune with the mafia and other powers to be. The drug traffickers love making the easy money but sometimes your greed opens other evil doors. These wide-ranging events occur often and prevalent, surviving is what they all believe in morally or dishonorably.

title: Chasing 3000
synopsis: Directed by Gregory J. Lanesey. With Ray Liotta, Trevor Morgan, Rory Culkin, Lauren Holly. Two brothers drive across country to see their hero, Roberto Clemente, get his 3000th hit.

title: The Rain Fairy
synopsis: Directed by Milan Cieslar. With Lenka Vlasáková, Vica Kerekes, Jakub Gottwald, Miroslav Donutil. The elements that rule Earth - Air, Fire, Earth and Water - are on their "regular inspection tour." We are following Water, in the form of the Rain Fairy (Lenka Vlasáková). Traversing the land dressed like a poor woman, she learns that people really have begun focusing mainly on money and that love and goodness are disappearing. The Rain Fairy is a classic romantic fairy tale, but one that deviates from contemporary story clichés.

title: Dhuntaaraa
synopsis: Directed by Amit Ojha. With Zaidaan Khan, Mradul Ojha, Muskaan Ojha, Neelam Ojha. Four children from city move to a village close by, for a fun filled vacation and end up finding answers to many of their hitherto unanswered questions that they had always harboured in their anxious young minds. They learn moral values and what life is all about, outside of their regimented school environment and how to handle it like young adults. The story revolves around how they meet an exceptionally talented but poor village boy Deepu and his mentor, an old gentleman fondly referred to by everyone as Bauji . Their friendship with Deepu turns out to be a learning experience for the city kids and they all also end up solving a dangerous puzzle in the village.

title: Jai Chhathi Maa
synopsis: Directed by Murari Sinha. With Preeti Jhangiani, Ravi Kishan, Gurleen Chopra, Rahul Jain. Chhathi Maa, a very popular goddess having a strong emotional attachment with more than 21 crore people staying in Bihar, Jharkhand, Uttar Pradesh, Delhi, Mumbai, Punjab, Bengal, Assam, Gujarat, and Himachal. Jai Chhathi Maa is a contemporary/mythological Hindi feature Film that showcases the origin/ history of Chhathi Puja, which is celebrated in almost all parts of the country. The film also shows the impact of the puja on our modern life, as the process of puja has a lot of science behind it.

title: Aghavan
synopsis: Directed by Ezhumalai. With Chirashree Anchan, Chinni Jayanth, Kishore, R.N.R. Manohar. A group of criminals hatch a plan to loot the wealth of a huge temple for their selfish needs.

title: Maa Purnagiri
synopsis: Directed by Ravi Sinha. With Madhu Bharti, Manish Chaturvedi, Gajendra Chauhan, Poonam Dubey. This movie is based on mythological place "Maa Purnagiri" situated at Tanakpur, Uttarakhand, India. Maa Purnagiri is well known a spiritual shaktipith one of 51. Maa Purnagiri is a symbol and aw tar of ma ta parvati. More then one lake disciple go to take ashirvad of ma ta purnagiri.

title: Zhili-byli my
synopsis: Directed by Anna Tchernakova. With Sonya Galishnikova, Leonid Bichevin, Anya Korneva, Dmitriy Pevtsov. One beautiful summer morning in a small Russian country town, six-year Marussya wakes up to the sound of her parents arguing. When her mum departs 'for the city' with no set date for return, and her dad suggests that he and Marussya take a train to Lake Baikal, Marussya is determined to delay the departure. She improvises a fairy tale, in which her mum, as a school-age girl, sets off on a dangerous journey to an imagined Russian past to save Marussya's dad, then her schoolmate.

title: Os Jovens Baumann
synopsis: Directed by Bruna Carvalho Almeida. With Daniel Mazzarolo. In 1992, during a meeting held at the family estate in the interior of Minas Gerais, all young heirs of the Baumann family mysteriously disappeared. The event is revisited by filming and old photographs, hoping to reconstitute his last days and solve the case.

title: Momi's House
synopsis: Directed by Yoshihiro Sakamoto. With Yu Futami, Sara Minami, Aoi Nakamura, Seina Nakata. A group home for youth called Momi's House is a location for troubled adolescents. Yasutoshi who runs the place with his wife has a way and methodology with the youth under his care. Sixteen-year-old Ayaka has a troubled recent past including disobedience, disinterest in school and studies and more. She is sent to Momi's House.

title: Enchanted Feather
synopsis: Directed by Zdenek Troska. With Anastázie Chocholatá, Lukás Pavlásek, Sárka Vaculíková, Lucie Polisenská. In this Cinderella-like fable, a woman conjures a Prince from a bird feather. Aninka, the youngest of three sisters, deals day in and day out with her bullying siblings. When Aninka and the Prince magically fall in love, they must work to break a witch's curse together.

title: Big Truck Factory
synopsis: Directed by Les Anas. With Les Anas. Timmy Uppet and his pals are at the Vidsville Big Truck Factory. They are testing for safety, learning different colors, shapes, and they are counting the big trucks.

title: Kazka staroho melnyka
synopsis: Directed by Aleksandr Itygilov. With Anna Koshmal, Ada Rogovtseva, Leonid Shevchenko, Ostap Stupka.

title: Sakura
synopsis: Directed by Hitoshi Yazaki. With Tamiyasu Chô, Masaya Katô, Takumi Kitamura, Yui Kobayashi. Three siblings share a home with their parents living a happy life. The oldest one is good-looking guy, which is something of a contrast from his younger brother who is at school. The youngest one is the girl and has two brothers to protect her. Unfortunately an accident knocks out the oldest sibling. It is not a happy time.

title: XiaoMei
synopsis: Directed by Yinqian. With Zhang LuHan. The movie "Xiaomei" tells the touching story of the protagonist Niu Xiaomei and the unrelated Guo family in a flashback. The film shows the great love between people with little love story, and presents a vivid, lively, rich and real picture of people in all aspects.

title: Tujhich Re
synopsis: Directed by Pravin Raja Karale. With Priyanka Yadav, Akshay Kambli, Milind Gawali, Sumukhi Pendse. A girl from hindu family falls in love with a christian guy who belongs to the middle class christian family.They gets drown to the unexpected uncertainty.Will they get success or the death falls them apart .

title: L.I.F.E. (Leading Individuals Forward Everyday) Symposium
synopsis: Directed by Carlos Wallace. With Carlos Wallace, Cherry Sawyerr, Michelle Wiggins, Rachel Birdow-Foy. The L.I.F.E. Symposium is a veritable Master Class in society's relevant issues and controversial ideas presented by A-list orators, and is inspired by the bestselling book, Life Is Not Complicated, You Are

title: Yume no Oto
synopsis: Directed by Takeshi Matsuura. With Chiaki Mayumura, Yumeno Koda, Kosuke Yamazaki, Eiji Fujimura.

title: Poesia e Melodia
synopsis: Directed by Flávio Colombini. With Flávio Colombini, Solange Kei, Gisele Freire, Lucinete do Nascimento Alves. A poet and a singer get together to create funny poems and songs for children. They strive to publish their work and to spread joy to all the children they meet.

title: Noah
synopsis: Travel with Noah as he fulfills God's wish, even amidst seemingly impossible odds and the scrutiny of onlookers.

title: Hello, My Cat
synopsis: Directed by Hye-Jin Shin, Woon Suk Bok. The Omnibus movie is composed of 4 episodes about human beings and cats.

title: Lunana: A Yak in the Classroom
synopsis: Як в классной комнате

title: The Ten Virgins
synopsis: Directed by Blessing Effiom Egbe. With Aanu Adeleke, Honey Adum, Tunbosun Aiyedehin, Ogechi Aniegboka. Ten Virgin maidens engaged to a great prince must remain faithful to him while he is away on an infinite journey

title: Welcome Home
synopsis: Directed by Sumitra Bhave, Sunil Sukthankar. With Mrinal Kulkarni, Sumeet Raghavan, Spruha Joshi, Mohan Agashe. Unable to find meaning in the relationship with her husband, Saudamini decides to move on in life. What follows is her struggle to come to terms with the decision.

title: Magic Fairytale
synopsis: With Andrea Ivett Eröss, Cristina Strecopitov.

title: From Sensei
synopsis: Directed by Wataru Hiranami, Hiroshi Horiuchi, Wataru Kudô. 'I've been consumed with how I should atone for my past misdeeds.' A young would-be writer named Tadashi Makita (Ryotaro Akazawa) working as an apprentice,is asked by Kyusaku Komiya(Naha takashi) to find "Kouya Komiya". He visited the literature editor who works for publisher Kazuma Taniguchi (Shogo Taniguchi) literature editor as Kyusaku said. It is discovered that the name of "Kouya" has won up to the primary selection stage of the rookie award. Kouya wrote a piece called 'Sensei's Testament'. Tadashi tracks the whereabouts of Koya to make Kyusaku's wish come true. At that time Kyusaku's wife,Kanae,tells her old student, Kousaku Mamiya (Toshiki Tateishi) who is working at club that provides male drinking companions for women, to visit room 202 at the apartment Kouya Komiya rents. Although Kyusaku, the guarantor, was contacted about the rent being in arrears, he says that he did not know anything. Kanae was suspicious that there may be a mistress. One day, a man who professes to be Komiya Komiya (Shunsuke Kobayakawa) appears, itis from here our story begins. Before long, Kyusaku tells Tadashi a secret that he has not revealed to anyone before. It was the story of the youthful period that Kyusaku (Naoya Kitagawa), Kenji Makita (Yoshimura Shinsaku), and Izumi Takada (Kaho Ito) spent together. After all, Who is Kouya Kouya? What is Kyusaku's Seacret? A new story begins with the Encounters attracted by each 'teacher'.

title: 10 Days with Dad
synopsis: Directed by Ludovic Bernard. With Franck Dubosc, Aure Atika, Alice David, Alexis Michalik. Antoine is the Head of HR of a big company. When his wife decides to go on holiday and leave him with the responsibility of their four kids, he knows it will be easy. But Antoine has underestimated the mess that it can be.

title: East & West
synopsis: Directed by Roberto De Tagle Jr.. With Joey Ruggiero, Christian Vilina, Kody Dixon, Tiffany Colt Marie De Tagle. Two high school friends, East and West, meet at the same spot annually where a tragic Event took place that would forever change their futures.

title: Infernal Guidon, or Cossack Christmas
synopsis: Directed by Misha Kostrov. With Aleksandr Pozharskiy, Kostyantyn Linartovych, Grigoriy Baklanov, Diana Rozovlyan. It is a fairy tale for children and adolescents. It tells about famous warriors Cossacks and their families. It's about the Paradise and the Hell, Christmas and evil powers. The Devil strikes a deal with St. Peter. If he can capture the best Cossack warrior and hold him until the Christmas night, he will be able to wipe the entire Cossack nation off the map. After that, the Devil catches a Cossack warrior Simon by using underworld trickery. Meanwhile, Simon's parents are trying to save their son. Traditional heroes of the Ukrainian folklore come to help. As long as our hero tries to free himself, the devil creates a mighty army and transforms Semen's friends into witches. In the end, Simon finds his Cossack way out of captivity to freedom.

title: Arthur L'aventurier en Afrique
synopsis: Directed by Jason Arbour. With Francois Tremblay, Sylvester Henry, Mze Laiboni, Annette Loy.

title: The Outsider
synopsis: Directed by Low Ngai Yuen. With Sofia Jane, Carmen Soo, Kk Wong, Sawyer Leong. A prejudiced man chases away a homeless woman sleeping behind his restaurant. To his shock, his wife then brings her home to live with them.

title: Take Over Zone
synopsis: Directed by Shimpei Yamasaki. What is a family? Become a family if you have been together for years. Become a lover if you have been together for years. How long have you been together to become friends? I wanted to see how the family changed.

title: Arthur l'aventurier : L'oeil de cristal
synopsis: L'oeil de cristal

title: Spasibo dedu za pobedu
synopsis: Directed by Teimuraz Taniyah. With Egor Beroev, Aleksey Onezhen, Kesou Khagba, Kseniya Alfyorova. An ordinary city boy goes with his father to visit his grandfather in the village. There he is met by not very friendly local boys and a girl with whom he immediately falls in love. His grandfather is constantly telling funny stories about his glorious military past, which open up a completely new, magical world for him, teach him the main values of life and make him a real man.

title: Rakhi Ke Laaj
synopsis: Directed by N. Mandal. With Akshara Dubey, Jay Krishna Dutta, Manish Nandan Jha, Mohan Jha. Maithili Future Film based on Dowry System. This film is directed by N. Mandal. This film is targeted to cater Maithli region. The family drama and social messages are the key elements of this Film.

title: Broken Souls
synopsis: With Jason Bannett, Christopher Goodman, Ronald Goodman, Toni Hoover. Priscilla Smith's sanity is tested when she is separated from her beloved husband Adolph who is called for military service in Afghanistan. Left to raise their only child Sophia alone, Priscilla struggles with self-esteem issues and hopelessly uses prescription drugs to help her cope with the emptiness she feels in a community that has lost its men to war and prisons.

title: Brother in Love
synopsis: Directed by Onur Bilgetay. With Cem Gelinoglu, Melis Babadag, Ege Kökenli, Müfit Kayacan. After a series of lies and misunderstandings, Aykut, a straightforward craftsmen, finds himself in the middle of wedding plans with Gulsah, an insurance broker. The problem is that Aykut is marrying with his fiance Nurhan a week later, whose family could kill him if they know the truth.

title: Koi Aane Parnavo
synopsis: Directed by Haribhai Maniya. With Abhay Chandarana, Zeel Joshi, Kalpesh Patel, Kalpesh Rajgor. Koi Aane Parnavo is a struggle for finding A Bride for Bhurabhai.. A simple and very innocent Village boy. A Out and Out Fund Ride when Bhura Bhai makes mess of every meeting for his marriage due to his innocence.

title: Arthur L'aventurier au Costa Rica
synopsis: Directed by Francois Tremblay. With Felipe Martin, Francois Tremblay.

title: Chidi Balla
synopsis: Directed by Radheshyam Pipalwa. With Chetan Sharma, Mayur More, Abhimanyu Singh, Suneel Sinha. In the 1980s, Principal of Shekhawati High School in Sikar, Rajasthan is faced with the daunting task of saving the school from shutting down. The only way he can save the school is by improving its academic results, which is impossible in a village that gambles and fritters away their time. The other option available for him is to somehow inspire the school to win the State Level Badminton Tournament. The Principal summons Bhagat and explains to him about the crisis faced by the school to stay afloat. Bhagat enjoys playing 'Chidi Balla' with his gang and has no idea about Badminton, is suddenly burdened with the responsibility of saving his school. Will Bhagat transform his game of Chidi Balla to Badminton and triumph against all odds to save his school? In Bhagat's quest to save the school, the indolent villagers rally around him and in the process; they themselves transform and turn over a new leaf. They go on to restore the forgotten heritage and culture of Sikar to its past glory.

title: A Wild Fox Life
synopsis: Directed by Ana Luisa Santos. A Wild Fox Life, chronicles the lives of three foxes, Hunter, Scar and Red who live on a large open savannah landscape in the Netherlands. Through the eyes and voice of Hunter, we follow how she grows up from being a 6 week old fox cub to raising cubs of her own. Filmmakers Ana Luisa Santos and Michael Sanderson followed and filmed these red foxes in the Dutch nature reserve Oostvaardersplassen. In this rare wildlife film, where every animal you see is 100% wild and free from manipulation, we delve into secret lives of truly wild foxes. Here they live and behave in a world without humans where they are the top predators and scavenge carcasses of large herbivores. Hunter hunts geese with high speed chases and Red shows his paternal tenderness towards his newborn cubs. We get to know the three siblings who take different paths in becoming adults. Come and take a journey inside the skin of Hunter, who will show you her side of the story in her wild fox life.

title: Finding Light at the Darkness Festival
synopsis: Directed by Yukiyasu Asano. A man with family troubles suddenly loses his job and finds a light of hope through a magnificent 1,000 year old community festival that he reluctantly joins.

title: Amber Light
synopsis: Directed by Hatsuki Yokoo. With Kumiko Endô, Saburô Ishikura, Arata Iura, Satoshi Judai. Taking inspiration from director Yokoo's own personal experiences, the story revolves around Ryota Hironaga's family where the parents have been divorced for almost as long as he can remember. He was raised by a single mother as a result. There was an empty seat at the dinner table as a result, which he and his sibling seek to fill by searching for their father.

title: Kaarmoda Saridu
synopsis: Directed by Udaya Kumar. With Manju Rajanna, Advithi Shetty, Akshok, Divyashree. After an unsuccessful suicide attempt, Karthik is able to see the ghosts of four people - an old man, a crying woman, a little kid and a chain smoker. This meet changes his life as he tries to fulfill the last wishes of these ghosts which helps them to rest in peace. Karthik discovers a purpose in his life as he finds happiness in the small things.

title: Kim Daha Mutlu?
synopsis: Directed by Hakan Haksun. With Ecem Özkaya, Serenay Aktas, Hasan Denizyaran, Ümit Erdim.

title: Oh! Squints III
synopsis: Directed by Neil LaBute, Cody Broadway, David Mickey Evans. With Philip Anthony-Rodriguez, Allen Chen, Andie Chen, Hanwei Chen.

title: Sestrenka
synopsis: Directed by Aleksandr Galibin. With Arslan Krymchurin, Marta Kessler, Usuf Rakhmetov, Ilgiza Gilmanova. As far back as Yamil can remember, the war was always. But Yamil is waiting for its end, because then his Father, known to the boy only through photos and letters, will be back home. One day his Mother goes to a distant city and brings a silent girl Oksana. Mother also brings his Father's order to take care of Oksana as if she were his sister.

title: The Fantastic Journey of Margot & Marguerite
synopsis: Directed by Pierre Coré. With Lila Gueneau Lefas, Alice Pol, Clovis Cornillac, Nils Othenin-Girard.

title: Kontora
synopsis: Directed by Anshul Chauhan. With Seira Kojima, Wan Marui, Hidemasa Mase, Takuzo Shimizu. Guided by her grandfather's WWII-era diary, Sora searches for a mysterious trove in the wilderness of her hometown. Meanwhile, a mysterious mute and backward-walking homeless man wanders into town who may be the catalyst to put her shattered relationship with her father back together.

title: A Christmas Hero
synopsis: Directed by Phil Wurtzel. With Michael Welch, Patrick Floch, Cat Grey, Peter Carey. When a young disillusioned war vet, home from Afghanistan, sees nothing good in his life during Christmas a visit by his guardian angel shows him that his life really did make a difference.

title: Kaden Ryan's Summer Adventure's
synopsis: Directed by Kaden Ryan Thompson. With Kinsey Chavis. This is a movie about Kaden Ryan and his friends Summer Adventures.

title: Ijang
synopsis: Directed by Seung-O Jeong. With Ri-woo Jang, Seon-hee Lee, Geum Sun-Ah Yoon, Kwak Min-Gyoo. Hye Yeong receives a letter of notification that her father's grave should be forcibly removed due to modernization projects. Hye Yeong and the sisters are gathered in a long time, but only the brother cannot reach easily.

title: Tolo Tolo
synopsis: Directed by Checco Zalone. With Checco Zalone, Souleymane Sylla, Manda Touré, Nassor Said Birya. Pierfrancesco "Checco" Zalone, a failed entrepreneur, seeks a new life as a waiter on a holiday village in Africa, but the appearance of ISIS forces him to travel again.

title: Masal Satosu: Sihirli Davet
synopsis: Sihirli Davet

title: The Nutcracker: The Untold Story
synopsis: Directed by Andrey Konchalovskiy. With Richard Philipps, Fernanda Dorogi, Kriszta Dorogi, Dániel Mogács. In 1920s Vienna, a young girl receives a magical doll on Christmas Eve.

title: Konusan Hayvanlar
synopsis: Directed by Mustafa Kotan. With Emir Özyakisir, Ferit Aktug, Ayça Erturan, Ebru Akel. Can is a child who lives with his family in the buildings inside of the animal protection park. His whole family is also working there. Can loves animals and he is also a different and special child, because he hears animals and talks to them. One day, the owner of the park decides to sell parks land. Can has no intention of leaving the park where he was born and raised...

title: Juf Roos is Jarig
synopsis: Directed by Jan-Willem Wit. With Melissa Drost, Jörgen Scholtens.

title: The Preparation
synopsis: Directed by Young-Jun Cho. With Anastasia Kim, Du-shim Ko, Cheol-min Park, Min-kwan Park. A mother who has been diagnosed with terminal cancer prepares her mentally disabled son for her inevitable passing.

title: Playmakers
synopsis: Directed by Reza Serkanian. Teenage migrants arrived in France without parents, go on stage to recount the exile and their brutally interrupted childhood. They dreamed of a better world, wanted to be free, to live in peace. After a long perilous journey to Europe, they discover a reality they did not know. They suffer but their dignity impresses. From victims to authors, they transcend to cultural playmakers.

title: Abar boshonto
synopsis: Directed by Ananyo Mamun. With Shajid Ahmed, Tariq Anam Khan, Imtu Ratish, Orchita Sporshia.

title: Doremi & You
synopsis: Directed by B.W. Purba Negara. With Adyla Rafa Naura Ayu, Devano Danendra, Fatih Unru, Nashwa Zahira. Four friends try to change the money from the extracurricular choir that they accidentally omitted, by participating in the Doremi and You singing competition.

title: Ife Aimo (unknown Love)
synopsis: Directed by Titi Jeje, Ololade Aderayo Ebong. With Yewande Adekoya, Jumoke George, Lanre Hassan, Peters Ijagbemi. An Indigenous Yoruba Film From Nigeria. It tells the story of God's Love for Man even when human being thinks HE does bad things.

title: Rumah Merah Putih
synopsis: Directed by Ari Sihasale. With Petrick Rumlaklak, Amori de Purivicacao, Pevita Pearce, Yama Carlos. Farel, Oscar et al, who live on the NTT-Timor Leste border, join the areca climbing competition. But instead of being united, they argue which prizes should be taken first. They fail and then blame each other. The problem becomes more complicated when two cans of Farel's red and white paint disappear. Afraid of being scolded by his father, Farel, Oscar and his colleagues try to raise money to buy paint. They learn that there would be another areca climbing competition with a red and white paint prize. In the race Oscar falls and hurts. This is the story of Farel, Oscar et al to celebrate August 17, the independence day.

title: Koki-Koki Cilik 2
synopsis: Directed by Viva Westi. With Ringgo Agus Rahman, M. Adhiyat, Faras Fatik, Alifa Lubis. Cooking Camp is opened again. The little chefs who come to the camp are surprised that the camp was closed. The problems are Chef Grant's credibility is doubted as a teacher at the camp, and the landowner wants to sell the camp's land.

title: Find My Way Home
synopsis: Directed by Li Peng. With Xiaonuo Kang, Tingting Gao, Yirong Chen, Zihan Wei. A girl raised a dog. When her dad decided to bring her and mom to live in a foreign country, they had to foster the dog to a relative family. The dog misses the girl, leaves the foster family and goes on the way home.

title: Parental Guidance
synopsis: Directed by Andy Fickman. With Billy Crystal, Bette Midler, Marisa Tomei, Tom Everett Scott. Artie and Diane agree to look after their three grandkids when their type-A helicopter parents need to leave town for work. Problems arise when the kids' 21st-century behavior collides with Artie and Diane's old-school methods.

title: Sabyan Menjemput Mimpi
synopsis: Directed by Alim Ishaq. With Nissa Sabyan, Anis Sabyan, Ayus Sabyan, Kamal Sabyan. The story of youngsers led by Ayus to build and develop a gambus musical group called Sabyan. Many interesting stories behind their struggle to reach a dream. They start to get famous thanks to simple video uploads on Youtube. Sabyan starts to have fans. There are even fanatical fans like Ndut Kece who are always present wherever Sabyan is. Also Bilal who has physical disability and is only able to see Sabyan in cyberspace.

title: The Love River/Xiang he
synopsis: Directed by Wanfeng Han. Narrator of the story

title: Iqro: My Universe
synopsis: My Universe

title: Two Blue Stripes
synopsis: Directed by Gina S. Noer. With Adhisty Zara, Angga Yunanda, Cut Mini Theo, Arswendy Bening Swara. A young couple violated the boundary without knowing the consequences. They try to take responsibility for their choices and their innocence is tested when the families who really loved them knew, then forced into their chosen journey.

title: Where We Belong
synopsis: Directed by Kongdej Jaturanrasamee. With Jennis Oprasert, Praewa Suthamphong, Saheoiyn Aophachat, Prawit Boonprakong. Sue, the crazy girl that feels as if she was born in the wrong place. But the craziest thing she's ever done is that she is about to leave everything behind, including Belle.

synopsis: tu primera película

synopsis: Tears of stone

title: Thodi Khatti Thodi Hatti
synopsis: Directed by Sachin Wagh. With Umesh Kamat, Urmilla Kanetkar Kothare.

title: My Wife & I
synopsis: Directed by Bunmi Ajakaiye. With Adeolu Adefarasin, Rotimi Adelegan, Bimbo Ademoye, Lilian Afegbai. Facing divorce, a married couple tries to give it one last shot - and find their bodies swapped. Will the magical (or cursed) switch bring them out of their slump?

title: A Thing Of Magic
synopsis: Directed by Nithin Anil. With Vaibhavi Pramod Kadam, Pradnya Parshuram Kadam. Gundu Kakka is a struggling harmonium player, who aspires to join a local drama troupe. One day, after watching a 3D movie, he presents a pair of 3D glasses to two sisters - Pradnya and Pratheeksha. He tells them that the glasses have magical powers, visible only to him. Though they initially refuse to believe him, an event soon occurs which raises the sisters' curiosity. And as the determined sisters try to find out the truth about the glasses, other tiny stories of the little village slowly unfold.

title: Begstvo rogatykh vikingov
synopsis: Directed by Ilya Belostotski. With Yevgeniy Oleshchuk, Dasha Chistyakova, Artyom Kozhevnikov, Andrey Laufer.

title: Destiny of a Child
synopsis: Directed by Frantz Jean Baptiste. With Fabien Gravillon.

title: Mulga (Marathi Movie)2010
synopsis: Directed by Devendra Supekar. With Amol Kolhe, Deepa Parab, Fayaz Shaikh, Kirti Sheriger. The Storyline revolves around an orthodox family based in an urban environment that believes in the male child as the real flag bearer of the family, Mulga has tried to bring out the real situation of girl child and her struggle to survive in the male dominated society.

title: Praseto
synopsis: Directed by Dragomir Sholev. With Rumen Georgiev, Hristofor Nedkov, Dimitar Nikolov, Yosif Shamli. The story of a 13-year-old Rumen, nicknamed

title: The Main Event
synopsis: Directed by Jay Karas. With Seth Carr, Tichina Arnold, Adam Pally, Ken Marino. After discovering a magical mask, an 11-year-old aspiring wrestler enters a competition to become the next WWE superstar.

title: The Rest Is Just Noise
synopsis: Directed by Christopher Hall. With Chris D'Ascoli, Jill Russell, Ryan Russell, Sarah Wayman. The Rest Is Just Noise follows the Trenton siblings as time rewinds and fast forwards over the course of 18 months.

title: Vriksham (The Tree)
synopsis: Directed by Aditya Kunigal, Surya Siddhartha. Sampekatte is a village where Raksha and her granny live. On a certian day Raksha learns in school that even plants have life. She develops an inquisitiveness about plants and starts to preach awareness about nature to her friends and eventually they start to believe that anybody who cuts trees is a murderer and one such person is Surappa. Learning Surappa's intentions of cutting down trees all the kids gather to stop him. To everybody's dismay Surappa's daughter is bitten by a snake who is part of the kid's team. Raksha's granny saves the child with her native medicines and finally Surappa realizes his mistakes .

title: Douch
synopsis: Directed by Amir Mashhadi Abbas. With Hossain Abbasi, Mohammad Amin Ahmadi, Soraya Ghasemi, Sorush Jamshidi. Ten-year-old Gholamreza, who lives in a village in northern Iran, needs a bicycle to win a bicycle race and pay off his father's debt. To get money for the new bicycle, he notices a prize for teaching an illiterate person how to read and write, but there aren't any illiterate people in the village except a 90-year-old bad tempered woman who does not want to learn anything.

title: The Truth About Santa Claus
synopsis: Directed by Chris Bayon. With John Amos, Chris Bayon, Kevin Dotcom Brown, Kevin P. Farley. After a "run-in" with Santa Claus, a man who does not want children finds the true gift of Christmas.

title: Whitestar
synopsis: Directed by Jamel Aattache. With Tina de Bruin, Victoria Koblenko, Daniël Boissevain, Valentijn Avé. Megan has a special relationship with discarded jumping horse Whitestar. When it turns out that Whitestar still has special talents, the owner takes him away from Megan for competitions, but has no success. Only when Megan and Whitestar are together again does Whitestar turn out to be a real winner because they bring out the best in each other.

title: A Little Bird Reminds Me
synopsis: Directed by Xin Shi. With Hai Huang, Chenhan Lin, Qiyue Ma, Ben Niu. A coming-of-age story follows the joy, sorrow and struggle of a Chinese boy and his family during the last decade of the 20th century.

title: Christmas on the Square
synopsis: Рождество на площади

title: The First Supper
synopsis: Directed by Shiro Tokiwa. With Shôta Sometani, Erika Toda, Yôsuke Kubozuka, Yuki Saitô. Under the helm of rookie director Tokiwa Shiro,a family reunites following the funeral, last rites and cremation for a meal. The widow has determined that she will cook the food for the funeral, but there is barely anything to eat. They realize that it was the dead man's will for it to be so. They eat eggs, reminisce, bond and talk some more. They remember the dead man and his ways and even laugh as they recall their better days.

title: 99 Names of Love
synopsis: Directed by Danial Rifki. With Acha Septriasa, Deva Mahenra, Ira Wibowo, Donny Damara. The life of a producer of popular gossip shows, suddenly changed drastically when she met a young cleric who appeared in his office to teach her religious lessons as the wish of her father as a debt favor to him.

title: Wife
synopsis: Directed by Kirsten Gaynet. A young woman named Alfinaz, the mother of two children is going to leaving for a long journey. Husband is a life prisoner and the wife is an exemplary woman and submissive to her husband. She is waiting for him and not losing hope for his release. The film tells us about a female power and submissiveness of a wife to her husband and to God. The message of the film also concerns hardships and praise to God, resignation of a woman who is destined to be a Wife.

title: Montmartre de Papa
synopsis: Directed by Byungwoo Min. The son can't stop wondering. What is dad going to do after retirement? So he starts filming him. Dad wants to have a shot at becoming a street artist in Montmartre, Paris, a longtime dream of his. To the mother, it sounds like just another absurd dream. Anyhow, 2 years later, the father puts his plan into action and sets off for France. Right until his departure, the mother doesn't know what to make of it. While dad spends one month as a street artist, the son and mother follow him to Paris...

title: The Zombie Club
synopsis: Directed by Aeyron Moore. With Timothy E. Goodwin, Dean Cain, Michael Sigler, Franco Maicas. After a mix-up in a shipment of lab frogs goes terribly wrong, 6 teens find themselves in a race against the clock to find a cure. A race that will alter their lives forever... and the lives of thousands.

title: Miracle on Highway 34
synopsis: Directed by Nathan Clarkson. With Josh Murray, Dan Davidson, Nathan Clarkson, Sharonne Lanier. A set of diverse characters wind up together in an old diner in a small town on Christmas Eve during a snowstorm while a young expectant couple tries to make it home on a night that's anything but silent.

title: It Takes Three
synopsis: Directed by Evan Tramel. With Thomas Carr, Simon Hill, Tina Shuster, Jacob Tyler. Sassy and Bella, along with their new friend Buddy, hit the road in an RV to reunite their family and save the day! There's plenty of adventure along the way, especially when they meet troublemaker kitty Jean-Clawed. Tune in and enjoy the ride!

title: The House of Us
synopsis: Directed by Ga-eun Yoon. With Na-Yeon Kim, Si-ah Kim, Ye-rim Joo, Ji-ho Ahn. A girl from a troubled family befriends two younger girls and begins to feel a sense of normalcy as they go adventuring at the seaside.

title: Feel the Beat
synopsis: Directed by Elissa Down. With Sofia Carson, Pamela MacDonald, Sonia Laplante, Nayo. After failing to find success on Broadway, April returns to her hometown and reluctantly is recruited to train a misfit group of young dancers for a big competition.

title: Intern-in-Chief
synopsis: Directed by Jd Dominguez. With Jules LeBlanc, Kianna Naomi, Kennedy Walsh, Giorgio Antoniazzi. Faced with another long summer of hard and strenuous work at the Crown Lake country club, Rhyme and Effie jump at the opportunity to work as fashion interns at the high-end magazine "Très Chic." This summer will be one for the books.

title: Mokala Shwas
synopsis: Directed by Kaanchan Adhikkari. With Sharad Ponkshe, Prateeksha Lonkar, Mohan Joshi, Mrunmayee Deshpande. Eknath is a skilled salesman who is unhappy about having three daughters. His extreme negligence towards them invokes the anger of one of his daughters.

title: His
synopsis: Directed by Rikiya Imaizumi. With Hio Miyazawa, Kisetsu Fujiwara, Wakana Matsumoto, Honoka Matsumoto. Shun and Nagisa first meet and fall in love during high school. However, despite strong feelings, they go their separate ways. Years later, Shun is now living alone in a rural area when Nagisa arrives with his six-year-old daughter, Sora.

title: Bitter Tree
synopsis: Directed by Nitin Bhaskar. With Vitthal Kale, Pandurang Pangam, Vishnu Joshi, Narendra Kadkade. KAAJRO is story of Tilgya, belonging to an untouchable caste. His village is celebrating the annual festival of Dasshera, marking triumph of Lord Rama over Ravana i.e. good over bad. Tilgya's ailing wife dies while the celebration is on. He is debarred from participating in festival procession and is forced to leave the village with his wife's dead body.

title: Tim Chong Cho Me
synopsis: Directed by Thuy Tran. With Chu Diep Anh, Hong Dao, Ha Viet Dung, Quang Minh.

title: Eurbane's Big Show!
synopsis: Directed by John Wilson. With Jessica Belz, Jeffrey Blasquez, Jay Corbett, Dash. When disaster strikes in the dressing room, it's up to Eurbane and friends to work together, and save the show.

title: Hayflower, Quiltshoe and the Feisty First-grader
synopsis: Directed by Lenka Hellstedt. With Lari Halme, Pirjo Heikkilä, Janne Kataja, Hugo Komaro. Big sister Heinähattu starts school and little sister Vilttitossu is jealous of that. Vilttitossu plots to take her sister's place in the class trip. Unaccustomed to the rules of school Vilttitossu ends up astonishing the classmates.

title: One Day We'll Talk About Today
synopsis: Directed by Angga Dwimas Sasongko. With Rio Dewanto, Sheila Dara Aisha, Rachel Amanda, Sinyo Riza. Three siblings live in happy-looking families, but one of them changes and gets warned by his parents, prompting the rebellion of the three siblings which led to the discovery of the secrets and great trauma in their families.

title: Dhehi- Her soul never surrendered
synopsis: Directed by Dhana Shekhar. With Kishore Kumar G., Upasana Gurjar.

title: Milo's Monster School Vlog 1 - Super Simple
synopsis: Directed by Brett Jubinville. With Andy Hayward. Welcome to Milo's Monster School Vlog, where six-year-old Milo Eugene Montague Monster tells you all the neat stuff he learned in monster school. Join Milo as he learns about dinosaurs, eating the rainbow, colors and more.

title: Milo's Monster School Vlog 2 - Super Simple
synopsis: Directed by Brett Jubinville. With Andy Hayward. Milo's Monster School Vlog is back! Join six-year-old Milo Eugene Montague Monster as he tells you all the neat things he's learned in monster school! Featuring all new episodes including musical instruments, the seasons and Milo's first 100 days at school!

title: Swimming for Gold
synopsis: Directed by Hayley MacFarlane. With Peyton List, Lauren Esposito, Daniel Needs, Candice Hill. A US women’s swim team Olympic hopeful suffers an injury that forces her to put aside her dreams and help the Australian men’s swim team get competition ready.

title: Carl's Car Wash: The Movie - Super Simple
synopsis: The Movie - Super Simple

title: Sing Along With Tobee 1 - Super Simple
synopsis: Directed by Troy McDonald, Matt Servo. With Caitlin Claessens. Tobee is an adorable little puppet with a curious mind and an infectious laugh. He loves to learn new songs from his friend Caitie. They dance a lot. They laugh a lot. And they learn a lot. Follow along as Catie teaches Tobee and the audience at home the words and gestures to classic nursery rhymes and original kids' songs from Super Simple Songs.

title: Kutumb
synopsis: Directed by Bapodra. With Shreyanshi Barot, Prinal Oberoi, Akash Shah, Vikram Thakor.

title: Sing Along With Tobee 3 - Super Simple
synopsis: Directed by Troy McDonald. With Caitlin Claessens, Andy Hayward. Tobee and Caitie are back. Follow along as Caitie and Tobee dance, laugh, and perform even more classic nursery rhymes and original kids' songs from Super Simple Songs.

title: Pressure Cooker
synopsis: Directed by Sujoi, Sushil. With Sai Ronak, Preethi Asrani, Rahul Ramakrishna, Abhinaya. A young man faces immense pressure from his family to move to America, get a job and have his life settled abroad.

title: When Mom Is Away... With the Family
synopsis: Directed by Alessandro Genovesi. With Fabio De Luigi, Valentina Lodovini, Diego Abatantuono, Angelica Elli. In this sequel to Папа за маму (2019), Carlo, Giulia and their three children go to Lapland to meet Santa Claus. Things will not go as planned.

title: 10 Horas para o Natal
synopsis: Directed by Cris D'Amato. With Giulia Benite, Juliet Donenfeld, Terrence Little Gardenhigh, Arthur Kohl.

title: The Persuit of Love
synopsis: Directed by GuangBin Jiang. With FengJun Hao, XiaoLiang Hao, EnFeng Hu, HuanNa Li.

title: Chhoo Le Aasman
synopsis: Directed by P. Chandrakanth, Niranjan Singh. With Babita Anant, Raj Pratika Bhosale, Anushka Kashid, Payal Kotangale.

title: Superstar Teacher
synopsis: Directed by Duc Thinh. With Thanh Pham, Duc Thinh, Miu Le, Mai Cát Vi. A dejected music teacher must stash his singing aspirations away when he is forced to transfer to an isolated island to teach five troublesome kids.

title: Teacher of the Year
synopsis: Directed by Vikram Panchal, Shounak Vyas. With Shounak Vyas, Alisha Prajapati, Mehul Buch, Archan Trivedi. Teacher of the Year is A Tale told with utmost compassion and Passion trying to bring back the Ideal , Applied, Practical approach to Life which is instilled in ones' Formative School days, will be a Journey to the Glorious Chapters of one's Past , Connecting the dots to the Future. Teacher of the year is the story based on the current education system. The movie highlight the relationship between student and teach.

title: Socorro, Virei uma Garota!
synopsis: Directed by Leandro Neri. With Thati Lopes, Lipy Adler, Bruna Altieri, Leo Bahia. Júlio wanted to be the most popular person in school but ends up getting more than what he wished for.

title: Nachtwacht: Het duistere hart
synopsis: Het duistere hart

title: The Cooler Friends
synopsis: Directed by George Stephenson. With Martin Locks, Lily Megan Wilson, Lee Joe Smith, Maddie Stephenson.

title: Sade Takes Lagos
synopsis: Directed by Chibuike Ibe. With Foluke Daramola, Cynthia Ebijie, Nkechi Emmanuel, Lilian Esoro.

title: Dads
synopsis: Directed by Bryce Dallas Howard. With Bryce Dallas Howard, Ron Howard, Judd Apatow, Chace Elijah. Director Bryce Dallas Howard teams up with her father, Ron Howard, to explore contemporary fatherhood through anecdotes and wisdom from famous funnymen such as Will Smith, Jimmy Fallon, Neil Patrick Harris, and more.

title: The Star Connection
synopsis: Directed by Gina Carey. With Marcus Lantero, Diana Hintergardt, Renee Poinard, Michele Davis.

title: Triple Seat
synopsis: Directed by Sanket Prakash Pavse. With Ankush Chaudhari, Shivani Surve, Pallavi Patil, Pravin Tarde. A young, happy guy receives a call from an unknown woman who claims to be in danger. A new take on the classic love triangle, Triple Seat brings to you a light-hearted story about wireless love.

title: Tholubommalata
synopsis: Directed by Vishwanath Maganti. With Vennela Kishore, Rajendra Prasad, Sampath Raj, Devi Prasad. Sodala Raju wanted to get his grand-nephew and grand-niece married, but when Raju dies, how the marriage will work forms the crux of the story.

title: Staged Fighter
synopsis: Directed by Chester Indiviglio Indiviglio. With Jovan Brown, David Dotterer, Evans Formica, Andrew Hess. Jack an out of work actor stunt fighter reconnects with his estranged daughter Helen. Meeting his grandson Harry for the first time, Jack learns Harry is being bullied by a group of neighborhood thugs. Jack teaches his grandson how to protect himself through pretend comical staged fighting in this family comedy-drama.

title: Googly
synopsis: Directed by Abhimanyu Mukherjee. With Soham Chakraborty, Srabanti Chatterjee, Aritra Dutta Banik, Kanchan Mullick. Arjun and Dali are a couple who suffer from a stammering problem but soon their lives change after the birth of their son, Googly.

title: Two Worlds
synopsis: Directed by Arkar. With May Kabyar, May Myint Mo, Nine Nine, Pyae Pyae. In the broken family, father Kyaw Htet, mother Eaindray and their daughter Thu Thu who hates her father, living separately. When they happened to go grandma birthday which holds every year, Eaindray is busy with her works so that she asks help to his husband to send their daughter Thu Thu. What will happen between clumsy dad and his daughter on their way to the birthday party?

title: Grihalakshmi - The Awakening
synopsis: Directed by Arvind Pandey. It's a story told between two sisters, where one who is introduced to this meditation, shows inner strength and conviction to win over the heart of her future ultra-rich Fiancée's mother, who sees the futility of a wasted life of glamour and indulgence after losing her husband early to disease hones the guilt of never having giving enough time and warmth to him. She sets out seeking a perfect Grihalakshmi (homemaker/ wife) for her one and only son, whom she wants to ensure, that he never faces the same fate as his father. In her intense desire to find that perfect Bride for her son, she chooses the younger simple-minded sister who does meditation, instead of the elder beautiful and glamorous one, whom she imagined was exactly her own mirror image.

title: Villmarksbarna - En eventyrlig reise
synopsis: Directed by Dag Rune Johansen. With Guro Krempig, Ida Krempig, Lars H. Krempig, Narve Krempig. The Krempig family journeys into the wilderness of northwestern Greenland. There, the landscape and Inuit culture offer them new challenges, excitement and many new experiences.

title: Pinocchio, Story of a Puppet
synopsis: Directed by Teagan Craft. With Kerry Craft, T. Craft, Teagan Craft, Tom Craft.

title: Cheer Up, Mr. Lee
synopsis: Directed by Kae-Byeok Lee. With Seung-Won Cha, Chae-Young Um, Park Hae-joon, Kim Hye-Ok. Cheol Soo has a perfect appearance, but he is a bit slow. One day, his daughter Saet Byeol appears in front of him. Saet Byeol has been sick and she has been in the hospital. They start on a trip.

title: Dorogoy papa
synopsis: Directed by Mikhail Raskhodnikov. With Ieva Andrejevaite, Ruslan Bankovskiy, Valentina Lyapina, Varvara Malkova. Wealthy manipulator Vadim falls victim to his own scheme when he writes down his corporation to his old mother. He has to meet his once forgotten daughter to fix this.

title: Yuuhi no ato
synopsis: Directed by Michio Koshikawa. With Shihori Kanjiya, Maho Yamada, Masaru Nagai, Satoru Kawaguchi. Akane moves from Tokyo to a small island where she works as a waitress serving the fishermen. People like her and glad she has made the move. Satsuki, however, is a local having grown up, married and given birth in the area. She has a foster son and after obtaining her man's permission decides to adopt him legally. Unfortunately it is the son's biological mother who has arrived on the island and is living nearby now.

title: Imperfect
synopsis: Karir, Cinta, & Timbangan

title: Kozhipporu
synopsis: Directed by Jibit George, Jinoy Janardhanan. With Indrans, Pauly Valsan, Jinoy Janardhanan, Navajith Narayanan. The story revolves around two families, portraying their relationship, and how a hen and its eggs changes it over time.

title: You Are Not Alone
synopsis: Directed by Leslye Abbey. Six children embark on a journey through healing when they become a part of the "You Are Not Alone" mural project; a 6x6 foot turtle-shaped sculpture developed by renowned artist Professor Marietta D'Antonio Fryer of Cheyney University.

title: Savarna deergha sandhi
synopsis: Directed by Veerendra Shetty. With Surendra Bantwa, Aprameya Bharadwaj, Krishnaa Bhat, Ravi Bhat. Muddanna is the leader of a gang that indulges in 'positive rowdyism'. He is in love with Amruthavarshini, an aspiring singer. The film revolves around the gags and misadventures of Muddanna and his gang.

title: Why Me
synopsis: Directed by Robert D. Parham. With Cynda Williams, Hawthorne James, Kendal Moseley, Daryl Green. Crystal is a very outgoing preteen who loves people, loves her life and loves just living. One day she started to change but everyone just assumed she was going through puberty. No one noticed until they had no other choice.

title: The Perfect Mate
synopsis: Directed by Aaron L. Williams. With Chico Benymon, Brittany Lucio, Lawrence Hilton-Jacobs, Jackée Harry. Hope (Brittany Lucio) is a control freak and a perfectionist and nothing would please her more than bringing the perfect Christian future husband home for the weekend to meet her father Reverend Adams (Lawrence Hilton-Jacobs), her mother Mrs. Adams (Jackee Harry), and sister Cherish (KD Aubert). On the day they're scheduled to leave she's dumped by her fiancé. That's when she enlists the help of her platonic male friend, Jesse (Chico Benymon), who is the epitome of everything ungodly, to impersonate her ex, the upcoming pastor. While there, he learns to appreciate family and faith in this hilarious Christian Romance Comedy.

title: Prati Roju Pandaage
synopsis: Directed by Maruthi Dasari. With Sai Dharam Tej, Raashi Khanna, Sathyaraj, Rao Ramesh. With only a few weeks left to live, an aging grandfather is visited by his grandson who wishes to fulfill his desires.

title: Horse Camp: A Love Tail
synopsis: Directed by Joel Paul Reisig. With Richard Karn, Jason London, Kristin Mellian, Teri Lee. It's a new year at summer horse-riding camp but everything is different this time-a new head counselor, new friends to make, and to spice things up, the ranch hand has a crush on the head riding instructor. When he is too nervous to reveal his feelings, the campers put competition aside and rally together to help him win over her heart while building friendships that will last a lifetime.

title: Opasnye kanikuly
synopsis: Directed by Olga Belyaeva. With Aleksandr Bobkov, Erikh Chupin, Ivan Kolesnikov, Evdokiya Kolesnikova.

title: I, the Sunshine
synopsis: Directed by Janchivdorj Sengedorj. With E. Amarbayasgalan, D. Asardari, B. Bayanmunkh, Bayra Bela. Told in three parts by a boy narrating the stories of his father, his mother, and his own, I, THE SUNSHINE features stunning cinematography by Nergui Erdenekhuyag throughout. The first story is a look back at steppe life when school's out for the summer. Commune members must travel to find a television so they can keep up with their favorite soap opera until Bodi's father brings home a television set to have at home. To their dismay, they discover their home lies too low to catch a signal, motivating Bodi and friends to find a way to remedy the situation. The second story is about mother Nandine living life in the city and working as a contortionist. Her career is cut short as her mother, who was in the same profession herself, is confined to a wheelchair due to an injury, while Nandine's father is working in the United States to support the family. Viewers will take delight in watching the beautifully shot contortionist performances. The son's story finds him living a far more privileged existence thanks to the wealth his parents Bodi and Nandine have accumulated. He is on his phone constantly and oblivious to those around him. As he is also shy, he encounters bullies daily but that changes when his computer mouse transforms into a girl that fends them off, granting any wish he desires which eventually makes for a rude awakening.

title: Mayaboti

title: Middleton Christmas
synopsis: Directed by Dale Fabrigar. With Michael Paré, Nancy Valen, Eileen Davidson, Anzu Lawson. In a small town, high-school dean Alana and her vivacious teenage daughter Samantha plan a holiday concert to save the school with the help of the new maintenance man, Army veteran Johnny, and his quiet son Max. But when a car accident lands Sam in a life-threatening condition, Alana turns to Johnny for support, and Max makes a desperate decision that will forever bond their families together. All four must question their values about sacrifice, family, and love - and what it means to be thankful for another Christmas.

Her boss tells her to go underground so she travels to a far off land and starts living with a family with a fake identity as chef. With no experience of household or emotions Zara finds it more fun and joyous to have a family. Adnan who eventually knows Lalain (Zara) is lying, decides to help her learn cooking. During this spicy and romantic ride Zara falls in love and explores the beauty of life. Now the issue is her original life and that fraud which starts haunting her. She has to go back and take whatever belonged to her. Whether it will be money or honey, this journey is all about that choice.

Class trip with Sophie, or his best friend Grandpa? Sune can't make his mind up so decides to do both. Or something in-between. At the same time, Rudolf is suspicious about the bride.
