title: Wild Bunch on Ice
synopsis: Directed by Tim McKort. With Bryden Belmore, Kyle Hazlehurst, Nick Armstrong, Kevin P. Farley. Billy Dombrowski and a rag-tag group kids set out on a journey to form a hockey team. To become a team, they must first learn to work together, trust in each other's abilities to win -- together they are persevering on thin ice.

title: Jelger de Goochelaar en de Schat van Nicolaas
synopsis: Directed by Jelger Dees. With Jelger Dees, Walter Vermeer, Joost Prinsen, Sebastiaan van Baar. Saint Nicholas can no longer buy presents and asks help. Jelger goes on a quest for a hidden treasure with 3 young fearless girls. But they are not the only ones when an escaped crook arrives in Belderplons.

title: Godmothered
synopsis: Directed by Sharon Maguire. With June Squibb, Jillian Bell, Sonia Manzano, Carlease Burke. An unskilled young fairy godmother ventures out on her own to prove her worth by tracking down a young girl whose request for help was ignored.

title: A Wrestling Christmas Miracle
synopsis: Directed by Chris T. Anthony. With Mario Del Vecchio, Buddy Fitzpatrick, Julie McCullough, Candy Fox. Stupid crooks hold the only copy of a youth's movie for ransom while his father's away in Africa staging a wrestling-based coup.

title: Skydog
synopsis: Directed by Tim Kaiser, Daniel Knudsen. With Daniel Knudsen, Vickie Lynn Smith, Dean Cain, Rosie Berryer. Colt Lifestone, a high school senior working on his pilot's license, must rescue his mother with the help of stray dog called Oreo and his new friend Alice

title: Chronicle of Space
synopsis: Directed by Akshay Indikar. With Neel Deshmukh, Anushree Wani. After his father's disappearance, eight-year-old Dighu seeks refuge from loneliness in his imagination and diary entries.

title: In My Dream
synopsis: Directed by Murat Çeri. With Nevzat Yilmaz, Harun Reha Pakoglu, Ferda Isil, Recep Çavdar. Tarik, 8 years old, lives in the city. He suffers a car accident with his father, who dies, and with his mother, who is in a coma in the hospital. Tarik suffers from memory loss. With no other relatives in the city, he is sent to a village to live with his grandparents.

title: A Cat and Mouse Game
synopsis: Directed by Christophe Duchiron. With Cheeky, Marcel. In the countryside, a family home is the theatre of a veritable hunting scene between the residents' cat and the previous occupants' mouse. But the game is far from over, and where the predator uses a wide variety of schemes to reach his target, his prey becomes even more resourceful in his bid to escape being caught.

title: Atabai
synopsis: Directed by Niki Karimi. With Hadi Hejazifar, Sahar Dolatshahi, Javad Ezati, Danial Noroush. The story is about Kazem, a middle-aged man who lives in a village. He has left the university because of a former love but when two sisters enter his life he falls in love once again.

title: Omok Girl
synopsis: Directed by Seung-hwa Baek. With Se-wan Park, Ahn Woo-yeon, Haet-Sal Jang, Yoon Jeong-ro. offbeat Korean comedy an ex board game champion turned aimless twenty something decides to return to her roots and win 2nd place in a national tournament and beat out a nerdy rival.

title: Sweety Satarkar
synopsis: Directed by Shabbir Naik. With Sangram Samel, Vinamra Babhal, Amruta Deshmukh, Gauri Jadhav. A loud and daring woman falls in love with a bold man and attempts to win his heart by trying everything in the book to attract him.

title: Jackie & Oopjen
synopsis: Directed by Annemarie van de Mond. With Frouke Verheijde, Sarah Bannier, Karina Smulders, Saar van Aken. 12-year-old Jackie has made Amsterdam's Rijksmuseum, where her mom works, her second home. While wandering around after hours, Oopjen from Rembrandt's famous painting suddenly comes to life. It seems she is looking for her long lost sister. Jackie is used to solving other people's problems and decides to take Oopjen home, so they can go look for her sister. For the woman from the Golden Age, this modern world, its customs and appliances are a great adventure. And Jackie, who doesn't really have any friends at school, finally gains a true BFF.

title: Dhauli
synopsis: Directed by Santosh Kumar Atreya, Ghanshyam Lamichhane, Santosh Kumar Atray. With Geeta Adhikari, Gajit Bista, Prakash Ghimire. Dhauli is a social drama that revolves around the story of a lover, where one is a low cast and the other is from a high cast.

title: The Final Base
synopsis: With Adesoji Adedoja, Modupe Adedoja, Emmanuel Okoro, Nike Oladeru.

title: The Great Ghost Rescue
synopsis: Directed by Yann Samuell. With Jason Isaacs, Emma Fielding, Georgia Groome, Toby Hall. Young Humphrey is a ghost with a big problem. He and his family, the Craggyfords, have been ousted from their home and left without a place to haunt. As they search for new haunting grounds they soon discover that they are not alone. Ghosts from all over the world have been exorcised from their dwellings, with dark castles and ancient buildings being destroyed by the living, and turned into shopping centers. With time running out, Humphrey digs deep inside, and decides to help save his family and the rest of the haunting community by scaring his way to victory.

title: Beauty and the Beast
synopsis: With Dan Osborne, Ian Summers, Holly Vernon-Harcourt.

title: Prinsessia: Het Prinselijke Bal
synopsis: Het Prinselijke Bal

title: Fathers
synopsis: Directed by Huy Yaleng. With Huy Yaleng, Sonyta Mean, Kong Sophy, Tep Sreypov. Based on a true story, Losing one leg, a man lives on his cyclo-trisaw drives to provide for two children his wife abandons at a pagoda's corner.

title: Le Fantastique Voyage de Zebrinou
synopsis: Directed by Caroline Drot. With Caroline Drot, Marilyn Lattard. Zébrinou is a small zebra that lives in the savannah. He was taken in by a family of Lions.

title: Miracle on Christmas
synopsis: Directed by Thomas Bonifield. With Erin Bethea, Jason Burkey, Brett Varvel, Micah Lynn Hanson. The holiday spirit seems distant for the Boyce family until an unexpected visitor and miracle change everything on Christmas Day.

title: Trees for Christmas
synopsis: Directed by Sterling Johnston. With Jacob Beardmore, Sydney Beardmore, Bailey Blanchard, Harley Davis.

title: Planning
synopsis: Directed by Bl Prasad. With Bashir Mahindra, Mamatha Kulkarni, Andrade Alisha, Chaitanya Reddy Adith.

title: Curtain Up!
synopsis: Directed by Kelly Ng, Hui Tong. With Hannah Balagot, William Cui, Kyle Garvin, Alice Hom. A group of kids in New York's Chinatown prepare for the musical production of "Frozen Kids" and begin to discover their identities. Behind the scenes, they face Asian stereotypes, families' expectations and uncertainties post-graduation.

title: A Music Story
synopsis: Directed by Anna Maria Jóakimsdóttir Hutri, Roger Westberg, Anders Widmark. With Claes Malmberg, Jan Malmsjö, Vikoria Ronnefall, Helen Sjöholm. Eleven-year-old Moa wants to become a musician like her father. When he loses his job as an on-air performer, Moa tries to keep her family and their dreams together. A musical story about sticking to your own path, regardless of what other people would like you to do.

title: Lucy Shimmers and the Prince of Peace
synopsis: Directed by Rob Diamond. With Scarlett Diamond, Vincent Vargas, Adam Hightower, Florencia Contreras Stevens. Second chances start when a hardened criminal crosses paths with a precocious little girl who is helped by an angel to change hearts during the holiday season.

title: Selfie Mummy Googl Daddy
synopsis: Directed by Madhu Chandra. With Srujan Lokesh, Meghana Raj, Achyuth Kumar, H.G. Dattatreya. Selfie Mummy Googl Daddy is a Kannada movie starring Srujan Lokesh, Meghana Raj and Achyuth Kumar in prominent roles. It is a drama directed by Madhu Chandra with Shamanth as musician, forming part of the crew.

title: Nang 3: Loi Hua Cua Cha
synopsis: Loi Hua Cua Cha

title: Paathshaala
synopsis: Directed by Milind Ukey. With Adil Feroz Khan, Nana Patekar, Shahid Kapoor, Ayesha Takia. A new English school-teacher also teaches music but ends up leading both teachers and students to revolt against the school management.

title: Ikko Mikke
synopsis: Directed by Pankaj Verma. With Satinder Sartaaj, Aditi Sharma, Shiwani Saini, Sardar Sohi. A young couple's souls get swapped accidentally, they lived each other's life and learn valuable lessons about love, respect and understanding.

title: Mnohaya lita. Stoyko
synopsis: Directed by Vyacheslav Bihun. With Stepan Stoyko, Rostyslav Stoyka, Natalija Bekhta, Ihor Yukhnovskyi. A 100-year-old Ukrainian scholar's inspirational story about longevity, mentality and nature.

title: Diary of a Wimpy Kid
synopsis: Directed by Thor Freudenthal. With Zachary Gordon, Robert Capron, Rachael Harris, Steve Zahn. Greg Heffley is a 12 year old who is fresh out of elementary and transitions to middle school, where he has to learn the consequences and responsibility to survive the year.

title: The Architect
synopsis: Directed by Jonathan Starrett. With Tyler Brooks, Maddie Call, Delaney Cleary, Trevor Easterling.

title: Joda Thath Ka
synopsis: Directed by Uttar Kumar. With Uttar Kumar, Kavita Joshi, Kanhaiya Baghel, Vikas Balian. The tip of the husband wife and the way of loving them is based on each other's quarrels and daily actions and the living conditions of the people of the village.

title: Flaming Ears
synopsis: Directed by Ursula Puerrer, A. Hans Scheirl, Dietmar Schipek. With Susana Helmayr, Ursula Puerrer, A. Hans Scheirl, Margarete Neumann. Flaming Ears is a pop sci-fi lesbian fantasy feature set in the year 2700 in the fictive burned-out city of Asche. It follows the tangled lives of three women - Volley, Nun and Spy.

title: Har Har Mahadev
synopsis: Directed by Chandrakant. With Dara Singh Randhawa, Jayshree Gadkar, Shahu Modak, Padma Khanna. The complete Shivpuran on celluloid.

title: 50 Feet of String
synopsis: Directed by Leighton Pierce. A 12 section film that invites viewers into a more visceral and less verbally analytical state of mind.

title: Asleep in the Sun
synopsis: Directed by Alejandro Chomski. With Luis Machín, Esther Goris, Carlos Belloso, Florencia Peña. Lucio Bordenave carries on the Grey lifestyle of an unemployed worker, dedicated to the trade of watchmaking, until in a somewhat mysterious way, his wife is admitted to a Frenopatic Institute. From this point on, the story enters a territory without parameters where reality is confused with the imaginary, sleep with wakefulness, and insanity with lucidity.

title: El horror de la dama del lago
synopsis: Directed by Diego Vázquez. With Sergi Soler, Sara Da Pin Up, Pilar Morales, Jean-Pierre Sèvegrand.

title: Gun of the Black Sun
synopsis: Directed by Jeff Burr. With Gary Douglas, Richard Lynch, Ian Wright, Mihaela Sinca. A Nazi Luger Pistol from W.W.2 with dark and mystical powers re-emerges in modern day Bucharest and is taken to London. En-route it falls into the hands of a Media Mogul intent on using its power to bring the return of the Forth Reich through Technology and Music .

title: Fantasy Island
synopsis: Directed by Jeff Wadlow. With Michael Peña, Maggie Q, Lucy Hale, Austin Stowell. When the owner and operator of a luxurious island invites a collection of guests to live out their most elaborate fantasies in relative seclusion, chaos quickly descends.

title: Bigfoot's Lament
synopsis: Directed by Edie Robinette-Petrachi. With Linda Lee, Robert Bruce Nelson, Luca Petrachi, Jack Robinette. Bigfoot has to the end of this Autumn to find a family to break the curse. He shape-shifts into animals and meets a group of campers. The campers half fear him and half understand him. Will he succeed or makes other plans?

title: Unmadiyude Maranam
synopsis: Directed by Sanal Kumar Sasidharan. With Shaji A.J., Rajshri Deshpande, Suni R S. A man named Unmadi's dreams causes disturbances in the society as his fellow citizens also start watching his dreams. Authorities insist him to censor his dreams before he start seeing them and when he denies the same they ban him from dreaming. But People of his country start watching his dreams illegally and start spreading it.

title: Paracelso
synopsis: Directed by Madness Bros. With Francesco Savarino, Stefano Accomo, Samuele Amato.

title: Bad Men from a Melting Moon
synopsis: Directed by Matt Orefice. With Louisa Beal, Meredith Binder, Henry S Brown Jr., Bethany Buer. A man believes he has been hit by a train.

title: Post
synopsis: Directed by Sergey A.. With Sergey A.. The suicide man after death finds himself in hell. Where all attempts to commit suicide lead to nothing, and only demonic essences slowly devour him from the inside.

title: Cirque du Soleil in Cinema: KURIOS - Cabinet of Curiosities
synopsis: KURIOS - Cabinet of Curiosities

title: Ishtar Speaks
synopsis: Directed by Dena Rayne. With Charles Biderman, Dena Rayne. When a woman meets the ancient Babylonian goddess, Ishtar, in her dream, she embarks upon a journey to complete a lethal mission.

title: Schwarzer Herbst
synopsis: Directed by Daria Orfa, Paul Miloslavsky. With Daria Orfa, Paul Miloslavsky, Valeria Alaska, Roman Antonov.

title: The Purser
synopsis: Directed by Jacques Aldridge. With Jacques Aldridge, Forest Baker, Amy Marie Bowersox, Dawne Ellison. An accountant takes LSD and disappears with incriminating evidence against his mysterious employers. The Purser is tasked with finding him and destroying the evidence.

title: Vodyanaya
synopsis: Directed by Aleksey Barykin. With Nikolay Nevzorov, Ekaterina Barykina, Nafisa Khayrillina, Ildus Gabdrakhmanov. Based on Tatar folklore, the story tells about kids, whose mother was taken away by a ominous lake spirit.

title: Sphere of Fear 2
synopsis: Directed by John Mitchell. With John Altman, Warren Baker, Chris Ball Hero, Gina Bee. It's back from Brazil and more "terriball" than before. Dylan Davis is a depressed mess, The Hunter has stolen Faye Le Mort from him, even his dead brother cannot help. Who can help Dylan? The Demon Football of course. Satan wants the Football's help, Dylan needs the Football's help, what can go wrong?

title: Big Feat
synopsis: Directed by Lindsay Gonzalez. With Amy Hamill, Polina Sokolskiy, Myriam Baillargeon, Ted Faye. On workplace orders to undergo psychiatric evaluation a demon clown revisits her past move to the big city. Painful memories of her pursuit to become a fairy reignite buried desires, sending her on paths that may result in the disappointment of her life coach.

title: Mysterious Raiders
synopsis: Directed by Yilin Dai. With Qiwei He, Yusi Peng, Yi Wen Wang. Poisoned corpses along the streets and rampant illness throughout the city -- the Qing Dynasty is fading fast, and along with it Shengjing City has become unrecognizable. Local resident Zhang Xiaozhi's great-grandfather was a tomb builder, and now Zhang is the last of his line to still know the way to the Water Palace Tomb hidden deep beneath the city's four pagodas. Within lies a hidden treasure, and He Miao wants Zhang to help her find it. But as the pair spend more time together they begin falling for each other, and dark secrets that have long lain beneath the earth begin creeping toward the surface.

title: In Bright Axiom
synopsis: Directed by Spencer McCall. With Geordie Aitken, Jeff Hull, Tracy Pfau, Anna Seregina. Under a code of ABSOLUTE DISCRETION, guests are invited into the House of the Latitude, a place where truth and fiction are indistinguishable.

title: Birdsong
synopsis: Directed by Hendrik Willemyns. With Kazuhiko Kanayama, Natsuko Kobayashi, Akaji Maro, Shinji Matsubayashi. Tokyo. Asuka, a young cleaning lady working the night shift, is ready to pay a high price to achieve her dream of becoming a music star. She manages to perform on a TV-talent show, but all her sacrifices backfire when she is accused of murder and is forced to reveal all the details of the dark path she has followed until then.

title: Suspiria
synopsis: Directed by Luca Guadagnino. With Chloë Grace Moretz, Tilda Swinton, Doris Hick, Malgorzata Bela. A darkness swirls at the center of a world-renowned dance company, one that will engulf the artistic director, an ambitious young dancer, and a grieving psychotherapist. Some will succumb to the nightmare. Others will finally wake up.

title: Rapunzel: A Princess Frozen in Time
synopsis: принцесса, застывшая во времени

title: Daisy
synopsis: Directed by Benjamin Wilkinson. With Sarah Chapleo, Bea Svistunenko. Two Sisters. Two Stories. One Truth.

title: The Curse and the Covenant
synopsis: Directed by Robert Towne. With Eric Michaels, Graci Clark, Danny Fogle, Josh Horton. In a dark time when the kingdoms of men have fallen and orcs dominate the earth, Akosh, the cowardly survivor of a dragon attack, seeks refuge in the mountains. There he must learn the ways of the sword from an exiled knight named Eli, and his daughter Zephra. But as Akosh gets groomed to take up the mantle of heroes who have passed in to legend, he begins to uncover dark secrets about Eli's family history. Set nine centuries before the events of "Song of the Starslayer," this new chapter delves deeper into the legends that form the history of Ashelon.

title: The Magic School
synopsis: Directed by Zicheng Tian. With Kathy Chow, Wantong Ci, Zezong Wang.

title: Saihate Restaurant
synopsis: Directed by Keita Matsuda. With Junq, Ryôta Murai. Inside a small restaurant there is a man named Ryota Misaki who greets the guests, and a Korean man named Han Ji Seok who prepares the meals. When a person dies they visit this small restaurant for one last meal before they cross the Sanzu River into the afterlife. Each person is allowed to invite one person who is already deceased to join them for a meal together.

title: Mandibles
synopsis: Directed by Quentin Dupieux. With Grégoire Ludig, David Marsais, Adèle Exarchopoulos, India Hair. When simple-minded friends Jean-Gab and Manu find a giant fly trapped in the boot of a car, they decide to train it in the hope of making a ton of cash.

title: Legion
synopsis: Directed by Scott Stewart. With Paul Bettany, Lucas Black, Tyrese Gibson, Adrianne Palicki. When a group of strangers at a dusty roadside diner come under attack by demonic forces, their only chance for survival lies with an archangel named Michael, who informs a pregnant waitress that her unborn child is humanity's last hope.

title: The rug
synopsis: Directed by Khaled Habib El Kebich, Khaled Habib El Kebich. With Tahar Amirouche, Amel Bensaad, Amina Hochine, Mohamed Nadjemi. When symbols, signs and rituals rules our lives.

title: Dosukoi! Sukehira
synopsis: Directed by Ryô Miyawaki. With Reina Ikehata, Ji-young Kang, Airi Matsui, Marina Mizushima. A fat girl finds that she has transformed into a stunning beauty.

title: Baked Alaska
synopsis: Directed by Kimmo Moyyky, Kathleen Bryson, Kimmo Moykky. With Kathleen Bryson, Jamie Alderson, Tony Bamforth, Emma Byrne. Baby, it's cold outside. So come inside where it's full of hallucinatory time-travelling Gold Rush cannibals instead.

title: Plus Minus
synopsis: Directed by Kundan Sad. With Ganesh Deshmukh. Man wakes up alone in a room with no doors or windows. His only tool is a machine. His only friend is a rat. What will he make of it?

title: Finding Tom Bombadil
synopsis: Directed by Joost van de Loo. With Joost van de Loo, Bernward Koch, Auke Hulst, David Hand. After years of investigating across five different continents, a holistic detective on a quest to find his favorite fiction character in the real world realizes that the search is only just beginning.

title: Shen hai ju yao
synopsis: Directed by Dawei Miao. With Siu-Wong Fan, Deshun Wang, Xinru Wang.

title: Beth
synopsis: Directed by Samantha Hindman. With Jade Butterfield, Maggie Evans, Caitlyn Frampton-Powell, Samantha Hindman.

title: Dark Place
synopsis: Directed by Kodie Bedford, Perun Bonser, Rob Braslin, László Baranyai, Liam Phillips, Bjorn Stewart. With Katie Beckett, Shakira Clanton, Tamala Shelton, Nelson Baker. Mystery, terror, suspense and fantasy. Dark Place is a collection of five gripping Australian Indigenous horror tales.

title: Lapse
synopsis: Directed by Sooeung 'Chuck' Chae. With Estelle Chen, Chengming Dong, Aohui Qu. Chengming, a university student who accidentally gains supernatural powers, finds out that he loses his memory every time he uses them and starts recording his daily life using his phone. Chengming and the witnesses of his accident, Lin and Hwei, grow closer together as they experiment with Chengming's supernatural powers. Chengming starts falling in love with Lin but gets anxious when he finds out that she is from a wealthy family, unlike his own background. Chengming realizes that his superpowers are not adding any value to his life when he is persuaded by Hwei to invade the factory owner that hurt his mother. He heads over to the factory solely relying on Hwei's camera.

title: Los Paramos
synopsis: Directed by Jaime Puertas. With José Daniel Brígido, Ángeles Moreno, Dulce Rodríguez. These lands had a different name in years gone by. They were inhabited by other beings. It is said that those beings founded cities. The prophetic stones with which they were built possessed an ancient power. It is said that such dark power keeps us confined amidst a mirage which makes us believe that we truly exist. But no one remembers anymore.

title: Inakunare Gunjo
synopsis: Directed by Akina Yanagi. With Ryûsei Yokohama, Marie Iitoyo, Honoka Miki, Kôdai Matsuoka. An island in Japan is the site for the dumped and the refuse. Nanakusa and Yu who were childhood and school friends meet on this island that is called Kaiden, a scary name that only refers to things not normal or earthly. The reunited friends strike a bargain and are soon involved in cases most would not dare be involved in or become entangled in.

title: Nine Days
synopsis: Directed by Edson Oda. With Winston Duke, Zazie Beetz, Bill Skarsgård, Benedict Wong. A reclusive man conducts a series of interviews with human souls for a chance to be born.

title: Mystic Shrine Maiden
synopsis: Directed by Takeshi Sone. With Takayuki Hamatsu, Takayuki Haranishi, Manmow Iida, Mau Nishio. Toko works as a shrine maiden. Her days are full of joy as she would be called out by the village people to play or sometimes simply savor time with nothing spectacular to do. One day, Toko finds out that the village festival which she has been waiting with great anticipation will be cancelled due to an old superstition. Toko who wants to make the festival happen starts preparations against the advice of the villagers. Events unfold in an unexpected direction when she meets a strange little girl by the lake..

title: The M Riders: Finding Pangu
synopsis: Finding Pangu

title: A Christmas Carol
synopsis: Directed by Marc Hamill. With David Hardware, Carl Hamill, Aaron Murray, Eve Harding. It was the night before Christmas. As the towns folk merried themselves at the annual Victorian fayre, Scrooge sat in his counting-house tallying his books. He was soon to set off on a journey that would change his life forever. A modern take on a Dickens classic.

title: The Eighth Day of the Week
synopsis: Jiang Wei (Wang Yi Miao & Ba Guan Jin), a big girl who was nothing, accidentally got the magic bracelet and got the "week 8" time. However, the bracelet was stolen and all falsehoods were successfully defeated. Jiang Wei finally understood that the meaning of magic is growth rather than pretense.

title: The Bird Who Saved the World
synopsis: Directed by Bo-Han Chiu, Arthur Tsou. With Weibird Wei, Ralf Chiu, Kuan-Chun Wu, Kerr Hsu. Wei plays an aspiring singer who is at a crossroads, wondering whether to pursue his career as a musician. At this difficult time, a giant bird enters his life, giving him a new perspective in assessing his future. This fantastic creature, the nature of whose existence we are free to speculate about, builds a strong relationship with the central character, but begins to fade from his life as things fall into place.

title: K-12
synopsis: Directed by Melanie Martinez, Alissa Torvinen. With Melanie Martinez, Emma Harvey, Megan Gage, Maggie Budzyna. A brave-hearted girl and her charming best friend make a bewitching pair as they embark on a mission to take down the oppressive schooling system of K-12.

title: Mag Mel Evil
synopsis: Directed by Woon-hak Baek, Seok-hoon Lee. With Park Sung-woong.

title: The Dead Matter
synopsis: Directed by Edward Douglas. With Andrew Divoff, Jason Carter, Tom Savini, Sean Serino. Tells the story of a vampire relic with occult powers that falls into the hands of a grief-stricken young woman who will do anything to contact her dead brother.

title: Pungo: A Witch's Tale
synopsis: A Witch's Tale

title: Vortex
synopsis: Directed by Christophe Karabache. With Romuald Bourdon, Claudia Fortunato, Joelle Hélary, Julien Romano. A desperate killer leaves the city behind and meets, on his way, a mysterious witch who's connected to nature. Thus begins a strange organic relationship, between life and death.

title: Aliens and Dragons
synopsis: Directed by Patrick Joel de Leon, Mark Steven Grove. With Jed Rowen, Sara N. Salazar, Mark Steven Grove, Patrick Joel de Leon. Captain KANE MADDOX and his trusted first mate R'OK voyage into the farthest regions of space in an effort to escape the clutches of THAYGORR, an intergalactic villain and his deadly crew of mercenaries. Forced to land on an uncharted planet, Kane and R'ok are drawn to a mysterious cave where they discover a secret that leads them to join RAELEN, a skilled archer, and ENDRIK, a young knight, on a quest to destroy an ancient evil that threatens to unleash its power throughout time and space. Two worlds collide in this epic tale that pits Science against Sorcery on an adventure unlike any other.

title: Serpent's Paradise
synopsis: Directed by Bernardo Arellano. With Ángel Garnica, Sky Zen Sangermani, Mariela Martínez Gómez, Fabricio Vergara Espinosa. A man appears in an abandoned area of the desert in a mysterious accident on the highway where he's rescued by a young cowboy (Sky) and his grandfather (Bernardo) a cockfighter. When the new tenant wakes up, he does'nt remember who he is or where he comes from. After having a mystical vision in a cave he begins to perform miracles of healing in the village; he makes the invalids walk, he returns sight to the blind, he heals the plague. People call him Prophet. The Priest of the community will oppose the stay of the inconvenient dweller who will test the church itself and its concepts on faith.

title: Across Bank Street Portal to the Clockworld the Movie
synopsis: Directed by Nancy Hanks. With Joni Bartel, Kimberlynn Budde, Paige Carlson, John Gessner. Will Nelson discovers that his childhood fantasy of a world through the rock retaining wall across Bank Street is real.

title: In the Mirror
synopsis: Directed by Laila Pakalnina. With Lauris Dzelzitis, Gatis Gaga, Elza Leimane, Madlena Valdberga. A CrossFit trainer becomes the father of a baby girl, Snow White. Snow White's mother dies, and her father marries a young woman obsessed with CrossFit and herself. She works out all the time in order to be the best. And she really is the best - she can do 50 burpees. In the meantime, little Snow White plays and grows up in the CrossFit gym. Time passes, and one day it turns out - while the Stepmother can do 50 burpees, Snow White can already do 53 burpees.

title: Sihirli Annem Bir'iz
synopsis: Directed by Mustafa Kotan.

title: Vise
synopsis: Directed by Yasuhiko Shimizu. With Natalie Emmons, Nobuaki Kaneko, Misuzu Kanno, Julian Koike. When Nature isn't enough... A suave beautician offers patients the chance to correct what they feel nature has gotten wrong. Governed by an unconventional morality, the beautician instead employs a deadly contraption to bring patients in line with the beautician's unnatural notions of beauty.

title: Peaches and Cream
synopsis: Directed by Gur Bentwich. With Maya Kenig, Gur Bentwich, Alon Aboutboul, Dover Koshashvili. An existential comedy about a neurotic film director whose fears of failure, death, and losing control all surface on the night his new film is released

title: Perceptarium
synopsis: Directed by Brian Hanke. With Daniel Carberg, Mary Hronicek, Paul Kandarian, Monica Saviolakis.

title: M&M: The Mall The Merrier
synopsis: Directed by Barry Gonzalez. With Vice Ganda, Anne Curtis, Dimples Romana, Tony Labrusca. After the death of their parents, a brother and sister compete to gain ownership of a shopping mall.

title: Mathius Marvellous Shop
synopsis: Directed by Paola Alvarez, Manuel Escorihuela. With Rebeca Hiles, Marta Bassols, Ivan Martinoz, Jorge Segura. MMS is a retro-futuristic comedy recreated in Berlin in the year 420 after the impact of a comet on Earth. This apocalyptic catastrophe destroys the old world, giving birth to a new order where segregation and prejudices disappeared.

title: Eggnoid: Love & Time Portal
synopsis: Directed by Naya Anindita. With Sheila Dara Aisha, Morgan Oey, Luna Maya, Kevin Julio. Eggnoid is a human who comes out from Eggnoid eggs. He's been assigned to look after and be a friend when a human feels lonely.

title: Sea of Lost Time
synopsis: Directed by Gurvinder Singh. With Anurag Urha.

title: Sanctorum
synopsis: Directed by Joshua Gil. With Erwin Antonio Pérez Jiménez, Nereyda Pérez Vásquez, Virgen Vázquez Torres, Javier Bautista González. In a small village on the edge of the war between the military and the cartels, a little boy escapes to the forest to plead to the gods of nature for his disappeared mother's safe return.

title: Tell Me A Fairy Tail
synopsis: Directed by Abramova Tatiana, Elena Tryapitsyna. With Abramova Tatiana, Elena Tryapitsyna, Andrey Sergeevich, Nikolai Zverev. What would you do if your life turned into a Fairytale? That's what happened to Adele whose younger sister Alicia was abducted by an evil witch. Now she must get in to an adventure to save her.

title: The Swarm
synopsis: Directed by Just Philippot. With Suliane Brahim, Sofian Khammes, Marie Narbonne, Raphael Romand. A single mother's business of a locust farm isn't doing so well. She discovers by accident that blood makes them thrive, and does her best to hide her secrets.

title: Iye the others
synopsis: Directed by Debesh Chatterjee. With Nitya Ganguly, Arpita Ghosh, Debshankar Haldar. An anthology film about three people in search of something that finally results them to meet.

title: Mystery of the Night
synopsis: Directed by Adolfo Alix Jr.. With Solenn Heussaff, Benjamin Alves, Gina Alajar, Elizabeth Oropesa. 1800 colonial Philippines. During the time of Spanish tyranny and oppression, a woman raised in the enchanted woods by nymphs experiences love for the first time from a man from town. When she is later betrayed and experiences heartbreak, hell hath no fury indeed like a woman scorned as she she transforms into the mythical Aswang out to avenge her pain and let the man suffer forever.

title: About Her
synopsis: Directed by Islam El Azzazi. With Nadah El Shazly, Fadwa Abed, Salah Fahmi, Ahmed Malek. She rejects grief as a reaction to loss. Instead confronting her misery face on and pushing herself to the brink, clinging to a flood of magic she experienced as a child as it flows across time from person to person and story to story.

title: Da ming ping yao zhuan
synopsis: Directed by Xiao-Chuan Guo. With Liu Yu, Liu Qian-Wen, Wu Xing-Jian. In a turbulent time in the Ming Dynasty, the Imperial Bodyguard solves humans' cases, while the Jinwu Guard takes charge of ghosts' and monsters' business. Eunuch Wei seizes great power and suppresses dissidents. Colluding with the monster Huo Feiyuan, he framed up Feng Tingzhang, the Director of the Grand Court. Zuo Changgeng, Feng's disciple, accidentally gets involved in the Jinwu Guard's monster hunting as he investigates the treasury's theft case. Though despising the Jinwu Guard, Zuo Changgeng has no choice but to ask the Jinwu Guard for help to save his master. Yi Shuihan is an upright half-human and half-monster member of the Jinwu Guard. Zuo and Yi work together and investigate in the humans' and monsters' worlds, before they gradually see through Eunuch Wei's intrigue. But the Jinwu Guard is framed up and then controlled by Eunuch Wei, and Yi and Zuo fall into Huo's trap. It turns out that Huo is the mastermind behind everything to destroy the Qianyuan Formation that suppresses the monster world and release monsters to the human world. Yi and Zuo cooperate and defeat Huo, but Eunuch Wei takes the merit of killing monsters and rescuing the Emperor, because of which he becomes domineering in the court. Seeing the chaotic world, Zuo and Yi leave the court and wander around to pursue peace of their own.

title: Ghost Rider: Spirit of Vengeance
synopsis: Directed by Mark Neveldine, Brian Taylor. With Nicolas Cage, Violante Placido, Ciarán Hinds, Idris Elba. Johnny Blaze, tortured by the Ghost Rider's curse, gets a chance of redemption through protecting the Devil's son, whose father is pursuing him.

title: Nezha Conquers the Dragon King
synopsis: Directed by Le Luo. With Siu-Ho Chin, Ziqi Fan, Xin Kan, Xianshi Li. Yin Shiniang finally gives birth after an unusual pregnancy lasting three years and eight months. Suddenly, Shi Ji the snake spirit appears, declaring that she has come for revenge for the harm she once suffered at the hand of Yin's husband, Li Jing. Mother and son are rescued by the powerful deity Taiyi Zhenren, who promises to teach the son, Nezha, the path of immortality once he comes of age. Eighteen years later, Nezha sets off to take up his discipleship, but things do not go as planned. Nezha slays a flood dragon to rescue a young woman, Ling Zhu, once again incurring the wrath of Shi Ji, who vows to kill Nezha and avenge the dragon. In the ensuing chaos, Nezha takes his own life rather than risking harm to innocent civilians in Chen Tang Pass. Taiyi Zhenren arrives and tells Lingzhu that there is a way to bring Nezha back-but it involves paying the ultimate price.

synopsis: Directed by Matthew Stalletti. With Michael Mior, Joseph Stalletti, Matthew Stalletti. Awoken from a long and mysterious slumber, the Traveller must adapt to unfamiliar lands, unexpected threats, and a second chance at life. Together with the Voice in his head, the pair will venture into the brutal wilds of an alien world and fight to fulfill a deeply personal quest.

title: Texas Flood

title: What If the Earth Is Flat?
synopsis: Directed by Jacob Grant. With Jeran Campanella, Robbie Davidson, Rick Hummer, Bob Knodel. "What if the Earth is Flat?" takes an unbiased approach to the topic and simply presents the impact of the movement on the world as a whole, though It does present the most convincing arguments in order to show why people are becoming Flat Earthers. What is the overall impact on Freedom of Speech when censorship begins with Flat Earth, How will this affect Creationists in general who are not even Flat Earthers? What are the conspiracies that Build up to Flat Earth? If supporting conspiracies to the overarching Flat Earth belief are proven factual, could important information be swept away with the offense of the term Flat Earth? Finally how has the Media, influenced the growth of the movement as a whole? Deep coverage of the Flat Earth Phenomena unlike any other.

title: Ghost Walk

One night, however, she finds she has become a ghost. As a ghost, she goes back in time, day by day, and tries to keep out of harm's way.

title: Un cuento Latinoamericano
synopsis: Directed by Juan Manuel Rampoldi. With Rodrigo Aragón, Ivania Cox, Victoria Hoyos, Joaquin Mendez. In the 40s, during the government of General Perón, a strange experiment was held in Argentina. The purpose was to create a new Latin American ideal society. But that experiment ended abruptly and all involved were exterminated. The first to be burned at the stake were prostitutes that the General had implanted to keep men encouraged and the new society in perfect balance. They say that the grieving of those women roaming the forest around that razed town still can be heard. Forgotten beings who can not rest in peace.

title: Potential Victim

Haunted by the ghosts of her victims, she longs for the end of curse of immortality. In the meantime, her music bewitch teenagers who see no meaning in their lives and who beg her to kill them, and transform them into internet ghosts.

title: Krasotka!
synopsis: Directed by Yana Gladkikh. With Yuliya Aleksandrova, Maksim Blinov, Andrey Burkovskiy, Marco Dinelli. Polina, an average-looking girl with an average life, wakes up one morning to find that she has become a beautiful woman, a hot babe. Is this real, or just her imagination?

title: 3 Days in Paris
synopsis: Directed by Clinton Stark. With Loni Stark. It was just a holiday in Paris - or was it? In this short film a woman dives deep into the art scene in the famed City of Lights. A unique film by Clinton and Loni Stark that combines scenes shot in studio with actual vacation footage shot on the streets of Paris.

title: Stick Monster Movie
synopsis: Directed by Raymond Lloyd. With Sara Murphy, Toby Ricketts. Hanna Lovelady grew up on a tulip farm - or in her words "a place where Roy G. Biv threw up." Needless to say, she has no desire to go back to the family business. You see, there was this party, and social media was there, which means her insect of a brother saw it and tried to blackmail her. Long story short, Dad's mad as a hornet and unless she aces her college video thesis, her dreams of becoming an entomologist are DOA. We'll go along for the ride as Hanna commandeers her roommate's video equipment to document the journey of "Charlie", a rare Chan's MegaStick, as she chauffeurs him to a remote research facility. But she'll arrive to find the place empty and it's not long before something "unnatural" rears its ugly head. Miles from civilization, no phone signal, and her hatchback squished - a direct result of the unnatural thing with the ugly head - she must rely on her budding bug skills to thwart off a giant mutant insect invasion that threatens to wipe out all humanity.

They say that Armugan moves through the valleys clinging to the body of Anchel, his faithful servant and together they share the secret of a work as old as life, as terrible as death itself.

title: Witch

She has been living in a village next to the US military base for more than 40 years. Never given the chance to learn how to read and write, In-sun has been drawing pictures on waste paper all her life, chronicling her painful and mysterious world of traumas. On a winter night, she finds out that her colleague has passed away and follows her silent funeral. The Death Messengers show up and spot In-sun. When they make up stories for their targets to lead them to afterlife, In-sun refuses to give in and creates her own story. The desire of fiction resides in resistance, and not staying as a victim.

SNAKE WHITE is a contemporary cinematic presentation of an immensely popular legend, faithfully preserved by Cantonese opera, and enhanced with modern music.

She must contend with a fractured reality and intrusive family members.

Soon Jason discovers himself experiencing myth and legend and is tasked with helping the mythical Magayon, or Woman in the Woods, in her quest to return home on a volcanic island in the Philippines.

Demon hunter Hao and his student collect the three treasures to incarcerate the malefic demon. The student falls for Yellow Demon Susu but Hao objects the forbidden love. Meanwhile the demon wakes again.

title: Shushan xiang mo zhuan 2
synopsis: Directed by Lingfeng Zhu. With Norman Chu, Kin-Yan Lee, Yusi Peng, Yinghao Sheng. To collect all the five spiritual stones that had been transformed from the ancient savage beasts in order to dominate the three realms, Yun Juyan, a traitor to the Emei Sect, resurrects the elders of the Emei and Kunlun Sects to kill every member of Emei. The three realms are caught in a huge crisis again after a temporary peace from the war between immortals and demons that had just come to an end. To end Yun Juyan's plans, Xiao He and Yuan Youqing, as well as other disciples of Emei, embark on the difficult journey of looking for the spiritual stones in the hope of collecting them before Yun. With the help of Xiaoyaozi, another elder of the Kunlun Sect, who had retired for many years, Xiao He and Yuan Youqing, together with others, fight and subdue monsters and evil dragons. They are even ready to die for their goal.

title: KL Vampires
synopsis: Directed by Daven Raghavan. With Josiah Hogan, Donny Alamsyah, Reen Rahim, Raja Ilya. Two groups of vampires, both descendants of Raja Bersiong, no longer consume human blood. They instead replace it with synthetic blood.

title: Las brujas
synopsis: Directed by Sebastián Jiménez Galindo. With Madisen Dempsey, Andrea Berrones Moreno. Drawing from T. S. Eliot, between the image and the word falls a shadow. Within that shadow, hidden from view, is a spirit that connects us all, beneath the skin. LAS BRUJAS is a personal vision of displacement, home, memory, literature and the relationship between personal and collective history through the ethos of collage. It is the starting point of the desire for honesty and unapologetic truths in personal filmmaking, deriving from video art, visual essay and poetry.
