title: The Lodger
synopsis: Directed by Baptiste Drapeau. With Alice Isaaz, Jacqueline Bisset, François-Dominique Blin, Bastien Ughetto. 20 years after her husband's death, a woman keeps more than just his memory alive. Needing help at home, she takes in a student, but soon detects a risk of losing her husband to the girl. Does the girl have even a ghost of a chance?

title: Gyrus
synopsis: Directed by Eric Chamberlain. With Carolyn Chamberlain, Eric Chamberlain. A strange man is trapped in a room while creating strange works of art. At first tormented by an unknown figure, Subject 8477447 escapes his captor and tries to make his way back home. The world appears to be in a perpetual apocalyptic state, and he is apparently in Limbo. Upon finding his home and entering, he is shocked to discover he is back where he started. Now, however, all of his creations disappear to reveal transition to the afterlife. His tormentor was actually God enabling his spiritual evolution. Upon achieving his spiritual evolution we hear sounds of destruction from earlier in the film, indicating a nonlinear reality. What his evolution means for humanity is he rest of the story.

title: The Yin-Yang Master: Dream of Eternity
synopsis: Мечта о вечности

title: Redroom
synopsis: Directed by Boneyboy. With Patty Bouree, Clay, Coleslaw, Robin Craddles. Miss Hollywood has fun with some of her friends in a red room.

title: Kishiryu Sentai Ryusoulger vs. Lupinranger vs. Patranger
synopsis: Directed by Katsuya Watanabe. With Hayate Ichinose, Keito Tsuna, Ichika Osaki, Yuito Obara. A Gangler remnant, Ganima, captures Tyramigo and the other Kishiryu inside his safe. To save them, the Ryusoulgers chase after Ganima and come into contact with the Patrangers and Lupinrangers.

title: Pathologie
synopsis: Directed by Max Ponischowski. With Matthias Schmidt, Thomas Kautenburger, Nora Charlotte Schilling, Ingo van Gulijk.

title: Wax Wings
synopsis: Directed by Wesley Rickert. With Bill Bisset, Mirella Kovach, Christina Kozak, Ian Malone. Aggregate anti-characters and the Canadian sound poet bill bissett hang breathlessly over poetic history to escape 2500 years of tradition, blood thirsty social mobs, censorship and the guilt of gravity. The ancient myth of Icarus, the Old Comedy of Aristophanes, the unhappy execution of Socrates, and the science of flight provide a thin atmosphere and suffocating hot sunshine. This art house narrative is hi-jacked for the viewer by a combination of souvenir go-pro summer vacation footage salvaged from a low flying sight-seeing helicopter, an assortment of low flying flight school Cessnas, anti-plot absurdist debates, the French Revolution, clouds that outburst, informal inquisitions that take notes, crudely animated space craft, lazy pigeons and scenery soaring around on sound effects.

title: Beastly
synopsis: Directed by Daniel Barnz. With Alex Pettyfer, Justin Bradley, Mary-Kate Olsen, Dakota Johnson. A modern-day take on the "Beauty and the Beast" tale where a New York teen is transformed into a hideous monster in order to find true love.

title: The Inconsiderables: Last Exit Out of Hollywood
synopsis: Last Exit Out of Hollywood

title: BloodRayne: The Third Reich
synopsis: Третий рейх

title: Ultraman Taiga: New Generation Climax
synopsis: Nyû jene kuraimakkusu

title: Royal Opera House Live Cinema Season 2019/20: The Sleeping Beauty
synopsis: The Sleeping Beauty

title: I choose to forget
synopsis: Directed by Shihyun Wang. With Charles DeNatale, Monika Ekiert, Cory Marlan Johnson, Corinne Laurance.

title: Hello Again - A Wedding a Day
synopsis: Directed by Maggie Peren. With Jonas Albrecht, Vilmar Bieri, Marion Breckwoldt, Claudia Brosch. Zazie is invited to her best friend's wedding. She decides to do everything to prevent what is in her eyes the mistake of his life. But when she finds herself trapped in the time-line of the wedding, things get complicated.

title: Green Snake
synopsis: Directed by Fei Xu. With Jiaming Ma, Sheng Nan. Green Snake was saved by Xunya, whose primordial spirit was a dragon, when she fell into the River after being struck by lightning. She suffers from a cold toxin from time to time, but she survived. Xunya built Sansheng Inn by the riverside for Green Snake to live in. He also turned a magic scroll into a teenager called Zhesheng to keep Green Snake company. 300 years later, Shenxiu asks Zhesheng for one of the best rooms in the inn, with clothing stained with liquor for an excuse. Zhesheng says no in anger. Xiaorou is saved by Green Snake when threatened by Rui, a dog spirit, but later, she insists that her husband was seduced and hidden in the inn by Green Snake. While they argue, Xiaorou turns into a bat, fights with Green Snake and asks her to hand over the most valuable treasure in Luochuan River.

title: War of ShanHai: The Revenge of Titan Monsters
synopsis: The Revenge of Titan Monsters

title: The Channeling of Alexander Hamilton
synopsis: Directed by Larry Stanley. With Larry Stanley, Laura Cifaldi, Tim Newkirk, Eddie Reed. When New Jersey Medium Laura Cifaldi agrees to take part in documentary and channel an unknown historical figure, Laura quickly learns she is talking to America's Founding Father Alexander Hamilton.

title: Doi Mat Am Duong
synopsis: Directed by Nhat Trung. With Huynh An, Huu Chau, Ngan Chi, Nguyen Trung Dan. The story begins after Trang recovers from a car accident coma and loses her memory. She starts seeing a ghost of a lady with blood-filled eyes wandering around her. She decides to investigate the case and discovers unimaginable secrets.

title: Recife Assombrado
synopsis: Directed by Adriano Portela. With Daniel Rocha, Germano Haiut, Márcio Fecher, Rayza Alcântara. Hermano searches for his missing brother in the city of Recife, which is haunted by scary folk legends.

title: She Dies Tomorrow
synopsis: Directed by Amy Seimetz. With Kate Lyn Sheil, Jane Adams, Kentucker Audley, Katie Aselton. Amy thinks she's dying tomorrow...and it's contagious.

title: Undine
synopsis: Directed by Christian Petzold. With Paula Beer, Franz Rogowski, Maryam Zaree, Jacob Matschenz. Undine works as a historian lecturing on Berlin's urban development. But when the man she loves leaves her, the ancient myth catches up with her. Undine has to kill the man who betrays her and return to the water.

title: Orbius
synopsis: Directed by Sergey A.. With Sergey A., Random People. Someone is walking in this world. Someone is looking for something better. Someone is trying to run away. Someone - it's you.

title: Cats city 2
synopsis: Directed by Seyed Javad Hashemi. With Yousef Teymouri, Amir Ghaffarmanesh, Ali Reza Khamseh, Mir Taher Mazloomi. each Cat who lives in Gorbestan tries to be singer , so be famous and transferred to Cats city . Shangoul the cute and funny cat has a different plan with his friend Khengoul.

title: Lucky Chan-sil
synopsis: Directed by Cho-hee Kim. With Mal-Geum Kang, Youn Yuh-jung, Kim Young-min, Seung-ah Yoon. Chan-sil, a film producer, finds herself unemployed with the sudden death of her long-time collaborated director. Out of prospects and out of luck, she moves into a bargain room in a shoddy neighborhood. But something doesn't seem quite right with her new elderly landlady.

title: Three Ladies
synopsis: Directed by Ardy Octaviand. With Tora Sudiro, Adipati Dolken, Tanta Ginting, Rianti Cartwright. Three men have something in common

title: 30 Chua Phai Tet
synopsis: Directed by Quang Huy. With Viet Anh, Truong Giang, Van Hong, Oanh Kieu. A guy left his home for 12 years till he came back to claim what's his from his father, the vast Land, just to uncover that he had to live that day, year-end Lunar day, for another 12 years.

title: Maya
synopsis: Directed by Roberto Madda. With Jeniffer Aldrighi, Sergio Barroso, Kátia Carnier, Luma Carolina. MAYA is a mystical thriller, telling the story of the presumed relationship between Icaro and Adriana, since the moment they met until the day when she disappears and cease existing.

title: Kratt
synopsis: Directed by Rasmus Merivoo. With Mari Lill, Nora Merivoo, Harri Merivoo, Elise Tekko. Children are left at grandma's house without their smartphones. Real life seems boring until they find instructions for kratt - a magical creature who will do whatever its master says. All they need now is to buy a soul from the devil.

title: Wanda's Wonderful World
synopsis: Directed by Icko Gonzalez. With Via Antonio, Ayaka Chanel Bunao, Danica Caritativo, Ivy Catucod. Wanda's Wonderful World is the story of Wanda, a former beauty queen who is now a most sought-after eventologist. She makes dream events happen for her clients but it's something she can't seem to do for herself. This comedy drama movie made for TV follows the roller coaster ride of Wanda's introspection on her life's triumphs, failed loves, and her endless search for true affection that will satisfy.

title: Lucky
synopsis: Directed by Natasha Kermani. With Brea Grant, Leith M. Burke, Dhruv Uday Singh, Hunter C. Smith. A suburban woman fights to be believed as she finds herself stalked by a threatening figure who returns to her house night after night. When she can't get help from those around her, she is forced to take matters into her own hands.

title: The Hobbit: The Desolation of Smaug
synopsis: Пустошь Смауга

title: Diva Senza Tempo
synopsis: Directed by Jonathan Gottesmann. With Rodica Alcalay, Maya Alkulumbre, Maria Rosaria Coscia, Joseph Di Bello.

title: Paradies
synopsis: Directed by Immanuel Esser. With Imke Büchel, Holger Daemgen, Jennifer Ewert, Leander Gerdes. In a world, where death has become a private service company, three workers rebel against their own mortality.

title: Langsuir
synopsis: Directed by Osman Ali. With Hannah Delisha, Syafiq Kyle, Julia Farhana Marin, Firdaus Nadxaman. Azlan and his friends are on holiday, visiting the forbidden island of Pulau Langsuir. There, Azlan meets Suri, a beautiful girl, and falls in love with her. Little did he know that Suri is a 'langsuir' ghost that inhabits the island. Envious of their romantic relationship, Azlan's friends plot to stab Suri's head with a nail to reveal her ghost form. This only brings chaos to the group as their plan has invoked the wrath of Suri's sister, Dewi.

title: Crema Caserta
synopsis: Directed by Jonathan Gottesmann. With Pasquale Marcellino Antunuccio, Tony Borlotti, Luciano Ricigliano, Aneta Rybaczuk.

title: Blood Sings
synopsis: Directed by Petrus de Bairros, Jorge Polo. With Rosalina Tamiza, Maricota, Lucas Inácio Nascimento, Noá Bonoba. Two monster friends decide to follow different directions. Decades after leaving, Naiana is a high school teacher in a small coastal town, where a hotel under renovation emanates a strange presence. Three thousand kilometers away, the devouring night involves Diego.

title: Dance with Me
synopsis: Directed by Sorush Sehhat. With Ali Mosaffa, Javad Ezati, Hanieh Tavassoli, Pejman Jamshidi. As Jahaan is going to die in a few months, Bahman, his brother, arranges for his closest friends to gather in Jahaan's farm house in north, to celebrate his (probably) last birthday together...

title: Skin
synopsis: Directed by Bahman Ark, Bahram Ark. With Javad Ghamati, Fatemeh Masoudifar, Mahmoud Nazaralian, Naser Hashemi. When demonic Jinns threaten his mother, a man must confront the sins of his family and a curse that spans generations. A tale of love, magic and superstition.

title: Orphea
synopsis: Directed by Khavn, Alexander Kluge. With Lilith Stangenberg, Ian Madrigal. A reinvention of the Greek myth of Orpheus and Eurydice, set in contemporary Manila as a rock musical.

title: Time Up
synopsis: Directed by Manu Parthepan. With Abhishek, Manu Parthepan, Motta Rajendran. A man is set a 30-day deadline to accomplish a task by an unknown person and is required to work accordingly, or else he might have to face the consequences.

title: The Mystical Treasure
synopsis: Directed by Zhang Zhu Lin. With Yang Xia, Bu Yuan. Ge Zhen joins a killer organization the 12 troops. Justice and evil coexist and the entanglement between loyalty and betrayal come one after another.

title: Revolution Launderette
synopsis: Directed by Mark Chua, Li Shuen Lam. With Keisuke Baba, Andhika Faisal, Satoshi Ikeda, Gabriel Kei. In Tokyo, Tomo plots to undermine the next punchline of his existence and is drawn deeper into the stranger side of the city, where he gets more than he bargained for.

title: The Ghost and the Tout
synopsis: Directed by Charles Uwagbai. With Toyin Abraham, Sambasa Nzeribe, Chioma Chukwuka Akpotha, Chioma Omeruah. Isla, a young woman from the ghetto, encounters a ghost called Mike who needs her assistance to communicate with the people he left behind. She soon becomes entangled in solving a murder mystery.

title: Death Files
synopsis: Directed by Sergey A., Mikhail Ryabkov, Nastasya Sharapova, Eldar Bogunov, Elisey Vishnyov, Mykola Yeriomin. With Mikhail Ryabkov, Evgeniy Toroschin, Nastasya Sharapova, Sergey A.. 2 locksmiths find a flash drive at an old warehouse. One of them activates the flash drive at a computer and opens the shocking world of mysterious creatures, broken lives and violence.

title: My Blood & Bones in a Flowing Galaxy
synopsis: Directed by SABU. With Tomoyo Harada, Kai Inowaki, Anna Ishii, Hana Kino. Hamada is seemingly a regular high school, junior student. He is indeed ordinary except he has a passion for righteousness and justice. His trait comes to the fore when he notices that his junior school-mate Hari is being bullied. He does not abide by it and decides to step in and help her. His intervention is welcomed and she seems him as a white knight of sorts. It is not a surprise then that the school girl and school boy become close.

title: The Ghost Tank
synopsis: Directed by Blaise Kolodychuk. With Frankie van Rooyen, Randolph West, Beth Murray, Jennifer Hartley. Beetrice and Charleenkaw are on the case when a dead serial killer from the 1980s has come back to commit a string of bizarre murders in Calgary. Luckily they are helped not only by a brilliant scientist, but also one of the victims. Leaping back and forth between our world and the ghost world, the clues come together and culminate in a supernatural, time travelling, terrifying time.

title: Chaos from the Old World. Part II
synopsis: Directed by Paul Miloslavsky. With Daria Chodacova, Vladimir Gorin, Dmitry Ikonnikov, Paul Miloslavsky.

title: The Washing Machine
synopsis: Directed by Mohamed Farouk, Essam Abdel Hamid. With Ahmed Hatem, Hana El Zahed, Mahmoud Hemida, Mohamed Sallam. The fictional story of an advanced washing machine that's also a time-traveling machine. However, what it truly offers is conflicts and ironies upon its users.

title: All the Moons
synopsis: Directed by Igor Legarreta. With Elena Uriz, Miriam del Prado, Justi Larrinaga, Maite Sáez de Vicuña. In late 19th century, a little girl hurt by a bomb at the end of the third Carlist war is saved by a woman who brings her the eternal life.

title: Vork and the Beast
synopsis: Directed by Fabrizio La Monica. With Fabrizio La Monica, Samuele Lindiner, Ninni Motisi, Ferdinando Gattuccio. Three concurrent stories involving a deadly female beast in the forest

title: Keystone
synopsis: Directed by Scorpione, Marco Savi. With Thomas Bonifazi, Claudio Cardella, Stefania Chiavoghilefu, Luke Denali.

title: Jaane Kahan Se Aayi Hai
synopsis: Directed by Milap Zaveri. With Priyanka Chopra Jonas, Akshay Kumar, Sajid Khan, Riteish Deshmukh. Rejected by the woman he loves, a man must find true love for an amazon from Venus.

title: Red Moon Tide
synopsis: Directed by Lois Patiño. With Rubio de Camelle, Ana Marra, Carmen Martínez, Pilar Rodlos. In a village where the sea and the moon are near, there was a monster, three witches, many ghosts and a shipwrecked man.

title: Du-ngan: The Spirit Within
synopsis: The Spirit Within

title: No Sanctuary
synopsis: Directed by Jake Stetler. With Ron Baker, Tommy Cahill, Melissa Dunphy, Branden Ehrhart. A group of outcasts take refuge in the ruins of a church to protect a young girl from a legion of demon-infested highwaymen

title: Gracie
synopsis: Directed by Jane A. Foster. With Aurélie Amblard, Tyrone Bacchus, Sylvie Bolioli, Darren Darnborough. 2am Waterloo Bridge. Despairing, alone, Gracie, (29) stares into the river, contemplates death. On the south side, Ellie (17) runs in fear for her life to escape a deadly pursuer. When Ellie runs onto the bridge and begs Gracie for help, destiny throws them both a chance at survival and redemption. But first they must survive a long, nightmarish, very odd night.

title: Monster SeaFood Wars
synopsis: Directed by Minoru Kawasaki. With Yûya Asato, Ayano Yoshida Christie, Hide Fukumoto, Kei Grant. Yuta, a young master at the Tsukiji Fish Market, accidentally drops his meal of mixed seafood into the Sumida River. Some time afterwards a gigantic mutated squid monster arises from the depths and begins to wreak havoc upon an awe-stricken Tokyo. Attempts by the Japan Self-Defense Forces to stop the creature prove futile. As it seems things couldn't get any worse an enormous mutant octopus monster emerges from the deep and heads into a clash of the titans with the gargantuan squid. As a last ditch effort, the government forms the "Seafood Monster Attack Team (SMAT)" and an all-new plan of attack is immediately put into action. But just as the tide appears to be turning in humanity's favor, a colossal crab monster appears, joining in the Monster Seafood Wars and plunging the world into culinary chaos.

title: Burn the Witch
synopsis: Directed by Tatsuro Kawano. With Edward Bosco, Kira Buckland, Griffin Burns, Sean Chiplock. Noel Niihashi and Ninny Spangcole are witch and protection agents for Wing Bind an organization for dragon conservation and management. Their mission is to protect and manage the dragons within London on behalf of the people.

title: Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows: Part 2
synopsis: Часть II

title: Coronavirus. Apocalypse
synopsis: Directed by Sergey A.. With Sergey A.. A symbolic art film shot exactly one month before the outbreak of coronavirus in Spain.

title: Aloevera
synopsis: Directed by Peter Sedufia. With Benjamin Adaletey, Aaron Adatsi, Ngozi Viola Adikwu, Kofi Adjorlolo. In a land where the people have divided themselves because of a disagreement long ago, a man and woman from the different sides fall in love. Despite the efforts of their families to keep them apart, they eventually become the reason the community becomes one again.

title: Attack of the Giant Teacher
synopsis: Directed by Yoshikazu Ishii. With Makoto Kojima, Takashi Toyoda, Takehiko Fujita, Miyuki Takase. Kenzo Miyazawa is an earnest teacher who works at a night high school. His class is filled with unique and slightly odd students. Suddenly, the night school witnesses a drop in student numbers and has no choice but to shut down by the end of the year. Mr. Miyazawa's class decides to create a musical for the school's last festival. Then, an alien beast invades Earth and begins destroying the town. Mr. Miyazawa challenges the alien beast to a fight. Directed by Ishii Yoshikazu.

title: Dragon Soldiers
synopsis: Directed by Hank Braxtan. With Antuone Torbert, Ruben Pla, Tarkan Dospil, Heath C. Heine. A lethal creature hides in the woods that surround a suburban area killing anyone who gets near. An elite group of soldiers comes into action.

title: Scare Me
synopsis: Directed by Thomas Fisco, Conrad Glover, Mark Stephens. With DeMarr Wright, Taylor Kilgore, Mark Justice, Caslin Rose. A group of college students ride share to a music festival and have a campfire story competition on the way. As the stories progress, the tensions rise as they realize they are in a story of their own.

title: Doctor Strange
synopsis: Directed by Scott Derrickson. With Benedict Cumberbatch, Chiwetel Ejiofor, Rachel McAdams, Benedict Wong. While on a journey of physical and spiritual healing, a brilliant neurosurgeon is drawn into the world of the mystic arts.

title: Hereafter
synopsis: Directed by Clint Eastwood. With Cécile de France, Thierry Neuvic, Cyndi Mayo, Lisa Griffiths. A drama centered on three people - a blue-collar American, a French journalist and a London school boy - who are touched by death in different ways.

title: White Demise
synopsis: Directed by Daeil Kim. With Kelly Macdougall, Lawrence Sams, John Spencer, Olivia Storm. A desperate woman embarks on a journey to find a life-saving bullet, seeking to reverse the tragic death of her daughter, but the only way to do that is through the man who revived her murderer.

title: Alieu the Dreamer
synopsis: Directed by Quincy Ledbetter. With Denzel Whitaker, Haley Webb, Rick Hearst, Trevor Zhou. In a world where mankind hasn't dreamed for three decades, a driven government agent finds a young man living in the projects who has suddenly started dreaming.

title: La Zona Elegida
synopsis: Directed by Conti Ariel. With Hinsch Martina, Esquivel Miriam, Firpo Emilio, Vénica Mariano. In an area of lagoons somewhere in the province of Córdoba (Argentina), local people begin to experience strange situations, related to altered dog behaviors that later also appear dead.

title: Secret of the Wings
synopsis: Тайна зимнего леса

title: Dance Til You Bleed: The World According to Hans Christian Andersen
synopsis: The World According to Hans Christian Andersen

title: Monstrous
synopsis: Directed by Bruce Wemple. With Anna Shields, Rachel Finninger, Grant Schumacher, Hannah McKechnie. A young woman goes searching for answers after her friend mysteriously vanishes in Whitehall, NY, an Adirondack town known for its Bigfoot sightings. She quickly learns that hiding in the woods is an evil more sinister than she could ever imagine.

title: Novoland the Castle in the Sky - Time Reversal
synopsis: Directed by Tommy Yu. With Danni Zhong, Ge Chai, Uvin Wang. After the battle of Sky City, Feng Ren declares war on the human tribe. Seeing that the human tribe has no means of retaliating, Fang Qiwu, the queen of Human tribe, tries to use a time machine device to return to the past so that she can possess the body of Nan Yinmeng, Feng Ren's beloved consort, and kill Feng Ren. However when she wakes up in another timeline, she is told that Feng Ren is dead. However, Fang Qiwu refuses to believe this and merely think this is a rumor. The body that Fang Qiwu wakes up in turns out to be Hong Luan, the top beauty of the human tribe. Ten days later, she is to marry Feng Qi, the crown prince of Yu tribe. As it is told in history that Feng Ren would play the Qin during the wedding ceremony, Fang Qiwu plans to kill Feng Ren during her wedding day. During this ten days, she is protected by a youth named Nan Feng. Fang Qiwu falls in love with Nan Feng as both share the same love for music. However on the day of the wedding ceremony, she finds out that Nan Feng's true identity is actually Feng Ren.

title: The Ghost Story: Love Redemption
synopsis: Love Redemption

title: Conquering Kings
synopsis: Directed by Curtis Everitt. With Lamar Allen, Aaron Brown, Gerald Brown, Billie Joyce Colbert. The Destroyer Prince Davian hides away in the forest with his guardian Phillip while the new ruler Camien hunts him like a wolf. Davian yearns to get out in the world, and in doing so befriends the mysterious Vesperelda.

title: Dino Dana: The Movie
synopsis: Directed by J.J. Johnson. With Michela Luci, Donald Henderson, Millie Davis, Nicola Correia-Damude. Follow Dana Jain, a feisty 10-year-old 'paleontologist in training' who eats, sleeps and breathes dinos, as she tries to solve dino experiment 901-where are all the kid dinos?

title: Imaginary Boys
synopsis: Directed by Scott Handcock. With James Baxter, Geoffrey Breton, Daniel Brocklebank, Liam Dascombe. 17 year-old David Taylor begins to see the world in a different light when he meets Lawrence. Lawrence is new in town, new to Earth actually - he claims to be from Verbatim Six, a small planet about three hundred light years away. A strange but very real story of a burgeoning teenage relationship, with all the fear and confusion that goes with it.

title: Love like the Falling Rain
synopsis: Directed by Lasja Fauzia. With Jefri Nichol, Aurora Ribero, Axel Matthew Thomas, Nadya Arina. Kevin and Nara have been friends since childhood and they promise to always be best friends. But when Nara falls in love with a mysterious boy, Kevin feels that there is no hope for him to be with her forever.

title: The Enchanting Phantom
synopsis: Ren jian qing

title: Zookeeper
synopsis: Directed by Frank Coraci. With Kevin James, Rosario Dawson, Leslie Bibb, Ken Jeong. A group of zoo animals decide to break their code of silence in order to help their lovable zookeeper find love, without opting to leave his current job for something more illustrious.

title: Forbidden Empire
synopsis: Directed by Oleg Stepchenko. With Jason Flemyng, Andrey Smolyakov, Aleksey Chadov, Agnia Ditkovskyte. An eighteenth century English cartographer, Jonathan Green, sets out on a journey to map the uncharted lands of Transylvania, only to discover the dark secrets and dangerous creatures hidden in a cursed, fantastical Romanian forest.

title: Kaijuu Girls Kuro: Ultra Kaijuu Gijinka Keikaku
synopsis: Ultra Kaijuu Gijinka Keikaku

title: Aletheia
synopsis: Directed by Thotti Cardoso. With Nathalia Cavalcanti, Joana Ferraz, Cristal Gabetto, Jorge Hissa. The supervisor of the western land reflects on his existence while trying to finish the duty with a nation that is not his own.

title: Let Me In
synopsis: Directed by Matt Reeves. With Kodi Smit-McPhee, Chloë Grace Moretz, Richard Jenkins, Cara Buono. A bullied young boy befriends a young female vampire who lives in secrecy with her guardian.

title: Vampire Madness
synopsis: Directed by Joey Harlow. With Ron Baratono, Sylvia Brikho, Kim Croes, Christi Dumar. A young woman is discovered by a six hundred year old vampire. He finds a striking resemblance in her to his mate who died hundreds of years ago. He sets out to find her and win her over.

title: Utraan
synopsis: With Hiroshini Komali, Jangiri Madhumitha, Priyanka Nair, Roshan Udayakumar. Revolving around a college romance, Utraan tells the story of students whose lives turn upside down after a certain incident. Vijay gets into a series of life-threatening troubles because of his love with Nandini.

title: The Great God Monkey 2
synopsis: Directed by Qiao Tan. With Miao Xie, Miao Zheng, Yanna Jin, Cheung-Yan Yuen.

title: Monkey King
synopsis: Directed by Kwok-Man Keung, Jing Wong. With Benny Chan, Kar-Ying Law, Tze-Chung Lam, Mars.

title: The Tree
synopsis: Directed by Manika Sharma. With Varsha Agnihotri, Shabana Azmi, Jayati Bhatia, Jaya Bhattacharya. Produced by Raajaysh Chetwal (Rhombus Films), 'The Wishing Tree' is a magical, inspirational and an extremely entertaining story of five children in a hill-station somewhere in India, who come together to save their 'wishing tree' from being cut by vested interests. The film is extremely lively, endearing and engrossing so that the underlying message to protect trees and environment is seamlessly driven home.

title: The Book of Mythical Beasts
synopsis: Directed by Zhang Tao. With Wah Yuen, Qiu Yuen, Yusi Peng, Mika Wang.

title: The Future
synopsis: Directed by Miranda July. With Hamish Linklater, Miranda July, David Warshofsky, Isabella Acres. When a couple decides to adopt a stray cat their perspective on life changes radically, literally altering the course of time and space and testing their faith in each other and themselves.

title: The Sorcerer
synopsis: Directed by Elanor Togliatti. With Sergio Togliatti, John Gross, Siobhan Togliatti, Paul Supplee. Omar Ney is a 200-year-old sorcerer doing good works for humanity. He is powerful; but can he fend off great challenges to his purpose here and meet his destiny before his time on earth runs out?

title: Ginger's Tale
synopsis: Directed by Konstantin Shchekin. With Yuri Askarov, Sergey Burunov, Vasiliy Dakhnenko, Aleksey Elistratov. A poor Potter finds an old magic Flint, which brings the Potter money, but at the same time makes him cruel. The evil Queen, in order to take possession of the artifact, decides to deal with the Potter, but his faithful friend the restless and resourceful girl Ogonyok rushes to the rescue, confronts the evil and tries to disenchant the Flint.

title: Accidental Luxuriance of the Translucent Watery Rebus
synopsis: Directed by Dalibor Baric. With Rakan Rushaidat, Ana Vilenica, Frano Maskovic, Niksa Marinovic. Martin is on the run because he tried to fight the system. Sara is a conceptual artist. Together they join a revolutionary commune in the countryside, with the police on their trail.

title: Kiddyzuzaa
synopsis: Directed by Melissa Czaja. With Eva Yacobi, Scarlett Archer, Naina Bhatia, Lilibet Biutanaseva.

title: A Dream is a Life Lived and Lost
synopsis: Directed by Eli Hayes. With Natalie Brancaccio, Susie Brancaccio, Eli Hayes. Filmed and edited over a five year period of time, and shot across several states from the Midwest to the Northeast to the South, Hayes' film is an experimental documentary in the form of a dreamscape.

title: Adrift Under Light
synopsis: Directed by Caleb C. Lorentz. With Joe Sterrey, Kaitlin Moews, Ben Friedman, Joseph Masson. A young man is haunted by an entity that resembles an old man, while his wife mysteriously falls ill in the midst of his fragmented reality of lost memories and regrets.

title: Chi hu shu sheng
synopsis: Directed by Haolin Song, Liqi Yi. With Li-Nong Chen, Xian Li, Hani Kyzy, Chao Jiang. Fox spirit Bai gets a quest for immortality in human world where he befriends the innocent scholar Wang. They ally to fight mythic creatures and evil spirits on their journey. Yet, to finish Bai's quest, he must sacrifice Wang after all.

title: Queen Kobra
synopsis: Directed by Matt Spease. With Alivea Disney, Johnny Sanchez, Ashley Brewer, Graham Vowell. This film follows a couple and their altercations with snake creatures, who they inadvertently kill the male one - which makes the female plot a course of revenge on them and their friends.

title: Death Note
synopsis: Directed by Adam Wingard. With Nat Wolff, LaKeith Stanfield, Margaret Qualley, Shea Whigham. A high school student named Light Turner discovers a mysterious notebook that has the power to kill anyone whose name is written within its pages, and launches a secret crusade to rid the world of criminals.

title: Book of Laughter
synopsis: Directed by Xiaoqiang Chen, Guotao Hou. With Yuan Qiao, Kai Song, Di Jin, Zhikun Dou.

title: Paramapatham
synopsis: Directed by Thanesh Perrabu, Perrabu Viknesh. With Thanesh Perrabu, Viknes Perrabu, K.S. Maniam, Dr. Ganteeben. The fantasy game board adventure story of 4 friends and the how the game is start affect their daily lives.

title: L'amore ai tempi del Covid
synopsis: Directed by Brando Improta. With Brando Improta, Adele Vitale, Roberto Ormanni, Alessandra Barile.

title: Nephilim
synopsis: Directed by Danny Wilson. With John Savage, Noah Blake, Yuval David, Gulshan Grover. NEPHILIM begins with the first signs of warfare evolving between good and evil. Set in modern times, two archangels, an atypical priest, an ex-homicide detective and a resurrected spirit form an unlikely alliance to unite against an insurgence of fallen angels and the termination of free will. It is written that the final battle is destined when the seeds for the race of Nephilim were planted by Beshwa, the first fallen angel to mate with humans during the ancient days on earth. Now, Father Markus must lead the battle against Azazel, a fallen angel who plans to create a new race of Nephilim. If born, the new race will prevail over all mortals and wreak unmitigated havoc and unstoppable evil. Indeed, with the birth of the Nephilim, a final battle between good and evil is set to begin.

title: All Through the Night
synopsis: Directed by Farzad Motamen. With Amir Jafari, Elnaz Shakerdoost, Azadeh Samadi, Mehdi Soltani. One night, Mahta, a 24-year-old medical student decides to pay a visit to Alphaville Café. She has heard that Allphaville is the right spot to find Davoud Moradi, a filmmaker. She wants to figure out what happened between her sister and Moradi, that has caused her sister to fall asleep for over two months - On her way there, Mahta encounters a taxi driver who is accompanied by a young girl that has been beaten up. Regardless of all his problems, the driver decides to find the person who is responsible for doing this to her passenger.

title: Gagarine
synopsis: Directed by Fanny Liatard, Jérémy Trouilh. With Alseni Bathily, Lyna Khoudri, Jamil McCraven, Finnegan Oldfield. Yuri fights to save his home town - which he shares with his namesake, Yuri Gagarin - from demolition.

title: Hollywood Salutes Israel
synopsis: Directed by Tal Yaari. With Mayim Bialik, Billy Crystal, Eric Dickerson, Kelsey Grammer.

title: 1979 Big Bang of the Present
synopsis: Большой взрыв сегодня

title: A Frenchman
synopsis: Directed by Andrey Smirnov. With Anton Rival, Evguenya Obraztsova, Evgeniy Tkachuk, Aleksandr Baluev. In 1957, a French student Pierre Duran arrives in Moscow for an internship at Moscow State University. Here he meets the Bolshoi Theater ballerina Kira Galkina and photographer Valera Uspensky. Thanks to these acquaintances, Pierre is immersed in the cultural life of Moscow, not only official, but also underground. For a year, Pierre has lived in Moscow for a lifetime, completely unlike everything he knew. But internship and acquaintance with different aspects of the life of Soviet people is not Pierre's only goal. He is looking for his father, a white officer Tatishchev, who was arrested in the late 30s.

title: The Anti-Fascist Struggle in the Middle-East
synopsis: Directed by Leonidas Vardaros. With Rigas Axelos. 1941. Just like today, war and hunger triggered waves of refugees; only the path they followed was reversed. From occupied Greece, thousands are forced to cross rough seas and many are lost in their efforts to reach the Turkish coast. The ones that made it settle in camps in Cyprus, Egypt, and Syria. The men don their uniforms and join the Greek Armed Forces in the Middle East. The British intervention marks the beginning of the Greek Civil War.

title: 1964: O Brasil Entre Armas e Livros
synopsis: O Brasil Entre Armas e Livros

title: Flowers Fade Early: Kakopetros, August 28th, 1944
synopsis: Kakopetros, 28 Avgoustou1944

title: We Shall Not Die Now
synopsis: Directed by Ashton Gleckman. With Benjamin Ferencz, Simon Srebnik, Filip Müller, Richard Glazar. A chronicle of the Holocaust, exploring stories of survival, tragedy, hope, and resilience through one of history's darkest chapters.

title: My People, My Country
synopsis: Directed by Kaige Chen, Hu Guan, Hao Ning, Muye Wen, Zheng Xu, Xiaolu Xue, Yibai Zhang. With Bo Huang, Qianyuan Wang, Hao Ou, Bai Qing Xin. An anthology film consist of 7 short stories directed by several different directors, which are based on 7 moments since the founding of People's Republic of China.

Directed by Rodrigo Reyes. With Eduardo San Juan. Upon the 500-year anniversary of the Spanish Conquest, a ghostly Conquistador arrives in modern Mexico. As he journeys toward the capital city, he remembers events from his past while encountering the testimonies of real people, the survivors of contemporary violence. History and the present begin to merge, giving nightmarish reflection on the enduring legacy of colonialism in our world today.

title: The 11th Green
synopsis: Directed by Christopher Munch. With Campbell Scott, Agnes Bruckner, George Gerdes, Leith M. Burke. A respected journalist uncovers the truth behind the mythology of President Eisenhower's long-alleged involvement in extraterrestrial events.

title: Migranti 1950
synopsis: Directed by Enzo Acri. With Lorenzo Crea, Marianna Pepe, Noemi Belfiore, Enzo Lucarelli.

title: Ratne price sa Kosara
synopsis: Directed by Sladjana Zaric. With Nenad Jezdic.

title: Direct to Video: Straight to Video Horror of the 90s
synopsis: Straight to Video Horror of the 90s

title: Different Roads To Heaven
synopsis: Directed by Clinton Toughill. With Michael Barsness, Brian Beavers, Randy Berg, Jacob Bloomstrand. Different Roads To Heaven asks the question, out of the different denominations of Christianity, what separates them and what brings them together?

title: Khorfakkan
synopsis: Directed by Ben Mole, Maurice Sweeney. With Rashid Assaf, Qays Sheikh Najib, Ahmed Al Jasmi, Khalifa Albahri. In the beginning of 1500's, during the Portuguese conquests on Indian Ocean, Red Sea, and Arabian Gulf, a village on the edge of sea revolts against the Portuguese rule and conquer after years of oppression, In pursuit of freedom.

title: State Funeral
synopsis: Directed by Sergey Loznitsa. With Iosif Stalin, Nikita Khrushchev, Lavrenti Beria, Vyacheslav Molotov. The enigma of the personality cult is revealed in the grand spectacle of Joseph Stalin's funeral.

title: Manor House
synopsis: Directed by Cristi Puiu. With Agathe Bosch, Ugo Broussot, Frédéric Schulz-Richard, Diana Sakalauskaité. A landowner, a politician, a countess, a General and his wife gather in a spacious manor house and discuss death, war, progress and morality. As time passes by, the discussion becomes more serious and heated.

title: Tropical Abyss
synopsis: Directed by Paulo Caldas, Barbara Cunha. The anguish of an artist on the day of the presidential elections in Brazil in 2018.

title: Libertines
synopsis: Directed by Lionel Baillemont. With Rui Ferreira, Marina Delmonde, Jérémie Hamon, William Beaux d'Albenas.

title: Memoria de la Sangre
synopsis: Directed by Marcelo Charras. With Miguel Avila, Xavier De Mahieu, José Luis Gonzalez, Antonio Las Heras. Documentary film that tracks down the traces of Jacques de Mahieu, a Nazi refugee who lived in Argentina. He was a scientist, obsessed to prove that the civilizations of America are of Aryan origin.

title: memORIA
synopsis: Directed by Giorgos Iatrou. With Kostas Panagiotou.

title: Shadow Country
synopsis: Directed by Bohdan Sláma. With Magdaléna Borová, Csongor Kassai, Stanislav Majer, Robert Miklus. How to reconcile with killings committed by your own neighbors? How to face growing evil that nobody stands against? What can human will overcome and what is the value of humility and hope?

title: Buganda Royal Music Revival
synopsis: Directed by Basile Koechlin, Jules Louis. Whereas the music of the kingdom of Buganda (Uganda) is on the verge of oblivion, some remaining royal musicians are brought together to sound their instruments once again.

title: Story of the Men Who Wanted to Burn New York
synopsis: Directed by Giorgio Carella. The story of the "Decima Mas", an Italian commando frogman unit of the Regia Marina (Italian Royal Navy) created during the Fascist regime.

title: Home Front
synopsis: Directed by Lucas Belvaux. With Gérard Depardieu, Catherine Frot, Jean-Pierre Darroussin, Yoann Zimmer. In a village where everyone knows everyone, four veterans of the Algerian War are haunted by their past.

title: The City of Las Vegas: The Early Years
synopsis: The Early Years

title: The 47 Ronin in Debt
synopsis: Directed by Yoshihiro Nakamura. With Yoshiyoshi Arakawa, Yûdai Chiba, Gaku Hamada, Keisuke Horibe. Following a nefarious plot by Kozukenosuke Kira Takuminokami Asano Tono is ordered to take the blade and commit suicide. he has loyal foot soldiers however. Kuranosuke is one. He vows vengeance and is ready to wield his sword. to enact his revenge he needs funds and turns to an accountant in the fiefdom. Together they hatch a plan. It is time to put the plan into motion.

title: Gross Century
synopsis: Directed by Adam Cuttler. Not your traditional narrative, Gross Century takes viewers on a cinematic walk through the 20th century. The film stars 100 fictional films and takes place chronologically over 100 years, beginning with 1900 and ending in 1999.

title: La casa dei bambini
synopsis: Directed by Francesca Muci. Immediately after the war, the brigade of Jewish engineers of the British army, Solel Boneh, managed to bring to safety hundreds of children who had escaped the terror of the extermination camps. For three years, from 1945 to 1948, a small Lombard town named Selvino, became their home. Orphans of their respective families of origin, lost in that tragedy, the "children of Selvino" slowly managed to find moments of serenity and resumed a normal life. Between 1946 and 1949, most of the "children of Selvino" were boarded on the motorboat Rondine Enzo Sereni. Almost everyone is welcomed in Eretz Israel, in the kibbutz Tze'elim and Hanita. Today, they live there together as a big family, replicating their happy Selvino model.

title: Love Boat: Taiwan
synopsis: Taiwan

title: Efunsetan Aniwura
synopsis: Directed by Joshua Ojo, Funmi Holder. With Clarion Chukwura-Abiola, Alex Usifo Omiagbo. The story of the most powerful and wealthiest Yoruba woman. She dealt in slave trading and ammunition in the 17th Century. She was an advocate for equal rights among men and women until she lost her only child and became depressed and vicious which led to the killing of her slaves.

title: Il capitano dei ghiacci
synopsis: Directed by Matteo Raffaelli. Lieutenant Colonel Bepi Magrin, great alpinist and military expert of mountain areas, has collected a very uncomfortable testimony and over twenty years, on spring, comes back on glacier looking for rests of Captain Berni. This year occur one hundred years from his death so a special shipment is arranged.

title: Bulli e pupe
synopsis: Directed by Steve della Casa, Chiara Ronchini. With Rocco Tedeschi. After journeying through the Italy of the "musicarelli" from the 1960s with Nessuno mi può giudicare, Della Casa turns his attention to post-WWII archives. The result is an X-ray of a different country

title: The Soviet Garden
synopsis: Directed by Dragos Turea. A filmmaker from Moldova tries to discover the truth about Soviet experiments in atomic gardening.

title: Zero!
synopsis: Directed by Nidhal Chatta. With Hichem Rostom, Yassine Ben Yahia. A father and his son leave in quest of Zero, a most weird figure. Indeed, Zero fascinates as much as it worries and disturbs.

title: Warsaw: A City Divided
synopsis: A City Divided

title: Suba Theraniyo
synopsis: Directed by Sumith Kumara. With Ruwangi Rathnayake, Roshan Ranawana, Sriyantha Mendis, Dilhani Ekanayake. Life of prominent Buddhist nun Subha, who delivered thirty four Therigathas. The film will be released in celebration of 1562 Sambuddha Jayanthi which marks the 1562th year since the Enlightenment of Lord Buddha.

title: Catonsville: Music City Maryland
synopsis: Music City Maryland

title: Boss: The Black Experience in Business
synopsis: The Black Experience in Business

title: Swimming Out Till the Sea Turns Blue
synopsis: Directed by Zhangke Jia. With Huifang Duan, Liang Hong, Pingwa Jia, Zhangke Jia. Filmmaker Jia Zhangke chronicles his local literature festival in Shanxi, China which includes a multi-generational roster of the country's most esteemed writers.

title: Neither Hero Nor Traitor
synopsis: Directed by Nicolás Savignone. With Juan Grandinetti, Inés Estévez, Agustín Daulte, Gastón Cocchiarale. Buenos Aires, 1982. 19-year-old Matías dreams of studying music far from the Dictatorship, but his environment wants him to 'grow up'. Will desertion be his first adult decision?

title: Is Brexit Definitely Going To Happen?
synopsis: With Ece Özlem Atikcan, Jessica Elgot.

title: Rebirth of the Elwha
synopsis: Directed by Shelly Solomon, Kent Cornwell. A Story of Ancient Values and Modern Stewardship This film chronicles the truly progressive salmon habitat restoration work undertaken by the Lower Elwha Klallam Tribe, of the Pacific Northwest. Scientists from many disciplines, working together with the tribal river restoration crew spent two decades preparing the Elwha River for eventual dam removals. This truly visionary effort has resulted in the greatest number of Engineered Logjams ever installed in a watershed and, together with the dam removals begun in 2011, represents the largest restoration project for salmon recovery ever attempted. More importantly, this is a story of the Klallam People taking into their own hands the future health of their river, the salmon that depend on it, and the survival of their culture.

title: Ya No Basta con Marchar
synopsis: Directed by Hernan Saavedra. With Sergio Gilavert, Paulina Gonzalez, Cristian Inostroza, Ignacia Moraga. Chile, 2011, the conflict for Chilean education explodes. The protest doesn't revolve around violence, it's a creative revolution leading the social struggle. This is the story of the people who dared to paint, film, dance, act, and motivate to redefine forever the Chilean protest.

title: Dasdhunga Chapter 2
synopsis: Directed by Kumar Bhattarai. With Divya Dev, Saugat Malla, Surakshya Panta, Dayahang Rai. Dasdhunga chapter 2 is Nepali Movie based on real events of the mysterious death of Leader of CPN-UML Madan Bhandari . Dasdhunga chapter 2 reopen the case with some shocking twists and political conspiracies.

title: 3D Cung Tam Ke
synopsis: Directed by Xuan Trang. With Tuan Dung, Van Hong, Xuan Nghi, Minh Nhí.

title: Broadway Treasures
synopsis: Directed by Haeyong Moon. With Wally Shidler, Bob Baker, Joseph Musil, Jan Westman. A love letter to the historic theaters of Los Angeles. Explore a historic theater near you. Treasure what remains of the past.

title: The King's Letters
synopsis: Directed by Jo Chul-Hyun. With Song Kang-ho, Park Hae-il, Mi-seon Jeon, Choi Deok-moon. A historical film about King Sejong who risked everything of his to invent the Hunminjungeum (Korean Script) for his people and the people who weren't recorded in history.

title: Salonika: A City with Amnesia
synopsis: A City with Amnesia

title: Icon
synopsis: Directed by Nenad Ilic. The history, purpose, and use of icons in the Orthodox Church.

title: Secrets in the Sky: The Untold Story of Skunk Works
synopsis: The Untold Story of Skunk Works

title: The 24th
synopsis: Directed by Kevin Willmott. With Trai Byers, Bashir Salahuddin, Aja Naomi King, Mo McRae. It is the story of the all-black Twenty-Fourth United States Infantry Regiment, and the Houston Riot of 1917.

title: 7 Years: Journalism Without Journalists
synopsis: Directed by Jin-Hyuk Kim. With Il-Song Hwang, Deok-soo Hyeon, Dae-Gyoon Jeong, Young-Ha Jeong. A total of 17 journalists have been fired since 2008, the beginning of Lee Myung-Bak's presidential term. They fought against the companies that they worked for succumbing to power and are now frustrated at reality where censorship of the press by authority has now become a norm. Can they continue their activities as journalists?

title: Run As One
synopsis: Directed by Alex Fynn. The inspiring history of how an ultra-marathon, that started in 1970 with 26 white male runners, now brings more than 25 000 South Africans together each year.

title: Jazavac Pred Sudom: With the Badger on Trial
synopsis: With the Badger on Trial

title: The Bravest Escort Group
synopsis: Directed by Mengxi Tao. With Yongli Che, Shaohuang Fan, Xing Yu. During the reign of the Kangxi Emperor, when Wu Sangui died, the senior general Ma Bao begins to seek protection to escort Chen Yuanyuan and his grandson to live in seclusion. Qingping Escort Agency, the No. 1 Escort Agency, takes the heavy responsibility by accident. In the end, they make a narrow escape after going through bloody battles with various forces.

title: Kina Ma? 2019
synopsis: Directed by Tamang Sangraam. With Moktan Jayanti, Thapa Mahesh, Limbu Prashant, Limbu Dikshant.

title: Sanctuary
synopsis: Directed by Kaye Harrison. With Khaled, Léon van Schie. Khaled fought against the "beast" of terror when working as an interpreter for the Coalition Forces in Iraq. Born Iraqi but raised in the Netherlands he believes in Western ideals of freedom like any Dutchman. But Khaled couldn't escape the legacy of violence and spends the next 10 years travelling across 4 continents in search of safety. In the age of terror, Khaled is someone to be feared and is treated inhumanely. In 2015 he documents his quest to return home. Will he find sanctuary and have the life he always deserved or will he finally crack and become the "beast" they all fear him to be?

title: Enchained
synopsis: Directed by Moges Tafesse. With Zerihun Mulatu, Yemesrach Girma, Tesfaye Yimam, Firehiwot Kelkilew. Ethiopia, 1916

title: Inventing the Future
synopsis: Directed by Isiah Medina. With Erik Berg, Kelley Dong, Dahyeon Eunice Hwang, Avery Medina. A lightning fast montage plays against a reading of a text calling for a futuristic economy , with automation eliminating unnecessary work and a universal basic income helping to reinvent new forms of the self and of society.

title: Baharestan House of Nation
synopsis: Directed by Babak Behdad. With Shahram Derakhshan. It is about the historical and social geography of Baherestan region (Iranian Parliament) in Tehran.

title: Behead the King
synopsis: Directed by Jae-soo Kim. With Yoon Kang, Yeon-Jung Kang, Ro-sa Kim, Joo-Hwang Kim. Seongjong who history remembers, earns a reputation for appreciating the motto 'making the people feel comfortable and putting political affairs right'. He is known as the king who led his country in the most peaceful and steady way during the Joseon times. However, was Seongjong really a wise king? Enthroned by Queen Jeong-hee, Queen In-soo, Han Myeong-hoi and his supporters, the 13-year-old king made 73 of his supporters his retainers! Numerous noblemen were happy that he became king. However, some of his people had to cry blood because he became the king. Seongjong, the puppet who dreamt of a reign of peace, wishes to behead the king who dominates the people!

title: The Red Ghost
synopsis: Directed by Andrey Bogatyrev. With Aleksey Shevchenkov, Vladimir Gostyukhin, Yuriy Borisov, Polina Chernyshova. December 30, 1941. In Vyazma ('Vyazemsky cauldron') there is a small group of Soviet soldiers, who are trying to reach their own comrades after having escaped a Nazi encirclement. In the movie they are suddenly caught in an unequal battle with a special unit of the Wehrmacht. None of these brave people was born a hero but they became heroes. And were helped in their battle by the Red Ghost. The myth of the red ghost of the movie is about a lone hero who picks off Nazi soldiers one by one. He seems to be able to vanish almost magically into the forests and even to come back from the dead.

title: Santo Domingo
synopsis: Directed by José Enrique Pintor. With Sebastian Kahuna, Hector Then, Uxio Lis, Víc Gómez. The story of the foundation of the first city in the Americas.

title: The Battle: Roar to Victory
synopsis: Directed by Shin-yeon Won. With Hae-Jin Yoo, Ryu Jun-Yeol, Woo-jin Jo, Kazuki Kitamura. Over a 4 day period, a fierce battle takes place between Korean independence militias and imperialist Japanese forces in Manchuria, China. The militia includes a master swordsman and an expert marksman.

title: Between Pain and Amen
synopsis: Directed by Toma Enache. With Vali Popescu, Constantin Cotimanis, Kira Hagi, Ana Parvu. A young composer and double bass virtuoso, who returns to Romania after studying in Vienna, is arrested by the political police soon after getting engaged and taken to the Pitesti prison, where a brainwashing and torture-based experiment is under way. The horrible communist experiment, copied after the Soviet model, is headed by the much-feared Ciumau. The composer survives unimaginable torture due to his strong religious belief and composes Ode to God. His music will eventually save his fiancee, Lia.

title: On Broadway
synopsis: Directed by Oren Jacoby. With Emanuel Azenberg, Alec Baldwin, Christine Baranski, Sidney Baumgarten. An all-star cast tells the inside story of the Broadway theater, and how it came back from the brink thanks to innovative work, a new attention to inclusion and a sometimes uneasy balance between art and commerce. Legends of the stage and screen, including Helen Mirren, Christine Baranski, August Wilson, James Corden, Alec Baldwin, John Lithgow, Viola Davis, Hugh Jackman and Ian McKellen, take us behind the scenes of Broadway's most groundbreaking and beloved shows, from "A Chorus Line" to "Hamilton." Iconic performances by Lin Manuel Miranda, Patti Lupone, Bernadette Peters, James Earl Jones and Mandy Patinkin lead the way on a hurly burly ride through Times Square, once again the main street of American show business in ON BROADWAY, directed by Academy-Award nominee Oren Jacoby.

title: Viking Warrior Women
synopsis: Directed by David Bartlett, Sebastian Peiter. With Moa Stefansdotter, Stina Edström, Dennis Bengtsson, Bjarne Dahl. Drama led documentary follows the life of Signe, an orphaned Chief's daughter, who driven by revenge becomes an explorer and trader in the lands of the Rus Vikings.

title: This Earth of Mankind
synopsis: Directed by Hanung Bramantyo. With Iqbaal Dhiafakhri Ramadhan, Mawar Eva de Jongh, Sha Ine Febriyanti, Giorgino Abraham. A native Javanese boy and a mixed-Dutch girl fall in love during the early 20th-century colonial turbulence in Dutch East Indies (now Indonesia).

title: The Fugitive
synopsis: Directed by Richard Oh. With Adipati Dolken, Ayushita, Ernest Samudera, Khiva Iskak. Six months after PETA's failure to fight Nippon, Hardo returns to his village in Blora. His presence is smelled by Nippon, tracked and pursued. In a chase one day and night before the proclamation of independence, a drama of struggle is revealed. The betrayal of Hardo's fiance's father is juxtaposed with the betrayal of his best friend Karmin; the resistance of Dipo and Kartiman juxtaposed with Hardo's resistance; the cruelty of the war and the ego of the invaders, a shidokan of Nippon juxtaposed with the deterioration of war victims of Hardo and Ningsih's father.

title: Shattered Waves
synopsis: Directed by Habib Mestiri. With Ahmed Hafiane, Fatma Nasser, Ivana Pantaleo, Atef Ben Hassine. Hassouna, an officer in the french army, is committed to the cause of independence of his country. In disregard of the risks, he transmits information to the independence activists' networks. Once he discovered a list of Tunisian betrayers, he faces rejection and persecution.

title: A Tree Remembers
synopsis: Directed by Kostas Follas. With Tasos Raptis. This is the story of Lidice, levelled and - literally - eradicated by the Nazis in retaliation for the assassination of Reinhard Heydrich in Prague. However, despite the heavy death toll it paid, the Czech village not only was not erased from the map but constitutes a symbol in the fight against Fascism.

title: The Future Cries Beneath Our Soil
synopsis: Directed by Thu Hang Pham. The intangible yet haunting consequence of the Vietnam-American war is sculpted in the relationship of love and hatred among men living in a village right at the boundary between North and South Vietnam.

title: Boy Soldiers: The Secret War in Okinawa
synopsis: The Secret War in Okinawa

title: America's Founders Friends of the Deaf
synopsis: Directed by Gary Brooks. With Conrad Baer, Thomas Baldridge, Luke Campbell, Paul Christie. A visual narrative of how Thomas Hopkins Gallaudet, with the help of Laurent Clerc and Dr. Mason Cogswell, established schools in America to provide an education for deaf children.

title: Seeds of Hope: The Andrew Jackson Foster Story
synopsis: The Andrew Jackson Foster Story

title: The Feather the Agatha Tiegel Hanson Story
synopsis: Directed by Gary Brooks. With Adyson Acton, Adam Anderson, Shali M. Anousheh, Conrad Baer. Agatha Tiegel became the first deaf woman to graduate from Gallaudet College's four year program with a Bachelor of Arts. Her valedictorian speech argued for the recognition of the Intellect of Women, a cause she advocated throughout her career.

title: To stari
synopsis: With Nikos Giannopoulos, Menelaos Haralambidis, Nikos Kourmoulis, Vasilis Manousakis.

title: Another Paradise
synopsis: Directed by Olivier Magis. With Sabrina Jean, Serge Aristide, Thomas Docherty, Alan Duncan. Fifty years ago, the entire Creole population of the Chagos Islands was expelled by the British authorities. This secret operation took place to facilitate the leasing of the main island, Diego Garcia, to the US government so that it could build one of its largest and most secretive military bases overseas. As the military lease is about to expire, Chagossian exiles are attempting to recover their home in the middle of the Indian Ocean from Great Britain. The charismatic woman leading their fight in the UK is Sabrina Jean. Through unrelenting activism, including the exile community's improbable participation in the World Football Cup for Stateless People, she strives to keep the flame of hope alive in her community with one single goal

title: De zomer van '69
synopsis: Directed by Robin Vandenbergh. " A documentary about the most epic 24 hours of the last century

title: Homme Fatale
synopsis: Directed by Da-Jung Nam. With Jun-Ho Lee, Jung So-Min, Gwi-hwa Choi, Jisu Choi. Cute lover boy Heo Saek becomes Joseon's first male gisaeng and a flower-like woman named Hae Won who thinks ahead of her time, search for true love together.

title: Je ne vous oublierai jamais
synopsis: Directed by Pascal Kané. With Rudi Rosenberg, Fanny Valette, Pierre Arditi, Hannelore Elsner. Marseille, 1941. Despite the war, young Levilé still hopes to save his mother and sisters in Poland and organize their departure for Argentina.

title: Decline
synopsis: Directed by Mark Penney. With George W. Bush, Barack Obama, Donald Trump, Joe Biden. A stylized montage of various news stories showing the decline of the west.

title: Labyrinth of Cinema
synopsis: Directed by Nobuhiko Ôbayashi. With Tadanobu Asano, Takuro Atsuki, Mickey Curtis, Tokio Emoto. The story centers on a group of young people who travel back in time when they are in a movie theater just before closing time. They witness deaths during the closing days of Japan's feudal times and on the battlefront in China before they are sent to Hiroshima just before the Aug. 6, 1945, atomic bombing of the city.

title: Endless Night
synopsis: Directed by Eloy Enciso. With Misha Bies Golas, Verónica Quintela, Manuel Pumares, Suso Meilán. Anxo is a man that returns to his home village in the Galician countryside in Franco-era Spain after the war.

title: Woodstock: 3 Days That Changed Everything
synopsis: 3 Days That Changed Everything

title: The Trial of the Chicago 7
synopsis: Directed by Aaron Sorkin. With Eddie Redmayne, Alex Sharp, Sacha Baron Cohen, Jeremy Strong. The story of 7 people on trial stemming from various charges surrounding the uprising at the 1968 Democratic National Convention in Chicago, Illinois.

title: Safe Corridor
synopsis: Directed by Dito Tsintsadze. With Goga Pipinashvili, Dato Bakhtadze, Tamar Abshilava, Mariam Jibladze. A story of the film is based on real events that occurred during the Russian military intervention in Georgia in 2008. Shindisi is a name of the place where Russian occupation forces sieged Georgian military after peace corridor was promised, this is when ordinary villagers took risks to save wounded Georgian soldiers.

title: La Mora
synopsis: Directed by Mohamed Ismail. With Erramdani Abdilah, Mohamed Assou, Tirma Ayerbe, Chakib Boulaiche. After her mother, Maria, passes away, Rosa, a young Spanish woman, discovers the secret of her biological roots in one of her mother's old letters. The letter recounts how Maria fell in love with Rosa's father, Choaib, who was one of the many young Moroccan soldiers (known as the Regulares) forced to fight alongside General Francisco Franco's troops in the Spanish Civil War. Rosa journeys to Morocco to meet her paternal family and discovers the reasons for her father's death.

title: Fatteshikast
synopsis: Directed by Digpal Lanjekar. With Mrinal Kulkarni, Chinmay Mandlekar, Harish Dudhade, Ajay Purkar. Fatteshikast is a Marathi movie starring Chinmay Mandlekar, Mrinal Kulkarni, Annup Sonii, Ankit Mohan, Mrunmayee Deshpande, Nikhil Raut and Sameer Dharmadhikari in prominent roles. It is a drama directed by Digpal Lanjekar.

title: The First Swallows
synopsis: Directed by Le Nguyen Bao.

title: Desert One
synopsis: Directed by Barbara Kopple. With James Q. Roberts, John Limbert, Gerald Rafshoon, Jimmy Carter. Using new archival sources and unprecedented access, master documentarian Barbara Kopple reveals the story behind one of the most daring rescues in modern US history

title: Dear Comrades!

With holidays starting, Carlos plunges into a carefree August, wandering around with his friends and falling in love for the first time. Little does he know about the country's uncertain future, until one by one, neighbors and friends leave in search of a better life, friendships break apart and families split up. In this hot summer, the world of Carlos will turn upside down.

The narration of the film goes on sometimes by evocations, sometimes by pointing out historically important phases in the political, social and cultural life of the city. A city which rapidly went out the reconstruction phase and became a national guide in the creation of an economic development model based on small and medium enterprises, on distribution and production foods consortia, on building mutual companies and local banks. On the other side, Bologna put fore-front social services in the field of elderly persons cares, of family and children sustains, with a great efficiency in the health care and in the public green safeguard. Bologna was the ex-partisans's and anti-fascist's invention of a possible city

But is the virus really of natural origin? Or was it engineered to provide the next generation with a fresh start (and the State with an easily controlled population)? Quarantine, resistance, riots - Slowly but surely, the old man starts questioning the authenticity of his own memories, while growing increasingly conscious of another truth. One of them is the legendary Abulkhair Shaibani, who usurped power in the White Horde. The two legitimate heirs to the throne, Kerei and Zhanibek, call the part of the nomadic tribes to leave the hard ruler. After migrating from the far west of Desht-i-Kipchak to Mogolistan in Zhetysu, they revive their ancient shanyrak Ak Orda, the Kazakh Khanate. The first khan elected a direct descendant of Jochi and Urus Khan, Sultan Kerey. Here it is, the promised land when you can live peacefully and freely. But the enemies are trying to strangle the fragile Kazakh khanate even in the cradle and bloody battles, severe trials, the bitterness of losses and the joy of victories await them.

title: Santikhiri Sonata
synopsis: Directed by Thunska Pansittivorakul. With Somchai Muso, Phasakorn Pemie, Kitjakarn Saedu, Saijeaw Somdee. This hybrid film was shot in an area called Santikhiri, which means 'the Hill of Peace', the name granted by the Kingdom of Thailand in 1978 in order to create a new image for this land. Located in the northernmost part of the country, the are is now a significant tourist destination due to its mix of cultures between Thai and Chinese, despite a CIA report in 1971 that the area was one of the biggest centers of heroin production in Southeast Asia. However, after General Prem's government came to power in the 80s, everything - drugs, communism, corruption, human trafficking, and stateless persons - in this area was entirely suppressed to foster order and peace. But, in reality, can this place be as peaceful as its new name? Since that time, what has been its continued impact up to this very day and beyond? These are the questions that the film poses. Director's note This film is a Sonata in three movements, indicating the present, past, and future. Forty years ago, when I was a kid, the TV was filled with propaganda, instilling in people's minds that the military government protected the country from different threats, while simultaneously emphasizing political violence in foreign countries

The establishment of the Helicopter Attack (LIGHT) Squadron THREE Seawolves would mark an unprecedented chapter in Naval Aviation. Approximately 2,556 men; Maintainers, Pilots, Personnel and Gunners VOLUNTEERED for duty. With hand-me-down Huey's and the spirit of ingenuity, courage and resolve, the Seawolves would become the most decorated Squadron in Naval Aviation History and of the Vietnam War. 50 years later - this is their story.

title: Of Rails & Sails
synopsis:
Directed by Joseph E Daniel. With Johnny Day, Jim Horning. Of Rails & Sails is a one-hour docudrama about the extraordinary life and times of Arthur Curtis James, a relatively unknown railroad baron, prominent and intrepid yachtsman, generous philanthropist, avant garde socialite and secret philanderer, who was one of the ten richest men in America in the 1920s and 30s, owning one-seventh of all the railroad track in the United States. Unlike his contemporaries - Vanderbilt, Morgan, Rockefeller - Arthur Curtiss James is not a household name. Arthur was a private man who did business quietly, efficiently, and smartly. His far-reaching, enormous philanthropic activities were done without fanfare, often anonymously. Yet he is an exemplar of privileged life during the Golden Age. He was the last great railroad developer, building the final and most complete transcontinental railroad system in America. He was also an extraordinary yachtsman who owned and sailed three of the great, legendary yachts of the time - over a quarter of a million lifetime nautical miles!

His main residence was Beacon Hill House, a 33-acre estate in Newport, Rhode Island, but he owned expansive mansions in Manhattan and Tarrytown, New York, and in Coconut Grove, Florida. By all accounts he was a likable, reasonable gentleman of good humor. He was a patron of art and culture, and a generous benefactor to those in need. He was adventurous and fun loving - perhaps a little too fun loving, as whispered rumors of his infidelity and womanizing were not uncommon amongst the employees living on his estate. One such insinuation cost a close relative her inheritance. Drawing on the remarkable likeness of actor James Horning as Arthur, and Johnny Day as his friend Peter (and the film's narrator), Of Rails & Sails tells the story of this remarkable man, who died in 1941 but whose footprint still looms large today.
