title: Darkness
synopsis: Directed by Emanuela Rossi. With Valerio Binasco, Denise Tantucci, Gaia Bocci, Rebecca Caria. It's the story of Stella, a young girl living with her father and two little sisters in an isolated house with bolted windows. Because of a solar explosion occurred years before, the man is the only one able to get out of the house. But his version of the truth seems to hide a huge lie.

title: Gone with the Light
synopsis: Directed by Runnian Dong. With Bo Huang, Luodan Wang, Zhuo Tan, Bai-Ke. 'Gone With The Light' is a 2019 Chinese sci-fi thriller, revolves around a group of people that disappear after a mysterious light falls upon the city, leaving the survivors to try and unravel the mystery.

title: Annabellum: The Curse of Salem
synopsis: The Curse of Salem

title: Inland
synopsis: Directed by Jon Blåhed. With Irma von Platen, Eva Melander, Albin Grenholm, Ann Petrén. A young woman from Stockholm moves to her boyfriend's hometown in northern Sweden, but the relationship quickly ends. She finds a job and stays, for reasons she doesn't even understand herself. How do you become part of something new?

title: Sherlock Holmes: Bound to the Dark
synopsis: Bound to the Dark

title: In Paradox
synopsis: Directed by Hamad AlSarraf. With Faisal Al-Ameeri, Jafra Younes, Samer Ismail, Jaber Jokhadar. While being relentlessly attacked, a Man seeks to uncover a mystery and stop the unknown memories that are controlling him, only to learn the difference between reality and illusions.

title: The Black Bay Sequence
synopsis: Directed by Elina Brotherus. A study with the camera placed at a consistent vantage point, of the water and sky, with the horizon as constant back drop. Due to the consistent framing of the image we notice how the weather impacts on the scene. At times the water is tranquil, a flat and reflective surface like a mirror, whilst at other points it is turbulent and becomes unwelcoming and wild.

title: La donna dello smartphone
synopsis: Directed by Fabio del Greco. With Mariagrazia Casagrande, Chiara Pavoni, Silvana Porreca, Hanad Sheik. An old and sick man finds a smartphone

title: The Lost Women of NXIVM
synopsis: With Keith Raniere, Michelle Wong, Roger Stone, Frank Parlato. This feature documentary will explore what happened to four women who were members of NXIVM who either vanished or died in mysterious circumstances.

title: Evidey
synopsis: Directed by K.K. Rajeev. With Shebin Benson, Asha Sharath, Prem Prakash, Manoj K. Jayan. Evidey unveils the mystery of a man missing through the story of a woman and her family in an intense search.

title: Operation Nakshatra
synopsis: Directed by Madhusudhana K.R.. With Niranjan Wadayarr, Aditi Prabhudeva, Yagna Shetty, Likhit Surya. Operation Nakshatra is a Kannada movie starring Aditi Prabhudeva and Niranjan Wadeyarr in prominent roles. It is a drama directed by Madhusudhana KR.

title: My Girlfriend Is a Serial Killer
synopsis: Directed by Kayoko Asakura. With Yôsuke Sugino, Haruka Fukuhara, Noriko Eguchi, Manami Enosawa. Etsuro is a loner who does not leave his place. He is isolated, has no friends and suffers emotionally after failing to gain acceptance into college. He attempts suicide, but is even a failure at that. He happens to see the girl next door and she tickles his fancy. The problem is she is a killer - no not a killer babe, a killer period. Nonetheless, he is cool with it and they begin dating. Is he safe or does she have plans for him as well?

title: Dushman
synopsis: Directed by Rajeev Kumar. With Surinder Bhardwaj, Devanshu, Nagesh Dhawan, Soumya Joshi. A non-linear narrative on honor killing .

title: American Detective
synopsis: Directed by Anish Saripalli. With Shadye Alvarado, Paul Berney, Hadley Boyd, Camari Brown.

title: KAYA: The Mystery Unfolds
synopsis: The Mystery Unfolds

title: A Febre
synopsis: Directed by Maya Da-Rin. With Regis Myrupu, Rosa Peixoto, Johnatan Sodré, Edmildo Vaz Pimentel. Justino, a 45-year-old Desana native, is a security guard at the Manaus harbor. As his daughter prepares to study medicine in Brasilia, Justino is taken over by a mysterious fever.

title: Now You See Me... - Part 2
synopsis: Directed by Nicolás de Jesús. With Alexis Adrián, Nicolás de Jesús, Mariel Landeros, Wendy Brito. Kelevra continues being the main attraction in Kesselring's fair, and making stronger their partnership, as well, the relation between him and Lindsey. Meanwhile, Bordem and Gretchen start planing something to finish the glory of Kelevra.

title: Soul
synopsis: Directed by Emir Ezwan. With Farah Ahmad, Mhia Farhana, Harith Haziq, June Lojong. Set in the past, in which a family gets a visit from a strange little girl with a frightening prediction.

title: Influence
synopsis: Directed by Trey Haley. With Roger Guenveur Smith, Deborah Cox, Kellita Smith, Drew Sidora. NY Times Best Selling Author Carl Weber introduces us to the Hudsons, a family of African-American lawyers lead by famed attorney Bradley Hudson. They are handed the task to defend Grammy Award Winning singer Savannah who has been charged with the murder of her husband Kyle Kirby.

title: A Genealogy of History of Insanity
synopsis: Directed by Anoush Masoudi. With Elnaz Khamenehpur, Anoush Masoudi. A young girl is invited to an unknown feast. Later she figures out, it is not a feast but a court for an insane girl.

title: Into the Void
synopsis: Directed by Jordan Cantello. With Ioan Sebastian Tirlui, Molly Dyson, Bill McNaughton, Cory Hawkes. An apocalypse survivor defies the colony to seek help for a sick ex-lover, encountering an outside world of desperate humans and ravenous zombies while being forced to confront a past that haunts him.

title: Shattered Lives
synopsis: Directed by Madeleine Fichera. With Nicholas Acord, Elliot Anderson, Gabe Auer, Genevieve Auer. An idyllic setting in the woods is the perfect spot for a family reunion, but when long-buried secrets emerge, things will never be the same.

title: Long Time Ago
synopsis: Directed by Cihan Saglam. With Onur Dikmen, Serdar Orçin, Nihan Okutucu, Reha Özcan. Two brothers unexpectedly find themselves in the middle of a murder, uncovering the secrets of their family.

title: The Queen of Black Magic
synopsis: Directed by Kimo Stamboel. With Ario Bayu, Hannah Al Rashid, Adhisty Zara, Muzakki Ramdhan. Revisiting the orphanage where they grew up, three men and their families discover a horrific supernatural presence lingering in their former home.

title: Sacrilege
synopsis: Directed by David Creed. With Tamaryn Payne, Emily Wyatt, Sian Abrahams, Naomi Willow. Four lifelong friends head to a remote lodge for a weekend of fun. What begins as an idyllic retreat quickly descends into a fight for their lives when a local Pagan cult offer them up to their Goddess as a sacrifice for the Solstice.

title: Iberion
synopsis: Directed by Nico Wilcox Cano. With Joan Castillo Faraco, Kevin Hidalgo López, Guillermo Llorca Andreu, Nuria Rodrigo Ortiz. Jack finds a book and things start happening. Some days are good, others are bad.

title: Barot House
synopsis: Directed by Bugs Bhargava Krishna. With Amit Sadh, Manjari Fadnnis, Aaryan Menghji, Kishaa Arora. A series of inexplicable and gruesome killings tear the Barot family apart and destroy the close relationship between father and son. Who could be behind this mindless slaughter? When the truth is discovered, it throws the family into further turmoil. But is the truth really the truth or games of a troubled mind?

title: Bardo
synopsis: Directed by Agvaantseren Enkhtaivan. Algaa is a street cleaner in modern-day Ulaanbaatar, the capital city of Mongolia. His life is turned upside down when the death of Erdentsetseg, a young mother, results in her spirit haunting him. In some schools of Tibetan Buddhism, Bardo, is the state of existence intermediate between two lives on earth. BARDO is a modern and contemporary Mongolian film produced by Idugan Entertainment and made to convey a message of spiritual awareness.

title: Hell House LLC III: Lake of Fire
synopsis: Озеро огня

title: Landfall (1734-1987-2018)
synopsis: Directed by Wahab Iqbal, Thomas Watchorn. With Hayley-Marie Axe, Emma McDonald, Jodyanne Richardson, Duncan Hess. A land surveyor is sent to work on Romney Marsh, where her predecessor went missing months before. The new surveyor's strange experiences may either hold the key to the mystery, or simply deepen the frontier marshland's enigmas.

title: Hubie Halloween
synopsis: Directed by Steven Brill. With Adam Sandler, Kevin James, Julie Bowen, Ray Liotta. Despite his devotion to his hometown of Salem (and its Halloween celebration), Hubie Dubois is a figure of mockery for kids and adults alike. But this year, something is going bump in the night, and it's up to Hubie to save Halloween.

title: Blink
synopsis: Directed by Deeptanshu Sinha. With Heath Bhatt, Mark Mecwan, Harnam Singh Sandhu. Larry, an editor at 24/7 News finds himself in a confusing situation as he unable to keep track of the present timeline. Fluctuating constantly between the past, present and the future, Larry finds out that his blink is the root cause of the fluctuation.

title: Anveshanam
synopsis: Directed by Prasobh Vijayan. With Jayasurya, Shruti Ramachandran, Vijay Babu, Leona Lishoy. Aravind is informed that something unexpected has happened to his family and has to reach the hospital immediately. What awaits him comes as a shock as he is soon sucked into a miasma of questions that he has to fight to find the answers.

title: Lampor: The Flying Coffin
synopsis: Keranda Terbang

title: Castle Freak
synopsis: Directed by Tate Steinsiek. With Clair Catherine, Kika Magalhães, Jake Horowitz, Emily Sweet. An Albanian castle with bloodthirsty creatures is inherited by a young woman.

title: Afflatus
synopsis: Directed by Peter Kovacs. After losing everything beyond time, mankind seek to find inspiration in nature, in the void and in life itself, while struggling with dreams of future existence.

title: Game Over
synopsis: Directed by Gary Bell. With Josh Hartley, Ken Harris, Courtney Jennings, Tommy Lee Thomas. A war vet with severe PTSD is threatened by a online video gamer crew for being too good at beating them. He finds out about a personal connection to him that makes him snap.

title: Held
synopsis: Directed by Travis Cluff, Chris Lofing. With Jill Awbrey, Bart Johnson, Travis Cluff, Zack Gold. A couple's ailing marriage is put to the test when they are held hostage in an isolated vacation rental by an unseen Voice that commands their every move.

title: The First Aliens
synopsis: Directed by John Michael Ferrera. With Ryan Barry, Jonah Feintuck, John Michael Ferrera, Rene Gauthier. This documentary film brings up many questions and openly thinks about the existence of aliens. There's various interviews and perspectives on aliens throughout the film.

title: The Key
synopsis: Directed by Ayman el Refaie. With Ayman el Refaie. The curiosity of a young couple interested in black magic leads them to visiting an ancient temple during a trip to Eastern Europe. The temple was famous for being cursed and cursing anyone who visits it no matter where they go. Being a big mistake that they got themselves into this, they opened the gate to a dark world of evil; and they are facing their unknown destiny wherever they go.

title: The Oak Room
synopsis: Directed by Cody Calahan. With RJ Mitte, Peter Outerbridge, Ari Millen, Nicholas Campbell. During a raging snowstorm, a drifter returns home to the blue-collar bar located in the remote Canadian town where he was born. When he offers to settle an old debt with a grizzled bartender by telling him a story, the night's events quickly spin into a dark tale of mistaken identities, double-crosses and shocking violence.

title: A Night of Horror: Nightmare Radio
synopsis: Directed by Oliver Park, Jason Bognacki, A.J. Briones, Joshua Long, Sergio Morcillo, Adam O'Brien, Luciano Onetti, Nicolás Onetti, Pablo Pastor, Matthew Richards. With Patricia Arizmendi, Adrián Barriopedro, Claudia Beattie, Louisa Bland. Rod, radio DJ, hosts a popular horror-themed show packed with tales of terror for eager listeners. When he receives alarming calls from a horrified child things start to feel off.

title: Blood Cell
synopsis: Directed by Daniel Sowter. With Lucy-Jane Quinlan, David Cotter, Nicci Brighten, Suzie Houlihan. Barbara adjusts to her new life behind bars, her crimes start to haunt her. Her new cellmate Evelyn is about to start an obsessive and ghostly friendship with her, one that Barbara cannot escape from.

title: The Boy Behind the Door
synopsis: Directed by David Charbonier, Justin Powell. With Lonnie Chavis, Ezra Dewey, Kristin Bauer van Straten, Micah Hauptman. After Bobby and his best friend Kevin are kidnapped and taken to a strange house in the middle of nowhere, Bobby manages to escape. But then he hears Kevin's screams for help and realizes he can't leave his friend behind.

title: Dwitiyo Purush
synopsis: Directed by Srijit Mukherji. With Raima Sen, Parambrata Chattopadhyay, Abir Chatterjee, Anirban Bhattacharya. A crime repeats its pattern after 25 years .Is it the same killer or a new psycho on the streets?

title: Psychosomatika
synopsis: Directed by Jeff Dylan Graham. With Jeff Dylan Graham, Lynn Lowry, Peter Stickles, Debbie Rochon. A severely traumatized man, suffering from a condition which causes him partial blindness and amnesia, seeks answers to the mystery of what really happened to him.

title: Baphomet Mountain
synopsis: Directed by Austin Burnette Mitchell, Jeremy Reyes. With Jeremy Reyes, Austin Burnette Mitchell, Alexa Shackelford, Dc Glaza. A bizarre religious zealot entrusts the help of a hitch-hiking country singer in order to help find his younger brother, who he believes to be kidnapped by a cult that worships Baphomet somewhere in the desert outside Las Vegas, Nevada.

title: The Vigil
synopsis: Directed by Keith Thomas. With Dave Davis, Menashe Lustig, Malky Goldman, Lynn Cohen. A man providing overnight watch to a deceased member of his former Orthodox Jewish community finds himself opposite a malevolent entity, in writer-director Keith Thomas' electrifying feature debut.

title: By Chance
synopsis: Directed by Bassem Christo. With Joseph Aad, Gretta Aoun, Badih Bou Chakra, Pamela El Kik. A successful business man finds his life turn upside down after his suitcase is stolen by a teenager whom he follows into a poor neighborhood. While he embarks on a journey searching for it, he encounters a huge turn of events that will change his life forever.

title: Drown the Clown
synopsis: Directed by Justin Viggiano. With Claritza Brown, Tony Brown, Amy Renée Garcia, Carli Garcia. A newly hired night watch woman's deceased child's clown doll goes missing from her place of work and starts appearing in places it shouldn't weakening her already fragile sanity.

title: IIT Krishnamurthy
synopsis: Directed by Sreevardhan. With Prudhvi Dandamudi, Vinay Varma, Maira Doshi, Anand Bharathi. Krishnamurthy Who Is An IIT BOMBAY Student Comes To Hyderabad And Gets To Know That His Uncle Is Missing. Entire Story Revolves Around The Mysterious Missing Case Of Krishnamurthy's Uncle.

title: Amjeon
synopsis: Directed by Kim Jin-won. With Seo Ye-Ji, Jin Seon-kyu, Bo-ra Kim, Cha Yup. Mi-Jung (Seo Ye-Ji ) is a rookie film director and she has been preparing a horror film for the past 8 years. One day, Mi-Jung hears about a movie which was banned. Mi-Jung wants to know about the film. She begins to search for the movie. Her search takes her to meet Jae-Hyun (Jin Seon-Kyu), who is the director of the film. Jae-Hyun warns Mi-Jung to forget about his film, but she ignores his warning. Mi-Jung's obsession with the movie leads her to bizarre and horrible cases.

title: The Fever (IV)
synopsis: Directed by Jared Wardlaw. With Matthew Loucks, Catherine Moore, Fulton Lee Farrish, Isaac Kirk. A group of friends try to keep their heads straight on New Year's Eve as unexplainable events begin to occur, causing hysteria, paranoia, and distrust between them.

title: Detention
synopsis: Directed by John Hsu. With Gingle Wang, Meng-Po Fu, Jing-Hua Tseng, Cecilia Choi. In 1962 Taiwan during the White Terror martial law period, Fang Ray Shin, a female student at the hillside Greenwood High School is attending counselling with teacher Mr. Chang, and they gradually fall in love. It was a dangerous period where sensitive books were banned and free speech were restricted, but Mr. Chang secretly organised a study group for banned books, together with fellow teacher Miss Yin and male student Wei Chong Ting.

title: Repression
synopsis: Directed by Reza Goran. With Baran Kosari, Sara Bahrami, Roya Afshar, Pardis Ahmadieh. After a long time, three sisters come back to their paternal house. They face a caretaker along with their mother struggling with Alzheimer's. But there is no trace of the father who has disappeared in an early morning. A dead body is found, but none of the sisters are going to identify the body due to the hatred rooted in their hearts. There is a dark secret in the family, but no one intends to talk about it.

title: Eat Him by His Own Light
synopsis: Directed by Ruby Fuller, Marjorie Riner. With Kevin Lucero Less. A somnambulist attracts the unwanted attention of an envious funambulist.

title: Knorx
synopsis: Directed by Jacques Wissky. With Herold Vomeer, Thorsten Merten, Hazy Van der Lubbe, Gerdy Zint. Somewhere behind Beelitz something is cooking up. It's where the white gold is buried. Attention. If you drill too deep, you might come across things that are better left in the dark. Sven used to be with the BND. Today he works as a freelancer and accepts orders via the Darknet. His latest job takes him back to a small town, behind Beelitz. Professionally he was already in this place years ago. After an initial triumphal march, former BND agent Sven soon finds his limits and ends up in the cross hairs of an organization whose plans he has crossed. Between chicken innards and fish leftovers a war for supremacy in the crystal business begins. Greed, betrayal and resentment continue to drive the spiral of violence. When Sven is caught up in his past, a race against time begins. He could do it. If there were not Harro and Gert.

title: Kathanam
synopsis: Directed by Rajesh Nadendla. With Adabala, Arjun, Ashok, Srinivas Avasarala. Anu (Anasuya Kasaba) an aspiring director develops a script on a producer's request. Twist in the tale arises when the murders scripted in the story start happening in real life. The parallel story is crux of Kathanam.

title: The Enlightenment: Sons of the Silent Age
synopsis: Sons of the Silent Age

title: The Beach House
synopsis: Directed by Jeffrey A. Brown. With Liana Liberato, Noah Le Gros, Jake Weber, Maryann Nagel. A romantic getaway for two troubled college sweethearts turns into a struggle for survival when unexpected guests - and the surrounding environment - exhibit signs of a mysterious infection.

title: The Small Hand (Ghost Story)
synopsis: Directed by Justin Molotnikov. With Douglas Henshall, Louise Lombard, Adrian Rawlins, Cal MacAninch. An antique book dealer finds himself haunted by the ghost of a young boy, he decides to investigate the strange occurrences within his life.

title: Yancey McCord: The Killer That Arizona Forgot About
synopsis: The Killer That Arizona Forgot About

title: The Betrayer: Resolution
synopsis: Resolution

title: Home Sweet Home
synopsis: Directed by Tran Huu Tan. With Trinh Tai, Minh Hy, Duy Phuong, Bich Hang Tran. Thien Tam, a young but weak boy comes home after his treatment at the hospital to find that his cousin-sister, Hai Lam, has gone away from home. Tam decides to go look for her but then finds something horrible behind her missing.

title: The Doll Comes Home
synopsis: Directed by Mary Haflinger. With Schafie Weiss, Benny Damm, Marley von Hund, Pinguetta. While Marley and his friends are partying, his new doll gets possessed by a demonic presence. Without knowing what to do, they have to fight against the evil thing. But will everybody make it out alive?

title: Conjuror: The Crimes of Jason Mewes
synopsis: The Crimes of Jason Mewes

title: The Painting
synopsis: Directed by Tuz Sarkany Bogee, Valeri Lilov. With Lili Avramova, Tuz Sarkany Bogee, Yoan Bozhikov, Rubin Cara. When a group of kids get lost in Hell, they try to find the way back by investigating a series of haunted paintings they discover along the way.

title: Icelander
synopsis: Directed by Nils Oliveto. With Nils Oliveto. The mysterious journey of filmmaker Nils Oliveto's quest to find his missing father in Iceland after finding out about his dad's enigmatic double-life through various investigative interviews.

title: Objects in Mirror Are Closer Than They Appear
synopsis: Directed by Nils Oliveto. With Nils Oliveto. An out-of-work actor sees his life falling apart after being left at the altar by his fiancée on his wedding day.

title: Lost Angel
synopsis: Directed by Simon Drake. With Sascha Harman, Fintan Shevlin, Duncan Henderson, Maggie Clune.

title: One Night in Tehran
synopsis: Directed by Farhad Najafi. With Mina Vahid, Tirdad Kiaei, Mohammad Mehdi Hosseini, Babak Ghaderi. New York, Tokyo and Mumbai all have their own nightlife. And so does Tehran; a nocturnal underground world unlike any other - A girl looking for her happiness within the chaos of this swallowing world gets into a night cab, unaware of how her life is going to change forever.

title: Tell Me Who I Am
synopsis: Directed by Ed Perkins. With Andrew Caley, Alex Lewis, Marcus Lewis, Evan Milton. After losing his memory in an accident, Alex Lewis trusts his twin brother, Marcus, to tell him about his past only to discover that he's hiding a dark secret about their childhood.

title: Howling Village
synopsis: Directed by Takashi Shimizu. With Ayaka Miyoshi, Ryôta Bandô, Tsuyoshi Furukawa, Renji Ishibashi. After her brother goes missing, a young psychologist visits an infamous haunted and cursed location known as 'Howling Village' to investigate his disappearance and uncover her family's dark history.

title: Ashes Over Sun
synopsis: Directed by Bogomil Kalinov. With Julian Vergov, Silvia Petkova, Alexander Kalinov, Anastasia Lyutova. Dr. Stefanov is in the middle of a huge media scandal due to a patient's death. Antonia is a young journalist who bravely embarks on a journey to uncover what truly happened.

title: 13 avtobus
synopsis: Directed by Oleksandr Bezruchko. With Nataliia Mazur, Lina Pidcercovna, Kseniya Vertinskaya, Aleksey Vertinskiy. A conversation with a woman waiting at the stop of a non-existent bus #13 becomes a turning point in the life of all her interlocutors. People "wake up" from the power of stereotypes and false beliefs, and act in accordance with their new understanding. Their stories show that moral choice is not always legal, but legitimate - not always moral. This builds one of the main ideas of the film

title: Ceremony of Innocence
synopsis: Directed by Elliot Masters. With Mason Amdor, Ben Blackstone, Brendan Goodwin, Billy House. Peter and his friends find a snuff film at their High School Principal's house.

title: Parallel Forest
synopsis: Directed by Lei Zheng. With Xiaoran Tang, Xiaodong Zhao, Weisen Liu, Deng Fangyi. A mother who lost her child happened to find the entrance to the parallel world after being chased by another self in the forest.

title: Sweet River
synopsis: Directed by Justin McMillan. With Jack Ellis, Lisa Kay, Jeremy Waters, Chris Haywood. Hana's search for her son's body leads her to the sleepy town of Billing, where her investigations uncover more than she expected and threaten to expose the town's secrets - secrets that both the living and the dead will fight to protect.

title: I Don't Believe You Died
synopsis: Directed by Wimbadi J.P., Zeeman Artaboga. With Raditya Evandra, Kinaryosih, Farah Maudina, Deddy Sutomo. Bagong became a hit-and-run victim. Kinasih, his auntie who cares for him since childhood because her mother is depressed due to the man who impregnated her, ran away. Her paralyzed mother doesn't know that her child has died. Fantar, Bagong's friend, who doesn't believe that Bagong is dead, considered crazy by his classmates. That belief makes Bagong's soul return to the real world. These two friends of different nature go again as usual. Bagong is again caring for his mother Furthermore, these two friends are looking for the impactor.

title: The Lake of Ghosts
synopsis: Directed by Reza Jafari Jozani. With Ideh Abutalebi, Maryam Akbari, Pegah Hamidifar, Nazanin Alidoust. Portraying a philosophical and mystery fiction, 'Ghost Lake' is inspired by the poems of Rumi and follows the story of some young investigators who travel to the Ghost Forest in north of Iran.

title: It Ends with a Knife
synopsis: Directed by Kevin Lucero Less. With Kevin Lucero Less. A lonely man is convinced he must protect his solitary life.

title: Perplexion
synopsis: Directed by Colin Heinle. With Colin Heinle, Cali June, Wesley Welden, Adam S. Ford. A man reflects on the events that led up to his downfall thru the setting of a RV.

title: Razor Blade
synopsis: Directed by Michael Mandell. With Tony Devon, Charmar Jeter, Michael Anthony Belisaro, Shawn Miranda.

title: Chernobyl: Zona otchuzhdeniya 3
synopsis: Зона отчуждения 3

title: Chernobyl: Zona otchuzhdeniya 2
synopsis: Зона отчуждения 2

title: The Jealous Mirror on My Wall
synopsis: Directed by Frank Sabatini. With Brian Anthony Wilson, Thomas Walton, Adam Ratcliffe, Myke Michaels.

title: Mirror on My Wall
synopsis: Directed by Frank Sabatini. With Brian Anthony Wilson, Thomas Walton, Adam Ratcliffe, Myke Michaels.

title: Halloween Night Fever
synopsis: Directed by Niclas Schmidt. With Louise von Hoff, Laura Schmidt, Sue-Ann Moestchen, Annika Liie. It's the night before Halloween. Four long-term best friends want to spend it together before college-life begins. But a serial killer escaped from the sanatorium and wants vengeance! Soon the relaxed mood turns into big fear, and dead bodies are seen everywhere.

title: Aatakkuntu Lekkakkilla
synopsis: Directed by Ram .J. Chandra. With Kaddipudi Chandru, Achyuth Kumar, Mayuri Kyatari, Rashmi. This is a story of two couples, one of which is the newly-married Purushotham (Sanchari Vijay) and Meghana (Mayuri), both of whom are orphans, who lead a happy life, until a certain tragedy strikes and Purushotham's behaviour changes drastically. The other is also newly-wed couple, Sangeetha and Shyam, who happen to be in a haunted house and are then troubled by supernatural elements. As it turns out, Purushotham suffers from a paranoid schizophrenia and suspects that his wife has an extra-marital affair with the spirit of her former boyfriend, which, in turn, leaves their family in tatters.

title: Vera de Verdad
synopsis: Directed by Beniamino Catena. With Marta Gastini, Manuela Martelli, Anita Caprioli, Marcelo Alonso. The life of an Italian 9 year old girl and of a Chilean man working in the Atakama desert bond together in a unpredictable and mysterious way known to time and space only.

title: For the Sake of Vicious
synopsis: Directed by Gabriel Carrer, Reese Eveneshen. With Lora Burke, Nick Smyth, Colin Paradine, James Fler. An overworked nurse returns home to find a maniac hiding out with a bruised and beaten hostage. When an unexpected wave of violent intruders descend upon her home, it becomes a fight for survival.

title: Ghost of Lake Opeongo
synopsis: Directed by Sterling Johnston. With Desmond Bradshaw, Aiden Johnston, Lars Panchuk, Nolan Panchuk.

title: Murkal Estate
synopsis: With Prakruthy, Praveen. A group of students travel to Murkal Estate for a short holiday where they unknowingly disturb a devious spirit and struggle to escape.

title: Kingslayer
synopsis: Directed by Vahid Amirkhani. With Mahnaz Afshar, Hadi Hejazifar, Majid Salehi, Farid Sajjadi Hosseini. In a hotel in the middle of snow and blizzard a murder happens. Meanwhile all the residents of the hotel are accused of murder and have to prove that they are innocent.

title: Night Things
synopsis: Directed by Ward Crockett. With Kathryn Gould, Joey Nicole Thomas, Ari Azimi, Haidyn Harvey. Two women find themselves trapped between life and death by a dark and mysterious machine. As they search for an escape, they must battle the Lures, a race of creatures determined to imprison them until nightfall, when the vicious Night Things come out to feed upon those who stray from the light. Soon they discover that their only escape is the evil machine itself. But using it may require the ultimate sacrifice...

title: Walk with Me
synopsis: Directed by Ryon Lee. With Michelle Wai, Alex Tak-Shun Lam, Yuwu Qi, Anna Ng. With no one to talk to, a woman turns to a strange doll for help dealing with her bullies, when they end up dead, she fears the doll is responsible.

title: Miss Butcher
synopsis: Directed by Gil-woong Ji. With Im Sung Eon, Son Jong-hak, Kim Min Joon, Hye-ryeong Koo. Soon-Ae (Seo-Young) opens a butcher's shop. The butcher's shop is popular due to its flavorful meat. Most of the store's customers are male. Meanwhile, man's body is found at a hotel near the butcher's shop. The man was brutally murdered. Soon, more murders are found with similarities to the first murder. One day, Detective Kim (Kim Min-Jun) stops by the butcher's shop and meets Soon-Ae. Since then, Detective Kim keeps a watch on Soon-Ae.

title: A Witness Out of the Blue
synopsis: Directed by Chi-Keung Fung. With Louis Koo, Louis Cheung, Jessica Hester Hsuan, Philip Keung. Three months after a robbery in a jewelry store, one of the criminals is found murdered while the mastermind criminal Sean Wong becomes the prime suspect after the loot gets disappeared, and the only witness is a talking parrot.

title: Wednesday Disappears
synopsis: Directed by Kohei Yoshino. With Tomoya Nakamura. He looks like a normal and well-adjusted young man who is no different than anyone else. There is not a reason for anyone to suspect this man is different or suffers from an internal rage. he, however, harbours no less than seven different personalities. title: The Motorcycle Man
synopsis:
Directed by Shivrajj J.D. Khuman. With Yukti Modi, Naresh Poonia, Amit Galani, Surbhi Bhatti. It starts with Ashna, Ramji, Amit, they come to farewell party of Sir.

Ashna Loves Sir a lot, but Sir is not getting convinced by Ashna.

They reached at Sir's home; they started to talk about here and there.

Ashna many times tries to convince Sir to be with her and marry her, once Ashna proposed him in-front of everyone, He refused very rudely, so Ashna started to cry and goes inside the bedroom, so everyone around forced Sir to come up with the truth. Sir slowly and somewhat reluctantly, that he is Ashwatthama who has lived for more than 5 thousand years.

Sir begins his tale under the guise of a possible science-fiction film story, but eventually stops speaking in hypothetical and begins answering questions from a first-person perspective. Sir continues his tale, relating how is it possible that he means Ashwatthama can take part at the era of World War 1 and 2.

Ashwatthama also took part in freedom fight of India. In the course of the conversation, each of Sir's colleagues questions his story based on knowledge from his or her own academic specialty.

Sir says that one scientist in 1837 helped him to recover the curse (not completely but partially). The discussion turns to the topic of religion. After this revelation, emotions in the room run high.

Ramji begins crying, he is having Blood pressure condition so he became unconscious, Sir treats him, now Amit demands that Sir end his tale and gives the group a sense of closure by admitting it was all a hoax.

Sir says it was just a lie and he was making a film's script, all people goes and leaves the place....

Again Ashna proposes him, but he again rejects her proposal and leaves for infinity....

To be continued...

Three and its multiples. Archaic, spiritual, transcendent numbers. Three, Six, Nine. Carriers of wisdom that lead us to the heart of theological monotheisms. Three, the Christian Trinity. Six, the points of the Star of David, The Jewish Star. Nine, the face of God in Sufi tradition, according to Islamic culture. Three stories are intertwined in a land, Friuli, in the North-East of Italy, which extends along a triple border. The stories of Irene, a Carnian, Christian girl; Pavel, Ukrainian and Jewish; Mehdi, Iranian and Muslim. Udine. A beautiful city, but one that is perceived as cold and inhospitable by emigrants. Pavel and Mehdi are illegal immigrants, who share an apartment - and concerns about social matters - in the "ghetto" of Via Roma. In love with Pavel, Irene tries to help them, but her surge of solidarity goes perhaps too far, and she regrets it... "Above" them, the incarnation of metaphysical realities that rule the existence of men, three antagonists who raise the total number of characters to six. synopsis: Directed by Gautam Parwar. With Steffi Rebello, Kevin Fernandes. The story follows the experience of a girl living in two different environments of the future, one urban and another rural; where she works and lives respectively.

synopsis: Directed by Dan Trachtenberg. With John Goodman, Mary Elizabeth Winstead, John Gallagher Jr., Douglas M. Griffin. A young woman is held in an underground bunker by a man who insists that a hostile event has left the surface of the Earth uninhabitable.

title: The Vanishing Field
synopsis: Directed by Antero Alli. With Douglas Allen, Sylvi Alli, Hogen Bays, Nita Bryant. Disenchanted with the corruption of society, Jacob joins a monastery where his meditation practice ignites a spontaneous out-of-body experience.

title: The Village of Shadows
synopsis: Directed by Fouad Benhammou. With Christa Théret, Bárbara Goenaga, Cyrille Thouvenin, Ornella Boulé. A group of young people are trapped in an evil village.

title: KEMI
synopsis: Directed by Kizito Samuel Saviour. With Edison Keith Abitegeka, Kiyaga Aisha, Kabagenyi Beatrice, Makubuya Elly. Kemi is forced to let go of her newly born baby after realizing that she could lose it through the struggle but her motherly heart can't let go.

title: Awakn
synopsis: Directed by Eduard Vijulie. With Robin Attinkara, Karlo Beyer, Chris Bucher, Rhea Careddu. During a hypnosis therapy program against insomnia, an ordinary man develops an extraordinary sleepwalking condition.

title: Ashes to Ashes
synopsis: Directed by Daniel Tucker. With Rachel Bellini, Brad Cabral, David Rodriguez, Kira Sedberry. An ex-cop is thrust back into the world that killed her girlfriend when she agrees to take a brokenhearted young man's case.

title: The Skin I Live In
synopsis: Directed by Pedro Almodóvar. With Antonio Banderas, Elena Anaya, Marisa Paredes, Jan Cornet. A brilliant plastic surgeon, haunted by past tragedies, creates a type of synthetic skin that withstands any kind of damage. His guinea pig

title: The Lincoln Lawyer
synopsis: Directed by Brad Furman. With Matthew McConaughey, Marisa Tomei, Ryan Phillippe, William H. Macy. A lawyer defending a wealthy man begins to believe his client is guilty of more than just one crime.

title: Pionien aika
synopsis: Directed by Joona Paavola. With Antero Warha, Roy Fritz, Aarni Ruuhimäki, Ville Viinikainen.

title: Charmed by Darkness
synopsis: Directed by Chris Lang. With Doug Batchelor, Sherry-Lynne Bredy, Amanda Cavanagh, Dondi Griffin. Roger Morneau was a demon worshiper who became a Christian author and prayer warrior. Family and friends testify that the battle with fallen angels is real and that prayer really can change things.

title: Meenak Enta
synopsis: Directed by Nadim Mehanna. With Ali Al-Zein, Nahla Dawood, Jihad El Andari, Saad El-Qadery. Issam is a mysterious grotto-man living in the wilderness, over viewing a rural village with a lot of happenings - For more than twenty years, they call him "the thief of food" as he steals nothing but something to eat, no one dares to confront him, he looks scary with his thick beard but "the Gost" is also friendly and loving, while he rescues inhabitants from all kind of troubles. From the city, Lynn, a beautiful stubborn girl, was raised by Yasmine, her dying very sick grandmother, who's only wish was to be buried in the same village next to her old house - Lynn not only buried Yasmine, but also wanted to understand all the mysteries of that very complicated village - Bechara, a special-forces commando officer, also lives in the village, will be dragged to many military operations loaded with action and thrill, and ends up facing a very aggressive gang of smugglers. Ramzi, the village governor (with a Syrian accent as his family was severally harmed during the war and was pushed to move and raise the kids in Damascus) will be the catalyst of most conflicts The events are diversified and fast, revolving around turning points now taking place but related to acts occurred two decades ago in this village, mysteries.

title: Sputnik
synopsis: Directed by Egor Abramenko. With Oksana Akinshina, Fedor Bondarchuk, Pyotr Fyodorov, Anton Vasilev. The lone survivor of an enigmatic spaceship incident hasn't returned home alone - hiding inside his body is a dangerous creature.

title: Takut ke Tak
synopsis: Directed by Muzzamer Rahman. With Nabil Aqil, Han Zalini, Ika Nabella, Arwind Kumar. Lamenting the overuse of cliches in horror movies, Abbas and his friends, Yang Guo, Linda, Amir and Sivar, are determined to make the best horror movie ever for their graduation project. The group of film students then pick a haunted house for their shooting location. But during the shooting, they begin feeling like they are in an actual horror movie as strange things begin happening. They enter a room after hearing strange voices and end up stumbling into a strange wardrobe. This group of friends must now figure out a way to escape the haunted house.

title: Right Yaaa Wrong
synopsis: Directed by Neeraj Pathak. With Sunny Deol, Irrfan Khan, Isha Koppikar, Konkona Sen Sharma. A decorated and disabled Police Officer becomes suspect in a double homicide.

title: Party Over
synopsis: Directed by Hilton Lacerda. With Irandhir Santos, Maria Barreira, Ariclenes Barroso, Amanda Beça. The carnival is over. A young French woman was brutally murdered in the city of Recife. Officer Breno returns early from his vacation to investigate the crime, surprising his son with three friends staying at his home.

title: Years of Macau
synopsis: Directed by Max Bessmertny, António Caetano Faria, Emily Chan, Koi Wang Chao, Albert Chu, Tou Kin Hong, Kin Kuan Lam, Ao Ieong Weng Fong, Peeko Wong. With Filipe Baptista Tou, Ricardo Brito, Sai Peng Chan, Choco Chu. Nine short stories set in Macau, between 1999 and 2019.

title: Ruthless
synopsis: Directed by Owen Franklin. With Celi Crossland, Luke Rhodri, Max Dinnen, Taheen Modak. When a students' getaway holiday descends into a bloodbath, a literally fearless young woman races to uncover the sinister truth behind the killings.

title: Death - Do Not Part
synopsis: With Marneen Fields.

title: Tabon
synopsis: Directed by Xian Lim. With Christopher Roxas, Leon Miguel, Benjie Felipe, Lao Rodriguez. A man's belief in reality is tested when suspects are accused of a crime they believe to not have committed.

title: Mastermind
synopsis: Directed by Azita Moguie. With Bahram Radan, Merila Zare'i, Pejman Jamshidi, Hanieh Tavassoli. Iran and Spain are about to lunch a big project in the Hendurabi Island in the south of Iran. Meanwhile many companies are trying to win the rights of this project at it's auction. Engineer Saeed Parsa who has divorced his wife Roya is one of them and others are trying to win the auction too. But in the way to do so many obstacles and difficulties are ahead of all of them.

title: Lapse
synopsis: Directed by Marianne Hansen. With Karolina Dryzner, Sirry Jons, Keith Roenke, Emmett J Scanlan. A woman wakes up one morning alone in the desert with no memory and blood on her hands. Reality and memory collide as she struggles to make sense of events.

title: 5 Adi 7 Angula
synopsis: Directed by Nandalike Nithyananda Prabhu. With Aditi, Chakravarthi Davanagree, Raasik Kumar, Pranaya Murthy. Ajay, Kiran and Shalini, who are best friends. One day Ajay, who is a young entrepreneur, plays a prank but things get out of hand and he gets entangled in it himself. With the police on the hunt for him, will Ajay get out of this mess?

title: Finding Randy
synopsis: Directed by Greg McNichol. With Paul Schragen, Beth Anne, Luke Schragen, Sam Meder. When an old friend's return home is disrupted by his sudden disappearance, what starts as a welcome home film becomes an unsettling search.

title: Monochrome Paradise
synopsis: Directed by Garrett Creighton, Sam Creighton. With Travis Beagley, Garrett Creighton, Raul Flores, Jill Sughrue. When James Dupin decides to quit school to pursue his private detective dreams, he quickly learns there's more to detecting than he's viewed in the media. After learning of his girlfriend Mina's secret involvement in a nearby cult, James becomes suspicious and begins his search for answers. What follows is a mysterious string of events that leads Dupin on an unpredictable and existential path.

title: Ouija
synopsis: Доска Дьявола

title: The Widow
synopsis: Directed by Ivan Minin. With Viktotiya Potemina, Anastasiya Gribova, Margarita Bychkova, Ilya Agapov. In a densely forested area north of St. Petersburg people have been going missing for three decades.The few corpses ever found were naked. On October 14, 2017 a team of volunteers went out into the woods in search of a missing teenager. Soon, all communication with them was lost. Locals believe they were taken by the same dark spirit that took the others. They call it the Limping Widow.

title: Social Distance
synopsis: Directed by B. Luciano Barsuglia. With Vernon Wells, Dawna Lee Heising, Sheri Davis, Rachel Riley. A slow slide into insanity as a group of distance workers discover their work-from-home mandate is part of dark and deceptive conspiracy meant to dwindle the numbers of middle class workers.

title: Anonymous Vol. 1 - The Dreamland Adventures the Mysteries of Atlantis
synopsis: Directed by David Christians. With Lance Caver, David Christians, Tristan David Luciotti. 1.0 - An agent in NASA receives a packet by a new nation created from Hitler's escape; has armed a doomsday device. Agent Schwartz turns to his Russian family as he tries to diffuse the weapon of mass destruction.

title: Cecily and Lydia at the Waypoint
synopsis: Directed by Juliette Strangio. With Calli Ryals, Amber Washington. On a lush, but lonely earth, Cecily walks. Alone in her house, Lydia waits. One balmy afternoon, the two women meet.

title: The Inevitable
synopsis: Directed by Joshua Michael Gennari. With Christopher Hoard, Rebecca May, Bill Read Jr..

title: The Doors Between Us
synopsis: Directed by Max Aguiar. With Waseem Aad, Max Aguiar, Bill Collins, Logan Diemert. Eight complete strangers are tested like never before when they wake up locked inside a mysterious house. With no memory of how or why they are there paranoia takes over, forcing them to make their own decisions on who to trust and how best to escape. A surreal midnight comedy hidden inside the strangest book Stephen King never wrote.

title: Anthony Blake El Sol Es El Cerebro De La Tierra
synopsis: Directed by Julián Génisson. With Julián Génisson. A boomer's reflections on mirrors, money, doors, the sun, the brain and several other paranormal topics.

title: Snatched!
synopsis: Directed by Kirk Bowman. With Danilo Mancinelli, Debbie Day, Rob Ozman, Michael Q. Schmidt. After neutralizing the original curse, Guido, the jewel smuggler who was the only gangster to survive the shoot out in the warehouse, has learned that the spirits of those who were deceased in the gunfight have returned to once again torment the ladies. Guido must know gather himself and figure out who is responsible for the black magic that has brought back the curse.

title: The Ethicist
synopsis: Directed by Jared Goudsmit. With Michele Condon, Matt Earnhart, Matt Gaglio, Saige Galovski. A mysterious ethicist hires a blunt representative to help four troubled teens.

title: The Perfect Man
synopsis: Directed by Alex Del Arco, Paflo, Enrique Camacho. With Alex Del Arco, Susana Teruel, Javier Quintana, Irina López. Sebas, a former police officer, searches for his missing companion, meanwhile, an intriguing new neighbor moves in next to Vicente de León, a peculiar comic artist.

title: Return of the Poker King 2
synopsis: Huang Jin Du Cheng

title: Black Grove
synopsis: Directed by Timothy Nennig. With Tamara A. Alba, Pete Chiboucas, Brenden Cundy, Arjuna Dingman. After the mysterious death of his wife, Leo Stone (Justin R. Warner) becomes obsessed it had something to do with a town called Black Grove and an evil witch cult led by Hereti Black (Rummy Rose). Meanwhile a mystery woman (Evelyn Gail) may be Leo's only hope, as cult master Harold Kaufski (Matt Woodman) breeds sinister plans for both of them.

title: One More Lie
synopsis: With Joe Gaminara, Tamaryn Payne.

title: The Mermaid of Zennor
synopsis: Directed by Celia de Wolff. With Teresa Gallagher, Joe Gaminara, Alice Hoskyns, Nigel Lindsay.

title: The Retreat
synopsis: Directed by Bruce Wemple. With Grant Schumacher, Dylan Grunn, Chris Cimperman, Rick Montgomery Jr.. A man finds himself alone and lost after a horrifying encounter with a monster during a backpacking trip into the Adirondack High Peaks. Now, he must fight for his life, and sanity, as he battles the evil Native American legend, The Wendigo.

title: Kyulyuk Khomus
synopsis: Directed by 'Hiki' Pyotr Struchkov. With Rimma Fyodorova, Dmitriy Khoyutanov, Aelina Kolesova, Yeva Kuzmenko. Sardaana arrives at a village for work as a teacher. She meets a photographer Nyurgun, and he invites her to look at the museum full of spooky items. When Nyurgun is absent, Sardaana falls under the influence of the call of an ancient harp in a locked box. Not realizing what she's doing, Sardaana begins to play on the harp. A vision comes to her, which she doesn't have time to realize.

title: Kathah Vichitrah
synopsis: Directed by Anup Antony. With Harry Correa, Sri Harshavardhan, Anu Poovamma. Sana, a young girl, about to be married to Karan, a businessman. One night, when Sana is home alone, she feels the presence of a supernatural power around her. The story takes a twist when Sana tries to locate the source of the paranormal activity.

title: And thanks to the Rajabi family
synopsis: Directed by Farzad Farahvashi. With Behrooz Baghayi, Ashkan Eshtiyagh, Farzad Farahvashi, Reza Fayyazi. Behrouz Baghaei has decided to review his memoirs at the Rajabi family home. After twenty or so years, he goes to that house and tries to remind his colleagues of that time.

title: We are not well now
synopsis: Directed by Farzad Farahvashi. With Parviz Bahram, Alireza Bashkandi, Kazem HajirAzad, George Petrosi. Since the 2000s, dubbing has declined sharply in Iran. With the advancement of technology, the conditions for dubbing became more difficult, and fledgling speakers were able to expand their activities underground.

title: I am Hassan Azimi
synopsis: Directed by Farzad Farahvashi. With Dariush Asadzade, Hassan Azimi, Gholamhossein Dolatabadi, Majid Jafari. Hassan Azimi, one of the last survivors of Iran's traditional theater, narrates a clear narrative of this kind of drama and the issues surrounding it from the point of view of the audience.

title: Seventh
synopsis: Directed by Micah Mayes. With Gage Clift, Micah Mayes, Nathan Mayes.

title: Two Eyes Staring
synopsis: Directed by Elbert van Strien. With Hadewych Minis, Barry Atsma, Isabelle Stokkel, Charlotte Arnoldy. Moving into her parents' mansion after she inherits it, a woman, her husband and their daughter stumble upon a dark and terrible family secret.

title: Cover the Mirrors
synopsis: Directed by Aaron J. Davis. With Normeka Ageous, Genevieve Alleyne, Patrick Cox, Kerseh Dahn. Aaron, Kimberly, and Malcolm all grew up together from the age of seven years old. Aaron and Kim married, while Malcolm was still a best friend until he got fired from CMS writing firm. Malcolm then became more envious of Aaron's life, having a successful writing career and a beautiful wife. Malcolm goes behind Aaron's back and rapes Kim in front of the Mirrors - but the Mirrors tell all.

title: The Boy with Moving Image
synopsis: Directed by Roufy Nasution. With Hafidz Aulia, Bryancini Galgala, Nithalie Louisza. Vaiyang, a film director, wants to rent a house for making his new movie that owned by a woman named Ning. However, the agreement has the condition that he must accompany Ning until her death prediction is coming tomorrow.

title: Short Time Heroes
synopsis: Directed by Christine Wagner, Roman Gonther. With Thomas Scharff, Francesco Pahlevan, Stephanie Kellner, Hans-Dieter Brückner. It is the year 2025. Under the direction of David Joshua, head of the space agency ISA, Captain Herc Heros and his crew embark on the first faster than light flight of humanity. Any of the previous attempts failed and the crews were lost. During the flight this crew also sleds into an impervious maelstrom of seemingly unexplainable events.

title: The Speed of Thought
synopsis: Directed by Evan Oppenheimer. With Nick Stahl, Mía Maestro, Taryn Manning, Blair Brown. Joshua Lazarus has a special gift -- but will this gift destroy him before he can escape to freedom with his newly found soul mate?

title: Amsteroid
synopsis: Directed by John Higbie. With Mike Ancrile, David Beaulieu, Canton Belanger, Mark Bernstein. Two brothers, one dreamy and starry-eyed, the other earthy and rational, search for their mother in the asteroid city of Amsteroid.

title: El Camino
synopsis: Directed by Fernando Campos, Jaime Jasso. With Gustavo Sánchez Parra, Yam Acevedo. In order to sustain his family, a troubled pilot accepts one last crooked deal to transport a dangerous cargo inside his spaceship.

title: 2177: The San Francisco Love Hacker Crimes
synopsis: The San Francisco Love Hacker Crimes

title: La noche polar
synopsis: Directed by Florencia Romano. With Sol Busnelli, Gonzalo Pastrana, Gael Rossi, Patricia Russo.

title: Ascend
synopsis: Directed by Christian Albrecht, Chris Puterbaugh. With Christian Albrecht, Griffin Barnhart, James Calvin, Bethany Mccurry. In the year 2035 a young teenager, Nick Sels (Chris Puterbaugh) and his friends come across a message on a old computer dating back to the early 2000s. The message they reveal ultimately uncovers a futuristic alien civilization in which the society they live in is on the brink of collapse. Now on the way to inhabit their city and eventually the entire planet; the government and army militia has total control and the group must find answers to the extraterrestrial's terroristic motives.

title: Ascend Chapter II
synopsis: Directed by Christian Albrecht, Chris Puterbaugh. With Christian Albrecht, Griffin Barnhart, James Colvin, Bethany Mccurry.

title: Simply Us
synopsis: Directed by Cire Hensman. With Lila Hart, Brian Larios, Steve Lee, Al Medina. In the future, you can decide how you appear, but then you might have to decide who you really are.

title: The Marked
synopsis: Directed by Laura Duval. With Dari Lynn Griffin, Diana Boylston, Rebecca Collins, Taylor Cornist. In a futuristic dystopian world young women are remote viewers for the government. A remote viewer, on a journey to deliver a family heirloom, must decide whether she will die as a hero or escape to live the life of a regular teenager.

title: Equinox
synopsis: Directed by Zach Cortino. With Van Ferro, Maggie Hall, Chantelly Johnson, Matt Johnson. Conrad Harland is the country's top astronomer in the year 2035, and he alone has access to the most powerful observatory in the world. One night both he and his co-worker Michelle Quinton discover a catastrophic event on the horizon that is sure to bring the end the universe. And with them having the most powerful view into the stars, nobody else will see it coming until it's too late. The two are conflicted as they try to come to terms with the fate of humanity, while also trying to not let the grim truth get out.

title: Not All Who Wander
synopsis: Directed by Simon Phillips. With Simon Phillips.

title: The Halt
synopsis: Directed by Lav Diaz. With Joel Lamangan, Piolo Pascual, Shaina Magdayao, Pinky Amador. Madmen control Manila in 2034 after massive volcanic eruptions have plunged Southeast Asia into darkness.

title: Adam's Package
synopsis: Directed by Andrew Chiaramonte. With Andrew Rogers, Serena Hendrix, Shay Denison, Tim Mollen. Living as an alien model in Hollywood certainly has its ISSUES.

title: Kapsul
synopsis: Directed by Martias Ali. With Mahathir Mohamad, Faizal Hussein, Jue Aziz, Zila Bakarin.

title: Dead Americans
synopsis: Directed by Ken Collins. With Ken Collins, Jay Hewlett, Andrea Forcina, Heidi Caldwell. Consumed by rage after losing his wife on 9/11, Michael Penn (Ken Collins) enlists in the military with an obsession for vengeance on the battlefield. Penn soon becomes entangled in a deadly black project designed to generate the ultimate assassin. Renamed

title: Cyber Bride
synopsis: Directed by Louisa Warren. With Rebecca Finch, Andrew Hollingworth, Claudine-Helene Aumord, Peter Cosgrove. After his wife tragically dies, a desperate widowed husband finds a service online that can bring her back - But not all is as it seems.

title: Existence
synopsis: Directed by David Robert Deranian. With Anya Alexandria, Scott Asmar, Maria F. Blanco, Braden Bullard. John, a promising young professor of science has recently been diagnosed with a fatal disease that gives him at most a year to live. Determined that he will not cease to exist, John experimentally implements his unproven research ideas to embed his consciousness onto the internet as a simulated, or is it real, version of himself. John's wife Sarah, a first year graduate student in Anthropology, fears that John's experiments will at best simply fail, or at worst create an artificial entity that is not her husband. Even as death is closing in on him, John perseveres to create an AI consciousness that resides on the internet. His best friend Tim Sterling who is a recent medical school graduate and neurology resident at the local hospital, helps John to stave off the debilitating effects of the disease for as long as possible to help allow John to push forward with his research. Despite her doubts, Sarah supports John's efforts in a race against death even while struggling with the idea of a metaphysical solution prompted by an old friend of the family Mildred, that death is not the end but rather a pathway to eternity. Throughout, John's father Henry is dogmatically obstinate against his son's efforts that he believes are an abomination by making one's self equal to God.

title: Monster Mayhem
synopsis: With Zuqing Yang, Boniing Yu, Jun Zhang.

title: The Purger
synopsis: Directed by Paul Van Beaumont. With Paul Van Beaumont, Mark Sears, Stevie Alexandria Maxwell, David J Biscoe. A Sci Fi Western.Deputy Westcote reports in to his Ship,But receives information that Marshall Deacon has taken space outlaw Kurtis Karver for his own personal justice.

title: Munnariv
synopsis: Directed by Ashik Kumar Satheesh. With Ajesh Babu, Syju John, Shahid Khair, Anoprabha Lal. A work-from-home Malayali IT Engineer starts hearing the voice of his daughter from the future, trying to help him change the course of the world.

title: All people disappeared forever
synopsis: Directed by Sergey A.. With Sergey A.. The year 2222. All people disappeared. No one human lives at Earth.

title: The Photon Effect
synopsis: Directed by Dan Poole. With Dan Poole, Derek Minter, Brian Razzino, Ariana Almajan. During a freak accident involving an experimental microwave antenna, two tower engineers gain superhuman abilities. While the powers they gain are similiar, the paths they decide to take are not. Derek Powers wants to use his abilities to help others and to uncover the truth behind Randall Communications Incorporated (RCI), the company who designed the antenna. Meanwhile, Jay Powers secretly becomes part of the experiments performed by RCI, whose lead scientist, Tina Viccarini, is a former love interest of Jay. This series of events ultimately leads to the birth of a new superhero and supervillian.

title: Immortal
synopsis: Directed by Fernando Spiner. With Belén Blanco, Analía Couceyro, Daniel Fanego, Diego Velázquez. Ana returns to Buenos Aires to claim her inheritance. She meets her father's close friend Dr. Benedetti, a scientist, where he has discovered a doorway to another dimension which allows Ana to reconvene with the dead.

title: The King of Fighters
synopsis: Directed by Gordon Chan. With Maggie Q, Sean Faris, Will Yun Lee, Ray Park. Live-action feature based on the video game "King of Fighters".

title: Executive Order
synopsis: Directed by Lázaro Ramos, Flávia Lacerda. With Alfred Enoch, Seu Jorge, Taís Araújo, Aldri Anunciação. In a dystopian near future in Brazil, an authoritarian government orders all citizens of African descent to move to Africa - creating chaos, protests, and an underground resistance movement that inspires the nation.

title: Aquatic-X
synopsis: Directed by Tony Wilson. With Davis Aguila, Jeff Criswell, Tom Dubyna, Sumerlyn Haynes. A mission that goes forcefully wrong,soldiers trapped on a alien world.An operation to search for a new planet to save the human race has now turned into an obligation of surviving the unknown.

title: 111 the Force
synopsis: Directed by Boysing Samuel. With Tobias Armand, Dominick Buttner, Phil Cappadora, Smitty Chai. 3 NYPD Detectives defuse tensions between New York Cities 5 boroughs extraterrestrial residents.

title: For the Good of Others
synopsis: Directed by Oskar Santos. With Eduardo Noriega, Belén Rueda, Angie Cepeda, Cristina Plazas. Diego is a doctor who is immune to the pain of others, but after being shot his reality changes.

title: Live Cinema Astronauta Fantasma
synopsis: Directed by Alejo Crisóstomo, Ana María Moreno. With Kattia G. Zúñiga, Ana María Moreno.

title: The Singularity Is Near
synopsis: Directed by Anthony Waller, Toshi Hoo, Raymond Kurzweil. With Pauley Perrette, Raymond Kurzweil, Anthony Robbins, Alan Dershowitz. Computer avatar saves the world from self-replicating microscopic robots.

title: Givers of Death
synopsis: Directed by Addison Henderson. With Addison Henderson, J.J. Alfieri, Jonathan Sterritt, Louis Lombardi. After a virus wipes out a third of the world's population, many of the infected either take their own lives or hire a professional to do it for them. Amidst a city on the brink of collapse, a hit man seeks peace while on the run.

title: Resemblance
synopsis: Directed by Elizabeth Berry. With Jacklyn Daniel, Eric Hanson, Leona Worcester, Garry Nation. Nicole returns home with little memory of her traumatic past, only to discover that what has been erased has not resolved deeper conflicts.

title: Repo Men
synopsis: Directed by Miguel Sapochnik. With Jude Law, Forest Whitaker, Alice Braga, Liev Schreiber. Set in the near future when artificial organs can be bought on credit, it revolves around a man who struggles to make the payments on a heart he has purchased. He must therefore go on the run before said ticker is repossessed.

title: Black Widow
synopsis: Directed by Milos Twilight. With Michelle Claire Moffat.

title: A Dark Path
synopsis: Directed by Nicholas Winter. With Makenna Guyler, Mari Beaseley, Thomasin Lockwood, Jimmy Essex. Two girls in Eastern Europe on their way home from a hen party in a car with no GPS signal headed for a very unusual forest local people will not venture into this forest

title: Queen
synopsis: Directed by Deeptanshu Sinha. With Kashish Bharti, Mark Mecwan, Harnam Singh Sandhu. A queen has to choose sides between her brother and her husband in war whose consequences all already known to her.

title: Custer at Nuremberg
synopsis: Directed by Philippe Mora. Somewhere in the universe General Custer is on trial at Nuremberg for crimes against humanity.

title: AI Amok
synopsis: Directed by Yû Irie. With Sei Ashina, Sumire Ashina, Alice Hirose, Takanori Iwata. Artificial Intelligence has permeated every aspect of planetary life in 2030. Tokyoites experience AI in every aspect of their lives whether medical, finance, transportation or their personal and day-to-day interactions. Many would tell you that AI is indispensable. Yet, as is often the case with technology jumping the gun on ethics and rules AI spins out of control and causes calamity after calamity. The city and the country are in chaos.

title: Don't Speak
synopsis: Directed by Scott Jeffrey. With Stephanie Lodge, Jake Watkins, Ryan Davies, Georgina Jane. Upon arriving at their grandparents farm, a family soon realise the entire town has been taken out by an unknown monster.. And soon, they become its prey..

title: Parallax
synopsis: Directed by Michael Bachochin. With Naomi Prentice, Nelson Ritthaler, Hattie Smith, Ted Gianopulos. A young artist wakes up in a life that she doesn't recognize, spending her time asleep haunted by nightmares of drowning in a black abysmal void. As she begins to uncover the truths of the life that she's found herself in, the gravity of her failing reality weighs heavily on her psychological identity and the reliability of her sanity is called into question.

title: Cyst
synopsis: Directed by Tyler Russell. With Eva Habermann, George Hardy, Greg Sestero, Jason Douglas. In the 1960s a nurse's last day is ruined when a doctor inadvertently creates a cyst monster that terrorizes the office.

title: Hawk Warrior of the Wheelzone
synopsis: Directed by Donald G. Jackson. With Scott Shaw, Joe Estevez, Frank Stallone, Karen Black.

title: Kafka's Supermarket
synopsis: Directed by Aaron Dylan Kearns. With Corey Gupton, Ben Holst, Aaron Dylan Kearns, Allison Maier. Kafka's Supermarket is an experimental surrealist science fiction dystopian horror film that concerns the issues of a current capitalist America, focusing on the alienation and dehumanization of commercialism.

title: Across the 4th Parallel
synopsis: Directed by Vangelis Papadiochos, Tasos Poziadis, Thodoris Skaris, Anty Vens. With Dimitra Chatzistavridi, Georgia Damigou, Alexandros Geranis, Chrysa Gwen Michailidou. Four stories about four young people unknown to each other, who must understand and survive separately in a universe where every choice has no turning point and that, all are dependent and connects their lives and fates even after the end.

title: Perazhagi ISO
synopsis: Directed by C. Vijayan. With Livingston, Shilpa Manjunath, Mahi Parasuraman, Rob Peck. Perazhagi ISO revolves around a 60-year-old granny who turns into a 20 years young beautiful girl after she accidentally falls into the hands of a business organization researching on the process of age reversing.

title: Between Waves
synopsis: Directed by Virginia Abramovich. With Fiona Graham, Luke Robinson, Sebastian Deery, Stacey Bernstein. It's about a woman's pursuit to join her missing lover by crossing into a parallel dimension.

title: Tur
synopsis: Directed by Uldis Cipsts. With Ilva Centere, Karlis Kuskis, Arturs Skrastins, Inara Slucka. A love story that develops in virtual world.

title: The Tree House

synopsis: Directed by Sam Housman. With Sean Cameron Dalton, Ivelisse Housman, Tanner Ingold, Travlyn Pantana.

title: Erratum 2037
synopsis: Directed by Elie Benoit, Emilien Benoit, Johann Benoit. With Teddy Arlot, Elie Benoit, Emilien Benoit, Timothe Beugnet. Leo Fucher, a high school student, accidentally intercepts a message from the future. He is then kidnapped and sent into the future where he has to stop the mad plans of the evil genius Emeric Boldenberg. Whether he wants to or not.

title: Toxic
synopsis: Directed by Ariel Martínez Herrera. With Jazmín Stuart, Agustín Rittano, Victoria Cabada, Sebastián Carbone. In the middle of a mysterious insomnia epidemic that slowly takes on catastrophic dimensions, Laura (39) and Augusto (42) flee the city in their motor-home to get away from the chaos. As they move down the route, the world becomes an increasingly strange and dangerous place. Finally, Laura reveals a story that changes everything. The road is depopulating, the silence grows and it is increasingly difficult to differentiate the reality from the dream.

title: Limitless
synopsis: Directed by Neil Burger. With Bradley Cooper, Robert De Niro, Abbie Cornish, Andrew Howard. A mysterious pill that enables the user to access 100% of his brain's abilities transforms a struggling writer into a financial wizard, but it also puts him in a new world with many dangers.

title: Dust
synopsis: Directed by Drew Maxwell. With Kevin Lucero Less, Leah Rose, R. Michael Gull, Jake Weninger. An Alien virus is unleashed on Earth, mutating millions into carnivorous beasts. Scientist Nick Richards, and a hard nosed team of survivors wage a losing battle against the alien force, desperately trying to restore Human life.

title: Resident Evil: Afterlife
synopsis: Жизнь после смерти

title: The Adventures of Flare
synopsis: Directed by Matias Perez. With Cascade Nerida, Brent Oliver, Adam Oscroft, Christina Nicole Roberts. A human by the name Kyle falls into a liquid and becomes a superhero.

title: A Machine to Live In
synopsis: Directed by Yoni Goldstein, Meredith Zielke. A Machine to Live In is a hybrid documentary linking the cosmic power structures of the state to the mystical architecture of cults and utopian cities in the remote hinterlands of Brazil.

title: Fairy
synopsis: Directed by Anna Melikyan. With Konstantin Khabenskiy, Ingeborga Dapkunaite, Ekaterina Ageeva, Vilen Babichev. The creator of the best virtual reality games is sure that he controls everything in his life. But a chance meeting with a young activist opens his eyes to the fact that the world is much wider and more complex than his ideas.

title: Monster
synopsis: Directed by Clay Moffatt. With Mackenzie Clark, Matt Conklin, Wesley Courtnay, Jordan Dean. A pair of college roommates find a mysterious camera and strange things begin to happen around them. As things start to worsen a scientist claiming to know the truth shows up. However, what he knows is only the tip of the iceberg.

title: Spark Riders
synopsis: Directed by Douglas Neff. With Meggan Anderson, Anne Brashier, Phoenix Carlson, Kristy Chavez. August Haynes invents a way for people to place their soul on the internet. However, her idea is stolen by a power hungry madman and a beautiful but greedy foreign spy.

title: Flu
synopsis: Directed by Micheal Bafaro. With Michael Mitton, Colm Hill, Nathaniel Vossen, Destiny Millns. Drawing inspiration from Rod Serling's landmark series, "The Twilight Zone, "FLU" is a chilling moral tale about a radio talk show host's descent into paranoia and madness amid a deadly global flu pandemic. But the greatest threat of all, doesn't come from outside - it can't be caught from someone on the street - the real pandemic is the one you create for yourself.

title: Moth
synopsis: Directed by Roxanne Gaucherand. With Lou Vaultier, Flavie Pons, Lucienne Gaucherand, André Gaucherand. In the middle of summer 2016, the box tree moth takes over Provence. Accidentally introduced into France, this moth forces inhabitants, virtually forsaken by the authorities and helpless faced with the scale of the phenomenon, to improvise defensive systems to fight the invasion of their houses and businesses as well as the devastation of their lands. In this apocalyptic climate, 18-year-old Lou spends her last summer in the South and discovers her feelings for her childhood friend, Sam. As their relationship gradually develops into a love affair, the urgency and upheaval that she feels echo her environment; an ecosystem subverted by an unexpected invasion. Guided by the voice of Lou, Roxanne Gaucherand's film interweaves sequences of journalistic investigation, documentary reporting, amateur video and coming of age account with brio. Edited like a thriller, Pyrale is a resolutely accomplished and intriguing cinematographic object whose universe constantly shifts between the real and the fantastic.

title: Caller ID: Entity
synopsis: Directed by Eric Zimmerman. With Triton King, Denny Kirkwood, Nathan Bexton, James Duval. A sci-fi conspiracy thriller, based on real phone messages and testimonials from victims of mind control technology.

title: Katatonia
synopsis: Directed by Hamed Eslami. With Amanda Azad, Shahab Hosseini, Mehdi Takloo Karimi, Omid Khakdan.

title: Iron Man 2
synopsis: Directed by Jon Favreau. With Robert Downey Jr., Gwyneth Paltrow, Don Cheadle, Scarlett Johansson. With the world now aware of his identity as Iron Man, Tony Stark must contend with both his declining health and a vengeful mad man with ties to his father's legacy.

title: World's End
synopsis: Directed by Simone Bartesaghi, Philip Kim, Neil Kinsella. With Jonathon Trent, Elizabeth Roberts, Jonno Roberts, Billy Drago. The future of America, when the world runs out of oil.

title: Idol Madness II: Revenge of Raja
synopsis: Revenge of Raja

title: Black Box
synopsis: Directed by Emmanuel Osei-Kuffour. With Mamoudou Athie, Phylicia Rashad, Amanda Christine, Tosin Morohunfola. After losing his wife and his memory in a car accident, a single father undergoes an agonizing experimental treatment that causes him to question who he really is.

title: Hot Tub Time Machine
synopsis: Directed by Steve Pink. With John Cusack, Clark Duke, Craig Robinson, Rob Corddry. A malfunctioning time machine at a ski resort takes a man back to 1986 with his two friends and nephew, where they must relive a fateful night and not change anything to make sure the nephew is born.

title: Manny
synopsis: Directed by Dace Puce. With Sonal Sehgal, Jurijs Djakonovs, Darta Danevica, Marta Grase. Journey of a woman on a writer's retreat, struggling with her identity as a closet homosexual. Her life unfolds through three love interests, one real, one a figment of her imagination and the third virtual - man, woman and AI.

title: The Things We Tell the Ones We Love
synopsis: Directed by Matt Wilkins. With Tim Alexander, Jeff Benson, Marek Brave, Dorothy Breininger. THE THINGS WE TELL THE ONES WE LOVE is an interactive sci-fi thriller about a designer virus that attacks the pre-frontal cortex of select humans, causing damage to executive functions. Those infected enter into a Frenetic Random Activity Period, in which they temporarily lose inhibitions, act on impulse and do dangerous things. The film is set a few years in the future, in Central Freedom Zone 2, an area of the Midwestern United States with no taxes, no public services and no regulations. An aspiring Mixed Martial Artist Billy has become estranged from his wife Sabrina after she contracted the virus, and lives with his mother Mary and 18-month-old daughter. As he is planning to take one last shot at his MMA career, Sabrina suffers an outbreak and attacks the house, obsessed with stealing back her daughter. With the help of his mother and sister Ashley, Billy defends their house from multiple FRAP invasions by Sabrina and her Syncro, Bunny Clown Dude. Unwilling to pay for private police service or the outrageously priced anti-dote, Billy's mother Mary is ready to solve the problem the old-fashioned way. As the story progresses, the audience will make the same tough choices the characters make about patience vs. violence, life vs. death, and how to cope with limited power in a disintegrating society.

title: RoboCop
synopsis: Directed by José Padilha. With Joel Kinnaman, Gary Oldman, Michael Keaton, Abbie Cornish. In 2028 Detroit, when Alex Murphy, a loving husband, father and good cop, is critically injured in the line of duty, the multinational conglomerate OmniCorp sees their chance for a part-man, part-robot police officer.

title: The Awakened
synopsis: Directed by Adrian DeLude, Eric Nichols. With Robert Picardo, Matt Corrigan, Richard Gross, Kara Hamilton. An alien space craft crashes in the deep woods in 1809 and lies undisturbed for two hundred years until a woman takes her surgeon boyfriend to visit her aunt and uncle on their isolated farm , the very day her uncle unearths it. This immediately triggers an emp burst and a response from Dreamland, men in black types , who converge on the farm to recover the UFO.

title: Comisery

title: Hide and Seek

A junior special agent goes rogue with a technological weapon of unimaginable power; but when she is pursued by both her friends and a mysterious assassin, she enters the most dangerous game of her life, whether she's ready or not.

A team of special ops mercenaries is sent on a mission to rescue a kidnapped kid, believed to be held in an abandoned government facility but this simple search and rescue turns into a fight for survival.

The CIA? Or the aliens he left behind?

On the surface, it seems like the perfect neighborhood. Everything you could possibly need is within walking distance. But the pastoral exterior conceals a dark past and an even darker secret. As a group of individuals (each with their own ties and agendas with the town and each other) converge on the enclave, strange things begin to happen. Very strange things. Strange enough to test (and then break) the very fabric of reality itself.

A man wakes up alone in the middle of the desert with a black hood on his head and his hands tied behind his back. At death's door, he is discovered by a woman living alone in the desert and is nursed back to health. Upon regaining consciousness, the man realizes he has amnesia, and has no idea who he is. His only clue, a piece of paper in his pocket with the name "Manny Elder" on it, sends him on a journey to Los Angeles to discover his past. But things and people are not what they seem and clues lead to something bigger and more unusual than the man could have ever imagined.

synopsis: With Markus Johansson, Helene Jönsson, Katla Nelander, Tomas Rydehed.

synopsis: Первый класс

The film tells the story of a cataclysmic event that leaves only 7 remaining people on earth and their desperate struggle to understand the events as they are hunted one by one by a demonic power.

John is a peaceful man living quietly, doing his chores and working with his beloved little dog, Doggo.One day, he wakes up to find out that Aliens have come to visit ,hovering over the city and scooping up hundreds of people.John wonders about helping out especially when his true self pops out in response to the stress he feels seeing the alien mother-ship so brazenly going about its business.

The fate of mankind now rests in the hands of a Broadcast Repairman, a Computer Nerd and the local Sheriff.

title: Holidays on Mars

Blurring the lines between narrative and concert film, virtual and reality, Muse's most theatrical tour to date launches the viewer through a supernatural spectacle, questioning the world around us.

synopsis: Enchanted Forest

When an alien prison ship crash lands and unleashes creature after creature in the California desert, the Prisoners make quick work of the dozen that tries to stop them. Now, the only hope of stopping the aliens rests with a secret Branch of the Government specializing in alien weaponry.

synopsis: How to Build Mazinger Z's Hangar

title: The Watch
synopsis: Directed by Akiva Schaffer. With Ben Stiller, Vince Vaughn, Jonah Hill, Richard Ayoade. Four men who form a neighborhood watch group as a way to get out of their day-to-day family routines find themselves defending the Earth from an alien invasion.

synopsis: Directed by Søren Peter Langkjær Bojsen. With Simon Bennebjerg, Hjalte Birkemose, Peter Christoffersen, Claudia Gregersen. It's 2028. There doesn't seem to be a limit to what can be automated. Activities reserved for humans are dwindling. Societies are marked by a discouragement, a resignation, an autumn. What do we celebrate, what do we raise a flag for? A creature lands in Estonia. He calls himself Rudolph. He travels through Europe to Copenhagen and meets a number of people who are each concerned in their own way with the relationship between man and technology. He himself is on a mission of sorts, looking for something, something he can transmit back to where he came from. But what? And what will he do if he doesn't find it?

title: A Foundling
synopsis: Directed by Carly Lyn. With Cindy Chiu, Tim Chiou, Nora J. Novak, Shelby Bond. Virginia - a young Chinese woman in the old west - rescues her long lost sister, Mattie, from a brothel in Arizona. On their journey home to San Bernardino, they discover the strange, steaming wreckage of an otherworldly craft. Inside the vehicle, Mattie finds a very mysterious baby.

synopsis: The Halloween Summoning
