synopsis: Directed by Ruth Chao.

title: Android Uprising
synopsis: Directed by Andrew Bellware. With Kate Britton, Julia Rae Maldonado, Jared van Heel. After a devastating war against the drones leaves Sergeant Barbara Slade paralyzed, her only chance for survival is to be placed inside an artificial body.

title: Apocalypse of Ice
synopsis: Directed by Maximilian Elfeldt. With Tom Sizemore, Emily Killian, Ramiro Leal, Torrey Richardson. Already in the throes of a viral pandemic, a massive polar vortex threatens to cover nearly all of Earth in ice. When it's discovered the only chance of survival from the cold is a 100-mile temperate zone near the equator, a virologist, with the pandemic's only cure, must reach the safe zone within 24 hours if humanity is to have any hope of survival.

title: Ghost from the Machine
synopsis: Directed by Matt Osterman. With Sasha Andreev, Lynette Biunno, Matthew Feeney, Emily Fradenburgh. After his parents are killed in a car accident, Cody is left dealing with enormous guilt, caring for his younger brother and the persistent thought of how to bring his parents back to life. Cody knows he is not the first person to have this idea or the first to have attempted to carry it through. After several attempts with his electromagnetic device, he becomes the first to breach the wall between the living and the dead But where is the line between life and death? And who actually comes back? What ghosts come out of the machine? "Phasma Ex Machina" is a sci-fi film that combines both heart and mystery with electronic veins and sheet metal.

title: Hataraku Saibo!! Saikyo no Teki, Futatabi. Karada no Naka wa Cho Osawagi!
synopsis: Directed by Hirofumi Ogura. With Shoya Chiba, Natsumi Fujiwara, Kana Hanazawa, Saori Hayami. Alcohol, smoking, and stress - in the body subjected to these irritants, the cells responsible for maintaining life seem to fight a war that never ends. Due to a severe shortage of workers, Red Blood Cell AA2153 has to quickly learn to deliver oxygen and collect carbon dioxide, even in dangerous conditions. Meanwhile, White Blood Cell U-1196 has to do her part by dealing with germs and viruses during life-threatening situations. In the midst of these crises, they have to work together to keep the body healthy, despite not knowing if their sacrifices will be worthwhile. Hataraku Saibou Black takes a different approach by showing the grittier side of the jobs our cells perform.

title: Enthiran
synopsis: Directed by S. Shankar. With Rajinikanth, Aishwarya Rai Bachchan, Danny Denzongpa, Santhanam. A brilliant scientist creates a humanoid robot to protect mankind, but things go awry when human emotions are programmed and inner turmoil causes the robot to switch sides.

title: Popovich: The Return of the Outcast
synopsis: The Return of the Outcast

title: P.O.W. Open Air am Meer
synopsis: With Mike Chaer, Demolition Davies, Philipp Ebner, Fabio Ferrari.

title: Blink of an Eye
synopsis: Directed by Paul Taublieb. With Michael Waltrip, Darrell Waltrip, Richard Petty, Richard Childress. An inside look at 2001's Daytona 500 featuring Michael Waltrip and Dale Earnhardt Jr.

title: Maybe This Year
synopsis: Directed by Kyle Thrash, Jenifer Westphal. Maybe This Year is the story of the Philadelphia Eagles football team and their improbable and incredible Super Bowl winning 2017 season - as seen from the perspective of some of their most die-hard fans.

title: On the Edge
synopsis: Directed by Eduard Bordukov. With Svetlana Khodchenkova, Stasya Miloslavskaya, Sergey Puskepalis, Aleksey Barabash. The film's two main protagonists are Russia's best saber fencers. One of them has long been in the limelight, the other only recently made it into the national team and has been winning almost every tournament since. The two athletes begin to fight for supremacy both on and off the arena.

title: Organized Mayhem: The B.A.T.S. Rugby Club Story
synopsis: The B.A.T.S. Rugby Club Story

title: One Day Ahead
synopsis: Directed by Matthew Jenke. With John Randal, Steven Fish, Paul Arneson, Jason Kelly. The story of eight New Zealand amateur cyclists attempting to complete the 2018 Tour de France race a day ahead of the professional race.

title: The Minor League Mecca
synopsis: Directed by Brendan Casey. With Phil Jackson, George Karl, Marc Kestecher, Tim Layden. As the premier franchise in the Continental Basketball Association from 1982 to 1992, the Albany Patroons left an indelible mark on the city of Albany, the CBA and the NBA. From elite coaches like Phil Jackson, Bill Musselman and George Karl to standout players like Michael Ray Richardson, Mario Elie, Tony Campbell, Sidney Lowe, Rick Carlisle and Scott Brooks, the Patroons' legacy continues to shape the world of professional basketball. We are working to bring you the untold story of the Patroons' quick rise, championship success and ultimate downfall. Beyond the franchise's ups and downs, the stories of the individuals involved, from fans, to executives to coaches and players are implausible, hilarious and inspiring.

title: Baalaa
synopsis: Directed by Sachindra Sharma. With Ashish Gokhale, Vikram Gokhale, Mihiresh Joshi, Upendra Limaye. Balaa is a Marathi movie starring Upendra Limaye, Kranti Redkar, Vikram Gokhale and Suhasini Mulay in prominent roles. It is a drama directed and written by Sachindra Sharma with Rakesh Singh as producer, forming part of the crew.

title: The Good, the Bad, the Hungry
synopsis: Directed by Nicole Lucas Haimes. With Joey Chestnut, Takeru Kobayashi, George Shea. Two competitors address their years-long rivalry on their sport's biggest stage

title: Valiant
synopsis: Directed by Cruz Angeles. With Sheri Aldrich, Deryk Engelland, Marc-Andre Fleury, Bill Foley. The story of the Las Vegas professional hockey team Vegas Golden Knights during their first year in the National Hockey League.

title: Bad Girl
synopsis: Directed by Marian Valev. With Lubomira Basheva, Stanislava Armutlieva, Deyan Donkov, Georgi Kadurin. Zhanet - an ex-champion in Gymnastics, currently a stripper, goes through drastic changes in her life after she lives through a family tragedy and becomes a victim of violence. In an attempt to find her place under the sun, she has to stand up against her mightiest enemy - herself.

title: Takedowns and Falls
synopsis: Directed by Todd Hickey, Kirk Ledger. With Walter Peppelman. Every autumn thousands of high school wrestlers throughout the state of Pennsylvania begin the season with the hope of making it to the PIAA State Championships in Hershey. Few ever make it, even less win, but for all, the journey to obtain one of the most elusive titles in high school athletics is one of pain, commitment and sacrifice. Takedowns and Falls follows a small cast through one high school wrestling season in Harrisburg, Pa. The film showcases the sport, the sacrifice of its athletes and dedication of its coaches. It reveals stories of triumph and defeat...pressure and expectation... mental and physical preparation and concepts of personal achievement, as told through the lives and experiences of... A Wrestler...A Coach...A Team... and the pursuit of a common dream. The film is about these former and current athletes dedicating themselves to a sport and lifestyle that has no hope of making them rich and famous. Never will they be a household name, but because of the sports incredible localized popularity, in places like Harrisburg, PA high school athletes often find themselves on the front page of the newspaper. Whether it is the misunderstandings of the sport and its athletes or self-imposed, wrestlers are often rather isolated from the world of "popular" sports. Despite its intense following and crowds, it is often the black sheep of high school sports programs. This film examines what separates these athletes from their peers and what makes them the same. Takedowns and Falls explores building foundations of humility, family, friendship, individualism and teamwork, via the quest for State Championships.

title: Children of the Norn
synopsis: Directed by Melanie Curran. With Neil Hamilton, Andy Hill, Jim Lenfesty, Long John McCurry. The North Coast of Northern Ireland boasts some of the most breathtaking beaches in the world. This film is about the people who surf them. Inspired by the enthusiasm of surfers in winter and summer; big waves and wee waves; onshore and offshore.

title: No Boarders
synopsis: Directed by Melanie Curran. With Neil Hamilton, Andy Hill, Martin Tk Kelly, Long John McCurry. A surf film about getting lost at home. sitting in vans-garage stops-coffee and crap-rubbish at your feet-checking charts-checking winds-checking spots-talking crap with friends-early starts-late nights-lighting fires-drinking beers-stinking wet wetties-sore shoulders-jump starts-allowance on sterling-bad times-good times-getting lost..

title: Kongernes fald
synopsis: Directed by Mads Kamp Thulstrup. With Erik Gundersen, Hans Nielsen, Ole Olsen.

title: Blindfold
synopsis: Directed by Taras Dron. With Maryna Koshkina, Oleg Shulga, Larysa Rusnak, Aleksandr Mavrits. Young MMA fighter Yuliya has lost her boyfriend in the war in eastern Ukraine. She starts a new relationship to make her life move forward.

title: Gimmick Tree Entertainment: Hustle and Grind 2
synopsis: Hustle and Grind 2

title: Q Ball
synopsis: Directed by Michael Tolajian. With Obada Adnan, Anthony Ammons, Lenny Costa, Rafael Cuevas. Documentary that explores the San Quentin Prison basketball squad - teammates and inmates at "the Q" - along their journey of rehabilitation and possible redemption.

title: The Pack
synopsis: Directed by Tomas Polensky. With Tomás Dalecký, Tomás Mrvík, Michal Dluhos, Anastázie Chocholatá. David, a talented 16-year-old-goalie freshly diagnosed with diabetes, joins a new ice-hockey team, the Wolves, where he becomes the outsider, bracing the avalanche of bullying that gradually gains speed.

title: Rapid Response
synopsis: Directed by Roger Hinze, Michael William Miles. With Stephen Olvey, Terry Trammell, Mario Andretti, Bobby Unser. Rapid Response is a fast-paced documentary that tells the story of medical and safety professionals who refused to accept the high mortality rate among American race car drivers, fundamentally altering the history of Motorsports.

title: The Magnificent Eleven
synopsis: Directed by Jeremy Wooding. With Josh O'Connor, Robert Vaughn, Sean Pertwee, Joseph Millson. A modernization of the classic western in which the Cowboys are a struggling local amateur soccer team, the Indians run a nearby Tandoori restaurant and the bandits are a group of menacing thugs led by a maniac known simply as 'American Bob'.

title: America's Greatest Airshows
synopsis: Directed by Don Ramey Logan. With Bill Tiger Destefani, Robert Gibson, Steve Hinton Jr., Kevin Lacey. Keven Lacey has seen it all in the Aviation industry and Kevin takes you inside the Reno Air Races like no one ever has. Keven talks with all the major players in this life or death motorsport that regularly see speeds over 500 mph. Visit the competitors in the hangers and on the tarmac, the Reno Air Races is unlike any motorsport on earth.

title: Sillages
synopsis: Directed by Léa Rinaldi. With Clarisse Crémer, Tom Dolan, Marta Guemes, Erwan Le Draoulec. It takes us on the journey of the solo cross Atlantic race, without assistance nor communication with the shores, on the smallest racing boat

title: Hockeytown
synopsis: Directed by Daniele Rielli. With Kai Suikkanen, Alexander Egger, Gino Pasqualotto, Martin Pavlu. The 2017-2018 season had started badly for the Hockey Club Bolzano

title: 3 Games to Glory VI
synopsis: Directed by Rob Gill.

title: Super Bowl LIII Champions: New England Patriots
synopsis: New England Patriots

title: Speed Is My Need
synopsis: Directed by Mark Sloper. With Shane Byrne, Colin Edwards, Leon Haslam, Ron Haslam. Inside the mind of a superbike racer, what makes these men risk their lives for the thrill of speed? Spectacular footage, unbelievable crashes, racing psychology and modern surgery, an intimate look inside the world of racing superbikes

title: 7 Hills
synopsis: Directed by Jesse Locke. With Tony Hawk, Joanna Arida, Mohammed Zakaria, Joanna A. Arida. Children's laughter and the sound of skateboards rolling have replaced explosions and screaming. Witness how the war torn Middle East acts as a backdrop to this amazing story of human survival.

title: Waking Maeve
synopsis: With Cain Kilcullen, Andrew Kilfeather, Stephen Kilfeather, Gearoid McDaid.

title: Waiting for Spring
synopsis: Mitsuki has a shy personality and she doesn't have many friends. Towa is her classmate and is on their school's basketball team. She begins to hang out the basketball team and her social life at school changes drastically.

title: Seaworthy
synopsis: Directed by Nathan Oldfield. With Belinda Baggs, Heydon Bunting, Matt Chojnacki, Heath Joske. This is the official trailer for 'Seaworthy', the long awaited second offering from independent operator Nathan Oldfield, the maker of the highly regarded and award winning underground surf film 'Lines from a poem'.Nearly three years in the making, Seaworthy documents a variety of individuals and the different ways that they approach wave riding. The film presents a left of center look at diversity in surfing, including alias, olos, toothpicks, single-fins, twins, thrusts, quads, fish, logs, surf mats and body-surfing. It is a unique, intimate and timeless perspective of surfing, surfers and the environment in which they live and find their being.

title: The Heart & The Sea
synopsis: Directed by Nathan Oldfield. With Johnny Abegg, Belinda Baggs, Ryan Burch, Brett Caller. 'The Heart and The Sea' is the third release from independent Australian filmmaker Nathan Oldfield, the creator of the highly regarded left of centre surf films 'Lines From a Poem' and 'Seaworthy'. Over three years in the making, 'The Heart and The Sea' explores the joy that lies at the very centre of a surfing life

title: Lines from a Poem
synopsis: Directed by Nathan Oldfield. With Belinda Baggs, Mikey DeTemple, Scott Dillon, Alex Knost. This is a documentary about an overlooked and under appreciated niche of the surfing experience

title: Pedro's Bay
synopsis: Directed by Eddie Obrand. With Derrick Disney, Eric Geiselman, Brendon Gibbens, Cam Richards.

title: Todo por el ascenso
synopsis: Directed by Jorge Piwowarski. With Tomás Fonzi, Ariel Pérez de María, Fernando Govergun, Gabriela Sari. The Final Football Match will be between "Club Gimnasia y Esgrima de Mendoza" and "Club Atletico Saavedra". The winning team will be promoted. For Nestor (Ariel Perez de María) and Rafa (Tomas Fonzi) this is the most important match of their lives. both fans are determined to travel all the way from Buenos Aires to Mendoza, more than 700 miles, with ease and time ahead to live that unique moment. Nestor's superstitions, their encounters with the Barras Bravas (Hooligans), one of the players being injured, and the sudden appearance of Fabian (Fernando Govergun) give them supreme power to win the match. And they'll do anything to win THE GAME.

title: The Return of the Cup - The Film
synopsis: 30 years after their last major title, Eintracht win the DFB Cup on 19 May 2018. It's a momentous occasion for both the club and the fans. The yearning of an entire region is satisfied and about 100,000 people rock Frankfurt's bank towers the next day. A film team accompanied the team from their arrival in Berlin for the match to the celebrations at the Römer in Frankfurt. The documentary provides exclusive insights into the inner workings of the team, recounting all of the emotions around the historic 3:1 victory over Bayern and the passion with which everyone involved worked to succeed in the final. Looking back on a historic weekend What did Coach Kovac say during the last team meeting at a Berlin hotel before the final? How does CEO Hellmann describe the situation and the mood at the club before the Cup Final? What does club legend Karl-Heinz Körbel say about his moment with the DFB Cup shortly before the presentation ceremony? What was going through Player Boateng's mind as the video evidence was being examined shortly before the end? What happened in the dressing room shortly after the game? The film answers all of these questions and offers a unique view of Eintracht Frankfurt' DFB Cup victory. The film is also a pure delight for neutral football fans, because it shows how an entire region's yearning for a major title was satisfied. Summary

title: The Heart
synopsis: Directed by Fendou Liu. With Kun Yang, Zitong Xia, Ailei Yu, Xianda Liu. To pay for his sins and the surgery of a new heart transplant, TAN Kai must put his boxing gloves back on one more time.

title: Kousalya Krishnamurthy
synopsis: Directed by Srinivasa Rao Bhimaneni. With Mahesh Achanta, Jhansi, Vennela Kishore, Vishnu Oi. Kousalya Murugesan, the daughter of Murugesan, a farmer, aspires to become an international cricketer so that she can put a smile on her cricket-loving father's face by helping the country win.

title: The Spirit of the Game
synopsis: Directed by Liam McEvoy. With Cyril Schweitzer, Yves Barthels, Peter Hult, Astrid Schuh Leduc. 'The Spirit of the Game' follows Luxembourgish amateur ice hockey team the 'Puckers' for a full calendar year to explore just what makes the team one of the most unique in the world.

title: Suatu Ketika
synopsis: Directed by Prakash Murugiah. With Namron, Pekin Ibrahim, Danial Akmal Fariz, Dheva Naish. A group of underprivileged local school kids go against all odds to form a soccer team to compete in the JG Davidson Cup tournament to fight the reigning champion - the highly privileged British school, St James.

title: Penalty
synopsis: Directed by Shubham Singh. With Lukram Smil, Kay Kay Menon, Shashank Arora, Manjot Singh. A story of a North-east Indian football player who's fighting day and night with the society in order to achieve his dreams. The film covers all kinds of layers in one single film from negative backlashes, social pressures to a complete change over in one's life.

title: Bludgeon
synopsis: Directed by Andy Deere, Ryan Heron. A group of competitive medieval combat enthusiasts from New Zealand hope to make the national team which is due to travel to Denmark for an international competition.

title: Les barbares de La Malbaie
synopsis: Directed by Vincent Biron. With Jean-Michel Anctil, Luc Boucher, Etienne Béliveau, Erin Carter. -Yves and JP, two cousins from northern Québec (in Canada), share a passion for hockey. When Yves, a one-time junior-league star who's been scouted for the NHL, is seriously injured in a game in the senior league, he finds refuge in painkillers. JP, some ten years younger, and dreaming of becoming a sports agent, plans Yves' comeback. Together, they drive across Québec and Ontario in the hopes of seeing Yves play in a championship game in Thunder Bay. Little do they suspect that their quest for glory will above all take them on a journey of self-discovery.

title: And We Go Green
synopsis: Directed by Fisher Stevens, Malcolm Venville. With Alejandro Agag, Jules Bianchi, Sam Bird, Orlando Bloom. Professional drivers on the international Formula E circuit - like Formula One, but with eco-friendly electric cars - race for victory across 10 cities in this white-knuckle documentary.

title: 28 Winters: A Nitro Snowboard Story
synopsis: A Nitro Snowboard Story

title: Crossing the Line
synopsis: With Allan Border, Michael Haysman, Michael Holding, Mark Nicholas. This is the story of the highly controversial 2018 Test series between Australia and South Africa involving the infamous ball-tampering scandal, Sandpapergate.

title: Finding Jack Charlton
synopsis: Directed by Gabriel Clarke, Pete Thomas. With Jack Charlton, Des Casey, Paul McGrath, Roddy Doyle. Finding Jack Charlton is the definitive portrait of an extraordinary man; an English World Cup winning legend, who became an Irish hero.

title: Fittest in Dubai
synopsis: Directed by Gerry Blaksley. With Mat Fraser, Samantha Briggs, Sara Sigmunsdóttir, Laura Horvath. "Fittest in Dubai" is a 60 min documentary film of the first CrossFit Sanctional event in the world. First place male and female competitors qualify for a position to the CrossFit Games in the United States.

title: Mata Dewa
synopsis: Directed by Andibachtiar Yusuf. With Kenny Austin, Brandon Salim, Agatha Chelsea, Nino Fernandez. Dewa (Kenny Austin) wants to bring his school, Wijaya High School, becomes the first DBL champion. Dewa and his team are assisted by coach Miko (Nino Fernandez).

title: By the Balls
synopsis: Directed by Simon Coldrick, Charlotte Purdy, Christopher Dudman. With Liam Dixon, Robert Hannah, Dom Lloyd, Finian Scott. Sport and politics most definitely do mix in this gripping look back at a brutal and turbulent time for New Zealand rugby, told from the point of view of the players themselves including David Kirk and Buck Shelford.

title: Min Alesh?
synopsis: Directed by Amleset Muchie. With Alebachew Mekonnen, Amleset Muchie, Dirbwork Seyifu, Haddis D. Tadesse. The story is set in Merkato, a sprawling market in Addis Ababa, Ethiopia, considered to be Africa's largest open-air market, narrating the story of a girl, Selam, whose kindness and perseverance transforms her life for the better. Selam confronts the hardship life of her village but is determined to change the circumstances she and her family face, through athletics. The film depicts the young girl as a symbol and an inspiration for women and girls and that they, too, can be destined for greatness.

title: Wingmen
synopsis: Directed by Thomas O. Christensen, Preben Peter Winther Hansen. Three of the world's most renowned BASE jumpers, Jokke Sommer, Espen Fadnes and Ludovic Woerth embark on an adventure around the world seeking out unique and challenging places to wingsuit proximity flying and BASE jumping. Directed and produced by Siesta Films and Ellioth and Winther Film, this exceptional journey takes Jokke, Espen and Ludo to Rio de Janeiro, Chamonix, The Reunion Island, The Tianmen Mountains in China, Bangkok, before their planned final jump in Dubai.All three athletes speak candidly about the moralities of the sport they risk their lives for and the emotions and rewards that push them to pioneer this sport.

title: 60 Seconds to Glory
synopsis: Directed by Tate Chalk. With Tate Chalk. This film created by Nfinity Athletic, follows a partner stunt competition hosted in New Orleans. Coed and All-Girl stunt groups battle for a trip to Mexico and a World Title. Winner takes all. No rules. Who will win?

title: Follow The Fraser
synopsis: Directed by Liam Mullany, Andre Nutini, David Peacock. With James Doerfling, Kyle Norbraten, Mark Savard, Tom Van Steenbergen. The story will follow three Mountainbike Stars as they travel north through British Columbia along the Fraser River, riding and building features along the way. Their journey takes them through towns they grew up in, and places which they never knew existed, eventually reaching a destination that is unknown, a secret waiting to be discovered.

title: Socorro Evolution
synopsis: Directed by Roberto Ochoa. With Tomoka Fukuda, Camila Jaber, Jean Jacques Mayol, Estrella Navarro. A team of marine wildlife ambassadors prepare themselves for a great adventure around Mexico's Revillagigedo Archipelago, a UNESCO World Heritage site. Internationally renowned free divers show us the beauty of how man can explore marine wildlife while still conserving it, posing the question, "Can we all learn to coexist with nature within our lifetime before we destroy it?".

title: Perceptions
synopsis: Directed by Basti Balser, Flo Eckhardt, Mathias Egle. Join a tight group of snowboard professionals on their journeys around the globe, always on the hunt for the best snow, the biggest jumps, the gnarliest lines and the most unique features. From the streets of Russia and Canada, to the mystical forests of Japan; from the steepest mountains of India and Alaska to the endless possibilities of the European Alps; to the spiritual slopes of Greenland, we not only captured the action but also the sense of traveling.

title: Passenger
synopsis: Directed by Andre Nutini, David Peacock. With Paddy Graham, Rob Heule, Thomas Hlawitschka, Mack Jones. Innsbruck. Hokkaido. Edmonton. Revelstoke. Haines. Queenstown. Stubai Glacier. Many have passed through these places over the last two years; workers, travelers, adventurers...among them was a collection of friends bonded by a shared affinity for chasing snow to all corners of the globe. This group of skiers has come to be known as Legs of Steel, and they've been travel companions for a long time.

title: Liverpool vs Sporting Lisbon
synopsis: With Sporting C.P., Liverpool F.C.. A friendly match Between Liverpool FC and Sporting CP. This match was played on the 25/07/19 and it was for the Western Union cup. The match ended in a 2-2 draw so the trophy had to be shared between the clubs. The goals were scored by Origi, Wijnaldum (Liverpool) and Bruno Fernandes and Wendel (Sporting). The crowd attendance was 31,112, with the majority of them coming to watch Liverpool. The match was televised on Liverpool TV.

title: Red Penguins
synopsis: Directed by Gabe Polsky. With Howard Baldwin, Alexander Baranovsky, George Bush, Bill Clinton. Red Penguins tells a story of capitalism and opportunism run amok - complete with gangsters, strippers and live bears serving beer on a hockey rink in Moscow. Shortly after the collapse of the Soviet Union, the Pittsburgh Penguins and the famed Red Army hockey team formed a joint-venture that showed anything was possible in the new Russia. Eccentric marketing whiz, Steve Warshaw, is sent to Russia and tasked to transform team into the greatest show in Moscow. He takes the viewer on a bizarre journey highlighting a pivotal moment in U.S. Russian relations in a lawless era when oligarchs made their fortunes and multiple murders went unsolved.

He resides there with his son Juanjo (17), a sensitive teenager who keeps him company and confronts him openly. Suffering from acute kidney disease which keeps him from competing professionally, Antonio is stuck in limbo, halfway between his glorious past and the impossibility of being who he once was. However, he is unwilling to give up his lifestyle, even if it kills him. In an attempt to reinvent himself, and seeking a better future for his son, Antonio plans a comeback to the Mexico bodybuilding scene, where he may relive his glory days.

After many fines and suspensions, Priest received a lifetime ban from professional bodybuilding. He has since made it his mission to speak his truth regarding the sport of bodybuilding and the professional league - earning him a label as the dark horse of bodybuilding. title: Heroes
synopsis:
Directed by Manish Pandey. With Mika Häkkinen, Tom Kristensen, Felipe Massa, Michèle Mouton. A new feature-length film focusing on the lives of five motor racing legends will be unveiled this July, in the week leading up to the British Grand Prix. The film, Heroes, has been written and directed by Manish Pandey, who ten years ago wrote the screenplay for the award-winning Senna.

This new movie - commissioned by the Motorsport Network - brings together drivers from F1, sportscars and rallying who tell their stories to each other over an evening in an English stately home.

The four racers are two-time Formula 1 world champion Mika Häkkinen, former Ferrari grand prix ace Felipe Massa, nine-time Le Mans winner Tom Kristensen and World Rally Championship runner-up Michèle Mouton.

"I wanted to get racers of different ages and disciplines together but in a location that was out of their comfort zone," says Pandey. "When you dig down into these characters, you discover - no matter what their background is - how much they have in common."

Though the motor racing disciplines differ, the stories they share across ten chapters in the film are broadly similar

synopsis: Directed by Bonni Cohen, Jon Shenk. With Maggie Nichols, Gina Nichols, John Nichols, Steve Berta. Follow the Indianapolis Star reporters that broke the story about USA Gymnastics doctor Larry Nassar's abuse and hear from gymnasts like Maggie Nichols.

title: With Drawn Arms
synopsis: Directed by Glenn Kaino, Afshin Shahidi. With Lonnie Bunch, Nelson George, Jemele Hill, Colin Kaepernick. Filmmaker Glenn Kaino partners with Olympic gold medalist Tommie Smith as he looks back 50 years to the moment that helped define a movement and changed the course of his life forever.

title: David Silva: Made in Gran Canaria
synopsis: Made in Gran Canaria

title: Djelac
synopsis: Directed by Alen Matusin. With Stjepan Cvek, Zlatko Dalic, Andjelko Herjavec, Bojana Herjavec. A story about Andjelko Herjavec. A charismatic former Croatian director of Varteks d.d. and Varteks F.C.

title: H20: Hardcore Kingdom 4
synopsis: Hardcore Kingdom 4

title: 34th FIG Trampoline Gymnastics World Championships Men's Trampoline Team Final
synopsis: With Jaydon Paddock.

title: Negri. Sport in the U.S.A.
synopsis: Directed by Francesco Gallo. With Guglielmo Favilla.

title: Surfer: Mastering Turbulence
synopsis: Directed by Daniela Vater. With Marielle Layher, Rouven Brauers, Trevor Carlson, Andrew Cotton. For all people, life begins in the water, in the protective body of the mother, where they are gently rocked back and forth. After birth, life meets them again in waves. And finally they return to the water to conquer or grasp it. There is the scientist who tries to measure and calculate waves in search of a formula. In the meantime, the shaper builds surfboards, always looking for the perfect shape. And finally there is the surfer who daringly throws himself into the most dangerous waves and looks out to sea to catch the largest of them if possible. A documentary film that deals with life, the waves and the power of the sea and whose different protagonists unite the love for the waves.

title: Resiliencia por Rafinha Alcantara
synopsis: Directed by Jep Barcelona. With Rafinha Alcántara, Marc-André Ter Stegen, Sergi Roberto, Thiago Alcántara. Rafinha Alcantara, an FC Barcelona team football player, wants to publicly show one of the most difficult stages of his professional career

title: Dheet Patangey
synopsis: Directed by Ravi Adhikari. With Muntazir Ahmad, Ali Murad, Priya Banerjee, Lakshya Handa. Four cricket-crazy friends set out to find answer and write their destinies, between the two big wins in 1983 and 2011.

title: AfterForever
synopsis: Directed by Shane Charlebois. With Jaeger Bailey, Max Buri, Brandon Cocard, Ethan Deiss. Change is the only constant. Resistance leads to stagnation and suffering while embracing it brings growth. What comes AfterForever? Everything.

title: B'ars to Bears: Hershey's Hockey Dynasty
synopsis: Hershey's Hockey Dynasty

title: No Place for Angels
synopsis: Directed by Sam Kalantari. It is about the Iran women's national hockey team and the problems and the difficulties in their way to go participate in the Asian matches.

title: Beyond the Mat
synopsis: Directed by Van M. Pham. With John Wynn, Mark Hapka, Sara Fletcher, Kurt Angle. A tale about two best friends, an uncensored look into the perilous world of high school wrestling, and the story of a teen who overcomes self doubt to find his true place.

title: Stay Tuned
synopsis: Directed by Shane Charlebois, Justin Hostynek. With Mikkel Bang, Red Gerard, John Jacks, Kyle Mack.

title: Isle of Snow
synopsis: Directed by Shane Charlebois. With Dylan Alito, Demetri Bales, Ryland Bell, Frank Bourgeois.

title: Moneyball
synopsis: Directed by Bennett Miller. With Brad Pitt, Jonah Hill, Philip Seymour Hoffman, Robin Wright. Oakland A's general manager Billy Beane's successful attempt to assemble a baseball team on a lean budget by employing computer-generated analysis to acquire new players.

title: Behobia
synopsis: Directed by Eñaut Tolosa. La Behobia; a long-distance race with 100 years of History. A challenge with thousands of stories of personal growth and infinite emotion.

title: Dumbbell Domination
synopsis: Directed by Christopher Wilson. With Christopher Wilson. Dumbbell Domination is a full body workout routine designed to build muscle, strength and leave you feeling pumped. Increasing muscle mass will allow your body to burn more calories which is important because weight loss often prevents diseases and makes you more confident and active. Weight training with dumbbells can help you tone muscles in key areas, resulting in a leaner and healthier look.

title: Dark Blood
synopsis: Directed by George Sluizer. With River Phoenix, Judy Davis, Jonathan Pryce, Karen Black. Dealing with nuclear testing and its deadly effects, the story portrays Boy, a young widower living in the desert on a nuclear testing site. Living as a hermit, he waits for the end of the world.

title: Escalade
synopsis: Directed by Charlotte Silvera. With Carmen Maura, Julie Durand, Renaud Cestre, Thomas Sagols. When a group of charming teenagers ring the bell of their high school headmistress (Carmen Maura) with a big bouquet of flowers and a birthday present, we are far from thinking that they are the protagonist of a machiavellian plan. Alice Nabat invites this group of jolly young people to have a drink, not knowing that once the door has closed behind them, they will become her tormentors. What is their purpose? As the plot slowly unfolds and thickens, we learn that they have been cheating in class all year and that they feel more powerful than the "authority" that they are challenging. They actually want to steal the answers to the Baccalaureat (French A Level), to order to pass the precious diploma without any effort on their part. A blackmail of insidious violence happens throughout the night between these "new barbarians" and their terrorized headmistress, hostage to their uncontrolled and threatening actions.

title: Irreversi
synopsis: Directed by Michael Gleissner. With Mei Melançon, Ian Bohen, Estella Warren, Kenny Doughty. A thriller about the effect of a financial windfall on a married couple.

title: The Yellow Wallpaper
synopsis: Directed by Logan Thomas. With Aric Cushing, Juliet Landau, Dale Dickey, Veronica Cartwright. After a devastating fire, Charlotte and John rent a countryside house and attempt to start life over, though Charlotte, upon seeing visions of her deceased daughter, retreats to the house's attic and pulls away from her husband and sister.

title: Dreamkiller
synopsis: Directed by Catherine C. Pirotta. With Dario Deak, John Savage, Tyrone Power Jr., Penny Vital. A young doctor is linked to a series of mysterious and brutally executed murders while performing a controversial medical experiment with mysterious origins.

title: The Secret Philosophy
synopsis: Directed by Mark Charles. With Vanessa Zachos, Roxana Alexander, Alexa Brown, Alexandra Burn. A filmmaker finds a more intriguing search than the meaning of life.

title: Bulletface
synopsis: Directed by Albert Pyun, Howie Askins, Joe Baile. With Victoria Maurette, Steven Bauer, Morgan Weisser, Jenny Dare Paulin. Horror and Revenge drive this thriller set in the sex and human trafficking underbelly of a nightmarish city where spinal fluid has become the drug of choice...with frightening consequences.

title: Torn
synopsis: Directed by Eric Manchester. With Scott Andrews, Vani Beaton, Betty Bobbitt, Tanya Braunovic. What if a stranger decides to ruin your life? Daniel, a timid bookseller, has a random encounter with Steve, a successful real estate agent. In Steve, Daniel suddenly sees all that is wrong in the world, and sets out to destroy him. When Steve realizes that his unknown enemy wants him to spend the rest of his life as a frightened, hunted man, Steve decides to defend those dear to him, before they are taken from him.

title: House Under Siege
synopsis: Directed by Mark Hazen Kelly. With Jeremy London, Bret Roberts, Sally Kirkland, Heather Marie Marsden. Two young boys and a girl commit a diamond robbery on Halloween. During escape the girl is fatally shot. One of the boys knows a doctor (Jeremy London) who has a private clinic in his house. They decide to go to his house instead of the hospital where they will expect the police. They enter the house quietly with no drama. But when the doctor tells them she needs an ambulance to the hospital or else she will die, and his co-worker picks up the phone ready to call, the boys bring their guns out. The doctor along with his family are taken hostages, and the boys threaten him to save the girl if they all want to stay alive.

title: Super Sketch
synopsis: Directed by Ravi C. Kumar. With Narsing Makkala, Indrasena, Sameerdatta, Shubhangi Pant. Super Sketch is Investigative suspense thriller. It is a story about Cop and Culprits.

title: Lo peor de los deseos
synopsis: Directed by Claudio Araya Silva. With Luigi Antezana, Jorge Jamarlli, Esmeralda Pinzón, Ines Quispe. Carlos Borjas plots to gain control of The Federation of Drivers of Bolivia, this meaning he is willing to go against Roberto, his close friend and the leader of the Federation. Meanwhile, the country is in conflict, which is causing rapid transitions that are making contraband a depleting option. Nevertheless, Margot- Roberto's wife- pressures him to block the streets and use his power in her favor. Her greatest wishes are about to be achieved. But, what is maintained well hidden is that every one of them holds a traitor within, that of their most intimate desires, which fools them into thinking that their ambitions can take them further than they actually can.

title: Revenge for Daddy
synopsis: Directed by Tom Shell. With Sarah Butler, Samantha Cope, Ashley Doris, Joely Fisher. When Lisa's father is killed in a hit and run, we discover that he has a secret daughter from his first marriage. Her name is Marie and she is a convicted murderer, out on early release from prison, and driven by a single purpose-revenge. Living under a secret identity as Bethany, Marie has connived her way to living and working close to Lisa, lurking and planning her revenge as payment for the life she feels cheated out of-a life she feels their father unfairly gave to Lisa. Marie has set a deadly trap for Lisa to take back what she is owed, leaving Lisa, her mother and their friends to fight for their lives against the murderous sister she never knew.

title: Staged Killer
synopsis: Directed by Christopher Ray. With Chrishell Stause, Nicole Bilderback, Jason Dolley, Darrin Dewitt Henson. When a former co-host, Jake Everett, works his way back into the professional life of popular TV morning show host Naomi Spencer, the show's success skyrockets, but Naomi's personal life begins to fall apart.

title: Mr Misfortune
synopsis: Directed by Rick Caplan. With Max Gideon, Hari Williams, Ryan Cafeo, Kelsey Fordham. In a misguided attempt to protect his friend from an extortionist, a man hijacks a blackmail scheme and puts himself and everyone he cares about in danger.

title: Adopted in Danger
synopsis: Directed by Craig Goldstein. With Sarah Aldrich, Jason Brooks, Christie Burson, Stephanie Charles. When a DNA test helps Candace connect with her birth parents, she realizes some family histories are better left untold

title: VI
synopsis: Directed by Jesus Pasos. With Jerry Velez, Jessica Sanchez, Olivia Gutierrez, Emanuel Garfias. Jerry fights his inner demons when he gives up drinking.

title: Zero Distance
synopsis: Directed by Abdulaziz Alshlahei. With Khalid Al-Saqer, Yagoub Alfarhan, Osamah Salih, Abdullah Alzaid. A photographer faces his questionable past when he finds a picture of a dead body on his apartment floor and his pistol missing a bullet.

title: Cyberlante
synopsis: Directed by James Smith. With Gavin Gordon, Emily Haigh, Mark Peachey, Mia Mills. A mysterious young man moves to a new town to work in a low level job in an isolated hotel, run by an unsympathetic bully who has deadly secrets of his own.

title: Despedida de soltero
synopsis: Directed by Manu Ochoa, Teresa Martínez. With Jonai Rodriguez, Víctor Valga, Manuel Toro, Ángel Maldonado.

title: Bhinna
synopsis: Directed by Adarsh Eshwarappa. With Srinivas Bindiganavale, Adarsh Eshwarappa, Sowmya Jaganmurthy, Sidhaartha Maadhyamika. The Script of a Film, she is going to be a part of; begins to blur lines between reality and imagination, for an Aspiring Actress, obsessed about Method Acting.

title: 1978: A Teen Night Out
synopsis: A Teen Night Out

title: Frenetic
synopsis: Directed by Gabe Villarreal. With Saskia Lynge, Omri Horowitz, Alex Nicole McConnell, Kiani Stone. While a detective investigates a missing person's case, a far more sinister chain of events unravels around her, threatening to destroy everything she's worked for, along with her family.

title: Miracle
synopsis: Directed by Rudrapatla Venugopal. With Suman Rana, Hari Vishnu, Sandeep Bharadwaj, Vijay Kumar Nazar. Movie story starts from the end of Veerappan , what if Veerapan comes back in disguise of an IPS officer. Can any man die twice in his life. Celebrity couple Mrs Lilitha and Harman shergill serve as IAS and IPS respectively. On a felicitation function where all the police official and judges and VIPS and the press are present Lilitha kills her husband Harman Shergill on the dias and now why she did that and how she is not proven guilty in the court of law is plot of the story.

title: Aadya
synopsis: Directed by K.M. Chaitanya. With Chiranjeevi Sarja, Sruthi Hariharan, Sangeetha Bhat, Ravishankar Gowda. A man gets a call from his ex-lover who needs his help to find her kidnapped daughter but during the investigation, all the evidence suggests that she never really had a daughter.

title: Multiple
synopsis: Directed by La'Marc Bishop. With Alex Jay, Troy Etheredge, Tisa Key, Cherrie McRae. Tamara Delaney is well known internet blogger with thousands of followers....She's living her best life until the unthinkable happens. She wakes up and finds her boyfriend murdered in her house...Jared Dobbs, an established defense attorney takes Tamara's case but soon learns that there is more layer behind her pretty face....Dobbs must prove his client is innocent even though he knows the truth..

title: Test Pattern
synopsis: Directed by Shatara Michelle Ford. With Brittany S. Hall, Will Brill, Gail Bean, Drew Fuller. Test Pattern follows an interracial couple whose relationship is put to the test after a Black woman is sexually assaulted and her White boyfriend drives her from hospital to hospital in search of a rape kit.

title: Incitement
synopsis: Directed by Yaron Zilberman. With Yehuda Nahari Halevi, Amitay Yaish Ben Ousilio, Anat Ravnitzki, Yoav Levi. Details the year leading to the assassination of Israel's Prime Minister, Yitzhak Rabin (1922-1995), from the point of view of the assassin.

title: Northland
synopsis: Directed by David Metzger. With Rachel Riendeau, Lincoln L. Hayes, Andrew Remillard. He came home from war to face his greatest battle.

title: Almas de la Niebla
synopsis: Directed by Juan Pablo Cortés. With Tato Alexander, Alejandro Caso, Marco Aurelio Contreras, Yadira Pascault Orozco.

title: Stolen Identity 2
synopsis: Toraware no satsujinki

title: Swayamvada
synopsis: Directed by Verma Vivek. With Aditya Alluri, Krishna Murali Posani, Anika Rao. Swayamvada is a psychological thriller centered on a rare disease which inflicts pain not only on the affected, but also the family members of the affected. The movie explores the love of nature, the tender feelings of companionship in a relationship between a man and a woman and the extent to which a woman goes if she suffers betrayal at the hands of her lover.

title: Special
synopsis: Directed by Vastav. With Ajay, Sai Akshatha, Jabardasth Appa Rao, Bhel Prasad. A suspended police officer sets out to investigate a medico with mind-reading abilities, and a cat-and-mouse game ensues between the two. Directed by Vastav, the film stars Ajay, Ranga and Akshata in the lead roles.

title: Greenfield
synopsis: Directed by Julius Telmer, Jevgeni Jevsikov. With Ethan Tomas, Liam Graham, Marthe Snorresdotter Rovik, Kym Bidstrup. James enters the small town of Greenfield to win his former girlfriend Kelly back, but tensions soon explode when her brother confides him with a volatile secret.

title: Valiyaperunnal
synopsis: Directed by Dimal Dennis. With Atul Kulkarni, Himika Bose, Joju George, Raza Murad. Movie revolves around a group of people living in a harbor town. The story delves into their love for each other and a certain festival of sacrifices.

title: A Stolen Life
synopsis: Directed by Viktor Tatarskiy. With Daria Lenda, Aleksey Mitin. A young couple Yulia and Vlad go to spend some quiet days on an island. Vlad is in his early thirties. He is kind and caring with Yulia. She suffers from a psychological trauma and partial memory loss. Complete isolation makes the young couple happy during first days, however, very soon the girl notices some strange behavior of her boyfriend. Terrifying hallucinations and memories that she cannot explain overwhelm her. Her trials to bring back her memory and find out the truth turn into struggle for life.

title: Indemnity
synopsis: Directed by Ethan Levesque, Eric Roth. With Sean Danforth, David Furtado, Ian Jones, Dominique LaGrange. Shortly after a down on his luck small town farmer makes a deal with a loan shark, local police raid the illegal organization. Now taken hostage, the desperate Maine man must cooperate with his captor, or face the various consequences.

title: Fixation 2 UpRising
synopsis: Directed by Bobby Peoples, Renee S. Warren Peoples. With Davon Alston, Tina Bridges, Needa-Mya Chambers, Tanika Crowther. Three years after the events of the first movie. The story picks up with Samantha and her life with her biological father and the teachings he has for her.

title: The German
synopsis: Directed by Noga Nezer. A docu-fiction thriller. Noga inherits the crumbling farm of her holocaust survivor grandmother, and hires the help of a stalwart young German, to handle the property. The German suggests that he move in with Noga in return for taking on more of the house work, to which both Noga's grandmother and mother are strictly opposed. A love affair develops between them, but their relationship is undermined when Noga begins to suspect that he is plotting something evil.

title: Werner Gruber
synopsis: Directed by Igor Sadovski. With Dumitru Ionascu, Constantin Ipati, Rada Ixari, Nicolae Jelescu. Out from the orphanage and after the first experiences, Mara decides to return to the home of her parents who have mysteriously died in an accident many years ago. Mara begins a new life

title: Rajsadan
synopsis: Directed by Shailendra Tikariya. With Gajendra Gadkar, Puja, Pratik Raj. The story of Ganpati Bappa of Rajur himself coming to the aid of a middle-class family in distress... A documentary showing the greatness of Ganapati of Rajur also known as "Rajur cha Ganapati", located in Maharashtra, India. It's trusted that lord Ganapati is always there to help needy people.

title: The Adopted One
synopsis: Directed by Kamilla Lanae. With Kamilla Lanae, Terrell Broadus, Matthew Deibert, Charmaine Warrington. After suffering physical and mental abuse and murdering his foster parents, Jonathan spends thirty years in a mental institution where he discovers he has schizophrenia.

title: Dangerous Lies
synopsis: Directed by Michael M. Scott. With Nick Purcha, Joe Costa, Camila Mendes, Briana Skye. When a wealthy elderly man dies and unexpectedly leaves his estate to his new caregiver, she's drawn into a web of deception and murder. If she's going to survive, she'll have to question everyone's motives - even the people she loves.

title: Whelm
synopsis: Directed by Skyler Lawson. With Francesca Anderson, Delil Baran, Ronan Colfer, Jacob Eaton. Set during the Great Depression, two Midwest brothers get tangled in a rivalry between a legendary bank robber and an eccentric young criminal.

title: American Skin
synopsis: Directed by Nate Parker. With Nate Parker, Omari Hardwick, Beau Knapp, Theo Rossi. A Marine veteran working as a school janitor tries to mend his relationship with his son after a divorce. When his son is killed by a police officer found innocent without standing trial, he takes matters into his own hands.

title: Mia's M.I.A
synopsis: Directed by Nicholas Aaron Robinson. With Alexis Marie, CeeJay Allen, Jamel D. Chambers, Jared D. Howard. A tale of love and hurt about a college girl named Mia, who's enjoying a night out with her friends and is soon visited by someone from her past she wished to forget.

title: Killer in Law
synopsis: Directed by Danny J. Boyle. With Kelly Sullivan, Nana Visitor, Brett Zimmerman, Violet Hicks. Melissa, a happily-married woman with an eight-year-old daughter, invites her husband's mother to live with them, only to realize that Grandma is unhinged and wants to kidnap Melissa's daughter to replace her own dead child.

title: Muras
synopsis: Directed by Azamat Arykov. With Azamat Arykov, Shahzoda Matchanova, Tynar Abdrazaeva, Marat Alyshpaev.

title: Delfin Pentagon
synopsis: Directed by Pascal Ilie Virgil, Adrian Popovici. With Dan Badarau, Irina Bucescu, Cristina Florea, Christine Popovich.

title: Cuadras Largas
synopsis: Directed by Juanjo Martínez. With Facundo Serrano, Tamara Rasch, Alejandro Destefani, Nerea del Río. Two cops must protect a witness on a trip throughout the capital of Buenos Aires, Argentina.

title: Deer Season
synopsis: Directed by Raymond Dussault. With Nick Fenske, John Douglas Ayers, Tom Hart, Michael Sorensen. Seven friends pack up for one last backpacking trip before the final end of summer. When they strike out into the wilderness and stumble on two ex-cons hell-bent on staying free, their peaceful retreat explodes into terrorized flight. A film that explores the dark depths of familial loyalty and pits friendship against survival, Deer Season will put a death grip on your pulse

title: Ingen skal sove
synopsis: Directed by Christian Andersen. With Yvonne Andersen, Thomas Biehl, Louise Bonde, Jakob Schmidt Clausen. Maria and Jonas are escaping an assault and ends up at an isolated farm, where things are not as peaceful as they seem to be.

title: Run Wolf, Run
synopsis: Directed by Carli Robertson. With Emma Jean Anderson, Maia Bence, Kylee Ealey Blackburn, Adreanna Boucher. A woman masks her weakening sanity as she fails to recall her actions during frequent blackouts

title: Opt-in
synopsis: Directed by Gabriel Gambetta. With Aaron Royce Jones, Gabriel Gambetta, Stuart Selesnick, Kiel Hooker. An idealistic engineer lands his dream job at the biggest social media company in the world. But when he discovers the dark side of the business, he must decide whether to stay silent or risk everything to expose the truth.

title: Kidnapped by a Classmate
synopsis: Directed by Ben Meyerson. With Andrea Bogart, Paige Searcy, Lucas Adams, Parker Thomas. Brooke is starting over in a new town with her mom and wealthy stepdad when she befriends a new guy she meets at school, which leads to her being abducted from her own home.

title: Superhit
synopsis: Directed by Niranjan Pandey. With Binita Baral, Sudam Ck, Divya Dev, Shishir Rana.

title: The Royal Opera House: Faust
synopsis: Faust

title: The Essence
synopsis: Directed by Kate Wissell. With Laura Colella, Stephanie Harrocks, Chelsea Griffith, Carol Lawton. Who would have thought a night of camping could possibly go so wrong? When Sam's friends convince her to go on a camping trip for their high school reunion, not all is as it seems. Lurking in the woods and ready for blood is something sinister. A night of horror faces the friends as they discover secrets from the past buried at Black Pond. Relationships are tested and morals are questioned. How far would you go for one more chance?

title: Purbo Poschim Dokkhin Uttor Ashbei
synopsis: Directed by Raajhorshee De. With Paran Banerjee, Daminee Benny Basu, Aryann Bhowmick, Arpita Chatterjee. The stories are based on the concepts of Paranormal, psychic situations Blind faith on black magic and witch craft , Severe superstitions and rituals Reincarnation, fake identity and mysterious comeback. The film rationalizes the good and the bad sides of popular belief and age-old ideas, the evil of superstition and the dark side of mankind.

title: Sarvasva
synopsis: Directed by Shreyas Kabadi. With Sathvika Appaiah, Ranusha Kashvi, Thilak Shekar, Chetan Vardhan. Inspired by the Kannada film legend Rajkumar, two friends, Guru and Ayush, set off to pursue their celluloid dream together. Through Sathvika, Ayush's love interest, Guru meets Jessie, a visually impaired who is mesmerized by him and decides to cast her as the lead actress in his movie titled Sarvasa. Their journey under the arch lights begins but all is not hail and hearty in this seemingly perfect world of love and friendship. Sacrifices, deceit, jealousy, hatred, and lies become a part of this journey and it's time to reap what they have sown.

title: El secadero de iguanas
synopsis: Directed by Antonio Donaire Sánchez. With Lola Arellano, Ramón Bocanegra, Juan Luis Corrientes, Marco Corrientes. A bar in the middle of nowhere. A girl facing her demons. Her twin brother. An incestuous relationship. A mother they never met. A violent, alcoholic father. The nomads' periodic visitations.

title: Deviant Love
synopsis: Directed by Michael Feifer. With Emma Bell, Nick Ballard, Bradley Bundlie, Gail O'Grady. A woman is charmed by a handsome man with a dark family secret who will do anything, including murder, to keep her forbidden love.

title: Evil Intent
synopsis: Directed by Michael Feifer. With Lyndon Smith, Abbie Cobb, Sean Faris, Griffin Morgan. A young couple Mira (Abbie Cobb) and Todd (Sean Faris) hire a live-in nurse (Lyndon Smith) to be the caregiver for their sick son, only to discover that she is an "angel of death" intent on replacing Mira through any means necessary.

title: Queen of Snakes
synopsis: Directed by Christopher R. Mihm. With Stephanie Mihm, Rachel Grubb, Michael G. Kaiser, Christi Jean Williams. Angry at her daughter/caretaker for being directly responsible for her paraplegia, the reclusive Mrs. Crawford accidentally receives a package containing a mysterious amulet. The ancient treasure grants her the horrific powers of a lesser Norse goddess known as the Queen of Snakes and, in a quest to control them, becomes a danger to herself...and potentially the ENTIRE WORLD.

title: Rainstorm Rescue
synopsis: Directed by Yujia Ding. With Jianyi Lu, Liang Miao.

title: Bastion
synopsis: Directed by Pierre Udren. With Melodie Mayer, Lambert Micheau, Elizabeth O'Donovan. Left on her own in a world at war, Alix decides to join the house of Juliette, her grandmother. Isolated in the middle of nowhere, the old lady slowly seems to lose touch with reality.

title: Girl Lost: A Hollywood Story
synopsis: Голливудская история

title: Hunting Evil
synopsis: Directed by Charles Peterson. With Lanny Rethaber, Orchid Tao. After losing repeatedly to demons, a man opens a paranormal investigation operation to find the one who took his family. Corbin Bernsen delights as a bereaved father looking for his own son.

title: A Killer Awaits
synopsis: Directed by Charles Peterson. With Lanny Rethaber, Matt Robinson. Witnessing the murder of your father by your own drug addict mother can take its toll. Jason tries to live a normal life, but his personal demons may be why he's a suspect in a killing spree that has the homicide division in disbelief.

title: Weekend
synopsis: Directed by Riccardo Grandi. With Lorenzo Zurzolo, Alessio Lapice, Jacopo Olmo Antinori, Eugenio Franceschini. Four friends, trapped in a mountain hut, isolated by a blizzard, have one chance to save themselves

title: 4th Republic
synopsis: Directed by Ishaya Bako. With Alfred 'Six Foot Plus' Atungu, Kayode Aiyegbusi, Audu Altine, Faith Animasahul. It deals with an irregular governor elections where in a district there are murders, which makes the commisssions annul in that place, that causes the candidate who lost to start a campaign where she proclaims herself the legitimate president and takes the case to court so that they can be do justice to electoral fraud.

title: Feral State
synopsis: Directed by Jon Carlo. With AnnaLynne McCord, Octavio Pisano, Ronnie Gene Blevins, Veronica Burgess. A misfit gang of runaways and orphans are taken in by a dark and charismatic father figure who together wreak havoc throughout swamps and trailer parks of central Florida.

title: S'ids Lake
synopsis: Directed by Kevin Ruiz, Kevin North Ruiz. With Kristian Pierce, David Solesbee, Michael J. King, Tom McLaren. Sid, a scared-up boy from birth, accidentally kills a girl in his sleep. He first invents an alter-ego to cope with his misfortune accident.

title: Ratnamanjarii
synopsis: Directed by PraSiddh. With Suresh Bhat, Raj Charan, Omkar K, Anil Kumar. A botanist with photographic memory takes interest in a recurring nightmare and decides to dig deeper, only to stumble on a murder mystery.

title: Con mis propias manos
synopsis: Directed by Óscar González. With Roberto Palazuelos, Mercedes Regina, Alejandro Camacho, Axel Alcántara.

title: Miriam Graves
synopsis: Directed by Richard Tur. With Shelli St. George, Gilbert Fajardo, Tara Strand, Anastasia Blackwell. Miriam Graves is coming apart at the seams. The normal life she longed for has eluded her. Lonely and impoverished, she aimlessly wanders the streets of Los Angeles. Her privileged sister, Sarah, lives the good life, but burdened with having to deal with Miriam's paranoid delusions. As their relationship deteriorates, so goes what's left of Miriam's fragile sanity. Miriam believes an angel of death is stalking her - and she may not be imagining it.

title: A Killer Next Door
synopsis: Directed by Andrew Jones. With Nigel Barber, Derek Nelson, Jason Gregg, Patrick O'Donnell. A young girl begins to suspect that her neighbor on a quiet suburban street is fugitive family killer John List.

title: Khanana
synopsis: Directed by Raadha. With Aryavardan, Avinash, Karishma Baruah, Bank Janardhan. After losing everything, a celebrated architect sets out for vengeance and redemption.

title: Last Days In Waldo County
synopsis: Directed by Matt Enos. With Paul Bernacki, Brian Collins, Mike Curtis, Matt Enos. Independent narrative/pseudo-documentary shot in Waldo County, Maine, between the years 2010 and 2012. An experiment in white trash excess and violence.

title: Trouble Down East
synopsis: Directed by Matt Enos. With Brian Collins, Mike Curtis, Bill Enos, Matt Enos. An escalation of violence erupts between two small town criminals as a result of stolen money and a broken jaw.

title: Yokai
synopsis: Directed by Cristobal Echevensko. With Francisca Sfeir, Diego Vacarezza. Lydia (28) works at Mr. Yokai's jewelry store and knows that he keeps a valuable diamond in his mysterious house. In order to help her ill sister, she decides to steal it and asks her friend Juan (27) for help.

title: Sightless
synopsis: Directed by Cooper Karl. With Madelaine Petsch, Deniz Akdeniz, Alexander Koch, Matthew Yang King. After an attack renders her blind, Ellen Ashland withdraws from the world to recover. But soon she plunges into paranoia, unable to convince anyone that her assailant has returned to terrorize her by hiding in plain sight.

title: Silo
synopsis: Directed by Marshall Burnette. With Jeremy Holm, Jill Paice, Jack DiFalco, Jim Parrack. Disaster strikes when teenage Cody becomes the victim of a grain entrapment accident.

title: Guard
synopsis: Directed by Yuriy Bykov. With Yuriy Bykov, Vladislav Abashin, Alla Yuganova, Aleksandr Kuzmin. The measured life of the watchman of an abandoned sanatorium is disturbed by the arrival of a strange couple who asks to stay in one of the rooms. All three have something to hide from and what to hide in the wilderness.

title: Hacker's Game Redux
synopsis: Directed by Cyril Morin. With Pom Klementieff, Chris Schellenger, King Orba, Alena von Stroheim. Loise and Soyan embark upon an intense but dangerous romance. After being in a virtual world, will Soyan and Loise risk everything for true love?

title: Devaki
synopsis: Directed by H. Lohith. With Juin Bagchi, Sunil Banarjee, Sohini Bose, Mustaque Chowdari. Devaki a single parent, is frantically in search of her 10-year-old daughter Aaradhya on the dingy streets of Kolkata.

title: Sinister Seduction
synopsis: Directed by Damián Romay. With Kristina Klebe, Sebastian Cabanas, Tanner Buchanan, Carson Rowland. A recent widow is glad when her son finds a new friend. But it soon becomes clear that he's after a different type of companionship. Will their attraction be her undoing? And what secrets is hiding?

title: Crawl to Me Darling
synopsis: Directed by Adam Wilson. With Makenna Guyler, Scott Whatley. After a bad first date Millie awakes to find herself tied to a chair and facing the man responsible. He will stop at nothing to make her learn to love him even if it means killing her. Will she learn to crawl to him before her time is up?

title: Discovery rose
synopsis: Directed by Aydin Tanseli. Soldiers, civilians, gangsters and criminals had to get together for one reason, to stay alive of a zombie apocalypse while they are safeguarding in a ship until find a safe place to survive from possible nuclear strike.

title: Alone
synopsis: Directed by Vladislav Khesin. With Elizabeth Arends, Sara Anne, Albina Katsman, Bailey Coppola. Follows a writer seeking peace and solitude in the countryside to recover from tragedy and finish her book. However, as the welcoming country house turns into hell, she soon realizes that her inner demons are not the worst of her problems.

title: Gharga
synopsis: Directed by M. Shashidhar. With Raagavi Gowda, Arun Ramprasad. Kannada film industry's most anticipated movie Gharga. Gharga is a suspense thriller with high visual treat with the implementation of technical knowledge. Goose bumps will be guaranteed while watching the film. A must watch film for all movie lovers.

title: Kachindo
synopsis: Directed by Urvish Parikh. With Bhavwini Gandhi, Bhavwini Gandhi, Raj Jatania, Murali Mali. A newlyvaded girl shifted to Paris first time and there are family hijacked, this will is full of twist and turn a great suspense make you really surprise.

title: Student Teacher
synopsis: Directed by Isaac Deitz. With Jonathan Horne, Emily Dunlop, Thomas Torrey, Mackenzie Messick.

title: The Big Fat Lie
synopsis: Directed by Darasen Richards. With Tana Adelana, Mercy Aigbe, Eniola Badmus, Blossom Chukwujekwu. James runs into his celebrity crush at the wrong time and place, he is mistaken for a captain, and for that reason Eni falls in love with him. James decides to play along; Big mistake.

title: Trash
synopsis: Directed by Bettie Wilde. With Karly Adkins, Juston Brown, Kathy Chadwick, Jerad Chambers. Young Hacker in the 80's is bullied and seeks revenge by destroying their lives.

title: The End
synopsis: Directed by Yogesh Joshi. With Pranjal Bhatt.

title: The Deadly Welcoming
synopsis: Directed by Rob Niter. With Rob Niter, Rita Niter, Nayana Niter, Jeannine Oliver.

title: Paper Tiger
synopsis: Directed by Paul Kowalski. With Lydia Look, Alan Trong, Elaine Kao, Seth Numrich. An immigrant mother fears her mentally-ill teenaged son is turning into a school shooter.

title: Night Out
synopsis: Directed by Rakesh Adiga. With Shruti Goradia, Bharath Nanjappa, Akshay Pavar. Two friends take a late auto rickshaw ride which takes an unexpected turn leading to a series of surprises.

title: Im toten Winkel
synopsis: Directed by Michael Roitzsch. With Marcus König, Helenie Mende, Ulrich Schwarz, Sarah Bauer. Gregor Neuss is a journalist who knows what will make a good story. When a man is convicted of a crime he cannot have committed, Gregor starts his own investigation. But as he tries to uncover the truth, he becomes a target himself.

title: Single Slipper Size - 7
synopsis: Directed by Parthiban Radhakrishnan. With Parthiban Radhakrishnan, Gayathrie, Deepa Venkat. An emotionally unstable murder suspect explains the modus operandi behind the crimes he had committed to a few cops which helps in unfolding some intriguing revelation.

title: Judgement
synopsis: Directed by Sameer Ramesh Surve. With Madhav Abhyankar, Kishori Ambiye, Shalaka Apte, Vijay Banu. A maniacal IAS officer murders his wife for giving birth only to daughters and not a son. Fifteen years later, his eldest daughter Rujuta, now a lawyer, decides to re-open the case and fight for justice.

title: Who Wants Me Dead?
synopsis: Directed by Lisa France. With Karynn Moore, Jade Harlow, Rosalie McIntire, Robert Adamson. After the death of her estranged sister Nikki, with whom she hadn't seen since they were separated in foster care, Carly is surprised to learn that she is named in Nikki's will as guardian of her adopted daughter Mallie. Upon moving across the country to honor her sister's wishes, Carly quickly realizes that not only was Mallie left a substantial inheritance, but that not everyone is happy about the existence of a long lost sister. Someone else wants custody of rich Mallie, and they aren't going to let Carly stand in their way for much longer.

title: Confined
synopsis: Directed by William Chaffin. With John French, Caitlin Drance, Chris Dettone, Brahm Corstanje. Donnie's wife Sara is kidnapped. He's left video messages by Noah, the man that took her showing her held in captivity. Noah gives Donnie one week to find Sara or she'll disappear. Noah presents all of his motivations upfront to Donnie showing him he has nothing to lose. How far will a man go for revenge when he does not fear consequences? How far will Donnie go to save Sara? Or will Sara save herself?

title: Friend Request
synopsis: Directed by Roger M. Bobb. With Kruze Princeton Dillard, Tanya Alina Galván, Marc Grapey, Vicky Jeudy. A successful family man is seduced by an ex-girlfriend who is out for revenge for a past wrongdoing.

title: Manipulation
synopsis: Directed by Pascal Verdosci. With Klaus Maria Brandauer, Sebastian Koch, Thomas Douglas, Susanne Abelein. Set in Zurich in the 1950s, a special agent who is near retirement receives a major assignment

title: Psychosynthesis
synopsis: Directed by Noam Kroll. With Jess Adams, Johnny Day, Stephanie Pearson, Gracelyn Awad Rinke. A sickly young mother's life unravels when she receives a heart transplant and begins to take on her donor's personality and memories.

title: Las Furias
synopsis: Directed by Tamae Garateguy. With Daniel Aráoz, Federica Cafferata, Celina Demarchi, Guadalupe Docampo. A curse threaten an impossible love between a young man from a Huarpes community and the daughter of the landholder of the town.

title: The Shift
synopsis: Directed by Alessandro Tonda. With Clotilde Hesme, Adamo Dionisi, Adam Amara, Jan Hammenecker. An Islamic terror attack at a school in Brussels.

title: The Apex
synopsis: Directed by Che Davis, Devlin Dinish. With Nick Benzschawel, Lisa Carswell, Ajamu Davis, Che Davis.

title: The Battle of Shangri-la
synopsis: Directed by Severino Neto, Rafael de Carvalho. With Luciano Bortoluzzi, Maria Ceiça, Laíze Cãmara, Rodrigo Fernandes. After the death of his foster parents, a young businessman goes into a journey in search of his biological mother. During the search he faces the social and religious prejudice that surrounds the LGBTTQ Brazilian community.

title: Hometown Killer
synopsis: Directed by Jeff Hare. With Kaitlyn Black, Ashley Gallegos, Jon Prescott, Kelly Marcus. A young woman finds her life in danger when an emotionally disturbed police officer she bullied in high school targets her in a twisted plan of revenge.

title: Immobilia Crime Story
synopsis: Directed by Khaled El Hagar. With Hany Adel, Tarek Abdel Aziz, Nahed El Sebaï, Azza Al-Husseiny. Immobilia Crime Story , is a psycho drama set in Cairo City Centre . It examines loneliness and the ways in which social media have taken control over our lives and relationships . The narrative focuses on Kamal Helmy , a famous writer in his late forties , who lives alone in Cairo's famous Immobilia Building . Since the death of his wife and his children leaving home , he has suffered from loneliness and a form of schizophrenia, which he has kept a closely guarded secret . One day he invites to his flat , a girl called Samah , whom he has befriended on Facebook , in an attempt to alleviate his isolation . But after she arrives , an accident occurs and he discovers , together with his neighbour and best friend Habib , that he has been used by her . Subsequently a number of mysterious murders start to happen in The building . . . .

title: The Last Stub Master
synopsis: Directed by Jonathan Gill. With Lj Ugarte, J.J. Crowne, Doug Walker, Jonathan Gill. After ten years of harrowing guilt, Jonathan Gill, a private investigator, is forced to face the death of his best friend, while using his "special" talents for one last job. Meanwhile, talk show sensation, Ethan Toth, is drawn into his most dangerous story yet.

title: Black Pool
synopsis: Directed by Dustin Morrow. With Tom Walton, Amber Stonebraker, Todd Van Voris, Kailey Rhodes. A gripping thriller about a revenge-fueled, cat-and-mouse game of imprisonment and interrogation between two Irish immigrants whose mysterious shared past sets them on a collision course with violence.

title: Entrapped: A Day of Terror
synopsis: A Day of Terror

title: Kalpten Gerdanlik
synopsis: Directed by Sultan Nil Turan. With Soydan Soydas, Suavi Eren, Tayfun Sav, Altug Seckiner.

The box can extend Susan's life using the memories embedded in the walls of their house. But Michael soon finds out that using the box comes with severe consequences.

Dan Hawk, an ex-detective turned writer, is re-instated onto the force after returning to his home town. A serial killer has 'donned the guise' of Hawks most famous book creation, and has begun to kill people off one by one.

title: Mopa diary
synopsis: Directed by Mahesh Rane. With John Dsilva, Satish Gawas, Rajesh Karekar, Dinesh Nayak.

synopsis: Directed by K.C. Binu. With Ajith, Sobha Ajith, Kottayam Nazeer, Kochu Preman.

Set against the backdrop of Brexit and its impending doom! Interwoven with this is a LGBTQ tale of a love triangle of three matriarchal characters - both stories dealing with slavery, gentrification, art, love, race, mental health and politics.

Yathaw is Myat Noe's friend who helps them for her wedding. She has a younger brother,Nat Shine Ko who is the son of her father 2nd wife. Yathaw hates Nat Shine Ko and she always quarrells with him. One day,she break the photo album of his mother, Nat Shine Ko acridity to her. Then, Tracy and Nat Shine Ko meet and they try to reprisal to each others.

They are charged with a dangerous mission against the mafia men, who steal a large diamond shipment. But Orabi Decides to carry out the operation for his personal account, and runs away to Morocco, and start settling accounts and fierce battles.

When Karina becomes friends with Lena and her daughter Mallie, she begins to suspect that Mallie isn't Lena's daughter at all, but a girl named Emily who was kidnapped from her biological parents several years prior.

title: C++
synopsis: Directed by Suresh Leon Rey. With Suresh Leon Rey, Adarsha Sanjeeva, Vishu Veer, Viraj Vismith. An engineer is dragged against his will into a whirlpool of criminal conspiracy.

title: Steel Rain 2
synopsis: Саммит

synopsis: Directed by Richard Switzer. With Natalie Brown, Sarah Fisher, Alexa Rose Steele, Reha Sandill. Hope has always been close to her daughter Lacy. But since her divorce from her husband, Hope has been worried about Lacy, who is struggling to cope. So Hope is excited when Lacy brings home a new friend, Cassie, whose parents recently divorced as well. Lacy and Cassie quickly become the best of friends. But when Cassie begins to drive a wedge between Lacy and her mother, Hope begins to wonder if Cassie is the godsend she first imagined.

It is a father's story told to his son about himself when he was a younger man and involved in the world of street racing.

title: Soul Reaper: The Cursed Gem of Ahriman
synopsis: The Cursed Gem of Ahriman

title: Lifelines

The young model Zhong Tonghui was 8 when she witnessed her mother's suicide from which the nightmare had been tormenting her. One day, Tonghui received a mysterious invitation to the funeral during her modeling session. The deceased was her wealthy aunt who had no children, she asked the housekeeper to invite Tonghui whom she seldomly in contact with when she was alive. Tonhui agreed to attend the funeral out of sympathy. Upon arriving at her aunt's mansion in a remote countryside, Tonghui met a gentle and elegant woman, and a handsome man, Li Baile, who was also invited to attend the funeral. For a few nights Tonghui couldn't sleep well as the scene of her mother's suicide appeared in the nightmares again. She also discovered blood in the bathtub of the bedroom, same like her mother's death in the house when she was young. Tonghui made a secret investigation with Li Baili, and saw that there seemed to be someone who's still living in her aunt's room. Does it mean that her aunt's still alive? Tonghui was puzzled day by day, only Li Baile's companion comforted her. One day, they took a walk in the field, but a pair of gangsters suddenly appeared, accusing Li Baile of being an ungrateful guy who changed his name to be a gigolo. Li Baile used to be called Yang Lihao, a poor guy not worth to be mentioned. When the gangsters robbed Li Baile's ring away, Li Baile suddenly changed to another different person with shock and helplessness in his eyes, shouting from his mouth with one word

synopsis: The Mission

title: Dank
synopsis: Directed by Pushkar Manohar. With Sharad Ponkshe, Smita Shewale, Ananda Karekar, Falguni Rajani. One renowned and reputed doctor who encounters unusual paranormal activities and finds his colleagues in the same mess. The situation becomes critical when killings of crime partner's start and the doctor is helpless. He confesses his crime with near ones but they refuse to help and he finds himself alone in the hands of a girl which is a GHOST.

title: Frequent Visitors
synopsis: Directed by Moe McCoy. With Jonathon Allen, C.J. Ballard, Sadat Banks, Terence A. Banks. A female serial killer is on the loose in the Western Michigan area - Grand Rapids and Holland. A focused detective is determined to track her down before it's too late. Who will be her next victim?

title: Bhayam
synopsis: Directed by Veer Narayan. With Bina Bhatt, Gaurav Chansoria, Angad Dev Dogra, Ankita Kashyap. The word Bhayam means Fear. The story is all about obsession for someone. It's a love story of Shree and Myra which no longer exists due to clashes between the families. Shree and Myra were the film making students where they along with their others friends had gone to a haunted hills to shoot for their short film for their final project. When they go to the hills for shoot they experienced some supernatural activities.Group members started missing Thus the obsession, thrill, horror and action clearly defines the name of the film. It will be quite interesting to watch the film in the theatre as it has all the elements.

title: All Against All
synopsis: Directed by Andrej Kosak. With Vlado Novák, Silva Cusin, Aleksandra Balmazovic, Iva Krajnc. A political drama with elements of a thriller discusses politics, electoral fraud, and the decay of moral values, taking place in the fictional town of Rovte under the idyllic Alps. Franta, a corrupt mayor, is about to lose the election. After a TV debate, where he fails utterly, Franta calls his mistress Jozica in desperation. She advises him to seek the aid of Fleischmann, a criminal who is the only one capable of solving the problem on such short notice. After all, there are only four days left until the elections.

title: Souvenirs

A woman and four men who barely know each other find themselves in an apartment in the sky above Paris. They have all been the victim of the same domineering pervert who is locked in a room. That night, they decided to finish it. In turn, they tell each other memories that bind them to this man and enter the room to confront him. But what happens between the monster and them remains their secret.

title: Vitrum - Riverberi nello specchio
synopsis: Directed by Marco Cei. With Chiara Ciofini, Carlo Monni, Giuditta Natali Elmi, Marzia Risaliti.

title: In the Black Box
synopsis: Directed by Sasha Alessandra Carlesi.

synopsis: Directed by Rosalinda Books. With Cory Kirk, Elliot, Adam Serio, Cody Gidley. A hairstylist becomes a serial killer and blames his abusive upbringing for his murderous tendencies.

synopsis: Directed by Mathilde Nocquet. With Taylor Ferguson, Kate Peck, Charlotte Williars.

synopsis: Directed by Kaila York. With Madison McLaughlin, Ava Allan, Heather McComb, Kara Royster. A popular cheerleader's life is turned upside down after a house fire kills her father.

synopsis: Directed by Omar Forero. With Oscar Alarcón, Fernando Bacilio, Robert de la Cruz, Hector Fabio Paredes. A region in Peru scarred by corruption and crime, held hostage by criminal syndicates. In the midst of all this

In the next 36 hours of his life, the mysterious Kamala turns Safar's perfect day into a nightmare.

title: Lorong
synopsis: Directed by Hestu Saputra. With Winky Wiryawan, Prisia Nasution, Nova Eliza, T. Rifnu Wikana. Waking up after giving birth, Mayang gets tragic news from her husband Reza

synopsis: Directed by Ajai Vasudev. With Mammootty, Meena, Raj Kiran, Siddique. A ruthless moneylender must tackle a wicked man's plan to outsmart his way out of the debt to achieve what's rightfully his.

The hunt for a highly intelligent and enigmatic professional killer leads to a novel named 'Nandanavanadol', within the pages of which lies the answer to his true identity. But what could be the mystery hidden between the lines of a novel revolving around a hockey match set in the 1970s?

title: Park Reverse Neutral Drive, PRND (Director's cut)

synopsis: A Grammar of Death

The movie cast includes Vijay Krishna, Firdous Banu, Zara khan are playing in the main lead roles while Chinni Krishna scored music.

title: Lady Usher

This motion picture is a suspense/thriller based on the short story; The Fall of the House of Usher by Edgar Allan Poe. This updated re-telling is written by award winning filmmaker George Adams and possesses the quintessential features of the Gothic

synopsis: Directed by Gabriel Ng Marino, Angela Paolini. With Gabriel Ng Marino, Angela Paolini, Gabriel Yepez, Nathalie Dlima.

synopsis: Directed by Bartosz Kruhlik. With Marek Braun, Marcin Hycnar, Marcin Zarzeczny, Agnieszka Skibicka. Three men, one place and one event that will change the life of each one of them.

title: Prison 13
synopsis: Directed by Kensaku Watanabe. With Mayu Hotta, Tomomi Itano, Mamiko Itô, Kenshirô Iwai. Inspired by the experiment at the Stanford prison in 1971 the film depicts university gal Mari who participates in an experiment where a controlled group is brought together in an environment they quickly recognize as a jail. The group is divided into prisoners and guards and given a week. Within the controlled group Mari is given the key and is a security guard. It does not take long for the assigned roles to act the part, take on the persona and receive or inflict violence.

title: Trauma
