synopsis: Directed by Mark Jury. With Scott Clarkson, Michael Austin, Flavia Fazenda. When a family take revenge on a lawyer.

title: The Fall
synopsis: Directed by Diego Rocha. With Letícia Bezamat, Jefferson da Fonseca, Rodrigo dos Santos, Beth Grandi. To overcome the fear of losing his ill and aging grandfather, a forensic photographer needs to discover the truth behind the alleged suicide of an elderly man.

title: Doctor Death
synopsis: Directed by Rob Pallatina. With Gina Vitori, Anthony Jensen, Matthew Pohlkamp, Kate Watson. After a skiing accident, Sarah's life is saved thanks to a brilliant surgeon, Dr. Vincent. But when Dr. Vincent mistakes Sara's gratitude for love, he becomes obsessed with her, determined to have her at any cost.

title: Wife, i
synopsis: Directed by Gssp Kalyan. With Surya Akondi, Gunjann Aras, Mozammel Hoshen Chowdhury, Fida Gill. I lost my wife. Who is responsible?

title: Untold Body
synopsis: Directed by Isara Nadee. With Patty Hokari, Chen Jinyun, Shan Sijie. Based on the Asian horror comic book Yin and Yang, this film tells the story of the Yin and Yang, which is commonly known as the world in the Republic of China. It is said that this mysterious coffin will have a horrible thing. According to the Republic of China Times, in the 34th year of the Republic of China (1945 during the Kuomintang rule), a strange child disappeared. A group of children playing hide and seek on the back hill suddenly had a mysterious disappearance. Since then, whenever a thunder is hit, there will always be a figure of a child on the roof of the temple behind the temple. The bizarre things happen one after another. It is the disappearing child revenge coming back for revenge, or the legendary Is yin and yang blaming?

title: Bell Chamber
synopsis: Directed by Ning Liu. With Zehao An, Monica Chan, Pei-Pei Cheng, Shanliushui Gao. Based on a Thai ghost story of Kuman Thong, the film revolves around a woman who has caused the death of her young brother a long time ago. When she returns to the old house where they lived before, she finds herself haunted by the spirit of her young brother wanting to take revenge for his death.

title: House of Good and Evil
synopsis: Directed by David Mun. With Rae Olivier, Christian Oliver, Marietta Marich, Jordan Rhodes. After a family tragedy in the chaotic city, Chris and Maggie Conley, in a last-ditch effort to save their dying marriage, purchase an isolated home in the deepest woods, to which they quickly discover evil has a key.

title: Dark
synopsis: Directed by Paul Schrader. With Nicolas Cage, Irène Jacob, Anton Yelchin. A government agent must track down and kill a terrorist before he loses his full memory from dementia.

title: The Translator
synopsis: Directed by Rana Kazkaz, Anas Khalaf. With Ziad Bakri, Yumna Marwan, David Field, Sawsan Arshid. A Syrian exile living in Australia returns when his brother is taken into custody by the Assad regime in 2011.

title: Dev-Ansh: Son of God
synopsis: Son of God

title: Kill-Fist
synopsis: Directed by James Lee. With Pearlly Chua, Mike Chuah, Jovi Heng, Yeet Koe. Zhang a middle aged man struggling with a dead end job as an insurance sales person, on the verge of divorce with his wife, losing custody of her daughter and on top of all this he had to take care of his father who's suffering Alzheimer's. Unknowingly Zhang was invited to join an underground fighting game for financial purposes but eventually Zhang becomes hooked on the fights and turns professional.

title: Hero
synopsis: Directed by P.S. Mithran. With Sivakarthikeyan, Abhay Deol, Arjun Sarja, Kalyani Priyadarshan. A fraudster gets to fulfill his childhood dream of being a superhero when he takes on a ruthless businessman whose business strategy is to crush the dreams of children.

title: Mockingbird
synopsis: Directed by Martin R. McGowan. With Mackenzie Barmen, Kosmos Bye, Aly Dynda, Ashleigh Gantert. Set in a fictional town in Pennsylvania, a private investigator hired to solve a decades-long string of murders uncovers a terrible secret.

title: The Dead Sleep
synopsis: Directed by Vicki de Mey. With Chris Armstrong, Sarah Foret, Robert Fente, Tatiana Armstrong. It could be that, after death, our spirits need to forget this world. Or maybe something in our mortalities is worth fighting for, even worth dying for a second time. In this supernatural thriller, Paul Wells plans to find out. His body has been in a grave for five years while his spirit witnesses the consequences of his transgressions. Driven to save his daughter from his unfortunate mistakes, Paul twists the boundary between the living and the dead.

title: Tag X
synopsis: Directed by Manuel Weiss. With Christina Arends, Joachim Birzele, Carina Diesing, Arianna Fritz. A single, widowed woman is abruptly torn from her difficult daily routine by the abduction of her daughter, only to discover a horrible family secret.

title: Human Animals
synopsis: Directed by Lex Ortega. With Roberto Duarte, Aroa Gimeno, Adrian Limon, Adriana Louvier. A married couple and their young daughter are terrified of the neighbors' dog, which ends up biting the girl. The dog is sacrificed to the desolation of its owners who saw it as their son. They enter the married couple's house at night to take revenge. What they want is justice

title: Parcel
synopsis: Directed by Indrasis Acharya. With Saswata Chatterjee, Rituparna Sengupta, Koushik Adhikari, Juin Bagchi. Parcel is story of a doctor couple and Nandini the female protagonist suddenly starts receiving some unanimous mysterious parcels with some of her older and recent photographs. This process creates a turbulence in their family and they go verge of terminating their marriage. Nandini tries to find out the root cause anticipating some black mailing purpose with association of her past wrong doings (As per her perception ). Its a multi-layered social story under a health system backdrop where nothing comes as explicit but a fear psychosis based on anticipation jeopardize everything.

title: Messages Deleted
synopsis: Удаленные сообщения

title: BearCat Wilson: Catfish Bob's Revenge
synopsis: Catfish Bob's Revenge

title: Operation Wolves
synopsis: Directed by Chen-Yang Yin. With Joel Adrian, Junyao Li, Kaiyu Xie. When medical worker Li Yao offers medical help to local residents in a village in Aiduli as a volunteer, he is suddenly attacked by bandits and captured. His father learns about it, and contacts Zhang Zhen and Wu You's security team. The security team saves Li Yao, but some other compatriots are still controlled by the bandits. So the security team goes back, takes away the bandits' means of transportation to send out signals in a high place. The security team members have a fierce fight with the bandits. Zhang Zhen, Lei Ting and Wu Ming die successively. Under the protection of Wu You, Li Yao and other survivors finally see people that come to rescue them.

title: Helen
synopsis: Directed by Mathukutty Xavier. With Anna Ben, Lal, Noble Babu Thomas, Aju Varghese. An ordinary suburban girl suddenly disappears, leaving her loved ones in a desperate search as she must face the ultimate battle - the one for her life.

title: Spell
synopsis: Directed by Mark Tonderai. With Omari Hardwick, Loretta Devine, Lorraine Burroughs, Hannah Gonera. A man crash lands in rural Appalachia and awakens in the attic of a traditional Hoodoo practitioner. He desperately tries to break free from her dark magic and save his family from a sinister ritual before the rise of the blood moon.

title: Samsara
synopsis: Directed by Abhijit Guha, Sudeshna Roy. With Rahul Banerjee, Ritwick Chakraborty, Sudiptaa Chakraborty, Tanushree Chakraborty. The story is of three friends from school who meet up after about 18 years. One of them is a successful businessman, the other runs his in laws business and third one is a writer with a writers block. He asks old friends to help. In the process the three get back some fun of the past. But as they can't help the writer and some strange things keep occurring the three friends quarrel. But then the writer gets a clue and the three friends embark on a journey. In the strange place they land up, the three keep meeting people who are look alike from their past. Initially they try to reason, but finally as all three get involved and remember the stories involving these look alike the three start fretting. They are uncomfortable and worried - Disturbed. And this disturbance, distress, confusion, turmoil . It's their past present and future all rolled into each other..Their mind is in a mess - Old memories comes back haunting them.

title: The Estate
synopsis: Directed by James Kapner. With Eliza Coupe, Greg Finley, Chris Baker, Eric Roberts. When the spoiled son and newest wife of a billionaire patriarch plot to murder him, they form a psycho-sexual bond with their brutally handsome hitman as they kill and kill (and kill) in their quest for wealth and recognition.

title: Husma
synopsis: Directed by Sudesh Wasantha Pieris. With Dasun Pathirana, Pubudu Chathuranga, Isuru Lokuhettiarachchi, Chamathka Lakmini. A famous young actress arrives dead to a morgue. Three men enticed by her beauty decides to explore her nude body.

title: The Crazy Between Us
synopsis: Directed by Richard Poche. With Emily Corbo, Vera Zadoinov.

title: Il gatto e la luna
synopsis: Directed by Roberto Lippolis. With Maria Grazia Cucinotta, Enzo Garinei, Enzo Storico, Enrico Lo Verso. A man is found dead in an office. Sonya, a charming 55-year-old woman, has abandoned her family for a love affair with a younger man. The two stories end up intertwining but nothing is as it seems.

title: King of the Road
synopsis: Directed by Danyael Sugawara. With Guido Pollemans, Majd Mardo, Sophie Höppener, Rian Gerritsen. Truck driver Barry is forced to accept a new co-driver, the Dutch Moroccan Sadiq. During their international ride, the tension rises high in the cabin. Does a special friendship arise here or does it lead to an ultimate confrontation?

title: Signal 100
synopsis: Directed by Lisa Takeba. With Kanna Hashimoto, Yûta Koseki, Toshiki Seto, Shouma Kai. A group of high school students are forced into a game where they are hypnotized to commit suicide on an unknown command. Where no one is safe from a sudden death, how can they avoid their fates?

title: Text
synopsis: Directed by Klim Shipenko. With Alexander Petrov, Kristina Asmus, Ivan Yankovskiy, Sofya Ozerova. College student Ilya spends 7 years in prison on a fake drug bust. Coming out, he wants revenge on the dirty cop, Pyotr. He gets Pyotr's smartphone filled with personal info and starts texting - pretending to be Pyotr.

title: Raahu
synopsis: Directed by Subbu Vedula. With Dinesh Akki, Kishore Babu, Ganesh Bandi, Srinivasa Rao Bethapudi. Bhanu suffers from 'conversion disorder a.k.a hysterical blindness' where she goes temporarily blind under severe stress, in her case triggered upon seeing blood, must fight her enemy who inflicts more bloodshed than she ever imagined.

title: Alter
synopsis: Directed by Steve Bacic. With Steve Bacic, Anthony Bolognese, Chelsea Gill, Bruce Crawford. Convinced that he's found the man who abducted and sadistically abused him as a child, Steve Bryant is determined to get him to confess to what he did - by any means necessary.

title: Underground
synopsis: Directed by Tinieblas González. With Brendan Michael Coughlin, Pino Moreau, Savitri Ceballos, Scott Cleverdon. Four young graffiti artists explore a new subway system, where they discover a half-human creature.

title: Intuition
synopsis: Directed by Mckinson Souverain. With Ladele Tojuola, Julian Hanlan, Ashley Arielle. Intuition takes place with workaholic relationship therapist, Dr. David Francis, who tries to help Kenny deal with his trust issues. The Doctor fails to realize his patient is having an affair with his fiancée Karen.

title: Jack Stone: End of the Line
synopsis: End of the Line

title: Edge
synopsis: Directed by Mark Cornwell. With Ted Archer, Lewis Campbell, Mark Cornwell, Conor Harris.

title: A Night in 97
synopsis: Directed by Sam Prudence. With Roger Ringrose, Ryan Early, Tracy Bargate, Matt Beauman-Jones. Set during the 1997 general election 'Scandal In 97' follows Bertie Oldcross, Labour's candidate for Scarborough and Whitby, and his campaign manager Simon, as they attempt to cover up a crime on the eve of polling day.

title: Elimination
synopsis: Directed by Juan Carlos Vargas. With Danny Vasquez, Nicole Warner, Daniel Fanaberia, Meredith Grau. Ten actors audition on a reality show for a million dollars. All they have to do is survive three killers, and each other - streaming live over the Internet.

title: Hauntsville
synopsis: Directed by K.C. Amos, Dale Stelly. With Kent Victor Schuelke, Saye Yabandeh, Roberto Sanchez, Sofie Norman. Hauntsville is a horror film about a husband and his family moving across the mid-west into a decent priced home to start a new job. The real estate agent did not inform the family on the past gruesome history of the home. The past residents unfortunately have been murdered inside the home and their spirits still lurks the premises long after their demise. The ghosts haunt the new family in an attempt to make them aware that their next door neighbor "Abe, 55 year-old disturbed man" is the real killer. Abe tries to make the family feel welcomed to the new neighborhood until one day he just looses it.There are two detectives on the case that have been trying to solve the mysterious deaths for years, but no leads have come up until now.

title: Hysteria
synopsis: Directed by Frank Lin. With Cheyenne Jackson, Laura Allen, Jeanene Fox, David Goryl. To celebrate their 10th-year high school reunion, a group of twenty-somethings throw an intimate house party to celebrate the event. However, when one of the group accidentally kills another with no explanation. As more brutalities occur, could this be the work of the individuals themselves or possessions by "The Walker"?

title: Killer Daddy Issues
synopsis: Directed by Danny J. Boyle. With Jillian Murray, Carolyn McCormick, Lisa Thornhill, Dan Amboyer. An equestrian discovers her family's estate harbors an unfathomable secret.

title: Killer Queen
synopsis: Directed by Ramin Fahrenheit. With Ramin Fahrenheit, Bruce Hayward, Roozbeh Jahanbazi, Aleksandra Maslennikova. Girl meets Boy does drugs and kills.

title: A Taste of Blood
synopsis: Directed by Santiago Fernández Calvete. With Lautaro Bettoni, Germán Palacios, Alfonsina Carrocio, Tomás Carullo Lizzio. The uncertain hours after a vampire hunt when it's unclear if the hunter has himself been turned into a creature of the night. Will his family find out in time, or will their sentiment make them easy prey for the novice nightwalker?

title: Byeonshin
synopsis: Directed by Hongsun Kim. With Sung-Woo Bae, Dong-il Sung, Jang Young-Nam, Kim Hye-jun. An evil spirit that changes faces infiltrates one family placing one brother in danger while the other tries to save him.

title: Kumbarees
synopsis: Directed by Sagar Hari. With Vijayakumar, Ramesh Pisharody, Eldho Mathew, Aswin Jose. Sagar reveals that it revolves around six to seven characters."Ashwin plays a mechanic named Shambu and Tito his friend John. There is a love track involving Shambu and a girl named Jincy. Their lives are changed forever upon their encounter with three other characters-Manu, Meera, and Anil. They become intertwined in an incident pertaining to a medical shop.'Kumbarees' is something friends call each other in Alappuzha. It's the Alappuzha equivalent of machan, or aliya, or saho, or bro. The film is essentially about friendship.

title: The Net
synopsis: Directed by Henry Jollands. With Karen Hunter, Henry Jollands, Adam Mitchell, Steven Pereira. There are many things that are unseen in this world. What we see on a daily basis could very well be the tip of the iceberg. With technology being an asset in most people's day to day lives, it's only a matter of time until it becomes a threat to the life of the user. In a world of danger, extremism and terror, it's becoming easier to publicise one's views, outlook - or even their plans. The Dark Web

title: Evil VID: Decade in agony
synopsis: Decade in agony

title: Peo-jeul
synopsis: Directed by Jinseung Lim. With Seonghyun Ji, Kiyoung Kang, Semi Lee. Dojun found himself that he became a murderer after having affair with Seryun who just looked like his wife. He is fighting for the truth behind the puzzle that he is in.

title: Iced Out
synopsis: Directed by Charlene Jeter. With Scott Konkel, Kenny Santiago Marrero, Charlene Jeter, Kaiti Wallen. When ICE shows up at Oscar Sanchez's job, he must confess his illegal status to his wife, Billie. While on the run, an ICE agent is killed and Oscar is framed for the murder.

title: Ethalaya
synopsis: Directed by Nalaka Withange. With Kelum Kularathne, Shyam Fernando, Dharmapriya Dias, Chamathka Lakmini.

title: Cheelzadap
synopsis: Directed by Dharmessh Mehta. With Twisha Bhatt, Ajay Chanchadiya, Hardik Chauhan, Kalpesh Chouhan. Cashier working in bank threaten by underworld don to be part of robbery. Things get complicated after look-alike of cashier is found in another city

title: Death By Midnight
synopsis: Directed by Chris Staviski, Vito Trabucco. With Steven Alexander, Saima Azhar, Kenny Campos, Chinook. Believed to be cursed by his father, Mike travels to Seattle in the hope that killing him will end both of their suffering.

title: Locked
synopsis: Directed by Simon Peacemaker. With Hilda Dokubo, Charles Granville, Grace-Charis Bassey, Sunny Neji. When a young woman brings her fiancee to visit her parents, she discovers that her mother killed her father in a psychotic fit after she found out that he was about to leave her for a younger woman. The mother proceeds to holds her daughter and her fiancee hostage.

title: Chakravyuh
synopsis: Directed by Satyen Verma. With Niharika Bhatt, Yamini Joshi, Zakir Khan, Jignesh Modi.

title: Maal
synopsis: Directed by Shubhendu Lalit. With Suved Kulkarni, Akshay Kale-Patil, Vaaman Vasishth, Saurabh Patwardhan. Suvya is on a torturous month long break from alcohol, and desperately looks for weed to fill the void as a documentary crew follows him around. He enlists the help of his two friends, and the three guys wander through the night, looking to score though the uncertain haze of smoke and hopeless youth.

title: The Belko Experiment
synopsis: Directed by Greg McLean. With John Gallagher Jr., Tony Goldwyn, Adria Arjona, John C. McGinley. In a twisted social experiment, eighty Americans are locked in their high-rise corporate office in Bogotá, Colombia, and ordered by an unknown voice coming from the company's intercom system to participate in a deadly game of kill or be killed.

title: Missing Audrey
synopsis: Directed by G.R. Claveria. With G.R. Claveria, Teresa Noreen, Brandon Rogers, Neelam Sahota. The story of a father's obsession to get his daughter back.

title: See Saw
synopsis: Directed by Tom Muschamp. With Aimee Denaro, Michael Graves, Mike DiGiacinto, Lou Martini Jr.. A woman with no memory of her past utilizes the eyes and ears of New York's surveillance empire in a quest to find out who she is.

title: Zindagi
synopsis: Directed by Seth Khalil. With Ijaz Baloch, Saeed Shad, Khalil Faqeer, Mohammad Hoth.

title: Vajramukhi
synopsis: Directed by Aditya Kunigal. With Sanjana Naidu, Dilip Pai, Neethu Shetty. A chance encounter with a mysterious girl in a resort throws the lives of a group of friends into chaos, as hostile spirits and eerie incidents start haunting them.

title: Taish
synopsis: Directed by Bejoy Nambiar. With Harshvardhan Rane, Jim Sarbh, Pulkit Samrat, Kriti Kharbanda. A story of friendship and loss of innocence when two worlds clash amid a wedding when a secret exposes a betrayal, and innocent friends converge with dangerous criminals and intense violence.

title: Delhi Bus
synopsis: Directed by Sharique Minhaj. With Neelima Azim, Azad Hussain, Tahir Kamaal Khan, Samiran Singh.

title: Lateef
synopsis: Directed by Sharique Minhaj. With Azad Hussain, Tahir Kamaal Khan.

title: Trim Line
synopsis: Directed by Brandon Colletti. With Lung Ti, Tony Devon, M.J. Dougherty, Billy Zane. Explorers tackle the highest mountain to encounter a time dimension.

title: The Prince
synopsis: Directed by Brian A. Miller. With Jason Patric, Jessica Lowndes, Gia Mantegna, Bruce Willis. When his daughter is kidnapped, a retired assassin is drawn back into the life he gave up. To rescue her, he must confront his former rival.

title: An Exquisite Meal
synopsis: Directed by Robert Bruce Carter. With Mike Jimerson, Amrita Dhaliwal, Victoria Nugent, Ross Magyar. A dinner party descends into sex, violence, and the absurd when one of the guests discovers something unexpected about what's for dinner.

title: Pagan Peak VR
synopsis: Directed by Ioulia Isserlis, Max Sacker. With Bennet Büker, Philipp Droste, Ioulia Isserlis, Christian Stotz. A journey to the darkest corners of the human mind.

title: 86 Melrose Avenue
synopsis: Directed by Lili Matta. With Dade Elza, Gregory Zarian, Anastasia Antonia, Michael Polak. An ex-marine with PTSD storms into a gallery, taking hostages and forcing them to confront their complex past and looming mortality, as time ticks by.

title: Whispers
synopsis: Directed by Elliot Masters, Sam Weisberg. With Andy Deluca, Ray Gorlin, Emmet Kowler, Elliot Masters. A College Professor begins to unravel during an unforgiving Midwestern winter.

title: Megan Is Missing
synopsis: Directed by Michael Goi. With Amber Perkins, Rachel Quinn, Dean Waite, Jael Elizabeth Steinmeyer. Two teenage girls encounter an Internet child predator.

title: Is My Daughter Really Dead?
synopsis: Directed by Colin Edward Lawrence. With Stephanie Charles, Matthew Pohlkamp, Mike Erwin, Stevie Lynn Jones. Olivia struggles to sort out truth from fiction after her daughter mysteriously vanishes during a camping trip with the new neighbors.

title: Deadly Promises
synopsis: Directed by Joseph Ramos. With Julian Crouser, Isabella Salazar, Michael-John Wolfe, Braeden Wilson. At Castle Park High, both Dillon and Travis have a crush on Megan. Dillon would kill for her but not if a hidden secret in the basement kills them first.

title: Fomalhaut
synopsis: Directed by Wann Teems. With Pablo Rodríguez Albi, Gastón Frías, Flor Piturro.

title: Buris
synopsis: Directed by Claus Klok. With Pia Aggerholm, Andreas Mosekjær Bjørn, Helle Borregaard, Christine Bruun. During the investigation of the death of several young people caused by a new drug, Red Devil, the police suspect a connection to an old danish legend - the legend of Prince Buris and Liden Kirsten.

title: Mayuran
synopsis: Directed by Nandan Subbarayan. With Anjan Dev, Ashmtha K. Dogra, Vela Ramamoorthy. A college student locks horns with a dreaded gangster after getting to know that his friend was killed by the latter.

title: Manhunt
synopsis: Directed by Charles Solly. With Leo Broadhead, Adam Cavender, Ashley Clarredge, Jordan Flynn. When Rodger Flank is invited to a college drinking game, things start to go terribly wrong. Told out of sequence, and from both sides of the fence, Manhunt is a story of revenge, psychosis, and childhood's end.

title: Priyappetta Nattukare
synopsis: Directed by Sreejith Paleri. With Said Alharbi, Mala Aravindan, Bala, M.R. Gopakumar. A political thriller centered around a communist party activist and his squabbles with the activist of an opposing party.

title: Chitkar
synopsis: Directed by Latesh Shah. With Chhaya Vora, Sujata Mehta, Hiten Kumar. This is a story of a dedicated doctor Markand Shah (Hiten Kumar), who puts everything at stake to cure his patient Ratna (Sujata Mehta), who is battling mental illness. He goes out of his way to get her the much sought-after acceptance from the society and even marries her. He provides her a 'normal' life, at the cost of even going against his own family and society to an extent.

title: Fourtouna Sto Ano Peukochori
synopsis: Directed by Kostas Christias. With Kostas Christias, Angelos Spyrakis. Evil little Teletubbies are starting to conquer the world after an experiment goes wrong. The only place still standing is a village called Ano Peukochori and now it has to fight back.

title: Studenac
synopsis: Directed by Borko Brajovic. With Predrag Vasovic, Borko Brajovic, Nikola Boskovic, Snezana Horvat. Davor is an ordinary young man living in the countryside. His life is very simple and he likes to play tennis, dreaming of turning pro someday. One day, Davor stops by accident in front of an old house, located very close to an old well. Driven by curiosity he decides to have a closer look. that will turn out to be a big mistake.

title: UnTrue
synopsis: Directed by Sigrid Andrea Bernardo. With Cristine Reyes, Xian Lim, Rhen Escano, Peewee O'Hara. A bruised and beaten wife named Mara (Cristine Reyes) seeks the help of Georgian police against her husband Joachim (Xian Lim). In this He-she said film, truths, lies and the dark past will be uncovered.

title: Shall We Play?
synopsis: Directed by Ann Forry. With Jess McLeod, Jeff Gonek, Matreya Scarrwener, Michelle Creber. A troubled teenage girl downloads a new app, 'Shall We Play?', in an attempt to heal her past, but unknowingly the app possesses her into the game.

title: Password
synopsis: Directed by Kamaleswar Mukherjee. With Dev, Adrit Roy, Paoli Dam, Rukmini Maitra. A police officer tracks down a cyber criminal that hacks the passwords of innocent people in order to destroy their lives.

title: The Binding
synopsis: Directed by Domenico de Feudis. With Riccardo Scamarcio, Mía Maestro, Giulia Patrignani, Mariella Lo Sardo. While visiting her fiancé's mother in southern Italy, a woman must fight the mysterious and malevolent curse intent on claiming her daughter.

title: Morgue
synopsis: Directed by Hugo Cardozo. With Francisco Ayala, María del Mar Fernández, Abel Martínez, Pablo Martínez. The story is about a night that Diego Martínez is locked inside the morgue of the Regional Hospital of Encarnación and recounts the paranormal events that the security guard spent.

title: Freaky
synopsis: Directed by Christopher Landon. With Vince Vaughn, Kathryn Newton, Celeste O'Connor, Misha Osherovich. After swapping bodies with a deranged serial killer, a young girl in high school discovers she has less than 24 hours before the change becomes permanent.

title: The Entice
synopsis: Directed by Altin Axel, Marcus Clemons. With Altin Axel, Breaunna Lake, Beth Hamouni, Marcus Clemons. A promotion at an architectural firm lands newlyweds Frank and Lisa DiMarco in a cross-state move. But triumph isn't always righteous. Temptation weaves a dark web of desires, secrets, and lies that challenges their credence. As they fight to regain balance, they soon learn that there is nowhere to go except down a tragic spiral of disaster.

title: Mga mata sa dilim
synopsis: Directed by Enzo Williams. With Derek Ramsay, Jessy Mendiola, Joko Diaz, King Gutierrez. When wealthy, powerful businessman Juancho (Joko Diaz) gets embroiled in a dangerous feud with a syndicate competitor, he ships his beautiful mistress Sui (Jessy Mendiola) out to a secure, remote island where he holds meetings and monitors his drug operations via high-tech camera system. There Sui meets Borgy (Derek Ramsay), a mysterious bodyguard who is actually an undercover cop sent to bring down the drug lord. Their constant contact eventually sparks a romantic attraction, which unknown to them, Juancho discovers via hidden cameras. Faced with an ultimatum, Sui must choose between Juancho, the millionaire, or Borgy, the bodyguard. Borgy, on the other hand, is torn between upholding his duty or risking his mission by helping someone with whom he has fallen in love. Together they must find a way off the island before Juancho hunts them down.

title: Run
synopsis: Directed by Uche Chukwu. With Adesoji Adeleye, Melvin Adie, Michael Akpan, Rogba Arimoro. A hardworking, uptight young woman who lives a dull and routine life, goes running one night and witnesses something that throws her life into chaos and puts her in situations she has never been in before.

title: Piligrim
synopsis: Directed by Aleksandr Barshak. With Vladimir Ilin, Vladimir Ilyin, Igor Petrenko, Aleksey Serebryakov.

title: Medulla
synopsis: Directed by Rudi Brekelmans. With Michael Pas, Astrid van Eck, Christine van Stralen, Bart Oomen. Charles Dujardin - psychiatrist - starts losing his precious sense of control when Lotte, a seductive and promiscuous client offers her confession. Since the death of her controlling husband she feels liberated. She gets back at him by seducing men indiscriminately. She shamelessly flirts with Charles. A stronger man would spot the trauma and resist. But Charles is not a strong man. Her story takes hold of his mind. After his ailing wife is sped off to the hospital Charles grows obsessed with Lotte. He starts losing control of his mind. Reality and fantasy start mixing. An ethical commission starts asking difficult questions. There's been a complaint. An official investigation is started. But he didn't do anything wrong. Did he?

title: Final Approach
synopsis: Directed by Lamonte Hawley. With David Burns, Damondray Christle, Rickey Colbert, Lamonte Hawley.

title: The British Expert
synopsis: Directed by Collins Archie-Pearce. With Nnenna Ani, Collins Archie-Pearce, Isha Bangura, Jimmy Bangura. Crime and corruption prevail in Sierra Leone and the Sierra Leonean government requests the assistance of the British government to help eradicate the prevailing crime and corruption in their country. The British government then sends an expert to Sierra Leone as requested and it was a difficult battle for the British Expert.

title: The End of the Season
synopsis: Directed by Konstantin Khudyakov. With Yuliya Peresild, Yulia Snigir, Anya Chipovskaya, Evgeniy Tsyganov. Three sisters happen to live out of Russia, in s small Baltic city. Like Chekhov's three sisters, they're desperate to move to Moscow. But the fate has its own plans.

title: Sinapsis
synopsis: Directed by Daniel Barrientos Torres. With Oscar Ganem, Iván Echeverri, Sebastián Grisales.

title: Death of a Telemarketer
synopsis: Directed by Khaled Ridgeway. With Lamorne Morris, Jackie Earle Haley, Haley Joel Osment, Alisha Wainwright. A smooth-talking telemarketer finds himself at the mercy of the man he tried to swindle.

title: Baggage Red
synopsis: Directed by Christiano Evans. With Alessandro Anglani, Simon Bass, Lucia Caporaso, Sabrina Carnevale. Two successful families are brought together through the marriage of Jack and Olivia. The happy couple move from London to Sorrento, and there they begin a picturesque new life together. But the paradise they seek begins to crumble as tensions lead them to dark temptations and addictions that rock the very foundations of their perfect lifestyle. Their lives slip out of control, as past family secrets are unearthed and brought back to life. Through this untrod and imperfect journey, they must come together and accept that their perfect lives will never be the same again.

title: The Quiet Ones
synopsis: Directed by Amel J. Figueroa. With Courtney Gains, Reggie Bannister, Bill Allen, Adam C. Edwards. A young man's rapid descent into madness fueled by memories of a distant past of painful family experiences. Main character Michael Rose believes a normal relationship in the form of a blossoming new love interest may save him from his own demons, only to find that recurring nightmares and memories of the past are too strong for any one love to quiet. {"Hush" is based on Figueroa's short story "It's Always the Quiet Ones" - Fiction Press 2002.)

title: In the Darkness
synopsis: Directed by Daniyar Akchabaev. With Nazerke Amirova, Daniyar Beysekeev, Maxim Bogomolov, Sabina Eralina. One day a group of student decide to check a haunted place situated in the forest at the foot of a mountain. They come there but do not find anything uncommon. However, when the night comes, the young folks find themselves in a trap.

title: Scarecrows
synopsis: Directed by Cooper Neidecker. With Cooper Neidecker, Trey Seaba, Kailan Erman, Abby Knoettgen. Three friends in the country put their safety at risk to befriend the obsessive son of their neighbor.

title: Forgotten Pills
synopsis: Directed by David Hefner. With Lindsey Gort, Jordan-Claire Green, Larry Bishop, Shane Callahan. Four friends meet to take mysterious pills that cause instant amnesia at the stroke of midnight.

title: Athaha
synopsis: Directed by Ved Aitharaju. With Noel Sean.

title: The Girl in the Yellow Jumper
synopsis: Directed by Loukman Ali. With Michael Wawuyo Jr., Rehema Nanfuka, Maurice Kirya, Michael Wawuyo. A man reappears after being kidnapped, but you'd never believe his story.

title: Deus Vult - Gott will es!
synopsis: Directed by Fernando Perez. With Sandro Stocker, Francisco Medianero, Stefan Wäfler, Davinci Marcucci.

title: Chaco
synopsis: Directed by Diego Mondaca. With Raimundo Ramos, Fabián Arenillas, Mauricio Toledo, Fausto Castellón. In 1934, Bolivia is at war with Paraguay. Liborio and Ticona and other Bolivian indigenous soldiers are lost in the hell of the Chaco, under the commandment of German Captain Kundt. They're looking for the Paraguayan enemy that they haven't seen for months, and that they will never find. They leave together in a search that will make them realize, progressively, the destiny they have been pushed into and the inevitable condition of a defeated troop. They're walking like shadows, wandering forever in the middle of dust and silence.

title: Come vincere la guerra
synopsis: Directed by Roland Sejko. 1917-1918. The United States intervene in the Great War, the war of the Europeans. Hundreds of thousands of men disembarks on the Continent. In Italy only one battalion arrives, but the 332o Infantry will be enough to tell the enemy - and the others Italians overwhelmed by the trauma of Caporetto - about a war that won't ever be fought. Thanks to rare, extraordinary materials from the American archive, the movie tells the Great War through out a different prospective. This is the story of how you narrate a war.

title: The Windermere Children
synopsis: Directed by Michael Samuels. With Thomas Kretschmann, Romola Garai, Iain Glen, Tim McInnerny. This is the stark, moving, and ultimately redemptive story of the bonds these children make with one another, and of how the friendships forged at Windermere become a lifeline to a fruitful future.

title: Trouble
synopsis: Directed by Mariah Garnett. A 1971 BBC documentary about love across the religious divide of Northern Ireland is the starting point of this heart-breaking story of a woman reuniting with her estranged father after many years. Los Angeles-based artist Mariah Garnett picks up her personal story with interviews and investigations revealing the traumatic effects of political upheavals on Belfast communities then and now. Mariah Garnett adds a queer playfulness through an incredible performance as her father, alongside multiple camera formats that interrogate constructions of identity. A remarkable debut film created partly with a local crew in Belfast, featuring trans actress Robyn Reihill playing the girlfriend of Garnett's father.

title: Advance Wave Upon Wave
synopsis: Directed by Xixi Gao. With Yuanyuan Cheng, Qiang Gao, Peter Ho, Duanduan Liu.

title: Beyond the Barbed Wire: An Artist View of the Holocaust
synopsis: An Artist View of the Holocaust

title: Donbass. Okraina
synopsis: Directed by Renat Davletyarov. With Gela Meskhi, Evgeniy Mikheev, Sergey Kholmogorov, Ulyana Pokhlebaeva.

title: Al-Shafaq - When Heaven Divides
synopsis: Directed by Esen Isik. With Kida Khodr Ramadan, Beren Tuna, Ismail Can Metin, Ahmed Kour Abdo. When heaven divides tells us an uncompromising story about loss, guilt, atonement and redemption.

title: The Forgotten Battle
synopsis: Directed by Matthijs van Heijningen Jr.. With Gijs Blom, Jamie Flatters, Susan Radder, Jan Bijvoet. 1944, the Second World War. A British glider pilot, a Dutch boy fighting on the German side and a Dutch female resistance member all end up involved in the Battle of the Schelde. Their choices differ, but their goal is the same

title: The Partisan
synopsis: Directed by Evgenie Nefeodov. With Inna Levitan. Inna Levitan, citizen of Israel who left her quite life, two children and joined the communistic brigade in the Ukrainian Civil war.

title: China Peacekeeping Forces
synopsis: Directed by Haiqiang Ning. With Honghao Xu, Yi Long, Shiteng Peng, Hao Shen. China's first military peace film, telling the story of current officers and men of China's peacekeeping force in the implementation of President Xi.

title: Dara of Jasenovac
synopsis: Directed by Predrag Antonijevic. With Biljana Cekic, Zlatan Vidovic, Anja Stanic, Luka Saranovic. Follows the story of a young girl named Dara who is sent to a concentration camp in Croatia during World War 2.

title: Eastman
synopsis: Directed by Andrii Ivaniuk. With Bogdan Benyuk, Anatoliy Maksymiyuk. This is a portrait of a man, for whom the war in Eastern Ukraine has become a personal challenge. Beard is a native of the Donbas, a man of about forty-five, a family guy, an ordinary worker. Director is a young man of about twenty-six, single, a west-man, coming from the intelligentsia. This is the usual day of the ordinary military. These are events and people whom you can meet there. This is the relationship between people who have to be here and now during the war. This is not only a unique life experience but also a kind of cultural exchange between different social strata and communities. This is the birth of new, special traditions.

title: Das Glaszimmer
synopsis: Directed by Christian Lerch. With Xari Wimbauer, Lisa Wagner, Hans Löw, Luis Vorbach. Pre-teen, shy Bavarian village boy Felix hears his father died on the front in World War II, so he's left with his mother. Luckily he becomes buddies with Karri, the cocky son of local Nazi boss Ortsgruppenleiter Feik 's son Karri and thus the petty tyrant's protege as well as a "war hero's heir". Karri drags Felix along in attempts to prove their bravery, terrorize rustic and even hunt down a deserter and a crashed US pilot. Felix already 'lacked toughness', but the deserter's true identity shakes his world, just in time as the war is lost and the Allies approach.

title: Moffie
synopsis: Directed by Oliver Hermanus. With Kai Luke Brummer, Barbara-Marié Immelman, Michael Kirch, Remano De Beer. A young man in 1981 South Africa must complete his brutal and racist two years of compulsory military service while desperately maintaining the secrecy of his homosexuality.

title: Scherza con i fanti
synopsis: Directed by Gianfranco Pannone, Ambrogio Sparagna. A tragicomic tour of Italy's recent history, and at the same time, a song of peace, the film is a backward glance that takes in over a hundred years, from the Unification of Italy to the present, to illustrate the rocky and often ironic relationship Italians have with the military and power in general. The film combines invaluable stock footage from the Istituto Luce Archives with marvelous folk songs and four diaries kept by

title: Erna at War
synopsis: Directed by Henrik Ruben Genz. With Trine Dyrholm, Ulrich Thomsen, Anders W. Berthelsen, Sylvester Byder. A woman disguises herself as a man to join the army in order to protect her educationally subnormal son who has been called up to fight in WW1.

title: Atlantis
synopsis: Directed by Valentyn Vasyanovych. With Andriy Rymaruk, Liudmyla Bileka, Vasyl Antoniak, Lily Hyde. A soldier suffering from PTSD befriends a young volunteer hoping to restore peaceful energy to a war-torn society.

title: Sher e Hindustan
synopsis: With Neeta Dhungana, Gopal Rai, Sushil Singh, Sunil Thapa.

title: The Dogs Didn't Sleep Last Night
synopsis: Directed by Ramin Rasouli. With Atefeh Amini, Negin Parsa, Amir Hossein Sadeghi, Fatemeh Khodadad. In a remote area in Afghanistan, stories of the lives of a young shepherdess, a bird catcher boy and a mourning teacher are intertwined by the wounds of war which are still bleeding.

title: There Will Be No More Night
synopsis: Directed by Éléonore Weber. With Nathalie Richard. To shoot

title: Truth & Privacy in the National Archives of the Netherlands
synopsis: Directed by Joshua van 't Hoff. With Paul Hellmann, Andrea Speijer, Sierk Plantinga, Ad van Liempt. Relatives of Holocaust victims and their search for truth in restricted World War II files.

title: The Escape from Auschwitz
synopsis: Directed by Terry Lee Coker. With Elliot Cable, Paul Joseph Bonnici, Alex Reece, David Winfield. After capturing Kazimierz Piechowski at the Hungarian border, he is sent to Auschwitz where he is forced to move corpses from the gas chambers to the crematorium.

title: Secret Weapon
synopsis: Directed by Konstantin Statskiy. With Maxim Animateka, Evgeniy Antropov, Nadezhda Antzipovich, Svyatoslav Astramovich. It's the Second World War. The Red Army had to retreat in a hurry and left their top secret weapon, "Katyusha", behind. A group of 8 soldiers is sent to do everything possible not to let "Katyusha" get into the hands of the Germans.

title: Osenyu 41-go
synopsis: Directed by Elena Borisova. With Filipp Litman, Oksana Dorokhina, Sergey Eremeev, Elena Glazkova.

title: Breakthrough
synopsis: Directed by Dejan Babosek. With Domen Valic, Jernej Gasperin, Ana Spik, Denys Bilash. Young partisan resistance fighter commander Franc Sever Franta faces an impossible task when he has to rescue 500 freedom fighters surrounded and outnumbered by a Nazi German division high in the mountains in harsh winter condition.

title: WW-II, Film Clips from Forgotten Movies
synopsis: Directed by Migdalia Etheridge, Ray Etheridge. With Obada Adnan. Battle scenes from 20 seldom seen war movies. Included are And Then There Were Three, War Devils, Go For Broke, Gung Ho, Hell In Normandy, Battle of El Alamein, Pacific Inferno, Commandos, Black Brigade, Immortal Battalion, Iron Angel, Five For Hell, Prisoner In The Middle, They Raid By Night, The Last Chance, Corregidor, Spitfire, Battle of the Eagles, Submarine Alert, and a newsreel.

title: Da guo chang jiang qu: Towards the river of glorious
synopsis: Directed by Oxide Chun Pang. With Shanshan Chunyu, Yue Yu, Tong Zhang. 1949. Just before the most important and brutal battle of Chinese civil war, an elite small group of PLA commandos infiltrated across the Yang-tze river into the heart of KMT regime. Other than fighting behind enemy lines, the captain of the group had one special task

title: It's Me
synopsis: Directed by Serhiy Morgunov. With Yevgen Bogutskiy, Yevgen Bondar, Andriy Boyko, Demian Burzum. The film is a series of interviews with veterans and soldiers. The characters share their life experiences and talk about the difficulties of re-adjusting to civilian life.

title: Invisible Battalion
synopsis: Directed by Alina Gorlova, Svitlana Lishchinska, Iryna Tsilyk. With Olena Bilozerska, Yulia Matvienko, Yulia Paievska, Andriana Susak. Despite the stereotypes, the armed conflict in eastern Ukraine involves Ukrainian women too. The "Invisible Battalion" will show the world the role of women in the war.

title: Between Brothers
synopsis: Directed by Joud Saeed. With Husain Abbas, Mohammed Al-Ahmad, Maamoun Al-Khatib, Rusul El-Husain. Khaldoun and Arif are two brothers separated by the war, both of them have different opinions, and between them Nejma and Nesma, between them a dream that will never come true.

title: Sharie Hayfa
synopsis: Directed by Mohanad Hayal. With Asaad Abdul Majeed, Iman Abdulhasan, Redhab Ahmad, Rudhab Ahmed. 2006, Baghdad is ravaged by sectarian violence. Haifa Street is the epicenter of the conflict. Ahmed gets dropped off there by a taxi on his way to his beloved Suad's home to ask for her hand for marriage, he gets shot by Salam, a sniper who's living his own personal hell on a rooftop above.

title: Road Through the Forest
synopsis: Directed by Xuan Cuong. With My Dung, Minh Hoàng, Tang Quynh Nhu, Chanh Thuan.

title: Women Who Run with the Wolves
synopsis: Directed by Amir Athar Soheili. With Leia Zanganeh. Jhaleh has gone after her husband to the war zone. She tries to hide in a trench, but an explosion destroys the entrance of the trench and she gets trapped there. Trying to get out and rescue herself, memories of the past come to her. Jhaleh's husband has served in the army and he was supposed to return home after the war ended, yet there is no news of him for a long time. Trying to find him, she understands that the resolution is violated and the war has begun again. Disappointed by her husband's colleagues, she reaches her brother who is a member of MEK. Her brother informs her that her husband was arrested by MEK for intelligence debriefing. Being pregnant and scared of war, she escapes to a trench but gets trapped there. Her brother sends a group for finding Jhaleh, but the operation fails. Jhaleh's brother commits suicide with cyanide, after revealing Younes is killed. Jhaleh is solely alone and disappointed and starts writing her testament, suddenly there opens a small hole to the out of the trench. A rescue team arrives but Jhaleh's bones are the only thing they find.

title: Soldier's Kiss: A PTSD Documentary
synopsis: A PTSD Documentary

title: Summerwar
synopsis: Directed by Moritz Schulz. Two kids, one war, one camp. Jasmin and Jastrip grow up in Ukraine. Surrounded by war and rising nationalism, they visit the Azovez camp. There they become real patriots and that is what they came for - but it's not why they stay.

title: Morning Calm
synopsis: The forgotten war on the Korean peninsula, remixed to romance.

title: Rocket Hunter
synopsis: Directed by Christopher Forbes. With Brad Owens, Scotty Sparks, William Wylie, Ronald Blanton. In one of the most dangerous missions of the war, an American B-17 pilot volunteers to fly a surrendered Messerschmidt 109 on a daring flight through the heart of Germany to try to prevent the people of London from being terrorized by the V-2 rockets. "Rocket Hunter" tells the story of an amazing pilot and his bombardier brother from the time they are teenagers dreaming of taking to the skies to the dark days of January 1945.

title: The Earth Is Blue as an Orange
synopsis: Directed by Iryna Tsilyk. With Ganna Gladka, Stanislav Gladky, Anastasiia Trofymchuk, Myroslava Trofymchuk. To cope with the daily trauma of living in a war-zone, Anna and her children are making a film together about their life in the most surreal surroundings.

title: Red Swan
synopsis: With Peter Anthony, Ray Hopper, Morgen Johnson, Julia Valenti. When her father, is Killed by the Nazi's, Anna Stifler sets out on a quest for vengeance. As the Nazis begin their hunt for the Jews, Anna tracks down the Nazi's, donning the name 'The Red Swan'.

title: Mah's Journey
synopsis: Directed by Don Hoe. With Julian Cheah, Jean Tan, Jeffrey Leong, Sam Loo. A true story during World War II of a Japanese war major and his soldiers hunting a woman and her children who are trying to escape Thailand to return home to Malaysia.

title: Vengeful 7
synopsis: Directed by Tristan van Doorn. With Geoffrey Alkemade, Rick Kuitems, Bauke van Boheemen, Jos Timmerman. June 1944. A group of seven Dutch resistance fighters receive an important mission to help the allied advance into occupied Europe. The mission goes wrong and they are starting to suspect that there is a traitor in their midst.

title: Two Chef in the War
synopsis: Directed by Wanfeng Han. With Min Sun. When Japan invaded China in the World War II,there was a local chef named Wen Yukun in the fallen Hainan Island. Although Wen and other chefs were forced to sell Japanese food, Wen risked his life to secretly cook a local cuisine-Hainan Chicken Rice for neighbors, bringing them hope and warmth in the dark age.

title: Bunker
synopsis: Directed by Jugal Raja. With Abhijeet Singh, Arindita Kalita, Gaurav Gupta, Dileep Singh Kushvaha. Lt. Vikram Singh is a lone survivor in a Bunker, at Poonch (Kashmir), after being hit by a mortar shell during a ceasefire violation.

title: Home Fires
synopsis: Directed by Sam Weeks. With Colin Hill, Harry Wells, Alex Francis, Daniel Dingsdale. A WW1 veteran recounts his time throughout the war.

title: Ihtiyar Kurtlar
synopsis: Directed by Selahattin Sancakli. With Mustafa Akyüz, Ege Aydan, Yusuf Aytekin, Mehmet Sah Celik. In the 1877-1878 Ottoman-Russian War, four veterans who fought together on the Pleven front gave their commander a martyr during a raid in Pleven. Years later, in the 1915 Dardanelles War, they heard that Lieutenant Yusuf, the nephew of their commander with the same name, was captured. Four old men and a handicapped young man undertake a prisoner rescue operation.

title: Ek Sainik - The Tale of a warrior
synopsis: The Tale of a Warrior

title: Kalashnikov
synopsis: Directed by Konstantin Buslov. With Yuriy Borisov, Olga Lerman, Artur Smolyaninov, Sergey Gazarov. Wounded as a tank driver in 1941 during WWII, Kalashnikov sees the latest Soviet machine gun fail. As he's also an inventor, he starts looking for improvements and in 1947 ends up with AK-47 assault rifle.

title: Silent Sonata
synopsis: Directed by Janez Burger. With Leon Lucev, René Bazinet, Pauliina Räsänen, Ravil Sultanov. Described as a Slovenian war drama.

title: Marked Man
synopsis: Directed by Delgerbayar Purevdorj. With Batnyambuu Enkhtaivan, Altanshagai Javkhlan, B. Otgonbayar. Dandar was one of the commanders in a horse battalion in Mongolian army during Khalkhiin Gol Battle against Japan's Imperial Army. He never lost a battle and was known as the most feared warrior in the battle field. His success wasn't openly invited by the secret services, since he was never injured and wounded during the battles. Due to personal jealousy of an investigating officer Dandar was persecuted for treason and served rest of his life in war camp alone with the very enemies he fought to protect his country.

title: Abadan 1160
synopsis: Directed by Mehrdad Khoshbakht. With Alireza Kamali, Mohammad Hassan Madjooni, Nader Soleimani, Hamid Reza Mohammadi. The struggle of a local radio station in Abadan in the begging of the Iraq invasion against Iran. A group of youngsters try to keep the station live and give the people hope under the shelling and bombarding by Saddam's forces.

title: Shihana
synopsis: Directed by Khaled El Hagar. With Layan Alshehri, Khalid Al-Saqer, Maysun Alruwaili, Majed Al Oteibi. Film events are based on a true story. Shihana is a young Saudi girl, who loves life and beauty, full of hope, with strong determination and good heart. She lives her life in Riyadh accompanied by bright colors, dreams and love that do not exclude anybody. Shihana and her brother Ibrahim were deceived by their mother, Munira, who promised them a tourist trip to Turkey, but she intended to join ISIS, paying no attention to the fate of her children. Suddenly, Shihana finds herself in the darkest and deadliest part of the world, inside the terrorist organization, to live between the flames of death and destruction, moving from one city to another to escape death trying to overcome her ordeal with love and color.

title: Dark As Summer Wine
synopsis: In Occupied France 1942, two Nazis who were childhood friends; one now in the SS, the other a wounded Luftwaffe Pilot, spend some time drinking at a rural hotel, run by a bizarre innkeeper and his blonde teenage daughter.

title: The Unwelcome Ones - Scottish War Time Sci Fi Horror
synopsis: Directed by Douglas Kyle. With Mark Bell, Andrew Kyle, Douglas Kyle. During World War Two, a German spy is sent to infiltrate a top secret military installation in the highlands of Scotland. However, forces are at work which threaten not only the outcome of the war, but also the future of man kind.

title: 1917: The Real Story
synopsis: The Real Story

title: VE Day: Forever in Their Debt
synopsis: Forever in Their Debt

title: Dog Jack
synopsis: Directed by Edward T. McDougal. With Louis Gossett Jr., Benjamin Gardner, Frank Kasy, Kenneth Craig. In the midst of the Civil War, a boy and his dog escape a plantation and embark on a life-changing journey. Inspired by true events, "Dog Jack" chronicles a turbulent moment in American history, and a tale that's never been forgotten.

title: Battle of Britain - Empty Skies
synopsis: Directed by Bruce Vigar. Stories from those who were there. A unique insight into what it was really like to be there. Interviews with the pilots , cut with archive footage paint the picture from one of History's greatest ever Air Battles.

title: Battle Scars
synopsis: Directed by Samuel Gonzalez Jr.. With Kit Lang, Arturo Castro, Illya Konstantin, Emily Trosclair. After his best friend is drafted to fight in Vietnam, a young man must grapple with the reality of life before and after war.

title: Shugaley
synopsis: Directed by Denis Neymand. With Oleg Abalyan, Khaled Houissa, Oleg Metelev, Kirill Polukhin.

title: Shadows in Paradise
synopsis: Directed by J. Stephen Maunder. With Mark Dacascos, Armand Assante, Tom Sizemore, Bruce Boxleitner. During a military raid to rescue in Iraq, Max Forrester's teammate and girlfriend Sasha, disappears mysteriously. Two years later, Max, who has since retired from the army receives a call from his former commander Captain Dyer, who informs him that Sasha is still alive and is in a place called Paradise Island, and also inform him that the army is ready to take action to recover it and accuse it of treason and desertion. Max then decided to go for help Sasha and once found, she learns from her that she was working undercover to discover and report a dangerous arms smuggling conducted by a handful of men called Shadow Company. Max and Sasha must now prevent the illicit trafficking takes place and retrieve the weapons in a spectacular and very dangerous showdown with Ghost, the head of Shadow Company.

title: Father Soldier Son
synopsis: Directed by Leslye Davis, Catrin Einhorn. With Brian Eisch, Isaac Eisch, Joey Eisch, Roxanne Gregory. When Sgt. First Class Brian Eisch is critically wounded in Afghanistan, it sets him and his sons on a journey of love, loss, redemption and legacy.

title: The Last Frontier
synopsis: Directed by Vadim Shmelyov. With Artyom Gubin, Lubov Konstantinova, Igor Yudin, Aleksey Bardukov. A film about the feat of the Podolsk cadets in October 1941 near Moscow. The cadets of the Podolsk artillery-infantry schools are ordered to take up defenses on the Ilyinsky line.

title: Top Gunner
synopsis: Directed by Daniel Lusko. With Eric Roberts, Carol Anne Watts, Ignacyo Matynia, Julian Cavett. Recent graduates of a secluded U.S. Air Force base must protect a gene-editing bio-weapon from the Russian military - who are desperate to seize the deadly viral agent at any cost.

title: Happy New Year
synopsis: Directed by K. Lorrel Manning. With Michael Cuomo, J.D. Williams, Monique Gabriela Curnen, Victoria Gates. A war-torn Marine returns home to face his fiercest battle yet - the one against himself.

title: Outside the Law
synopsis: Directed by Rachid Bouchareb. With Jamel Debbouze, Roschdy Zem, Sami Bouajila, Chafia Boudraa. A drama about the Algerian struggle for independence from France after WWII.

title: Fengxiang 1949
synopsis: Directed by Sun Jun. With Bai Feng, Shuangbao Wang, Sun Yajun, Zongru Yang.

title: Where Hands Touch
synopsis: Directed by Amma Asante. With Abbie Cornish, Amandla Stenberg, George MacKay, Christopher Eccleston. A rites of passage story of a bi-racial teen struggling for survival in Nazi Germany.

title: Ten' vraga
synopsis: Directed by Igor Senkov. With Igor Senkov, Pavel Savelev, Igor Denisov, Evgeniy Ivkovich. 1943 year. At the very height of the war, Soviet intelligence services are preparing an especially secret operation in the territory occupied by German troops. The situation at the front is at the edge of a turning point, which should re-establish the priorities of the belligerents, determining the beginning of decisive battles that bring the victory closer. Obtaining secret documents of the enemy is the most important task of the Soviet command.

title: The Laws of War
synopsis: Directed by François-Xavier Tregan. With Mohamed Al-Askari, Najim Al-Jabouri, Mostafa Al-Saygari, Oussama Chourbaji. The world has experienced an increased amount of non-state armed groups, cross-border conflicts, killer robots, and religious influence on the rules of battle. Civilians are now the primary victims of conflicts, not soldiers.

title: Impasse Rescue
synopsis: Directed by Jiaoshou Qin. With Zeyu Li, Xingying Shao. Li Zhuifeng, a famous general of Shenzhou, and some soldiers in Beipo City are surrounded by Shaman's 100,000 troops. The leader of Shaman intentionally releases the envoy of Gandang City. Huang Zizai, Vice General of Gandang City, understands what Shaman plans. To save Li Zhuifeng, he goes alone to a city in the oasis to ask for help, where he meets many people of vision, and organizes an army of 800 warriors. After overcoming dangers and difficulties, they finally meet Li Zhuifeng. Just then Shaman attacks again. Seeing Li Zhuifeng and the soldiers trying to guard the city regardless of their lives, Huang Zizai and the army are deeply moved, and work together to resist Shaman's army. Finally, Shenzhou's army arrives, and eliminates Shaman's army.

title: Peacekeeping
synopsis: Directed by Jeremiah Mason. With Caleb Cash, Elijah Golden, Madelynn Grutz, Nathan Lass. A soldier faces a desperate attempt to survive after being stuck behind enemy lines.

title: U-455, the Mystery of the Lost Submarine
synopsis: Directed by Stéphane Bégoin. A mysterious lost WWII submarine, German U-boat U-455 is discovered off the coast of Italy at 120 meters deep. For Lorenzo del Veneziano, an underwater marine archaeologist, it's an amazing sight. The U-boat is intact. It stands almost vertically at the bottom of the sea, its hull stuck in the sediment. What is the story of this ship? The history of U-455 and cause of the sinking are revealed.

title: War of the Gods
synopsis:
Directed by Jennifer Abbott. With Ahmed Al Dubayan, Yasser Arafat, David Ben-Gurion, Tony Blair. This documentary aims to prove to the world that religion has become the weapon used both by the devout, and political leaders, to win their wars. Jennifer Abbott's ambition is to show the world that true religion is not what our leaders use to create hostilities against other countries. This is why religion appears to be at the root of so many problems today. Is the warfare and corruption perpetrated by those leaders who claim to serve God, justified? She wonders what God they worship. It's certainly not the same God she knows. The fault lies not with all religion and religious leaders, but with false doctrine and false beliefs passed on to the people through unfair media, schools, and parental influence. What does God represent, and do we follow his words. The Bible teaches and plainly states, 

"Ye have heard that it hath been said, An eye for an eye and a tooth for a tooth

title: Battle of the Bulge: Winter War
synopsis: Winter War

title: Road 47
synopsis: Directed by Vincent Ferraz.

title: Lethal Nationalism: Genocide of the Greeks 1913-1923
synopsis: Genocide of the Greeks 1913-1923

title: Saints and Soldiers: The Void
synopsis: Пустота

title: Henri 4
synopsis: Directed by Jo Baier. With Julien Boisselier, Joachim Król, Andreas Schmidt, Roger Casamajor. A wide-ranging, energetic period piece tracing the rise of the Protestant Henry of Navarre as he goes from battlefield warrior to France's beloved King Henri IV. Director Jo Baier's epic is a classically-entertaining adventure, albeit one with much bloodshed and frequent bawdy sexual interludes. In late-16th-century France, Catholics and Protestant Huguenots are at war. Seemingly seeking peace, French dowager Queen Catherine de Medici summons Henry to her court to marry him to her daughter, which would unite the two warring factions. However, the Catholics slaughter the Protestant wedding guests in what became known as the St. Bartholomew's Day massacre and Henry--now married--must use all his guile to stay alive and maneuver for the throne.

title: Kandagar
synopsis: Directed by Andrey Kavun. With Aleksandr Baluev, Yury Belyayev, Bogdan Benyuk, Aleksandr Golubev. Based on the true story of five Russian pilots captured by the Taliban. They are forced to spend three-hundred-seventy-eight days in hell, while facing questions of loyalty, survival and planing their treacherous escape route home.

title: USS Seaviper
synopsis: Directed by Ralph A. Villani. With Tim Large, Jeremy King, Robb Maus, Steve Roth. The German U-Boat, U-234, from the Port of Kiel is trading cargo with the Japanese. USS Seaviper must locate and stop this dangerous exchange. The Captain of USS Seaviper must go ashore to conduct reconnaissance on an island near Sumatra, but the ship is left in the hands of Mister Cutter, after the Executive Officer is injured in battle. A conflict between Cutter and the Chief of the Boat puts the submarine in jeopardy. Seaviper is trapped below the surface, with decreasing oxygen, and a Japanese destroyer hunting them from above. Damage to the boat also leave her survival in question. They must fight the Japanese destroyer and get the information about U-235 back to Pearl Harbor.

title: The Forgotten Front: La Resistenza a Bologna
synopsis: La Resistenza a Bologna

title: Wolves Action 2
synopsis: Directed by Hulk Cheng. With Siu-Wong Fan, Tingwei Liang, Junyao Li, Yuan Hangming.

title: Fort McCoy
synopsis: Directed by Kate Connor, Michael Worth. With Eric Stoltz, Kate Connor, Lyndsy Fonseca, Andy Hirsch. A drama based on a true story when the Stirn family lived next to a Nazi POW camp in Wisconsin during W.W.II.

title: Trooper
synopsis: Directed by Christopher Martini. With Max Martini, Robert Walden, Suzanne DiDonna, Marisa Vitali. A story of a father and son, two veterans from two very different Wars, helping each other to get through each day, and heal the wounds of War.

title: The Hidden Strike
synopsis: Directed by Suzad Iqbal Khan. With Deepraj Rana, Mir Sarwar, Jimmy Sharma, Lakhwinder. The Hidden Strike is a fictional movie about a ground mission where a team of thirteen Indian Army officers and soldiers went across POK and destroyed the terrorist camp with a planned sub tactical strike. The film is dedicated to India soldiers and their families. The film shows what price our freedom fighters pay for the safety of our country. The Hidden Strike also highlights issues that the Indian Army faces from certain groups of people from the valley.

title: Matchless Mulan
synopsis: Directed by Chen Cheng. With Xue'er Hu, Wei Wei, Jarvis Wu. During the Northern Wei Dynasty, the Rouran army invaded the border, and the country called up military residents to go out to battle. To perform the duty for her father, Hua Mulan disguised herself as a man and came to battlefield.

title: The Guernsey Literary and Potato Peel Pie Society
synopsis: Directed by Mike Newell. With Jessica Brown Findlay, Tom Courtenay, Michiel Huisman, Katherine Parkinson. In the aftermath of World War II, a writer forms an unexpected bond with the residents of Guernsey Island when she decides to write a book about their experiences during the war.

title: The Challenge of Flight - Eagles Over the Gulf Stories of Desert Storm
synopsis: Directed by L. Douglas Keeney. The Challenge of Flight is the real story of military aviation. In this program go behind the scenes to meet the daring pilots who flew the missions and listen to their thrilling stories of Desert Storm.

title: The Day I Met Hitler
synopsis: Directed by Ronen Israelski. The second World War and the Holocaust in the eyes of children who met Hitler. How it changed their lives and ours. 75 years after the end of World War II The son of Holocaust survivor Embarks on a journey to find the last living people in the world Who Met Hitler. A lifetime of perspective.

title: Code 207
synopsis: Directed by Tino Struckmann. With Jack Dimich, Tino Struckmann, Denise Johnson, Caspar von Winterfeldt. A criminal ring kidnaps women and sells them to wealthy clients. When they kidnap the wife of an ARMY Ranger, their plans change dramatically, when he finds the abandoned Prison where they are held. a deadly cat and mouse game begins as he hunts them while trying to save the women from being sold and shipped away

title: Flash Drive
synopsis: Directed by Dervis Zaim. With Ali Suliman, Husam Ali, Saleh Bakri, Husam Chadat. Ahmet, as a soldier in the regular Syrian army, witnesses the cover-up of massacres and torture conducted to repress the civil unrest. He and his wife Leila try to flee through the war zone to bring testimony to the world.

title: Bura duse
synopsis: Directed by Goran Marsalek. With Darko Horvat, Drazen Hrzenjak, Zvonko Kovacic.

title: The Sacrifice
synopsis: Directed by Hu Guan, Frant Gwo, Yang Lu, Yusheng Tian. With Yi Zhang, Jing Wu, Jiuxiao Li, Vision Wei. In 1953, the Korean War is entering the final stage. The People's Volunteer Army of China has launched the last major battle in Kumsong. In order to arrive at the battleground on time and deliver enough force to the Kumsong front line, the soldiers have to defend themselves against the never ending bombing of enemy bombers and race with time to repair bridges, all under the circumstance of supply shortages and inferior equipment. The rarely told history slowly unfolds.

title: The Challenge of Flight - Eject! Eject!
synopsis: Directed by L. Douglas Keeney. With never-before-seen test crash footage, trace the progress of the pilot's safety system of last resort from inception to today's models.

title: The Challenge of Flight - Go to Guns
synopsis: Directed by L. Douglas Keeney. This program traces the development of air combat from the use of air balloons to advanced weaponry of this era. See rare historic battle footage, cockpit views, battlefield action, bombs-eye-view in actual attacks, and more.

title: The Challenge of Flight - Nowhere Else to Go
synopsis: Directed by L. Douglas Keeney. No job is more hazardous than Carrier Air operations. Witness amazing approaches and landings that seem impossible to make. You'll also see many of those that failed. Rare footage.

title: The Challenge of Flight - Violent Skies
synopsis: Directed by L. Douglas Keeney. Witness first hand a jet that has been struck, disoriented, killed by a missile shot, dying in violent skies. Pilots know that someday they'll face the challenge of such violence. And when they do, this is what they'll see.

title: The Challenge of Flight - Pushing the Limits
synopsis: Directed by L. Douglas Keeney. Exceed a limit and you kill yourself, push the limits back and you build an airplane that can kill the enemy. One finds the limits of flight in the dangers of flight testing.

title: The Challenge of Flight - Out of Control
synopsis: Directed by L. Douglas Keeney. Watch accident footage from actual mishaps, uncontrollable situations with stalls and drops, pilot induced oscillations, unrecoverable spins, massive structural failures, and many more astonishing fails.

title: The Challenge of Flight: Gettin' in Gettin' Out
synopsis: Gettin' in Gettin' Out

title: The Challenge of Flight - Limping Home
synopsis: Directed by L. Douglas Keeney. It is the nature of pilots to stay with their planes and bring them and their crews home, no matter what shape they are in and no matter the cost. See rare accident footage caught on film.

title: The Challenge of Flight - Vertical Flight
synopsis: Directed by L. Douglas Keeney. With newly obtained footage, you may now view the challenges of vertical flight from its beginnings to the development of modern aircraft. Includes near-crash mishap footage.

title: The Challenge of Flight - Vietnam: Zero Dark Thirty
synopsis: Zero Dark Thirty

title: The Challenge of Flight: Sounds of Freedom
synopsis: Sounds of Freedom

title: The Challenge of Flight: Adversary Air
synopsis: Adversary Air

title: The Challenge of Flight - Whatever It Takes
synopsis: Directed by L. Douglas Keeney. Witness first hand the moments when things do go wrong on military aircraft and when a small glitch brings down the finest technology. See pilots beat insurmountable odds and bring their aircraft home in one piece or many.

title: The Challenge of Flight - Aircraft Carrier Quals
synopsis: Directed by L. Douglas Keeney. With Fighter Pilots. Here is the real story of naval military aviation. Find out what it takes to serve on an aircraft carrier. One catapult incident can send pilots into the sea or to their death. Witness all the challenges of Aircraft Carrier Qualifications.

title: Adam
synopsis: Directed by Mario Sulina. With Zdravko Sinjori, Antonio Starinec, Jasmin Novljakovic, Vjekoslav Jankovic. Adam, a true war hero, and his son, the only thing he has, are living in an unnamed village. He raising him in his own way. The villagers do not recognize that and consider him an eccentric, an freak whose life they would like to examine.

title: Linea Gotica
synopsis: Directed by Mario Pratesi. With Daniele Di Stefano, Simone Raggi, Francesco Tola.

title: There Be Dragons
synopsis: Directed by Roland Joffé. With Charlie Cox, Wes Bentley, Dougray Scott, Rodrigo Santoro. Arising out of the horror of the Spanish Civil War, a candidate for canonization is investigated by a journalist who discovers his own estranged father had a deep, dark and devastating connection to the saint's life.

title: De Bitterbal
synopsis: Directed by Erik van 't Wout. With Tamara Friedman, Ariana Khan, Anne-Marie Marte, Jan Roelfzema.

title: Gyuri
synopsis: Directed by Mariana Lacerda. With Claudia Andujar, Davi Kopenawa, Peter Pal Pelbart, Carlo Zaquini. Gyuri traces an unlikely geopolitical line between the small Hungarian village of Nagyvarad and the Yanomami Indigenous Land in the Brazilian Amazon. A Jewish woman and survivor of the Second World War, Claudia Andujar found herself exiled in Brazil and has dedicated her life to safeguarding the Yanomami people. Her invaluable collection of photographs, her tireless militancy, her experience of the war, and the current vulnerability of the indigenous peoples are explored through dialogues between Andujar, the shamen Davi Kopenawa, and the activist Carlo Zacquini, with narration provided by the Hungarian philosopher Peter Pál Pelbart.

title: God Went Surfing with the Devil
synopsis: Directed by Alexander Klein. With Ibrahim N. Arafat, Matthew Olsen, Arthur Rashkovan, Gil Keren. A breathtaking look at the Israel-Gaza conflict through the lens of surfing.

title: The Battle of Pussy Willow Creek
synopsis: Directed by Wendy Jo Cohen. With Emily Mitchell, Christopher Lukas, Tim Cusack, Zeb Hollins III. Ken Burns meets Spinal Tap in a subversive tour de force relaying the outrageous life stories of four forgotten Civil War heroes

title: Near Enemies
synopsis: Directed by Michael Fredianelli. With Trevor B. Nagle, Jeffrey Alan Foster, Kenny Beers, Bryan Wilks. A squad of American soldiers hunt down a suspected spy that escaped an internment camp during WWII.

title: Birdsong
synopsis: Directed by Charlotte Peters, Alastair Whatley. With Tom Kay, Madeleine Knight, Tim Treloar, Liam McCormick. As an English soldier fights in the horrific trenches of northern France, he is haunted by the memories of his forbidden love affair with a French woman.

title: The Fifth Story
synopsis: Directed by Ahmed Abd. With Ahmed Abd, Adnan, Abd Jasim, Nassar Sabah. After decades of devastating war in Iraq, the horrors are still fresh in the minds of different generations. Their disturbing stories are filmed in a poetic style that also cautiously opens a door to beauty and contemplation.

title: Life on the Road
synopsis: Directed by Adnan Faroq, Sidra Rezwan, Ekhlas Heydar Samubud, Salva Soleiman Sedo. In 2015, producer Bahman Ghobadi and some colleagues taught children in a refugee camp in Iraq to film. After school, boys and girls recorded their own films, based on each other's routine.

title: When Pomegranates Howl
synopsis: Directed by Granaz Moussavi. With Arafat Faiz, Elham Ahmad Ayazi, Saeida Sadat, Freshta Alimi. A nine-year-old boy from Kabul decides to start a business as a cart pusher, hoping to raise enough money to follow his dreams.

title: Nosotras tambien estuvimos
synopsis: Directed by Federico Strifezzo. With Stella Carone, Ana Masito, Alicia Mabel Reinoso.

title: Tygyn Darkhan
synopsis: Directed by Nikita Arzhakov.

title: 100 Missions Surviving Vietnam 2020
synopsis: Surviving Vietnam

title: God of War: Zhao Zilong
synopsis: Directed by Ye Luo. With Mike Ho, Tianye Li, Sikai Nan, Liyun Wang. Story about one of five Tiger Generals Kingdom of Shu from Romance of Three Kingdom, Zhao Zilong who agrees to assist Liu Bei in his great mission to unite China.

title: WWII Liberation of Europe D-Day
synopsis: Directed by L. Douglas Keeney. From D-DAY to the capture of Berlin this program presents the greatest and rarest footage of the war in Europe.

title: Zibatar Az Zendegi
synopsis: Directed by Ensie Shah Hosseini. With Mohsen Avid, Hamed Komaily, Ghorban Najafi, Mahmood Pakniat. With the start of the imposed war, Hussein Alam al-Huda, commander of the Hoveyzeh Corps, rushed to the aid of the villagers with the help of the people's forces. But empty handed. . . But the sincere forces of the army, despite the opposition of Bani Sadr, rushed to their aid and while providing weapons assistance, in a joint operation, they attacked the aggressor enemy side by side. Until. . .

title: Beasts of No Nation
synopsis: Directed by Cary Joji Fukunaga. With Abraham Attah, Emmanuel Affadzi, Ricky Adelayitor, Andrew Adote. A drama based on the experiences of Agu, a child soldier fighting in the civil war of an unnamed African country.

title: I Am Fear
synopsis: Directed by Kevin Shulman. With Kristina Klebe, Faran Tahir, Said Faraj, Ali Saam. Held captive by terrorists, celebrity reporter, Sara Brown, sits in a cell awaiting her filmed beheading. Sara's captors wish to show the world the true face of terror but how can they, when even they have not seen it yet?

title: W.M.D.
synopsis: Directed by Richard Halpern. With Tom Kiesche, John Posey, Weetus Cren, Leila Birch. In this vision of a shocking alternate reality, a group of US soldiers do the unthinkable and kidnap the President of the United States. Will they uncover the truth behind the Iraq War?

title: How I Was Stolen by the Germans
synopsis: Directed by Milos 'Misa' Radivojevic. With Jelena Djokic, Douglas Henshall, Svetozar Cvetkovic, Dara Dzokic. "How I Was Stolen by the Germans" tells the story of director and writer Milos 'Misa' Radivojevic's childhood and how his life was influenced by the people he grew up with. As a child he felt neglected by his communist family and was taken care of by a German officer who occupied his home during WWII and was the only person who offered him any love and warmth during his childhood.

title: Coriolanus
synopsis: Directed by Ralph Fiennes. With Gerard Butler, Ralph Fiennes, Lubna Azabal, Ashraf Barhom. A banished hero of Rome allies with a sworn enemy to take his revenge on the city.

title: Blood of the Palm Trees
synopsis: Directed by Najdat Esmail Anzur. With Adnan Abdol-Jaleel, Amer Al-Ali, Majdi Al-Maqbal, Nawras Abou Ali. The story of the Syrian archaeologist Khaled Al-Asaad, who saved Palmyra's treasures from ISIS, only to pay for his brave stance with his life.

title: Syrian Lilith
synopsis: Directed by Ghassan Shamit. With Abdulrahman Abu Al-Qasem, Ola Basha, Majd Feda, Waddah Halloum. Depicts the life of a Syrian family during the war as they move from a conservative rural environment due to terrorist attacks to a safe area in a city with more diversity.

title: Dancing Stars
synopsis: Directed by Mohsen Mohseni-Nasab. With Parva Mahzoun, Anoushiravan Mohseni, Babak Noori. A young Iranian Officer on the frontlines of the early days of the Iran / Iraq war is informed that his wife has born him a daughter back in Tehran. Because of this he is ordered by his superiors to go back to Tehran to see his wife and newborn child for a few days. Even though he is conflicted, because of his war hero status and a genuine sense of camaraderie on the one side and the desire to see his wife and newborn daughter, he opts to ignore the order and chooses stay with his men to see them through the worst part of the fighting and destiny takes its course.

title: Legend of Zhao Yun
synopsis: Directed by Qingyun Ye. With Tao Wang, Mei Yang, Yankai Yu.

title: The Salt Caravan
synopsis: Directed by Guo Zhijun. With Zhao Rongbing, Zhang Xu, Kyle York.

title: When Soldiers Cry
synopsis: Directed by Joe Black. With Jess Weber, Doug Szczesny, Kristin Sargent, Bob Bozek. 1965 South Vietnam, two American Soldiers find themselves trapped in the Jungle with a War surrounding them. The only thing keeping them alive is the promises in their hearts they kept to their families - to return home at any cost. One Soldier, Private David M. Church awakes from being rendered unconscious to find all of his squad killed by the Vietcong. Three Days by foot, he must travel to the Landing Zone for extraction. In the distant Jungle, Church comes across an injured VC and makes him pay for the lives of his squad. Payment comes in the form of a bullet to the VC shoulder. Moving closer Church finds out the farmer dressed VC is actually an American Tunnel Rat. Mentally broken, Church carries the Tunnel Rat closer to the LZ. Along the way Church finds other American Soldiers in need of help. Death follows as Church makes a gallant effort to save lives in dire desperation to reach the LZ. The VC, and one of his own claim anyone that attempts to leave the Jungle. Church reaches the LZ, but it costs him everything, including his promise. Save yourself, or save a life other than your own... full well knowing you won't make it out of the Jungle alive.

title: 1944 Uprisings in Europe
synopsis: Uprisings in Europe

title: The Last Correspondent
synopsis: Directed by Eugeniusz Starky. With Zygmunt Aksienow, Adolf Hitler, Kazimiera Mika. The courage and dedication of one American documentary filmmaker, Julien Bryan, altered the course of human history. Due to Bryan's relentless dedication to the defenders of Warsaw, the world first learned of Hitler's wretched plans of war and complete world domination, one country at a time.

title: Habermann
synopsis: Directed by Juraj Herz. With Mark Waschke, Karel Roden, Ben Becker, Hannah Herzsprung. A mill owner in the Sudetenland and his family's lives are changed as Europe heats up in 1938.

title: The Holy Land of Tyrol
synopsis: Directed by Philipp J. Pamer. With Inga Birkenfeld, Wolfgang Menardi, Manfred-Anton Algrang, Verena Plangger. The film tells the story of Katharina who has to escape from Bavaria to Tyrol together with her husband. Of all the times in the year of 1809. There she faces these tough times of the revolution and its leader Andreas Hofer on a small croft in the Mountains of Passira, truly engaged in the chaos of war. An historical adventure reviving the 200th anniversary of the Hofer-Revolt against Bavaria and Napoleon. Shot on original settings.

title: The Roundup
synopsis: Directed by Rose Bosch. With Jean Reno, Mélanie Laurent, Gad Elmaleh, Raphaëlle Agogué. A faithful retelling of the 1942 "Vel' d'Hiv Roundup" and the events surrounding it.

title: The Emperor's Sword
