synopsis: Directed by Zhang Yingli. With Xu Chang Chao, Yilin Hao, Feng-bin Mou, Ruoyao Pan. A sword that bestows power upon its wielder was divided and hidden. A rebel seizes power and stages a massacre, leaving only one survivor. Now, the daughter of a great general is all that stands between a tyrant and his domination.

title: Dayan
synopsis: Directed by Behrouz Nouranipour. With Naser Babaian, Bahar Maroufi Azar, Hamid Jafari, Nasrin Izadi. A story about tomorrow's "war" and people who live in a village and are working hard for tomorrow.

title: Resistance
synopsis: Directed by Amit Gupta. With Andrea Riseborough, Alexander Dreymon, Michael Sheen, Tom Wlaschiha. In 1944 a group of women in an isolated Welsh village wake up to discover all of the their husbands have mysteriously vanished.

title: Mother of Apostles
synopsis: Directed by Zaza Buadze. With Bogdan Benyuk, Sergey Derevyanko, Yuri Kulinich, Serhii Medin. In search of her son-pilot, whose humanitarian plane was shot down over the occupied territories of Ukraine, the mother finds herself in a completely alien and aggressive world, where everything is permeated with hatred and suffering. In this hell, she is not only looking for a son, but, having great love and a merciful character in her heart, she changes everyone she meets on her way. And most importantly, she changes herself, gaining truly sacred power. Her despair and pain are reborn in the eternal motherly spirit of the earth, which brings her sons home alive or dead.

title: Twice Born
synopsis: Directed by Sergio Castellitto. With Penélope Cruz, Emile Hirsch, Adnan Haskovic, Saadet Aksoy. A mother brings her teenage son to Sarajevo, where his father died in the Bosnian conflict years ago.

title: El Pan Nuestro
synopsis: Directed by José Antonio González.

title: Jew Suss: Rise and Fall
synopsis: Directed by Oskar Roehler. With Tobias Moretti, Martina Gedeck, Moritz Bleibtreu, Justus von Dohnányi. Rise and fall of actor Ferdinand Marian, who takes the chance and stars in the anti-semitic movie Jud Süß (1940).

title: National Theatre Live: Antigone
synopsis: Antigone

title: Ashke Narges
synopsis: Directed by Ahmad Abdolahian. With Reza Iranmanesh, Mahmood Maghami, Zahra Meygoli, Rahman Moghadam.

title: In Darkness
synopsis: Directed by Agnieszka Holland. With Robert Wieckiewicz, Benno Fürmann, Agnieszka Grochowska, Maria Schrader. A dramatization of one man's rescue of Jewish refugees in the German-occupied Polish city of Lvov.

title: Beneath Hill 60
synopsis: Directed by Jeremy Sims. With Brendan Cowell, Alan Dukes, Alex T. Grant, Harrison Gilbertson. In 1916, the 1st Australian Tunnelling Company is tunneling beneath German fortifications and bunkers to detonate massive explosive charges.

title: Nebo Nad Bjelovarom
synopsis: Directed by Nedeljko Lajsic.

title: War Wrecks: The Untold Stories - The Duplex Drives of Omaha
synopsis: Directed by Serge Tignères. With Fabien Autin. In Normandy, June 6, 1944, a dozen Sherman tanks equipped with floats, the famous Duplex Drives (DD), leave their ship to swim to Omaha Beach, where not all of them make it, contributing to one of the greatest debacle of WWII.

title: The Birthday Party
synopsis: Directed by Abbas Lajevardi. With Ahmad Kaveri, Nadin Khoury, Omaia Malas, Aliram Nooraei. The Birthday Party is the story of a Syrian family living in the Zainabia district where the Takfiri terrorists are eager to conquer. While Rashad, the happy teenage boy of the family, is celebrating his little sister's birthday, his neighborhood is faced with a heavy attack from the Takfirist. After this dangerous event, his family decides to leave home and search for a safer place. On this path, Rashad faces many obstacles that deeply impact his character and outlook on life.

title: Under the North Star II
synopsis: Directed by Timo Koivusalo. With Ilkka Koivula, Vera Kiiskinen, Risto Tuorila, Ritva Jalonen. Continues to follow the life of a Finnish family from aftermath of the Finnish Civil War to the Second World War which unites the country. But at what cost?

title: The Day of the Beast
synopsis: Directed by Mikhail Konovalchuk. With Johannes Van-Utr, Svetlana Pati, Deanna Dezmari, Rinat Ibragimov. The action of the film develops in the last days of the Great Patriotic War. The Nazis are retreating from the occupied cities with battles, and in one of them a young sniper from the Hitler Youth is lost.

title: Amaru
synopsis: Directed by Robert A. Cuadra. With Monej Cruz, Vincent Leon, Brett Koontz, Ben Soriano. A young revolutionary questions humanity and the chaos of war during socio-political upheaval in the fictional Latin American country of Caldera.

title: Snow & Ashes
synopsis: Directed by Charles-Olivier Michaud. With Rhys Coiro, David-Alexandre Coiteux, Lina Roessler, Marina Eva. Blaise Dumas, war correspondent, covers an armed conflict in Eastern Europe. When he wakes from a temporary coma in his home town of Quebec City, Blaise discovers that his long time collaborator and photographer has not come back with him. He then sets out to recapture the events that led to his friend's disappearance and his own narrow escape from the war zone.

title: Bruc, the Manhunt
synopsis: Directed by Daniel Benmayor. With Juan José Ballesta, Vincent Perez, Astrid Bergès-Frisbey, Santi Millán. 1808. The Napoleonic Army suffers its first defeat at the hands of a single man

title: 6 Foot Rule
synopsis: Directed by Arthur J. Mangano. With Tony Devon, Richard Jenkins, David Morse, Kelly Le Brock. A high-tech military squadron on a mission to kill find themselves in a city with no exits.

title: In Another Lifetime
synopsis: Directed by Elisabeth Scharang. With Ursula Strauss, Johannes Krisch, Orsolya Tóth, Franziska Singer. At the end of World War II, Hungarian Jews are forced on a death march to the Austrian concentration camp Mauthausen. Only few civilians try to rescue them.

title: Zoya
synopsis: Directed by Olga Tovma. With Aleksandr Demidov, Vladimir Dyomin, Egor Katushenko, Sergey Klyuchnikov. 1941 year. War correspondent Pyotr Lidov, contrary to the ban of the editor-in-chief of the newspaper Pravda, Pospelov, is conducting his own investigation into the execution of a young girl in a village occupied by the Germans. Its results force the hero to choose between loyalty to the system and the desire to tell the whole truth about what really happened.

title: Inner Wars
synopsis: Directed by Masha Kondakova. Since the uprising of a pro Russian insurgency in eastern Ukraine in 2014, hundreds of woman joined the army. Only a few made it to the front line. Filmmaker Masha embeds herself in the war zone to follow the daily life of three of them. By sharing the intimacy of these fighters, Masha soon becomes a victim of this brotherhood conflict jeopardizing this film and her life.

title: The Blue Danube
synopsis: Directed by Akira Ikeda. With Hiroki Konno, Kô Maehara, Hiroki Nakajima, Naoya Shimizu. The soldiers no longer know why they are at war, and when it even started. Daily and dutifully they march to the river and shoot at the opposite village from 9 to 5 - orders are orders after all.

title: Paper Grave
synopsis: Directed by Elchin Arifoglu. With Leyla Babayeva, Ramil Farzili, Jamshid Gubadov, Miryusif Hashimov. The film tells the story of innocent Azerbaijanis who died during the Khojaly genocide due to the closure of roads by Armenian terrorists and whose names are unidentified due to the collection and cremation of their bodies.

title: On the Front Line: WWII Britain
synopsis: WWII Britain

title: 578 days waiting
synopsis: Directed by Ahmad Abdolahian. With Saideh Arab, Khatereh Asadi, Abdoreza Hamidi Ashtiani, Heshmat Ghasemi. In connection with the great operation of Jerusalem and the conquest of Khorramshahr; This film depicts the time and time of release.

title: Mr. Pip
synopsis: Directed by Andrew Adamson. With Hugh Laurie, Xzannjah Matsi, Healesville Joel, Eka Darville. As a war rages on in the province of Bougainville in Papua New Guinea, a young girl becomes transfixed by the Charles Dickens novel Great Expectations, which is being read at school by the only white man in the village.

title: 5 Days of War
synopsis: Directed by Renny Harlin. With Rupert Friend, Emmanuelle Chriqui, Richard Coyle, Heather Graham. A drama set centered around the war between Russia and Georgia, and focused on an American journalist, his cameraman, and a Georgian native who become caught in the crossfire.

title: The Battle Above: True Stories from WWII Pilots
synopsis: True Stories from WWII Pilots

title: The Pacific War: Okinawa & Guadalcanal
synopsis: Okinawa & Guadalcanal

title: Churchill: The Road to Victory
synopsis: The Road to Victory

title: Baker Boys: Inside the Surge
synopsis: Inside the Surge

title: Rendez-vous au monument aux morts
synopsis: Directed by Marie Chevais. With Annette Becker, Rémi Dalisson, Franck David, Élise Julien.

title: Oliver Sherman
synopsis: Directed by Ryan Redford. With Garret Dillahunt, Donal Logue, Molly Parker, Fiona Highet. Feeling lost and disconnected, with no family of his own, veteran Sherman Oliver sets out to the countryside in search of the soldier who saved him back in the war. That man, Franklin Page, has long since moved on - to a wife, two children, and a reliable job in a reliably safe and quiet rural town. Upon arriving, Sherman seems at first a harmless if awkward shell of a man. But as he inserts himself further into the Pages' life, he reveals himself to be an angry, unstable individual prone to great jealousy and deep resentment. The stability Franklin worked so hard to establish is soon threatened, and the violence he believed he'd left behind in the war begins to re-emerge and cloud over both the household and the town itself.

title: Field of Operations: The Tunisia Campaign
synopsis: The Tunisia Campaign

title: Caterpillar
synopsis: Directed by Kôji Wakamatsu. With Shinobu Terajima, Shima Ohnishi, Ken Yoshizawa, Keigo Kasuya. During the Second Sino-Japanese War, in 1940, Lieutenant Kurokawa returns home as a honored and decorated soldier... but deprived of his arms and legs lost in battle in mainland China. All hopes, from the village men and women to close family members, turn to Shigeko, the Lieutenant's wife

title: Home of the Brave
synopsis: Directed by Luca Huff. With Serena Loomba, John Thomas, Joe Bekiranov, Max Beers. A trio of civilians set out on a perilous quest to rescue a lost soldier amidst a brutal second American civil war.

title: Land of the Free
synopsis: Directed by Luca Huff. With Max Beers, Joe Bekiranov, Shannon Bittner, Andrei Danilov. A young man joins a platoon of battle-hardened militiamen to protect his home state from invaders amid a second American civil war.

title: Fuhrerbunker: Adolf Hitler's Final Days
synopsis: Adolf Hitler's Final Days

title: Atomic Mom
synopsis: Directed by M.T. Silvia. With Howard Lukk, Emiko Okada, M.T. Silvia, Pauline Silvia. Atomic Mom is a feature-length documentary about two mothers, an American Scientist and a Japanese Survivor, who make peace decades after the bombing of Hiroshima.

title: 20 Cigarettes
synopsis: Directed by Aureliano Amadei. With Vinicio Marchioni, Carolina Crescentini, Giorgio Colangeli, Orsetta De Rossi. Autobiographical story about an assistant director who receives an offer to shoot a film in Iraq.

title: Under Jakob's Ladder
synopsis: Directed by Mann Munoz. With Jeff Stewart, Christopher Elliott, Sal Rendino, Quentin McCuiston. Jakob, a former teacher who lost his job due to the new Communist system, can only stand by and watch as the world around him slowly disintegrates, and fear and suspicion rule the day. Like most of the men, he soon finds himself in a Soviet prison.

title: Family Work
synopsis: Directed by Valeriy Balayan. Family work is an Ukrainian documentary film. It tells us a story of three families from the Eastern Ukraine, stereotypically Russian-speaking part of the country. When the Russian military intervention started in Ukraine in 2014, all families members decided to defend their homeland from the Russian aggressor. It has become a family work for them.

title: Faithful to Its Duty
synopsis: Directed by Tkachenko Yuri. In the imagination of many people, the concepts of "devotion" and "faithfulness" are enshrined in one common image of a "true faithful friend"

title: Nisei Stories of Wartime Japan
synopsis: Directed by Mary McDonald. Somewhat overlooked in the history of Japanese-Americans during World War II are the experiences of American citizens of Japanese ancestry who were in Japan during the war. 'Nisei Stories of Wartime Japan' features interviews with these Americans who tell us their eyewitness accounts of events in wartime Japan and relate social and political conditions of the time.

title: Silent Shame
synopsis: Directed by Akiko Izumitani. With Ren Hanami, Akiko Izumitani. A Japanese-born filmmaker took seven years to peel back the cultured facade of her country, and uncovers its darkest secrets giving us a shocking and provocative look at Japan's inhumanity in war.

title: The Unknown Woman
synopsis: Directed by Elina Kivihalme. With Onerva Hintikka, Pirkko Hämäläinen, Anna-Kaarina Jaakkola, Eeva Jalo.

title: Standing Army
synopsis: Directed by Thomas Fazi, Enrico Parenti. With Olivier Bancoult, William Blum, Noam Chomsky, Yôichi Iha. Over the course of the last century, the US has silently encircled the world with a web of military bases unlike any other in history. No continent is spared.They have shaped the lives of millions, yet remain a mystery to most.

title: Ilhaq
synopsis: Directed by Jahongir Ahmedov. With Dilorom Karimova, Dilrabo Mirzaeva, Fotih Nasimov, Dilnavoz Akhmedova.

title: Flag of My Father
synopsis: Directed by Rodney Ray. With William Devane, GiGi Erneta, Andrew Sensenig, Patrick Kirton. William Devane portrays the family's patriarch, while John Schneider plays the sister's protagonist, her cynical civilian brother.

title: Laissez-faire
synopsis: Directed by Ruggero Arenella. With Stefano Accomo, Giovanni Agnelli, Jaime Roldós Aguilera, Salvador Allende. A historical and ideological perspective through which to identify the fundamental problems of the economic mechanism on which Western societies that have influenced the daily life of populations all over the world are based.

title: Ryabinovyy vals
synopsis: Directed by Alyona Semyonova, Aleksandr Smirnov. With Karina Andolenko, Elizaveta Arzamasova, Mariya Berdinskikh, Leonid Bichevin. They were young, their life was in bloom and their hearts were longing to love.

title: The Attempt Dossier
synopsis: Directed by Jorge Fons. With Daniel Giménez Cacho, José María Yazpik, Julio Bracho, Irene Azuela. Tells the story behind an assassination attempt perpetrated in 1897, by a dipsomaniac man, against the President of the Mexican Republic, General Porfirio Diaz.

title: The Butterfly
synopsis: Directed by Ghasem Arab. With Farajollah Golsefidi, Biuk Mirzaei, Ali Tajdary. A student tries to show the problems of a chemical warfare victim to others and faces many challenges. The main actors are Ali Tajdary and Mahmoud Maghami.

title: Chosin
synopsis: Directed by Brian Iglesias. After 60 years of silence, the survivors of the Chosin Reservoir Campaign of the Korean War take us on an emotional and heart-pounding journey through one of the most savage battles in American history.

title: Essential Killing
synopsis: Directed by Jerzy Skolimowski. With Vincent Gallo, Emmanuelle Seigner, Zach Cohen, Iftach Ophir. An Afghan POW attempts his escape.

title: Ploque
synopsis: Directed by Ghasem Arab. With Farajollah Golsefidi, Mahmood Maghami, Ali Tajdary. plaque the story is about reza, a boy who has a sick mother and has to pay for his mothers surgery. he is forced to steal with his other friend and faces many challenges. reza(Ali Tajdary)is the main character in the story

title: Amigo
synopsis: Directed by John Sayles. With Arthur Acuña, Irma Adlawan, John Arcilla, Merlin Bonning. A fictional account of events during the Philippine-American War.

title: For Greater Glory: The True Story of Cristiada
synopsis: Directed by Dean Wright. With Adrian Alonso, Rubén Blades, Catalina Sandino Moreno, Eduardo Verástegui. A chronicle of the Cristeros War (1926-1929); a war by the people of Mexico against the atheistic Mexican government.

title: The Night Cook
synopsis: Directed by Jay Irving. A 66 year old Night Cook living in Toronto goes in search of his family, traveling to his native Czechoslovakia for the fist time in 38 years.

title: 48 War Movies
synopsis: Directed by Christian Marclay. This 12-hour single-channel video installation screens forty-eight war films simultaneously, on loop in overlapping boxes, in a menacing and hypnotic daze of violence that could run forever. Shown as a continuous loop, dimensions variable.

title: Top Secret Rosies: The Female 'Computers' of WWII
synopsis: The Female 'Computers' of WWII

title: 71: Into the Fire
synopsis: Directed by John H. Lee. With Seung-Won Cha, Kwon Sang-woo, Seung-Hyun Choi, Seung-woo Kim. The story of student-soldiers trying to protect a middle school during the early days of the Korean War.

title: A Very Short War
synopsis: Directed by Myles Conti, Bill Young. With Bill Young, Matthew Dyktynski, Deborah Kennedy, Kevin Golsby. "A VERY SHORT WAR" is a deeply personal story, exploring the ramifications of loss. It follows the short life of early Australian aviator, Cliff Carpenter, using his narrative as a template to speak for all lives senselessly lost in wartime conflict. The documentary climaxes in the skies over Oslo, Norway as two Messerschmitt Bf110's attack a RAF Sunderland Flying Boat. Nine airmen perish and one miraculously survives. The story is told through the eyes of Bill Young, the nephew Cliff would never know.

title: Day of the Sparrow
synopsis: Directed by Philip Scheffner. DAY OF THE SPARROW is a political wildlife film. It centers around a country where the border between war and peace fades. On November 14, 2005, a sparrow is shot dead in Leeuwarden, the Netherlands, after it toppled over 23000 domino stones. A German soldier dies in Kabul as a result of a suicide bombing. With these headlines appearing side by side, Philip Scheffner is induced to use ornithological methods in his quest for the war. In Germany, not in Afghanistan.

title: Camp Victory, Afghanistan
synopsis: Directed by Carol Dysinger. Camp Victory, Afghanistan is the true story of the American Exit Strategy. Using 300 hours of footage shot over the course of three years, the film follows a battle-tested Afghan General and the steady stream of U.S. National Guard soldiers deployed to train the men of his newly formed battalion. It is the first film to examine the reality of building a functioning Afghan military-- but it is also a story about friendship and the unlikely bonds that form across cultural, political and social barriers.

title: Home by Christmas
synopsis: Directed by Gaylene Preston. With Tony Barry, Martin Henderson, Chelsie Florence, Tai Berdinner-Blades. A film memoir based on NZ filmmaker Gaylene Preston's interviews with her father about his World War II experiences.

title: War Time Rapes: The Unspoken Weapon
synopsis: Directed by Danièle Alet. With Celine Bardet, Bok Dong Kim, Denis Mukwege Mukengere.

title: Chicogrande
synopsis: Directed by Felipe Cazals. With Damián Alcázar, Juan Manuel Bernal, Bruno Bichir, Alejandro Calva. Butch Fenton, major of American army, comes for Villa's head and he's gonna get it. The "Punitive Expedition" proved to be the last major campaign of the U.S. Cavalry. Mexican revolution is the first social movement of the century.

title: My Way
synopsis: Directed by Je-kyu Kang. With Jang Dong-Gun, Joe Odagiri, Bingbing Fan, Kim In-kwon. In World War II-era Korea, rival runners, one Korean (Jang Dong-gun) and one Japanese (Joe Odagiri), go to war together against the Soviets.

title: Minus One
synopsis: Directed by Jon Osbeck, Marc Wiskemann. With Jon Osbeck, Roger Bailey, Remy Brommer, Jennifer Schaaf. When three soldiers from am Army Reserve unit are called to fight in the Middle East, they must prepare themselves for the possibility of never returning home.

title: Red and White II: Blood of Eagles
synopsis: Directed by Conor Allyn, Yadi Sugandi. With Donny Alamsyah, Ario Bayu, Atiqah Hasiholan, Alex Komang. The second movie of "Red and White" trilogy and set during the Indonesian revolution in 1947-1948, as a band of guerrillas fight for Indonesia's freedom on land, sea, and air against the Dutch empire.

title: The American Dream
synopsis: Directed by Jamil Walker Smith. With Malcolm Goodwin, Jamil Walker Smith, Michael Trotter, Bradley Stryker. Armed with dreams that extend beyond their block, Luis and Ronald, two best friends from Los Angeles, videotape their last 36 hours before shipping off to Afghanistan. One hundred days before Obama's inauguration, these young men have joined the Marines together to face the obstacles and circumstances that seem to overwhelm their passage into manhood. Luis wants to be a filmmaker and Ronald wants to travel the world and raise a family. Through the lens of Luis's video camera, they capture their friends, family members and places they call home - to remember who they are and where they come from. In their darkest hour, they turn on the video camera for the last time and document the final moments of their journey home. They soon realize that their dreams and promises of a new life mean nothing in a place called War.

title: Kingdom of Dust: Beheading of Adam Smith
synopsis: Directed by Heath Jones. With Elyes Gabel, Stephen Hogan, Alyy Khan, Dhafer L'Abidine. In a basement, somewhere in war torn Baghdad, hostage Adam Smith is waiting to die.

title: Until We Meet Again, as Winners!
synopsis: Directed by Nikolaos Noulas. With Ilias Metallidis.

title: Eisis
synopsis: Directed by Seth Blaustein. With Erik Nelson, Wachiraboon Boonyaruttapun, Tom Brown, Christian Cartner. The story of Captain Eisis Thorsson, a life-long special operations soldier from the Nordic country of Saesland, and his journey into the forests of Anlawath, Southern Asia. Eisis is pitted against the odds in this tale of subtle complexities. As the lone survivor of a chance land-mine explosion, Eisis must survive the forest home of an indigenous native tribe, the La-Wah. His warrior instincts lead him into a web of fateful encounters with the local Shaman, who lives by her own set of instincts. Allow yourself to be drawn into the ebb and flow of instinctive actions in this story that appeals more to intuition than to intellect.

title: WWII Aircraft: Designed for Victory
synopsis: Designed for Victory

title: Irena Sendler: In the Name of Their Mothers
synopsis: In the Name of Their Mothers

title: Adios Mi Amigo
synopsis: Directed by Kalpna Singh-Chitnis. With Carlo Astuti, Raj Champaneri, Nirvan Chitnis, Vishwa Chitnis. When the love is unconditional, it can't be undone.

title: For Honor with Valor
synopsis: Directed by Kevin McElroy. With Ryan Hallberg, Cheryl Berg Wineman. Ryan Hallberg is a young Iraq Veteran from Minnesota that tells his story of his life in the Military and experiences from the time that he enlisted right out of high school, to the convoy mission that ended his Military career due to a roadside bomb; an IED attack. He shares his hardships with the aftermath of the attack that left him critically injured, enduring weeks of treatments and surgeries in the hospital, but also shows his courage and will to move forward in life even after his leg was amputated. If he had a choice to go back and do it all over again, he would still choose the same path into the military because of his honor and respect that he has for his country.

title: Patrol Base Jaker
synopsis: Directed by Kevin Kerwin, David Scantling. With Gus Biggio, Brian Huysman, Michael Kuiper, William McCollough. A documentary film about the US Marines and the practice of counter-insurgency in Helmand Province, Afghanistan.

title: Mausam
synopsis: Directed by Pankaj Kapur. With Shahid Kapoor, Sonam Kapoor, Anupam Kher, Supriya Pathak. A war, religious conflicts, and misunderstandings create obstacles for a couple of different faiths.

title: Muhabbat Bahori
synopsis: Directed by Ibrahim Rasulov. With Hamza Hasanov, Shakhnoza Hozhimurodova.

title: Kamenge, Northern Quarters
synopsis: Directed by Manu Gerosa, Salva Muñoz. Kamenge, Northern Quarters is the picture of a whole country, Burundi, which asks for freedom and justice, the ideals Alexis Sinduhije is fighting for. The Northern Quarters of the capital city Bujumbura are the symbol of one of the most cruel wars the world has ever known, the conflict between hutu and tutsi. The background and the glances of the ones who have not left are interwoven with the life of Alexis who gave up his job as a journalist in 2007 to stand for President in 2010. It is possible to build a liveable Burundi. You must only believe it and take the risk. Alexis says. In Burundi, although the present government was elected democratically, the people who profess freedom of speech put their life in danger.

title: A Farewell to Fools
synopsis: Directed by Bogdan Dreyer. With Gérard Depardieu, Harvey Keitel, Laura Morante, Bogdan Iancu. Once upon a time, during World War II, somewhere in Nazi occupied Romania, a night of comic misadventures ensues when a boy discovers a dead soldier.

title: The Patience Stone
synopsis: Directed by Atiq Rahimi. With Golshifteh Farahani, Hamid Djavadan, Hassina Burgan, Massi Mrowat. In a war ridden country a woman watches over the husband reduced to a vegetable state by a bullet in the neck, abandoned by Jihad companions and brothers. One day, the woman decides to say things to him she could never have done before.

title: Delta Zulu
synopsis: Directed by Chris Hickey. With George Katt, Chris Rymer, Stephen Brou, Paul Champy. Humanity has survived what seemed to be the apocalypse, but a threat still remains. Delta Zulu follows Clark, a freelance reporter who will be amongst the few civilians ever allowed into a Red Zone, a lawless quarantined area that still breathes war. Clark has been embedded with a team of mercenary contractors from White Shield International, one of the thousands of Private Military Companies that travel into The Zone on a daily basis to fulfill contracts for the government, large corporations, and private individuals. Clark attempts to find a story amongst a group of forgotten soldiers in a forgotten war and gets more than he bargains for.

title: Armadillo
synopsis: Directed by Janus Metz. Danish soldiers are sent to Afghanistan in 2009 for 6 months, to help stabilize the country against the Taliban. They're stationed on Armadillo military base in Helman province. Unlike other war movies, this is the real deal - no actors.

title: The Wereth Eleven
synopsis: Directed by Robert Child. With Corey Reynolds, Ken Arnold, Chris Cudzilo, Thomas McArdle. During World War II, 1.2 million African-Americans served in America's Armed Forces. Fully 125,000 served overseas. 708 were killed. Among these were The Wereth Eleven. Their story was lost to history. Until now.

title: Postcard
synopsis: Directed by Kaneto Shindô. With Etsushi Toyokawa, Shinobu Ôtake, Naomasa Musaka, Akira Emoto. Toward the end of World War II, middle-aged soldier Keita is entrusted with a postcard from a comrade who is sure he will die in battle. After the war ends, Keita visits his comrade's wife Yuko and bears witness to the tragic life she has led. This year's Oscar entry from Japan finds SHINDO in top form and his 49th and reportedly last film as fresh and poignant as ever.

title: All or Nothing
synopsis: Directed by Craig Anderson. With Craig Anderson, Heather Anderson, Jim Anderson, Jimmie Anderson. A group of terrorists kidnap CEO's and their families and torture them to gain control of their companies to take their drug running to a new level. A special forces team is sent in to investigate and bring back the proof of the atrocities. When the team witness brutal murders of the hostages, tension rises as Smith changes the mission from one of recognizance to one of rescue at all cost. This film will keep you on the edge of your seat as director Craig Anderson takes you through the brutal and gory battles and plot twists of his first feature length production.

title: Air War Over Europe - The Liberation of Europe
synopsis: Directed by L. Douglas Keeney. Seen through archival images and seldom seen still photography Air War Europe is a history of airborne combat throughout WWII.

title: Across Occupied France - The Liberation of Europe
synopsis: Directed by L. Douglas Keeney. Across Occupied France chronicles this momentous liberation of France, eventually bringing allied troops to the very brink of Nazi Germany.

title: Into Nazi Germany - The Liberation of Europe
synopsis: Directed by L. Douglas Keeney. Relive one of the broadest offensives in history as Allied troops move in towards the German Roer Valley.

title: Attack of the Wehrmacht - The Liberation of Europe
synopsis: Directed by L. Douglas Keeney. Witness the darkest hours of the war in Europe since D-day - the war's most grueling battles at Bastogne, St. Vith, and The Battle of the Bulge.

title: WWII Liberation of Europe - Victory Over Germany
synopsis: Directed by L. Douglas Keeney. This program traces the aftermath of the Nazi surrender. From quelling remaining resistances, hunting for saboteurs, creating sustainable towns, and saving countless emaciated prisoners of war.

title: 442: Live with Honor, Die with Dignity
synopsis: Live with Honor, Die with Dignity

title: Special Forces
synopsis: Directed by Stéphane Rybojad. With Diane Kruger, Djimon Hounsou, Benoît Magimel, Denis Ménochet. A French journalist in Afghanistan is kidnapped by the Taliban.

title: East Wind Rain
synopsis: Directed by Yunlong Liu. With Yunlong Liu, Bingbing Fan, Xiaoran Li, Takayuki Takemoto. The story of spies working for different countries attempting to decode coded weather forecasts.

title: Oba: The Last Samurai
synopsis: Последний самурай

title: The Painted Bird
synopsis: Directed by Václav Marhoul. With Petr Kotlár, Nina Sunevic, Alla Sokolova, Stanislav Bilyi. A young Jewish boy somewhere in Eastern Europe seeks refuge during World War II where he encounters many different characters.

title: Private Peaceful
synopsis: Directed by Pat O'Connor. With James McArdle, Hero Fiennes Tiffin, George MacKay, Jack O'Connell. Set in the fields of Devon and the WW1 battlefields of Flanders, two brothers fall for the same girl while contending with the pressures of their feudal family life, the war, and the price of courage and cowardice.

title: Elle s'appelait Sarah
synopsis: Directed by Gilles Paquet-Brenner. With Kristin Scott Thomas, Mélusine Mayance, Niels Arestrup, Frédéric Pierrot. In modern-day Paris, a journalist finds her life becoming entwined with a young girl whose family was torn apart during the notorious Vel' d'Hiv Roundup in 1942.

title: Forgotten Bomb
synopsis: Directed by Stuart Overbey. With Bud Ryan, Michael Hall, Dave Ward, Gar Alperovitz. When the Cold War ended, worry about nuclear weapons receded. But has the nuclear threat really diminished? Join Bud Ryan on a personal and global journey to discover what the bomber can learn from the bombed, and what our prospects look like for finally living in a nuclear-free world. Features interviews with bomb survivors from Hiroshima and Nagasaki, former U.S. Secretary of State George Shultz, authors Gar Alperovitz and Jonathan Schell, and many more.

title: Habibi Rasak Kharban
synopsis: Directed by Susan Youssef. With Maisa Abd Elhadi, Kais Nashif, Yussuf Abu-Warda, Amer Khalil. 'Habibi Rasak Kharban' (Darling, Something's Wrong with Your Head) is a dramatic feature that tells the story of a forbidden love in Gaza. The film is a modern re-telling of the famous ancient Sufi parable 'Majnun Layla'.

title: Back in Nam
synopsis: Directed by Jason Gerbay. With Shanthal Artelle, Blair Bloom, Dennis Cage, Cristen Cumblewood. An aspiring screenwriter becomes his latest writing assignment; an enraged Vietnam veteran.

title: Frozen Hell
synopsis: Directed by Ville Suhonen. With Vilma Melasniemi, Eero Saarinen, Antti Seppänen, Antti Virmavirta.

title: Afghan Luke
synopsis: Directed by Mike Clattenburg. With Nick Stahl, Nicolas Wright, Stephen Lobo, Steve Cochrane. An experienced journalist risks returning to Afghanistan in pursuit of a sensational story.

title: Sengadal
synopsis: Directed by Leena Manimekalai. With Jesuthasan Antonythasan, Munusamy M., Leena Manimekalai, Nimal S.. Dhanushkodi, the Indo-Sri Lankan border town, is the crucible wherein History is brewing this concoction of defeated lives and exhausted dreams. Manimekalai, the filmmaker, Soori, a half-wit Sri Lankan Tamil Refugee, Munusamy, the fisherman, Rosemary, the social worker in Jesuit Christian Refugee Services, try hard to retain their sanity in this mad jumble. Their interactions with the dead or living refugees, their skirmishes with the Indian and Sri Lankan States, their personal lives overrun by external events - form the kernel of this narration. ,

title: The Sleeping Voice
synopsis: Directed by Benito Zambrano. With Inma Cuesta, María León, Marc Clotet, Daniel Holguín. During the Spanish postwar, Pepita leaves her village for the capital to be near her sister, pregnant while in prison. There, she falls for a bourgeois who still keep the fight alive in the hills.

title: War Flowers
synopsis: Directed by Serge Rodnunsky. With Christina Ricci, Jason Gedrick, Gabrielle Popa, Tom Berenger. North Carolina 1863, the Civil War is raging. In this inspired story of tragedy and love we follow the lives of Melody, a precocious seven-year old, and her young mother Sarabeth as they struggle on their farm to survive the war.

title: Serdtse vraga
synopsis: Directed by Aleksandr Vysokovskiy. With Tatyana Arntgolts, Pavel Boloyangov, Andrey Chadov, Vyacheslav Ilin.

title: 4 Days in May
synopsis: Directed by Achim von Borries. With Pavel Wenzel, Aleksey Guskov, Ivan Shvedoff, Andrey Merzlikin. A group of Russian soldiers are sent into Northern Germany at the tail-end of WWII, where they occupy a children's home in close proximity to a larger German unit. Against these odds, a friendship forms between a German orphan and a childless Soviet captain.

title: Tears of Gaza
synopsis: Directed by Vibeke Løkkeberg. In a rough style, by way of unique footage, the brutal consequences of modern wars are exposed. The film also depicts the ability of women and children to handle their everyday life after a dramatic war experience. Many of them live in tents or in ruins without walls or roofs. They are all in need of money, food, water and electricity. Others have lost family members, or are left with seriously injured children. Can war solve conflicts or create peace? The film follows three children through the war and the period after the ceasefire.

title: Di Xue De Hong Du Juan
synopsis: Directed by Zhanjun An. With Yang Jinger, Irina Kaptelova, Qi Li.

title: From Terror to Resistance: Nazi Camp Pavlos Melas, Thessaloniki 1941-1944
synopsis: Nazistiko Stratopedo Pavlou Mela, Thessaloniki 1941-1944

title: 13 Minutes
synopsis: Directed by Oliver Hirschbiegel. With Christian Friedel, Katharina Schüttler, Burghart Klaußner, Johann von Bülow. In November 1939, Georg Elser's attempt to assassinate Adolf Hitler fails, and he is arrested. During his confinement, he recalls the events leading up to his plot and his reasons for deciding to take such drastic action.

title: Wunderkinder
synopsis: Directed by Marcus O. Rosenmüller. With Gedeon Burkhard, Natalia Avelon, Gudrun Landgrebe, Michael Mendl. Three musically talented children look to the future, but their hopes crumble when Germany and Russia enter into war.

title: In the Land of Blood and Honey
synopsis: Directed by Angelina Jolie. With Zana Marjanovic, Goran Kostic, Rade Serbedzija, Vanessa Glodjo. During the Bosnian War, Danijel, a soldier fighting for the Serbs, re-encounters Ajla, a Bosnian who's now a captive in his camp he oversees. Their once promising connection has become ambiguous as their motives have changed.

title: Auschwitz
synopsis: Directed by Uwe Boll. With Steffen Mennekes, Arved Birnbaum, Maximilian Gärtner, Friedhelm Gärtner. Controversial director Uwe Boll depicts the harsh reality of the process inside one of the most infamous Nazi death camps by using brutally realistic imagery. Book-ended by documentary footage as well as interviews with German teenagers about what they know about the Holocaust, Boll effectively shows us just how depraved and sadistic life in the camp could be.

title: There Was Once...
synopsis: Directed by Gabor Kalman. This film is about a Catholic high school teacher in Kalocsa, Hungary who while doing research in local history discovers the lost Jewish community that once thrived there. She shares her research with her students, teaching tolerance, fighting prejudice. She organized a memorial for this lost community, which was attended by the Mayor, the Archbishop, several survivors and second and third generations. At the same time the neo-Nazi party of Hungary held a demonstration and a young girl visiting from New York was hit by a sling shot while attending a memorial service at the newly restored Jewish cemetery.

title: Witness Last Grave
synopsis: Directed by Aykan Yucel Irwins. With John Brandon, Merrilynn Brent, Jessica Brighten, Jeff Campbell.

title: C- Bar, II
synopsis: Directed by Patrick Ball. With Bob Anderson, Marcia Baugher, Mark Baugher, Jeannie Branstrator. The Barnett family is battling the death of Marcia Jean and Uncle NoName, Norm's sister comes to live at the C-Bar ranch, and John Doe puts a $5,000 bounty on Dockie's head.

title: Badland
synopsis: Directed by Justin Lee. With Kevin Makely, Trace Adkins, Mira Sorvino, Bruce Dern. Detective Matthias Breecher is hired to track down the worst of the Confederate war criminals. As he roams the Old West seeking justice, his resolve is tested when he meets a determined pioneer woman who is far more than she seems.

title: Cuenta Saldada
synopsis: Directed by Adrian Mora. With Nicole Brokke, Texi Gonzalez, Adrian Mora, RoChia.

title: The Outsider
synopsis: Directed by Timothy Woodward Jr.. With Jonathan Patrick Foo, Trace Adkins, Sean Patrick Flanery, Kaiwi Lyman. In search of a better life, a railroad worker (Foo) finds himself on the wrong side of a group of corrupt lawmen. As the Marshal (Adkins) attempts to control his town, tragedy strikes forcing him to decide between justice and family.

title: Tek
synopsis: Directed by David Cinnella. With Walter Nicoletti. TEK is the story of a lone gunslinger who roams the desert wastelands of the future in search of the man who kidnapped and killed his one and only daughter.

title: Gunfight at Silver Creek
synopsis: Directed by Tony London. With Jim Beaver, Jennifer Runyon, Charlie Schlatter, Charles Matthau.

title: American Confederate
synopsis: Directed by Christopher Forbes. With William Adams, Jezibell Anat, Kimberly Campbell, Jerry Chesser. "American Confederate" follows a group of Confederate cavalry, and a group of Union (Federal) cavalry, from late 1862 until the end of the Civil War in 1865.

title: Mudo
synopsis: Directed by Jacob Boatsman. With Sean Draheim, Eduardo Sanchez, Drew Colven, Jackson Workman. When two inmates, Lloyd "Bunny" Madison and a mysterious mute, escape prison, the Warden, mayor and their film partner pursue to hunt them down. Meanwhile, a retired cop, John Grover, goes after the case of the missing inmates for his own satisfaction.

title: Black Cowboy
synopsis: Directed by Dre Banks. With CJ Morrison, Tomathan McGinnis, Chaz Taylor, Shirley Corbin. Created by Colin A. Thompson, this is the story of Black Cowboy, an innocent man accused of a crime he did not commit. But, regardless of the accusations hurled at him, he remains positive and continues to do the right thing while doing all he can to prove his innocence.

title: Wyatt Earp Shoots First
synopsis: Directed by Christopher Forbes. With William Adams, Jezibell Anat, Meganiiq Barlet, Thomas Barlet. Wyatt Earp is one of the best lawman in the West and a first-rate gunfighter. But he is a conflicted individual who is haunted by what he was taught early in his career. Never, ever shoot first. But even a good man learns that sometimes, rules have to be broken to survive.

title: Elsewhere, TX
synopsis: Directed by McHenry Taylor. With Dalton Craft, Ricco Fajardo, Hunter Barnett, Tomorrow Shea. Set in a forgotten corner of the American South, a young boy and a stoic gunslinger seek revenge against a shared enemy. Despite their deadly focus, the journey becomes complicated as they encounter other inhabitants of this bizarre world.

title: Colomba Legend
synopsis: Directed by Rosario Neri, Vito Colomba. With Maurizio Bologna, Francesco Capizzi, Diego Gueci, Gioacchino Poma. Twenty-five years ago, Vito Colomba, a quarry worker from a small village in Sicily near Trapani, became famous throughout Italy for his "Quattro Carogne a Malopasso", a western film made in complete autonomy and without the use of professional actors. The children of the legendary characters will bring to life again the new film by the master of the prickly pear-scented western, Vito Colomba.

title: Showdown at Shelby's Shack
synopsis: Directed by Scott Hester. With Heather Bash, Bill Capskas, Thomas Conklin, Cindy Cook. Sheriff Austin Shelby is determined to uncover the dangerous & deadly facts behind the Nellie Harper murder for hire plot. After an attempt on his own life the Sheriff teams up with a mysterious US Marshal who has just arrived in town.

title: Black Mountain
synopsis: Directed by Chaz Lee. With Michele Bauer, Fran Booth, Dominic Bova, Jim Burton. Forged in iron vows, clandestine secrets surface bringing a cloak and dagger reunion of outlaws which sets in motion a volatile chain of events.

title: Christmas on the Range
synopsis: Directed by Gary Wheeler. With Erin Cahill, Nicholas Gonzalez, A Martinez, Lindsay Wagner. Kendall's one holiday wish is to keep the family ranch solvent. Her rival's charming son offers help-and maybe more-but can he be trusted?

title: Santa Clara
synopsis: Directed by Pedro Antonio Gutiérrez. With Cristian Mercado, Jorge Arturo Lora, Hugo Francisquini, Silvana Continanza. Santiago, a man in his 40's works as a cowboy, lives in the outsides of remote village in Beni. His past is unclear, rumors say that he's a fugitive, an assassin or a bandit. A work offer of driving a 2000 cattle herd to the Santa Clara ranch that is really far comes one day. Is a well-paid job offer, and he's the only one that can do it, he needs the money, but going to Santa Clara will force him to leave his past behind or finally take revenge from those who forced him to the exile.

title: The Warrant
synopsis: Directed by Brent Christy. With Neal McDonough, Steven R. McQueen, Casper Van Dien, Annabeth Gish. After fighting in the Civil War, two Union Army buddies find themselves on opposite sides of the law with the post-war peace at risk.

title: The Prodigal
synopsis: Directed by Jenny Huff, David Huff. With Casey Beymer, Ashley Cohee, Justin Cohee, Lacy Cohee. What happens when a disgruntled teenager leaves a broken home but comes back later? A story of revenge and betrayal. A dysfunctional family to say the least.

title: Bring 'em Black
synopsis: Directed by Michael Bonner. With Bruce Bennett, Nathan Criswell, Travis Dunn, Sandy Dutchak. A struggling female farmer is sworn in as sheriff when a desperate town finds itself in need of law and order.

title: Frontier
synopsis: With Sandra Guzman, Fernando Madrid, Roque Pantaleon Chavela. Texas. 1848. Mexican families are being forced off their land by the Saxon's who come to colonize this unpopulated state. Two Mexican families, the Iturraldes and the Villareals, find their peaceful existence shattered when they refuse to sell their ranches to the Mackenzies, an Irish family who will stop at nothing to get what they want. And what they want, lies deep in this extensive and fertile land...oil.

title: 7 Boozers
synopsis: Directed by Sergey Kuznetsov. With Vetal Baybakov, Andrey Fekhretdinov, Sergey Kuznetsov, Dmitriy Rakov. An unspecified future. The consumer society era is over. There are no cars, there are no horses. The seven heroes must cross the Enchanted Valley to find the Divine Bar.

title: Jimmy Attitude: Buffalo
synopsis: Buffalo

title: Yo Te Gusto?
synopsis: Directed by Edgardo González Amer. With Martina Krasinsky, Daniel Aráoz, Leticia Brédice, Marco Antonio Caponi. Teenager Nati lives in a humble neighborhood along with her brother Sebas. They distribute the food that their mother Mary makes, but this work fails to pay off her family's debt. Therefore, the two siblings decide to join a gang led by Yuca, an old man who carries out various crimes in the neighborhood, in a way too aggressive. The rebellion of Nati will cause conflicts in the group and the boss will turn his anger on her. But she will not stay with her arms crossed and will not forgive them.

title: Desertor
synopsis: Directed by Pablo Brusa. With Daniel Fanego, Marcelo Melingo, Santiago Racca, Pablo Tolosa.

title: Bloody Spurs
synopsis: Directed by Hector De La Rosa. With Victoria Stevens, Matthew Gooley, Mike Fass, Hector De La Rosa.

title: Ruthless Reprisal
synopsis: Directed by Johnny Ray Gibbs. With Johnny Ray Gibbs, Brent Rock. A lone sheriff on the hunt for a wanted man must find the killer before a mob of angry townspeople take the law into their own hands.

title: Never Grow Old
synopsis: Directed by Ivan Kavanagh. With Emile Hirsch, John Cusack, Déborah François, Molly McCann. An Irish undertaker profits when outlaws take over a peaceful American frontier town, but his family comes under threat as the death toll rises.

title: Not So Wild West
synopsis: Directed by Robert Ford. With Matthew Eidenbock, Nick Gomez, James Landry Hébert, Casey Swing.

title: Legacy River
synopsis: Directed by J.G. Turner. With Stephen C. Bell, Winston Gantt, Evan W. McCoy, J.G. Turner. After amassing a sizable fortune, a rancher must decide to save his ranch from foreclosure or pass the money to his god children while fighting off violent attempts pushing him to sell his ranch from a corrupt sheriff.

title: The Dalton Gang
synopsis: Directed by Christopher Forbes. With William Adams, Jezibell Anat, Gunner Bridger, Meghan Bridgers. When their brother is killed by an outlaw, three Dalton brothers join their sheriff's dept. When they're cheated by the law, they turn to crime. Trying to outdo Jesse James, they try to rob two banks at once in 1892. Things get ugly.

title: The Lone Ranger
synopsis: Directed by Gore Verbinski. With Johnny Depp, Armie Hammer, William Fichtner, Tom Wilkinson. Native American warrior Tonto recounts the untold tales that transformed John Reid, a man of the law, into a legend of justice.

title: Westerns: Cut to the Chase
synopsis: Cut to the Chase

title: Good Girl Lola
synopsis: Directed by Addison Heath, Jasmine Jakupi. With Cris Cochrane, Kieran Cochrane, Noah Cochrane, Rosaleen Cox. An actor and his dog try to survive in a post-covid19 world.

title: The Prodigal Cowboy
synopsis: Directed by Bo Bullock. With Scott McClard, Scott Mendes, Scott Mendes, Otto Thorwarth. Two brothers; Nick, an athletic high school football star and Mark, a rising name on the rodeo circuit have always been rivals. But, after a family tragedy, the competition heats up for their father's attention. Otto Thorwarth teams up with world champion bull rider Scott Mendes to deliver this Western-style, modern-day story of the prodigal son.

title: Mad Mad Wagon Party
synopsis: Directed by Dwight Brooks. With George Kennedy, Cathy Rankin, Slade Hall, Shane Dean.

title: A Portrait on the Search for Happiness
synopsis: Directed by Benjamin Rost. Documentary about the former diamond-diving village of Port Nolloth in South Africa.

title: The Rodeo Thief
synopsis: Directed by Brett Bentman. With Thom Hallum, Robert Keith, Sam Marra, Nadirah Shakir. An injured bull rider, that's seen his best days in the rodeo, agrees to steal roping horses for an unforgiving loan shark.

title: The Lion Kid 2
synopsis: With Thomas Freeley, Simon Hill, Eli James, Kelsey Painter. When Tuckerville's sheriff Kidd Mane gets back from vacation, he finds himself out of a job and the whole town up in arms

title: Western Movie Witness
synopsis: Directed by Aykan Yucel Irwins. With Ismet Ergun, Gina Gray, Aykan Yucel Irwins, Racheal Leigh.

title: The Mountaineer
synopsis: Directed by Richie Acevedo. With Quintin Acevedo, Richie Acevedo, AngelLee1993, Brandon Ashworth. Victoria Stokes, a young daughter of a wealthy businessman, runs away to escape an arranged marriage with an evil coal tycoon businessman Langley Prescott so she can instead be with the man she truly loves, Joshua Forbes.

title: Westopia
synopsis: With Jamie Chan, Thomas Freeley, Simon Hill, Larry G. Jones. Westopia's crooked mayor, Bucktooth Tucker plans to build a giant railroad system through the desert for fast travel to his town, but there's a problem, the owner of the last house standing in the road's way, Cody McFinster, refuses to sell. Cody will have to use his Southern charm and cunning to unite Westopia against its conniving mayor and save his home from destruction.

title: Gauchito Gil
synopsis: Directed by Fernando Del Castillo. With Roberto Vallejos, Claudio Da Passano, Paula Brasca, Estel Gómez. The story of the mitical Gauchito Gil from Argentina.

title: Full of Noise and Pain
synopsis: Directed by Nacho Aguirre. With Juan Alari, Emilio Bardi, Emanuel Gallardo, Facundo Sáenz Sañudo. Soria joins two bandits to rob a bank from a small village in Patagonia. He soon realises that he has made the greatest mistake of his life when he is forced to kill an innocent person.

title: Tales from Parts Unknown
synopsis: Directed by Cameron McCasland. With Larry Underwood, David Chattam, John Wells, Kenneth Garner. On Shackle Island, there is a somewhat dilapidated-looking mansion. And inside that mansion, there is a friendly and talkative scientist by the name of Dr. Gangrene.

title: Royals' Revenge
synopsis: Directed by Kellen Garner, Christopher Sheffield. With Kellen Garner, Alexis Moeller, Aaron Ginn-Forsberg, George Nelson. After an unscrupulous cattle baron announces his candidacy for governor, four estranged siblings set out in search of revenge for the death of their family.

title: The Wanderer
synopsis: Directed by Jon Cullen. With Andrew Blum, Luke Boger, Cody Dedon, Pappy Grant. Ash (AJ Neumann) roams the woods of the deep south in escape of a shrouded past until he comes across a gang of young outlaws. Its leader, Silas, (Cody Dedon) adopts Ash into their carefree life of petty crime and adventure. But when tragedy strikes at the gang's heart, Ash and Silas are set against one another on an irreversible path towards retribution and redemption.

title: Once Upon a Time in Tombstone
synopsis: Directed by Christopher Forbes. With Paul Clayton, Jerry Chesser, Jezibell Anat, Russell Dobson. This movie delivers all of the great characters you would expect in a film about Tombstone. The Earp Brothers, The Clanton Brothers, Doc Holliday, Johnny Ringo etc. and great gunfights. What the film delivers, is a multitude of pieces of the puzzle that complete the story, not just about why the gunfight happened but the real history about what led up to it and what followed.

title: The Loneliest Road in America
synopsis: Directed by Mardana M. Mayginnes. With Colin Michael Day, Chris Hayes, Abby Swagart, Jennifer Devereaux. On the road trip of his life, Jamie learns how to exploit women as a corporation would a resource.

title: Oro e piombo
synopsis: Directed by Emiliano Ferrera. With Maria Amato, Alfredo Angelini, Melina Arena, Philippe Boa.

title: The Platinum Peacemaker
synopsis: Directed by Bryant Hicks. With Stephen Brodie, Cassie Shea Watson, Edward Fontaine, Scott Yarnell. When a crooked land grabber with a desire to steal even more land and usher in the 'green movement' through violence, with a one-of-a-kind pistol, only one man can stop him...and he isn't available.

title: Desperate - An East Village Western
synopsis: Directed by Greg Shephard. With Merrith Bigfoot, Daniel Graf, Katya, Telephone Man. A portrait of a desperate man in the East Village circa 1996.

title: Big Money Rustlas
synopsis: Directed by Paul Andresen. With Violent J, Shaggy 2 Dope, Tony Borcherding, Blaze Ya Dead Homie. In the Wild West town of Mudbug, Sheriff Sugar Wolf arrives to confront an over-the-top villain, Big Baby Chips.

title: Ardor
synopsis: Directed by Pablo Fendrik. With Gael García Bernal, Alice Braga, Claudio Tolcachir, Chico Díaz. A mysterious man emerges from the Argentinean rainforest to help a poor farmer and his daughter, who are threatened by a band of mercenaries hired to force them to sell their land.

title: Sal
synopsis: Directed by Diego Rougier. With Fele Martínez, Patricio Contreras, Sergio Hernández, Javiera Contador. A film director obsessed with making a western decides to go to Northern Chile in search of a story for his screenplay. Being confused with another, a real adventure begins. Now he will have a good script... If he leaves alive The story of a man with no history. The journey of an author becoming his own character and his impossible return.

title: True Grit
synopsis: Directed by Ethan Coen, Joel Coen. With Jeff Bridges, Hailee Steinfeld, Matt Damon, Josh Brolin. A stubborn teenager enlists the help of a tough U.S. Marshal to track down her father's murderer.

title: Chasing Redemption
synopsis: Directed by Hayes Broadhead. With Erik Adair, Hayes Broadhead, Alden Jack, Candis Robbins. In 1890 a young man takes on a job as a hired gunman leaving his wife at home sad and alone. He finds himself chasing redemption when his wife is taken by a gang of bank robbers and is willing to do anything to get her back.

title: The Last Christeros
synopsis: Directed by Matias Meyer. After the mexican government tries to restrict religious practices, many people revolted, but now the wars is ending and the some of last rebels must decide whether to accept a pardon or continue their cause.

title: The Righteous and the Wicked
synopsis: Directed by Craig A. Butler. With Craig Myers, Billy Garberina, Justin Tade, Jeremy Owen. A wanted bandit gets caught up in a violent hunt for stolen cash when he learns outlaws have robbed the bank. Anyone who stands in his way will be killed until he gets back what's his.

title: These Lawless Lands
synopsis: Directed by Nicholas Pilk. With Marcos Camacho, Curtis Hubbard, Nicholas Pilk, Justin Manchette. Scavenger Jordan Lavonne and his posse only want to hunt down a thief who stole from their hellbent boss, Enoch Moss. But the wasteland is full of outlaws, viruses, and explosive mines. Lavonne must lead his men around the likes of a tribe of masked cannibals, a deadly virus, and a genocidal warlord known as Paris Cassidy. Moss, a warlord turned collector, will stop at nothing to make sure a golden idol is returned to his possession.

title: Heathens and Thieves
synopsis: Directed by Megan Peterson, John Douglas Sinclair. With Andrew Simpson, Gwendoline Yeo, Don Swayze, Richard Doyle. In the Old West, lawmen, drifters, and hired gunman converge on an isolated ranch, believing its Chinese owners possess stolen gold.

title: Horizonte Bajo Fuego
synopsis: Directed by Omar Saldaña. With Luis Mayorga, Franck Omar, Mary Paz, Jesús Robles.

title: Red Hill
synopsis: Directed by Patrick Hughes. With Ryan Kwanten, Steve Bisley, Tommy Lewis, Claire van der Boom. A young police officer must survive his first day's duty in a small country town.

title: Wild Horses and Renegades
synopsis: Directed by James Kleinert. With Jim Baca, Willie Morris Bioff, Tokala Black Elk, Michael Blake. Wild Horses and Renegades examines the plight of America's wild horses and the rapidly deteriorating condition of our wild Public Lands. The film follows the majestic Band Stallion, Traveler and his family who dwell in Disappointment Valley, Colorado. When the Bureau of Land Management conducts a massive wild horse roundup, Traveler and his family are torn apart. They are sent to Wild Horse prison in a brutal removal of two-thirds of their wild horse herd. The film tracks wild horse advocates as they work to return Traveler to his homeland. They have to do this before he is shipped to BLM Long Term Holding where he may face Euthanasia or worse, being shipped to Mexico for brutal slaughter.

title: Next Year Country
synopsis: Directed by Joseph Aguirre. Struggling to survive the worst drought since the dustbowl, three desperate Montana families hire a rainmaker -- a retired New York cab driver -- in a last ditch effort to save their farms. Like Burt Lancaster's magnetic character in the 1950s film 'The Rainmaker', who barnstormed the windswept tumbleweed towns of the drought-ravaged American prairie selling empty promises of rain, the rainmakers of popular imagination are never quite what they claim to be. But what about the rainmaker stories that appear from time to time in farm journals and rural newspapers across the American farm belt - personal accounts from farmers who claim success with rainmakers? Set against the backdrop of the rapid decline of the American family farm, and a prolonged period of drought which has U.N. climate scientists calling for a new understanding of what constitutes 'normal weather', NEXT YEAR COUNTRY is an exploration of an old American legend set in the contemporary American West.

title: Desert Rain
synopsis: Directed by Steve Loff. With Brea Angelo, William Arute, Todd Baker, Joey Garza. A young couple want to get out of their desert town and head for L.A. Before leaving they search for Lefty, a local music producer who took all of their cash. Everything they do takes them further away from their goal.

title: Swine
synopsis: Directed by Daniel Levitch. With Gregory Lee Kenyon, Åsa Wallander, Kellsy MacKilligan, Alex Rapport.

title: The Last Stand
synopsis: Directed by Jee-woon Kim. With Arron Shiver, Arnold Schwarzenegger, Titos Menchaca, Richard Dillard. The leader of a drug cartel busts out of a courthouse and speeds to the Mexican border, where the only thing in his path is a sheriff and his inexperienced staff.

title: The Gundown
synopsis: Directed by Dustin Rikert. With Peter Coyote, Andrew W. Walker, William Shockley, Sheree J. Wilson. Seeking revenge and justice, Cole Brandt finds himself in the lawless town of Dead River where he is faced with one last bloody showdown for freedom in order to protect The Majestic Saloon and a beautiful woman.

title: Snowblind
synopsis: Directed by Kilian Manning. With Robert Lyons, Mala Ghedia, Erik Hansen, Jana Pallaske. After the ice age returns civilizations and nations break down. A gunman is about to be executed when he is pardoned - conditioned on him killing someone. However, he ends up befriending his target instead but trouble doesn't end there.

title: The Magnificent Dead
synopsis: Directed by Shane Scott. With Bill Allgood, Linda Almanza, Larry Amaro, Karl Anderson. The Magnificent Dead takes place in the 1870's in the small Texas town of Rosewood where local rancher Jared Hamilton and his men have declared war on the town, using fear and death to prevent a new railroad line from coming through. Guided by a priest, Father Julian the desperate town leaders decide to hire a group of six gunmen to help clean up the town. These gunmen are legendary, as they are afflicted with Leprosy and fight with reckless abandon and ruthlessness, for they have nothing to lose.

title: The Way of the West
synopsis: Directed by Wyeth Clarkson. With Andrew W. Walker, Jessica Paré, Earl Pastko, John Wildman. A lone Mountie has come to town to clean up the corruption and crime. He prepares to take them down one by one in the most vicious showdown the town has ever seen.

title: The Academy
synopsis: Directed by Kenneth Barr. With Mustafa Al-Mosawi, Amanda Bladon, Dan Brodribb, Paul Brown. They are society's flotsam, murderers, sociopaths, criminals bred for Darwinian survival. A select group of convicted youths are given a second chance by a shadowy organization

title: Forajidos de la Patagonia
synopsis: Directed by Damián Leibovich. With Juan Manuel Rodil, Carla Pandolfi, Adrian Garavano, Horacio Dener. Pancho (Juan Manuel Rodil) is an independent filmmaker from Buenos Aires which is pushed by his grandfather Faust (Horacio Dener), to go after the loot of Butch Cassidy, who lived in Cholila (Chubut) between 1901 and 1905. Pursued by Commissioner Galvez (Oscar Huberty) for a crime he did't commit, Pancho will intersect with Nancy (Carla Pandolfi) and Anibal (Adrián Garavano). They will help him to find the treasure before Dimitri (Hernán Varela) a heartless professional searcher.

title: Redemption: For Robbing the Dead
synopsis: Directed by Thomas Russell. With John Freeman, Rance Howard, Robyn Adamson, Sierra Somerville. Henry Heath, a grieving lawman whose daughter has recently died, is assigned custody of the ghoulish Jean Baptiste, a notorious robber of 300 graves. Against the perilous Utah desert terrain Heath must somehow keep a marked man alive.

title: Guicheng (Ghosttown)
synopsis: Directed by Jon Cates. With Lal Avgen, Siera Begaye, Ei Jane Janet Lin, Emily Mercedes Rich.

title: Blackthorn
synopsis: Directed by Mateo Gil. With Sam Shepard, Eduardo Noriega, Stephen Rea, Magaly Solier. In Bolivia, Butch Cassidy (now calling himself James Blackthorn) pines for one last sight of home, an adventure that aligns him with a young robber and makes the duo a target for gangs and lawmen alike.

title: TV's Greatest Westerns
synopsis: Directed by Tom Edinger. It's the best from the Old West as we take a look at some of the most popular and best-known TV Westerns of their time.

title: Western Confidential
synopsis: Directed by David Lawrence. With Eric Amber, Renée Amber, Shauna Baker, Julian Black Antelope. Tells the story of two half-brothers on the run from a Buffalo baron with an embarrassing score to settle. Set in the 1880's among the vast plains, rolling foothills and winding rivers of Alberta.

title: El puesto
synopsis: Directed by Aurélien Levêque. Marin lives alone in a hut in the middle of the grand extents of Argentina. A few visits sometimes break his solitude. The meeting with a foal gives a human dimension to this wild tale. A western without shots nor fights.

title: Les colts de l'or noir
synopsis: Directed by Pierre Romanello. With Fredéric Ferrer, Romain Bertrand, Lionel Tavera, Marc Léonis.

title: Guns, Girls and Gambling
synopsis: Directed by Michael Winnick. With Christian Slater, Powers Boothe, Dane Cook, Jeff Fahey. 5 Elvis impersonators stay long after the contest playing poker, when a valuable mask is stolen from the Indian casino. Killers, incl. a sexy, blonde assassin, hunt down the Elvises to get the mask.

title: Casa de mi Padre
synopsis: Directed by Matt Piedmont. With Will Ferrell, Diego Luna, Pedro Armendáriz Jr., Genesis Rodriguez. Scheming to save their father's ranch, the Alvarez brothers find themselves in a war with Mexico's most feared drug lord.

title: Rasco
synopsis: Directed by Andrew Zuckerman. With Rudy Gapinski, Mark Kladar, Dillon Orth, Joe Wassweiler.

title: The Scarlet Worm
synopsis: Directed by Michael Fredianelli. With Aaron Stielstra, Dan van Husen, Brett Halsey, Derek Hertig. An aging killer trains a young hired gun in a plot to assassinate a meek brothel owner performing barbaric abortion acts on his prostitutes.

title: Yellow Rock
synopsis: Directed by Nick Vallelonga. With Michael Biehn, James Russo, Lenore Andriel, Michael Spears. Five men ride into the eerie town of Yellow Rock, hoping to rescue a family member and his lost boy.

title: A River of Skulls
synopsis: Directed by Suza Lambert Bowser. With Trent Anderson, Aleph Ayin, Bruce D. Cole, Donald Forrest. After her mother's death, Eula is forced to leave home and travel with a stranger into a world far more dangerous than she ever imagined.

title: Silent Anna
synopsis: Directed by Max Sokoloff. With Eoan Patrick Cray-Rudin, Christopher Greene, Valerie Heine, Byron Lambie. The West. An almost deserted fort by the ocean at the end of the Indian wars. (1890) One day a woman washes ashore, barely alive. She refuses to speak and reveals nothing about her past. Her presence triggers jealousies and obsessions among the soldiers. A young recruit, James, chosen to watch her battles between his duty and desire.

title: Roblox the Movie 2: The Attack of J.U.L.I.E.N
synopsis: The Attack of J.U.L.I.E.N

title: Hoodoo Voodoo
synopsis: Directed by Aaron Kurmey. With Barry Bunn, Scott Carpenter, Leona Flinders, Ryan Hatt. A lone ex-soldier is forced into a deadly struggle between corrupt cops, an evil crime syndicate, an elite mercenary unit, and endless miles of badlands.

title: The Way of the Spur
synopsis: Directed by Jakob Montrasio. With Dave Akolo, Christian 'Kang' Bachini, Jon T. Benn, Aimee Butler. Guerino, a cowboy from Italy, travels to Shanghai in search of his sister Elisa, who was working as a model in China but mysteriously vanished. In Shanghai, Guerino finds an unlikely ally in Jieikai, a local Chinese, whose girlfriend also mysteriously disappeared while working in the same modeling agency. During their search to uncover the truth, they are dragged into a dark world of criminality, corruption and human smuggling affairs. When things take a bad turn and innocent people start getting killed left and right, Guerino takes the matter into his own hands in order to save his sister before it's too late... Driven by his thirst for vengeance and his desire for justice, he vows to take down every single link to this chain of smuggling affair following his one and only rule

title: Western X
synopsis: Directed by Nathan Blackwell, Michael Flores, David Sabal. With Vernon Wells, R.K. Anderson, Kaily Alissano, Seth Gandrud. A man struggles to find out the truth behind his identity while fighting an evil army.

title: Forgiven
synopsis: Directed by Alan Autry. With Alan Autry, David Hart, Kimberlee Autry, Jim Tuck. Forgiven is an inspirational story in the tradition of High Plains Drifter and Pale Rider with a Faith-based message. It's 1878 and Jake Kincaid (Alan Autry from "In The Heat Of The Night") has just been released from prison for a crime he didn't commit. His heart is seeking vengeance on those responsible for landing him in jail, but he's also very interested in finding the gold he was accused of stealing. In his quest, he finds himself in the small town of Fairplay, California where Kincaid learns that love is far more powerful than hate and that redemption is more precious than gold. Forgiven is Alan Autry's directorial debut and a western the whole family can enjoy.

title: Sheriff of Contention
synopsis: Directed by Thomas W. O'Mary. With Angelo Ortega, Miguel Corona, Wendy Wiltsey, Thomas W. O'Mary. After numerous murders disrupt a small western town, a community is left on edge as the sheriff and deputy work together to catch the culprit.

title: Good for Nothing
synopsis: Directed by Mike Wallis. With Cohen Holloway, Inge Rademeyer, Jon Pheloung, Richard Thompson. A young English woman is immigrating to her uncle's ranch - but is kidnapped on the way by a rugged outlaw who discovers a problem he never knew he had - leading them on a wild ride across the West.

title: Single Action Colt
synopsis: Directed by Scott Harpt. With Barbra Alloy, Marc Brink, Olivia Brunette Weltz, Allison Brunette. When wimpy Sheriff Colt moves to Dirty Creek, bandits make their way to town to take advantage.

title: Los Siete
synopsis: Directed by Sergio Goyri. With Roberto Ballesteros, Humberto Elizondo, Perla Encinas, Isaura Espinoza. Seven bandits are threatening the inhabitants of a town, forcing them to sell their lands. When the identity of the leader of these thieves is discovered, there is no other choice than to kill the one who saw his face, provoking the rage of the powerful landowner Juan Arroyo, who has decided to fight the villains and protect the lands along with his brother and a beautiful cowgirl.

title: Patagonia Rising
synopsis: Directed by Brian Lilla. With Lalo Romero. A documentary that chronicles a plan to build five large hydroelectric dams on two of the world's purest free-flowing rivers in Patagonia, Chile.

title: Prospectors: All In
synopsis: All In

title: Bubblegum & Broken Fingers
synopsis: Directed by Sean Jackson. With Camme Tyla, Mandy Williams, Brenna Daly, Jason Nious. "If you don't have your own plan, you'll damn sure be a part of someone else's." That quote kicks off the first of multiple story lines, in the crime ensemble "Bubblegum & Broken Fingers." This character-driven collage of sex, violence and survival is equal parts western, gangster and love stories. We follow the journey of a mysterious silver briefcase and witness the havoc it brings each new owner. The seemingly unrelated stories continuously collide throughout for multiple plot twists. Rodney, a young mob bag-man tries to leave his life of crime but his partner Dominic has other plans. German tourists bite off more than they can chew. A tiny mute hitch hiker has a day she'll never forget. Blix, an escapee from a federal prison, goes on a destructive rampage. Playboy Doctor Sean Steele puts his life in jeopardy when he thinks with the wrong head. FBI agent Hampton and U.S. Marshal Yamato ruthlessly compete for the same arrest. These stories of dysfunction all smash together for a final resolution in the end. "Bubblegum & Broken Fingers" is a bizarre trip around the block that will leave you lifetimes away from where you started.

title: Dream Wagon
synopsis: Directed by Asad Farr. With Robert Miano, Silvia Spross, Gary Wasniewski, Justin Price. Two people see a green covered wagon that looks oddly out of place in Palmdale. They follow the wagon in their car and watch it disappear in front of their own eyes. They know after research that they have seen a spirit. A government Agent called Gabreil Samson hired by the US government in 1834 to eliminate the bootleggers who were illegally selling liquor to the Indians on the reservation.

title: Derailed and Departed
synopsis: Directed by Jeremy R. Stein. With Becky Ballagh, Kelly Ballagh, Nathan Beltran, Andrew Cross. Six Gun Sanders, a notorious gunslinger, has been found dead and it is up to you to figure out who killed the killer.

title: The Line Shack
synopsis: Directed by John Adrian Riley. With Jon Briddell, Steven K. Easterling, Jim Harworth, Joe Harworth. "Seems like we all got way too many yesterdays we can't take back." Set in the Old West of 1896, "The Line Shack" is the story of Nathaniel Sinclair Parker and of love. betrayal and revenge. When an act of friendship produces tragic consequences, Nat's life is changed forever. For nearly 25 years, he finds peace in the solitude of an old line shack up on the North Slope. A stranger's arrival at the ranch exposes the past, shattering Nat's tranquility forever. Written and directed by John Adrian Riley, "The Line Shack" features outstanding performances by L.A. actor Jon Briddell, "Criminal Minds," "CSI Miami," "Castle, "Midnight Movie," and Ohio Theatre Hall of Fame member Phill Wilson, "Teachers, "Mischief."

title: Silent Stranger
synopsis: Directed by Mike Murehead. With Dennis Allyn, Brian Black, Marci Brockman, Dan Caldwell. Texas in 1874 was a beautiful, wild and open country with no fences, boundaries or anything to limit a man's travels. This is about a man working his way through the Hill Country with nothing but his 50 caliber Sharps rifle, a riding mule and pack mule. Nothing to tie him down. You never know what may be waiting on the other side of the hill. There may be a friend or a potential enemy. In the 1870's you had to be prepared for anything. He knows how to deal with the wild animals and rough men but is he ready for Curly?

title: A Cold Day in Hell
synopsis: Directed by Christopher Forbes. With Karyn Belenke, Ronald Bumgardner, Kathryn Campbell, Kimberly Campbell. Sierra Nevada Mountains, 1887

title: Two Brothers: Prodigal Road
synopsis: Prodigal Road

title: Birth of a Legend: Billy the Kid & The Lincoln County War
synopsis: Billy the Kid & The Lincoln County War

title: Under the Western Sun
synopsis: Directed by Danny Cameron. With Mark Meir, Troy Streuer, Pam Eichner, Trenton Rostedt. John Miller wants a job at a prestigious newspaper. In order to get it, he must get the dirt on Mr. Billionaire, a now bankrupt tycoon. There's only one problem, Mr. Billionaire is John's father.

title: Django Unchained
synopsis: Directed by Quentin Tarantino. With Jamie Foxx, Christoph Waltz, Leonardo DiCaprio, Kerry Washington. With the help of a German bounty-hunter, a freed slave sets out to rescue his wife from a brutal plantation-owner in Mississippi.

title: Netherwood
synopsis: Directed by Cristobal Araus Lobos. With Owen Black, Will Hall, Mick Innes, Miriama Smith. Stan is a hard working Kiwi bloke who is always on the move. When he comes into the small town 'Netherwood' he finds himself wound up in a web of Murder, Love, Lies, and betrayal.

title: A Sierra Nevada Gunfight
synopsis: Directed by Vernon E. Mortensen. With Kirk Harris, Ryan Ballance, Michael Madsen, John Savage. Gold miner Roger Hazard brings his twelve year old son Casper to the treacherous gold fields of 1870s California. The two of them work a small mine in the southern fields but when Roger begins to lose touch with reality young Casper ends up on his own. Casper faces danger around every corner but must find the strength to save his father from himself and still manage to fight off the savage Indians and ruthless bushwhackers that plague them across California's breathtaking Sierra Nevadas. Genre

title: Devil's Crossing
synopsis: Directed by James Ryan Gary. With Michael Sharpe, Patrick G. Keenan, Kevin L. Johnson, Jenny Gulley. Nuclear war has ravaged the world. The remnants of humanity fight to survive, taking refuge in bleak settlements. The undead wander the earth, slaves to their blood-lust, or perhaps some higher power? The tattered town of Celestial sets the stage for the greatest battle of the New Dark Age! A score that must be settled and a reckoning that has been 235 years in the making. Shadrach a man who watched his life burnt to the ground! Left for dead, having sold his soul to the devil with his last dying breath. A slave to the devil. Born again as a "Soul Collector". Now centuries later Shadrach fights to be freed from the chains of the demons that torment him. To regain his soul and save the lives of an entire town he must fight the living dead as hell literally rises from beneath!

title: Cowboys & Indians
synopsis: Directed by Aaron Burk, Tyler Burk. With Alvin Cowan, Steve Guilmette, Katy Maloney, Dennis Ambriz. With the fate of the frontier hanging in the balance, a former cavalry officer is called back into action to rescue a beautiful maiden from the clutches a band of renegade Black Claw Indians led by a frightening medicine man.

title: Ambush at Dark Canyon
synopsis: Directed by Dustin Rikert. With Ernie Hudson, Sydney Penny, Andrew W. Walker, Abraham Benrubi. U.S. Marshall Duke Donovan is imprisoned, accused of being an accomplice in a bank robbery. After discovering that his partner is planning to kill his wife, he must escape prison in time to save his wife and clear his name.

title: Manoshangko: (Koshtipathor 2)
synopsis: (Koshtipathor 2)

title: Qurratu Aiyun: Je Jibon Juray Noyon
synopsis: Je Jibon Juray Noyon

title: Double Standard 2.0
synopsis: Directed by Sottayon Prokashon.

title: Ghosts of the West: The End of the Bonanza Trail
synopsis: Directed by Ethan S. Knightchilde. With Barron Christian, Arthur Martinez, Dane Bernhardt, Rowell Gormon. Lost mines, abandoned diggings, ghost towns. Generations later, their stories continue to fascinate and intrigue. And even haunt us.

title: Welcome to Shamatown
synopsis: Directed by Weiran Li. With Bei-Er Bao, Bingkun Cao, Yuen Che, Wei Gan. Shama Town has a legend of buried treasures around the town. When the town leader decides to promote Shama Town as a tourist destination, it unfortunately only attracts a gang of international thieves intent on finding the buried treasures

title: Sangre Negra: Aldo Knodell Debe Morir
synopsis: Aldo Knodell Debe Morir

title: Living by the Gun
synopsis: Directed by James Miller. With Tommy Admire, Jeffery Babineau, Amber Beasley, Charles Bird. A man returns from the bad blood and hard luck roads of redemption to his family homestead following his brother's death setting off his niece's quest for revenge.

title: The Man Who Shook the Hand of Vicente Fernandez
synopsis: Directed by Elia Petridis. With Ernest Borgnine, Barry Corbin, Carla Ortiz, Arturo Del Puerto. Ernest Borgnine plays Rex Page, an old man who is bitter about never becoming famous and having lived a life without any meaning. After suffering a stroke, he ends up in a nursing home staffed by Latin American immigrants. Put off by the situation, Rex focuses his energy on getting out, which places him at odds with the Latino workers. However, their relationship takes on new meaning when it is discovered that he once shook hands with Vicente Fernandez, a Mexican singer, producer and actor idolized throughout Latin culture. The employees soon begin to treat Rex like the celebrity he's always dreamed of being.

title: Hell at My Heels
synopsis: Directed by Brett Kelly. With Mac Dale, Phil Dukarsky, Christine Emes, Debra Ereaut. Two men are chained together and left to die in the unforgiving, scorching desert sun. With revenge on their minds, they are forced to overcome the elements so that they can kill the sadistic scoundrel that left them to die.

title: Black Hat
synopsis: Directed by Sean Tracy. With Shak Brenner, Edward Sheldon, Chaka Desilva, Jason Vail. A drifter is a town's last hope of salvation from outlaws, but he can't escape the past he's trying to forget.

title: She Had Some Horses
synopsis: Directed by Donna Wells. With Sandi Claypool, Jackie Fleming, Shelly Gibbs, Rachael Waller. A lyrical documentary about the heart-felt connection between women and horses.

title: Dawn Rider
synopsis: Directed by Terry Miles. With Christian Slater, Jill Hennessy, Donald Sutherland, Ben Cotton. After his father is killed, John Mason is willing to turn the world inside out to find the man responsible. What he doesn't know is the killer might be in his own house.

title: Mirage
synopsis: Directed by Szabolcs Hajdu. With Isaach De Bankolé, Razvan Vasilescu, Orsolya Török-Illyés, Dragos Bucur. An African football player committed a crime and has to escape. He finds refuge on a farm deep in the Hungarian flatland. Soon he realizes that the farm is a modern slave camp where he is forced to fight for his freedom and his life.

title: Rites of Passage
synopsis: Rites of Passage

title: A Fistful of Diamonds
synopsis: Directed by David Keeling. With John Boylan, John Carey, Áine Lane, Adam O'Keeffe. A modern-day Irish Western in which a wayward stranger, a wronged thief and a bereaved daughter collide in the search for an elusive stash of stolen diamonds.

title: Gang of Roses II: Next Generation
synopsis: Next Generation

title: Samurai
