synopsis: Directed by Gaspar Scheuer. With Alejandro Awada, Agustina Muñoz, Nicolas Nakayama, Norma Argentina. A Japanese family is exiled from their country, settling in Argentine lands, lands of gauchos, to cultivate the land and forge a new future. But the grandfather, faithful to his tradition, deliriously raves that Saigo is walking around recruiting a new army to fight the Empire.

title: Out West
synopsis: Directed by Lee Brownstein. With Jennifer Elise Cox, Sean Astin, Beth Grant, Ray Wise. Celebutante Prissy Alcott leaves her luxe Reno life behind for her childhood home in Colorado when she learns that her family has gone broke and is selling their ranch. She tries to reboot the family enterprise as a dude ranch with the help of her three gay friends.

title: Hay Road
synopsis: Directed by Rodrigo Areias. With Vítor Correia, Nuno Melo, Inês Mariana Moitas, Ângelo Torres. This is the story of a man who after living over ten years isolated away from his country, returns to avenge His brother's death. Inspired by the writings of Henry David Thoreau, he is translating 'Civil Disobedience' into Portuguese. The action is set between 1908 and 1910, between the assassination of the Portuguese King and Prince and the creation of the Portuguese Republic, an era where anarchists who fight against the monarchy often cross the path of burglars. On a country where corruption is set, the state representatives try to rob, arrest and kill innocents. The main character faces the tyranny of the state and tries to save the rest of his family. But this is a country where nothing changes.

title: Code of the West
synopsis: Directed by Rebecca Richman Cohen. At a time when the country is rethinking its drug policies large and small, one state raises to the forefront of national attention. Once a pioneer in legalizing medical marijuana, the state of Montana is poised to become the first in the nation to repeal its medical marijuana law. Set against the sweeping vistas of the Rockies, the steamy lamplight of marijuana grow houses, and the bustling halls of the State Capitol, CODE OF THE WEST follows the 2011 Montana State Legislature as it debates the fate of medical marijuana. This is the story of the many lives and fraught emotions tied to one of the most heated policy questions facing the country today.

title: Dead Man's Burden
synopsis: Directed by Jared Moshe. With Barlow Jacobs, Clare Bowen, David Call, Joseph Lyle Taylor. A western set on the New Mexico frontier a few years after the Civil War and centered on a struggling young family and the mining company who wants to buy their land.

title: Occupy Los Angeles
synopsis: Directed by Joseph G. Quinn. With George Carlin, Deepak Chopra, Albert Einstein, Mohandas K. Gandhi. From the Arab Spring to the American Autumn, director Joseph Quinn seeks to find out the origins of the Occupy Movement and shine a light on its long-term goals.

title: Drought
synopsis: Directed by Everardo González. Metaphor of a small town that hides from death.

title: Prospects
synopsis: Directed by Curtis Imrie, Rick Schmidt. With Sue Conroe, Curtis Imrie. The old west is certainly dead, but Colorado pack burro racers don't know it yet. Everett Winfield - played by five-time world champion burro racer Curtis Imrie - runs and breeds his own stock. But all is not well at the ranch. When a bank officer refuses him a home loan, Winfield unwisely flaunts the prospects of winning $5000 at an upcoming race as his 'employment record.' Of course it's no dice. As options narrow, his current girlfriend offers to share her homestead. But not one to relinquish his free-range freedoms, Winfield instead becomes involved with a young rodeo queen half his age, to the chagrin of his same-age niece. As morals slip, and the financial noose tightens, Winfield drifts toward setting things right, old-west style.

title: Hatchet County
synopsis: Directed by Adam Hulin. With R. Keith Harris, Matthew B. Moore, Paul Shaw, Jess Barbour. In 1869, a small group of men battle a demonic evil unleashed in Hatchet County, Virginia. Believing themselves victorious, the posse disbands; two members stay to watch over the area and all is quiet for the next four years. In 1873, Hell breaks loose in Hatchet County! This time all of its citizens, along with their two protectors, are forced to fight against 7 powerful demons, each representing the one of the 7 deadly sins.

title: Say It with Bullets
synopsis: Directed by D.W. Phillips. With Larry Clabby, Darrin Fleming, Ray Freedman, William Howerton. The "Legend of Blaze" comes alive in this new comical adventure from Sword and Sandal Film Productions. "Say It With Bullets" is the story of intrigue, danger and western-style payback in a time when the West was won with a gun. Travel to the Oregon frontier of the 1880's and experience the justice that can only be had when Blaze says it with bullets!

title: Wild Horse, Wild Ride
synopsis: Directed by Alex Dawson, Greg Gricus. With Carlos Chee. The Extreme Mustang Makeover Challenge is an annual contest that dares 100 people to each tame a totally wild mustang in order to get it adopted into a better life beyond federal corrals.

title: Any Last Words?
synopsis: Directed by Vaughn Taylor. With Tom Lagleder, Vaughn Taylor, Elizabeth Tinder, Madison Tinder. After a violent war, one man finds himself shot and waiting for death. As he lies there, he's left to make his toughest choice - whether to live or die. Inspired by the life of Bat Masterson.

title: Cooper
synopsis: Directed by Matthew Smaglik. With Benjamin Dawley-Anderson, Marc Glines, Steven Michael Hilton, John Hosking. A struggling ranch family in Montana learns that blood is not always thicker than water, when their son goes missing in the woods.

title: Outlaw
synopsis: Directed by Daniel Moersener. With Aleksandra Karadeniz, Andreas Moersener, Christian Moersener, Paul Moersener.

title: Hatfields and McCoys: Bad Blood
synopsis: Bad Blood

title: Jane Got a Gun
synopsis: Directed by Gavin O'Connor. With Natalie Portman, Joel Edgerton, Ewan McGregor, Noah Emmerich. A woman asks her ex-lover for help in order to save her outlaw husband from a gang out to kill him.

title: Bald Mountain
synopsis: Directed by Heitor Dhalia. With Wagner Moura, Sophie Charlotte, Jesuíta Barbosa, Matheus Nachtergaele. A journey to the biggest open mining of the contemporary age. It's 1978 and friends Juliano and Joaquim leave Rio de Janeiro in search of their dream of striking it rich. Like thousands of other men, both get to the Amazon Rainforest full of hope and illusion. But routine in the mines changes everything and the obsession of wealth and power destroys them. Juliano becomes a gangster. Joaquim leaves all his values behind. This is a story about golden fever, greed and violence, a great friendship and its end.

title: The Carolinian
synopsis: Directed by Patrick Shanahan. With Patrick Shanahan, Rob Rice, Charles B. Allen, Frank Daniels IV. One hundred and fifty years ago, this nation was divided by war. Thousands of men lost their lives, though one Man, Levi Cane, was given a second chance. In a search across North Carolina for his long lost love, Cane finds out he's in for more than he bargained for. Hunted by five shooters and on an all out run to to the coast, young Levi Cane must find the will, physically and spiritually to make it out alive.

title: Trash and Progress
synopsis: Directed by Abraham Dieckman. With Maryssa Wanlass, Remi Barron, James Camblin, Lindsay Cookson. A rookie journalist has returned to the abandoned frontier of Earth with the dream of writing a career-making story about the descendants of those who were left behind. There she finds a decaying society ruled through fear by a mysterious, ageless despot.

title: Highclimber
synopsis: Directed by Rocky Hessler. With Alex Walters, David K. Brown, Joseph Buttler, Kimberly Adair. A desperate farmer leaves wife and children, following his volatile brother West to stake their claim in the savage 1890's timber boom.

title: Tales from Dell City, Texas
synopsis: Directed by Josh Carter. Meet the people of Dell City, and watch their movies.

title: The Redemption of Henry Myers
synopsis: Directed by Clayton Miller. With Drew Waters, Erin Bethea, Jaden Roberts, Ezra Proch. Henry Myers lives a hard life. After his latest heist goes wrong and his partners betray him and leave him for dead, Henry is surprised to find extraordinary kindness from a widow and her children. Soon he begins to question the choices he's made in his life. Just as things begin to make sense again, they take an interesting turn.

title: The Murder of Hi Good
synopsis: Directed by Lee Lynch. With David Nordstrom, Cory Zacharia, Al Bringas, Eric H. Heisner. Part documentary, part magical realist reenactment, The Murder of Hi Good details the assassination of Northern California's most infamous Indian hunter, "Hiram Good".

title: Cole Younger & The Black Train
synopsis: Directed by Christopher Forbes. With Cody McCarver, Jerry Chesser, Janice Baxter, Mike Baxter. The outlaw Cole Younger partners with Jesse James to create the most notorious outlaw band of the old West, the James-Younger gang.

title: Sweetwater
synopsis: Directed by Logan Miller, Noah Miller. With Ed Harris, January Jones, Jason Isaacs, Eduardo Noriega. In the late 1800s, a fanatical religious leader, a renegade Sheriff, and a former prostitute collide in a blood triangle on the rugged plains of the New Mexico Territory.

title: Dead Men
synopsis: Directed by Royston Innes. With Ric Maddox, Aaron Marciniak, Richard O. Ryan, Shawn Parsons. Set in the lawless Old West, a young man and his brother are forced on a journey to avenge the death of their father, protect the Apache tribe they have grown to love and reclaim the land and gold that is rightfully theirs.

title: Common Outlaws
synopsis: Directed by Louie Iaccarino. With Louie Iaccarino, John Druska, Gregory P. Loomis, Mark Clem. Set in the "timeless" River City, Indiana, The Hurley Boy's set out to absolve the sins of their wrongfully accused father. But what is the cost of revenge? A tragic tale of family, revenge, and the consequences of hate.

title: Forsaken
synopsis: Directed by Jon Cassar. With Esther Purves-Smith, Kiefer Sutherland, Donald Sutherland, Lex Cassar. In 1872, an embittered gunslinger named John Henry Clayton attempts to make amends with his estranged father Reverend Samuel Clayton while their community is besieged by ruthless land-grabbers.

title: Aatsinki: The Story of Arctic Cowboys
synopsis: The Story of Arctic Cowboys

title: Und sie kehrten niemals wieder
synopsis: Directed by Günther Brandl, Helmut Brandl, Monika Brandl. With Günther Brandl, Carolina Rath, Vlasto Peyitch, Timo Tirado. A man waking up in barren hills, surrounded by corpses, has forgotten who he is. A crippled woman seeks justice for the assassination of her husband. Two different posses hunt a man named McCanahaugh. A female bounty-hunter wants to reclaim her toddler from his foster-parents, the male of which molests his grown daughter. The Amnesiac takes her with him, but she knocks him down. Then the bounty hunter finds him and all the lines rope together.

title: Las puertas del cielo
synopsis: Directed by Jaime L. Lozano, Jorge Piwowarski. With Rosa Avila, Gabriel Boscarino, Enrique Bustos, Miguel Angel Coronel. Camilo goes to the sugar cane harvest but he comes across a bandit badly wounded from his last assault and whose last wish is

title: Gunfight at Yuma
synopsis: Directed by Alveraz Ricardez. With Christopher Mur, Joe Estevez, Kelli Ruttle, Kassianni Austin. Seven Years after his wife's murder and the events that changed his life, Caleb Williams has become a gunfighter known as The Tailor.

title: A Night in Old Mexico
synopsis: Directed by Emilio Aragón. With Robert Duvall, Jeremy Irvine, Angie Cepeda, Luis Tosar. After being forced to sell his family ranch to developers, a financially strapped, but proud senior citizen, and his estranged grandson, find themselves targeted by drug dealers in search of a missing money bag.

title: Falcon Song
synopsis: Directed by Jason Corgan Brown. With Rainey Qualley, Gabriel Sunday, Martin Kove, Jim Storm. A guitar-playing drifter helps a rancher's granddaughter find her true calling. They soon find themselves in the middle of a land war driven by quirky characters and magical realism.

title: The Never Daunted
synopsis: Directed by Edgar Muñiz. With Nicholas Null, Joe Freeman, Kokou Aurelien Gaya, Celeste Marie Martinez. Unable to cope with his infertility and the monotony of a dead-end job, Murray becomes withdrawn from his relationship and grows obsessed with a strange Western that comes on television late at night, which only he can see.

title: Del Rio
synopsis: Directed by Brett Celestre, Matthew Celestre. With Corey Duffel, Jesse Gale, Joel Jutagir, Steven Ruge. As an extravagant locomotive, the Loxodonta Express, navigates through Del Rio carrying a prosperous assortment of passengers and wealth; their destination will collide with the horrific dangers that unknowingly lay ahead.

title: The Debacle
synopsis: Directed by Ryan N. Wood. With Christopher Koenig, Ryan N. Wood, Victoria Vega, Matt Newton. Long time friends Vaughn (a devout hypochondriac) and Larry (a hapless and perpetually single romantic) have never met a challenge they haven't run from. When a chance encounter with a stranger leads to their finding themselves transported to an old west town in the 1870s, they're forced into situations where failure appears to be a foregone conclusion. Terrified by change and even the hint of danger, Vaughn and Larry are a given a task that must be completed within two weeks or risk never returning to their modern day reality. Given their built-in limitations, a hilarious series of events ensue as they work to overcome their fears, competing interests and they must do battle with an ill-tempered gunslinger in an effort to return home.

title: Gold
synopsis: Directed by Thomas Arslan. With Nina Hoss, Marko Mandic, Peter Kurth, Uwe Bohm. In the summer of 1898, a small group of German compatriots head into the hostile northern interior of British Columbia in search for gold at the height of the Klondike Gold Rush.

title: Clay Walker: Jesse James
synopsis: Jesse James

title: Revelation Trail
synopsis: Directed by John P. Gibson. With Daniel Van Thomas, Daniel Britt, Jordan Elizabeth, Robert Valentine. In the late nineteenth-century, a holy man known only as the Preacher confronts unspeakable evil as a gruesome power consumes the frontier.

title: West of Thunder
synopsis: Directed by Jody Marriott Bar-Lev, Steve Russell. With Dan Davies, Clifford Henry, Corbin Conroy, Steve Garcia. South Dakota 1899. A mysterious stranger visits a small town on the outskirts of the Lakota Pine Ridge Reservation and brings with him a terrible resolve.

title: South of Black Drink Crier
synopsis: Directed by Kenny Wheeler. As a prelude to the civil war, General lee and his Kansas Brigade devastate the western counties of southern Missouri. Weary of the inhumanity, Evelyn, disguised as a member of Lane's Brigade, takes it upon herself to leave the regiment and find her missing father. With the help of her friend Tenny and a local Chaplin, the three set off across the southwest Missouri countryside to find the lost scout.

title: They Die by Dawn
synopsis: Directed by Jeymes Samuel. With Rosario Dawson, Giancarlo Esposito, Kelly Hu, Jesse Williams. Four outlaws with a bounty on each head, set a date for a shootout in Langston, Oklahoma. The last man takes the collective bounty. Violence and mayhem ensue.

title: The Name on the Bullet
synopsis: Directed by James Overton. With Denver Dewitt, Jerry Hatton, David Hickman, Lonnie Jarvis. New from Alpha Vision Films! This revisionist Western takes a second look at a fabled myth of the American frontier. Spanning the post-Civil War era to the turn of the century, "The Name on the Bullet" will call to question the generally accepted version of the fate of one of the most widely studied personalities in American criminal history. The production was filmed on location at the Frontier Culture Museum of Virginia in Staunton, Va.

title: Bloody Border
synopsis: Directed by Bryan C. Goff. With Nathan Staveley, Bear Vash, Diana Gomez, Edward Behle. What do you get when you mix two hit-men brothers, their cocky protege, a couple of injured illegal immigrants, border patrol agents and a few colorful townsfolk in the small border town of Bisbee, AZ whose water supply has been contaminated with MDPV otherwise known as 'bath salts'? A wild night of chases, gun fights, zombies, heated arguments touching on the controversial issue, AZ's SB1070, oh and a lot more zombies as this colorful group of individuals tries to escape the night on the Bloody Border.

title: Five Fingers for Marseilles
synopsis: Directed by Michael Matthews. With Vuyo Dabula, Zethu Dlomo-Mphahlele, Hamilton Dlamini, Kenneth Nkosi. Lives change forever when Tau, the young lion, kills two corrupt policemen in a South African shanty town.

title: The Homesman
synopsis: Directed by Tommy Lee Jones. With Tommy Lee Jones, Hilary Swank, Grace Gummer, Miranda Otto. Three women who have been driven mad by pioneer life are to be transported across the country by covered wagon by the pious, independent-minded Mary Bee Cuddy, who in turn employs low-life drifter George Briggs to assist her.

title: The Magnificent Seven
synopsis: Directed by Antoine Fuqua. With Denzel Washington, Chris Pratt, Ethan Hawke, Vincent D'Onofrio. Seven gunmen from a variety of backgrounds are brought together by a vengeful young widow to protect her town from the private army of a destructive industrialist.

title: Lone Wolf
synopsis: Directed by Sebastien de Buyl, Axel de Ville de Goyet. With Andrew Bolton, Aurélia Bonta, Vincent Doms, Jean-Louis Fils. A lone wolf is someone who commits or prepares for, or is suspected of committing or preparing for violent acts in support of some group, movement, or ideology, but does so alone, outside of any command structure.

title: Cowboy Spirit
synopsis: Directed by William F. Miller. With Rich Manley, Ayla Brown, Jenna Laurenzo, Mike Allison. Ted has it all, a great job, a beautiful fiance, and a wonderful life ahead of him, but a twist of fate leads him to rely on the lessons he learned in the summers of his youth with his grandfather - a former champion rodeo cowboy. To save a dying young girl, he must make the ride of a lifetime.

title: Possessions
synopsis: Directed by David Colon. With Phil Armenia, Richard Baker, Clay Brocker, Matthew Buri. A band of ex-confederates looking for the lost gold that had been stolen from the Virginia Bank, believes they have the man who knows where the bounty is hidden. War hero, Braden Hill's daughter has been kidnapped to force his cooperation ... but a tragic turn of events spins everything out of control... This father / daughter story set in a post-Civil War backdrop, will keep your heart engaged as you discover when are your Possessions truly worth dying for.

title: Scheme with Me
synopsis: Directed by Anzi Pan. With Richie Jen, Tenggeer, Hao Chen, Qiuchi Han.

title: The Duel
synopsis: Directed by Kieran Darcy-Smith. With Woody Harrelson, Liam Hemsworth, Alice Braga, Emory Cohen. A Texas Ranger investigates a series of unexplained deaths in a town called Helena.

title: Recommended by Enrique
synopsis: Directed by Rania Attieh, Daniel Garcia. With Sarah Swinwood, Lino Varela. An aspiring actress and an aging cowboy arrive in the small border town of Del Rio, Texas each with a different pursuit. But when things don't go exactly as planned for either of them--the actress slowly begins to realize that the film she came to town for is not at all what she expected (the 'director' is nowhere to be found, the set is run by a group of teenagers), and the associate that the cowboy was supposed to meet had to leave town unexpectedly--the two are forced to wait out their time, exploring the town, and its people. A Latino tale of mysticism, tradition, and the dream of celebrity.

title: The Keeping Room
synopsis: Directed by Daniel Barber. With Brit Marling, Hailee Steinfeld, Muna Otaru, Sam Worthington. Left without men in the dying days of the American Civil War, three women must fight to defend their home and themselves from two rogue soldiers who have broken off from the fast-approaching Union Army.

title: Bone Tomahawk
synopsis: Directed by S. Craig Zahler. With Kurt Russell, Patrick Wilson, Matthew Fox, Richard Jenkins. In the dying days of the old west, an elderly sheriff and his posse set out to rescue their town's doctor from cannibalistic cave dwellers.

title: The Reaping Men
synopsis: Directed by Jim Powers, Steve Powers. With John Stegemann, Justin Craig, Jim Powers, Nate Howard. Grizzled Civil War veteran Thos Murphy returns to his childhood home to piece together his brother's murder. Only to learn the dark secret of the men behind it, and the harsh bitterness of revenge.

title: Frontera
synopsis: Directed by Michael Berry. With Ed Harris, Michael Peña, Eva Longoria, Amy Madigan. A former Arizona sheriff's wife is killed while riding on their ranch property. It would appear a Mexican man illegally crossing into the US is at fault. As the former and the current sheriff search for answers, lives are changed forever.

title: A Million Ways to Die in the West
synopsis: Directed by Seth MacFarlane. With Seth MacFarlane, Charlize Theron, Amanda Seyfried, Liam Neeson. As a cowardly farmer begins to fall for the mysterious new woman in town, he must put his newly found courage to the test when her husband, a notorious gun-slinger, announces his arrival.

title: Spindrift: Ghost of the West
synopsis: Ghost of the West

title: Man Negahdar Jamali Western Misazam
synopsis: Directed by Kamran Heidari. With Negahdar Jamali. "My name is John Ford and I make Westerns" this is how John Ford introduced himself at the American Film Directors' Association gathering. Negahdar Jamali, an Iranian from Shiraz introduced himself the same way when I first met him without knowing John Ford that well. He introduced himself with self-confidence and without any weakness in his statement; not in the Monument Valley or in the Grand Canyon but in Shiraz and the deserts surrounding the city. He has been making Western films continuously for the past 35 years under hard conditions, and this film is about the struggle with his family, friends, society,... to make what he likes the most in his life "Western Movies".

title: The Retrieval
synopsis: Directed by Chris Eska. With Ashton Sanders, Tishuan Scott, Keston John, Bill Oberst Jr.. On the outskirts of the U.S. Civil War, a boy is sent north by his bounty hunter gang to retrieve a wanted man.

title: Dawn of Conviction
synopsis: Directed by Robert Cammisa, Dennis Donovan, Patrick Hendrickson, Matthew Petterson. With Vanessa Bartlett, Patrick Ginnetty, Walker Hare, Cody Jones. Dawn of Conviction is a Western feature film following the exploits of The London Gang. From their start as a close family of loggers to their career as gun slinging bandits fighting the law and each other, the three young men try to make their way through 1880 Dakota Territory. The film poses questions about relationships

title: The Dark Valley
synopsis: Directed by Andreas Prochaska. With Sam Riley, Tobias Moretti, Paula Beer, Thomas Schubert. Through a hidden path, a lone rider reaches a little town high up in the Alps. Nobody knows where the stranger comes from, nor what he wants there. But everyone knows that they don't want him to stay.

title: American Mustang
synopsis: Directed by Monty Miranda. With Alison Eastwood, Daryl Hannah, Jim Neubert, Luke Neubert. A young girl discovers that America's wild horses are in danger of being wiped off the land they've called home for thousands of years, as American Mustang the Movie unveils the compelling story of the wild mustang.

title: Muerte Salvaje
synopsis: Directed by Joe Morford. With Scotty B, Gen Celle, Caesar Garcia, Jay Gold. A solitary rancher rides out of the desert plains to reap revenge on the murderous bandits that massacred his village a decade earlier. His enemies prove more vicious than expected and his friends more loyal than he believed.

title: The Trail
synopsis: Directed by William Parker. With Jet Jandreau, Shannon Brown, Tommy Nash, Brianna Oppenheimer. A young housewife is stranded alone in the woods after a tragic accident along The Oregon Trail. Far from home, she is tested mentally, physically, and spiritually in a battle for her life.

title: The Tarryall
synopsis: Directed by Matthew Ryan Anderson. With Matthew Ryan Anderson, Wayne Bjorkman, Ron Burkhardt, Omar Garcia. Deep in the Rockies of Colorado, it's the late 1800's as a group of four friends make their way to The Tarryall.

title: Kinderwald
synopsis: Directed by Lise Raven. With Frank Brückner, Emily Behr, Max Cove, Corinna Burns. Pennsylvania, 1854. German Immigrant John Linden struggles to set up a homestead in the mountains with his brother's widow Flora and her two young sons. When the small boys suddenly vanish without a trace, the neighboring community first helps, then turns their back on the family, leading to a violent and tragic aftermath.

title: Hot Bath an' a Stiff Drink
synopsis: Directed by Matthew Gratzner. With Jeffery Patterson, Timothy V. Murphy, Mirelly Taylor, Ronnie Gene Blevins. Marshal Vance Dillinger makes a shocking discovery -- his twin, presumed dead 30 years ago, is the notorious outlaw 'The Lucky Bandit.'

title: In a Goodly Way
synopsis: Directed by Matt Hewitt. With Nate Bernot, Tyler Bjarke, Stephen Heath, Matt Hewitt. A 'Murder Ballad' inspired tale of Simon Carmichael's criminal activities and flight from the law. A pair of ruthless lawmen follow in pursuit as the desperate creature flees across the countryside, encountering a variety of filthy miscreants and sordid cretins.

title: Darkness on the Edge of Town
synopsis: Directed by Patrick Ryan. With Brian Gleeson, Olwen Catherine Kelly, Emma Eliza Regan, Maura Foley. A troubled teenage sharpshooter decides to avenge the death of her estranged sister after she is found murdered in a public bathroom.

title: The Secret of Wilson Hill
synopsis: Directed by Roger Slagle. With Dennis Ambriz, Lynda Baker, Loren Clark, David Everson. When Jim finds an old journal in a barn he reads of a time when the civil war led the hearts and minds of his countrymen, a time when slaves were property, Native Americans had healing powers, and when gold was discovered and hidden. Will Jim learn the Secret of Wilson Hill?

title: Revenge
synopsis: Directed by Gabriel Schmidt. With Jacqueline Cereceres, Sal Landi, Walker Haynes, P. David Miller. A life lived in fear is no life at all. When her husband falls foul to the lawlessness of the Wild West, a Sheriff's wife learns that sometimes the only true justice can come from barrel of a gun.

title: The Preacher and the Gun
synopsis: Directed by Scott Hester. With Dennis Cole, Wendy Cole, Rich Henrich, Mark Edwards. As they find out the Railroad will be bypassing their town, Stephen and his wife find themselves along with everyone else in town struggling with the forces of greed and their own faith to overcome fear even to the point of death.

title: Injun
synopsis: Directed by Bob Cook. With Patrick Louis Ah-Wong, Kevin Brassard, Debra Cassano, Bob Cook. When six raiders kill her husband, child and workers on her ranch, a white woman raised by the Commanche' claims an Indian blood rite.

title: Sin sangre nunca
synopsis: Directed by Yerko Espinoza. With Laura Buitrago, Yerko Espinoza, Piero Olmedo, Dayana Tenloy. Two foreigners, Yerks and Cony, travel to Spain to fulfill their dream. But soon they will realize that this country is not what they expected... It will rather become their worst nightmare when she enters into a world from which she won't be able to escape by herself.

title: Day of the Gun
synopsis: Directed by Wayne Shipley. With Eric Roberts, Raw Leiba, LaDon Hart Hall, Jim Osborn. An ambitious widow vows "There will be hell to pay" when a prominent Montana rancher puts up a barbed wire fence between their properties.

title: Hardin
synopsis: Directed by Bob Misiorowski. With Martin Kove, Marshall R. Teague, Frank Stallone, John Luder. The true story of John Wesley Hardin

title: The Dressmaker
synopsis: Directed by Jocelyn Moorhouse. With Kate Winslet, Judy Davis, Liam Hemsworth, Hugo Weaving. A glamorous woman returns to her small town in rural Australia. With her sewing machine and haute couture style, she transforms the women and exacts sweet revenge on those who did her wrong.

title: Bald Knobber
synopsis: Directed by Michael Johnson. With Mel Barber, Angelina Sauber, Dale Green, Laura Fogle. This true story is about the 1880s vigilante group that terrorized Taney County Missouri.

title: Billy the Kid
synopsis: Directed by Christopher Forbes. With Dan Beck, Christopher Bowman, Graye Bumgardner, Patty Bumgardner. A bounty hunter from New Mexico and a gang of horsemen called "Four of the Apocalypse" set their sights on the town of Dogma.

title: Storm Rider
synopsis: Directed by Craig Clyde. With Kevin Sorbo, Kristy Swanson, Danielle C. Ryan, Jacob Buster. When her father is put into jail, the spoiled teenager Dani loses everything. Forced to live with her uncle Sam on a farm without horses to ride and to train a sad Dani takes care of a young mule and learns what really counts.

title: 6 Bullets to Hell
synopsis: Directed by Tanner Beard, Russell Quinn. With Tanner Beard, Crispian Belfrage, Russell Quinn, Ken Luckey. When a farmer's wife is brutally murdered by the ruthless bandit Bobby Durango and his gang of killers, Billy Rogers goes back to his old gun and starts to hunt them one by one.

title: Echoes of War
synopsis: Directed by Kane Senes. With James Badge Dale, Ethan Embry, William Forsythe, Maika Monroe. A Civil War veteran returns home to the quiet countryside, only to find himself embroiled in a conflict between his family and the brutish cattle rancher harassing them.

title: Bull BulBul Bandook
synopsis: Directed by Karan Butani. With Dheerendra Dwivedi, Kay Kay Menon, Shriya Saran, Jimmy Shergill.

title: Wrenched
synopsis: Directed by Ml Lincoln. With Edward Abbey, Dave Foreman, Peg Millett, Robert Redford. Wrenched reveals how Edward Abbey's anarchistic spirit and riotous novels influenced and helped guide the nascent environmental movement of the seventies and eighties. Through interviews, archival footage and reenactments, this documentary captures the outrage of Abbey's friends who were the original ecowarriors. In defense of wilderness, these early activists pioneered monkeywrenching, a radical blueprint for wrenching the system.

title: Amukan
synopsis: Directed by Francisco Toro. With Luis Corvalán, Pedro Manquepi. Nekul is a teenage Mapuche who lives in the high peaks of Los Andes Mountains. His mother is sick and gets worse every day. The mother's illness open up new opportunities to Nekul, a journey, a path to travel to find his own place in life.

title: All in the Valley
synopsis: Directed by Luke J. Hagan. With Steve Hope Wynne, Daniel Jordan, Richard Pawulski, Rory Wilton. In 1855 a wounded solider returns from the Crimean War and is given the chance of new life in Van Diemen's Land but in exchange he must track down a murderous gang of thieves across the desolate Cornish moors.

title: Bullies: The Benediction
synopsis: The Benediction

title: Popovich and the Voice of the Fabled American West
synopsis: Directed by Jerry Thompson, Mike Thompson. With Gregory Popovich, Jason Neistadt, Antonio Fargas, Melody Melendez. Popovich is an ex circus legend struggling as a street performer in the wild west streets of Las Vegas. When his junkyard home full of stray animals gets into trouble, he and his animal buddies use all their circus tricks to save it.

title: The Bounty Killer
synopsis: Directed by Chip Baker. With Crispian Belfrage, Ethan McDowell, David Gilliam, Antonio Mayans. A bounty killer is hired by a Mexican landowner to rescue his daughter after she's kidnapped by a gang of outlaws on her wedding day.

title: Big Muddy
synopsis: Directed by Jefferson Moneo. With Nadia Litz, Justin Kelly, David La Haye, Stephen McHattie. Martha Barlow, a modern-day outlaw, must reconcile her dark past after her teenage son commits a horrible crime.

title: Ravenwood
synopsis: Directed by Luke Henderson, Emmanuel Icaza. With Rex Adams, Kate Alloway, Jimmy Alvarez, Cole Baca. Vampire Cowboys v/s Zombie Indians

title: Polvareda
synopsis: Directed by Juan Schmidt. With Horacio Camandulle Luna, Eduardo Cutuli, Leandro Cóccaro, José Manuel Espeche. A gang of professional thieves pulls off their great hit

title: Becoming Bulletproof
synopsis: Directed by Michael Barnett. With Vanessa Halby, Peter Halby, Ila Halby, Ajani A.J. Murray. A group of men and women with disabilities come together to star in a unique new western film in which they have the leading roles.

title: Wasteland
synopsis: Directed by Hermes Cavagnini. With Patrick Sane, Reynolds Washam, Petra Wright, Tim Taylor. Four outlaws and a female bounty hunter follow a path of violence and murder along the Texas/Mexico border, only to discover overlapping pasts

title: La gente del sol
synopsis: Directed by Gonzalo de Miceu, Nicolás Lira. With Santiago Asorey, Nicolás de Terán, Miguel Krstulovi, Valeria Leyton. Two friends travel through the desert to attend a soccer game between Argentina and Chile. Lost along the route they challenge themselves to a penalties duel. The ball bounces away. Without second thoughts, they leave everything behind to penetrate Atacama Desert wilderness in search of the ball. In another part of the desert, an adventurer wanders seeking the hidden treasure of the aborigine Mazuree. Both journeys will unite in a fantastic odyssey filled with representative characters of the Andean mythology.

title: El Camino Christmas
synopsis: Directed by David E. Talbert. With Dax Shepard, Kurtwood Smith, Luke Grimes, Emilio Rivera. Eric comes to El Camino looking for his unknown dad. He's harassed, hit and jailed by a drunk local cop, who later shoots at a liquor mart with Eric +4 inside. The sheriff and deputy then shoot up the place, answering each other's fire.

title: El Hijo de Dios
synopsis: Directed by Mariano Fernández, Gaston Girod. With Paulo Soria, Juan Lo Sasso, Ignacio Ballone, Agustín Repetto. THE SON OF GOD is a film about football. Frame as a parody of the western genre code, it plays with the idea of placing the book 'Football - Dynamics of the unthinkable' by D.Panzeri, in the religious context of the New Testament. Good and evil represented through well or badly played football. Football "de Potrero" vs. Catenaccio. Spontaneity vs. tactics. Playfulness spirit vs. Industrial spirit. The dynamics of the unthinkable as Bible.

title: Roaming Wild
synopsis: Directed by Sylvia Johnson. With Samantha Layne. Roaming Wild is a modern day Western about the federal government's controversial wild horse round ups, and a cowboy, an activist, and a mountain man searching for solutions to protect life and land.

title: Mosquito: A Fistful of Bitcoins
synopsis: A Fistful of Bitcoins

title: The Brick House
synopsis: Directed by Gustavo Cervantes. With Carolina Adame, Sergio Adame, Josh Buzzard, Thom Clark. The Brick House is a modern retelling of the classic 'three little pigs' tale in a fantasy-western drama, where three estranged brother pigs are reunited by the inheritance of their Uncle's countryside homestead after his death.

title: Wichita
synopsis: Directed by Nicholas Barton. With Justin France, Karina Wolfe, Blake Webb, Reylynn Caster. A drifter, a fugitive, and a bounty hunter all land in the sleepy cow town of Wichita, Ks during the 1882 cattle runs and find out there's far more than meets the eye in this Western/Noir.

title: Doc Holliday's Revenge
synopsis: Directed by David DeCoteau. With William McNamara, Eric Roberts, Tom Berenger, Ashley Hayes. While taking a stand against one of the West's greatest legends, Elizabeth Cooley will discover that justice comes in many forms.

title: I, Scorpio
synopsis: Directed by Patrick McGuinn. With Coleman Kent, Christian Isaac Cruz. An experimental narrative exploring the relationship that develops between a Mexican hitchhiker and a drug dealer that he meets on a desert road in 1974.

title: The Lonesome
synopsis: Directed by Daniel Araujo. With Eugene Brichacek, Tim Morrill, Daniel Araujo, Jennifer Morrill. In the post-Apocalyptic United States, a man must battle the undead while searching for an antidote after being infected by one.

title: Once Upon a Time in Shangri-La
synopsis: Directed by Phil Gorn. With Jeremy London, Jason London, Susan Duerden, Masiela Lusha. In this post-apocalyptic mystery set in California, Alexander lives in exile for the killing of his brother. Then Alexander discovers his brother is very much alive. Overjoyed but knowing he killed him, Alexander must root out the truth.

title: Lonesome Dove Church
synopsis: Directed by Terry Miles. With Tom Berenger, Greyston Holt, Alex Zahara, Andrea Whitburn. The true story of the formation of the Lonesome Dove Church in Texas.

title: Blood and Spurs
synopsis: Directed by Mark Tarrant. With Clint Hummel, Jackamoe Buzzell, James Blackburn, Albert Fry Jr.. An Underground contest of fighting skill in the Wild West. Two men enter the arena, only one man advances,winner of the tournament claims the bounty of 20 thousand dollars and a pardon for him and his gang.

title: In Searching
synopsis: Directed by J.L. Topkis. With Jake Borelli, Jacob Grodnik, Aley Underwood, Evan Hall. When Jon returns on his first trip home from college, he inadvertently triggers events that inspire him to embark on an auspicious journey through the night to return a lost locket.

title: Blood Moon
synopsis: Directed by Jeremy Wooding. With George Blagden, Tom Cotcher, Barrington De La Roche, Raffaello Degruttola. A stagecoach of travelers, a gunslinger and two outlaws arrive in a deserted mining town lit by the glow of a reddish full moon. As their worlds collide, they are hunted by a beast that only appears on the night of a blood moon.

title: Suit of Lights
synopsis: Directed by Jeff Rowles. With Richard Bishop, Dan Considine, Susana Espino-Rodriquez, Dennis Fitzpatrick. A famous matador is ushered through a transitional state where he's given the opportunity to end his suffering by destroying his own ego, and along with it the identity that gives meaning to his life.

title: The Lonesome Trail
synopsis: Directed by Arlette Thomas-Fletcher. With Johnny Alonso, Megan Caulfield, Vivian Yoon Lee, Lamont Easter. A preacher comes to a small western town in the 1890s, settles in the outer lands near one of the biggest land owners in town and changes the whole landscape of the town.

title: Fishtail
synopsis: Directed by Andrew Renzi. With Tylee Abbott, Harry Dean Stanton. The Fishtail Basin Ranch in Montana is a free-range cattle ranch, and a large supplier of beef to such gourmet groceries stores as Whole Foods. This documentary chronicles the lives of the cattle and of the ranchers during calving season, the time each year when the cows give birth.

title: Too Close to the Raven
synopsis: Directed by Malcolm King-Fontana. With Jeffrey Alan Solomon, Kiah Toth. Too Close to the Raven is a Western Neo-Noir tale of the timeless conflict triangle between a charismatic crime boss, an idealistic young gun, and a damsel in distress.

title: In a Valley of Violence
synopsis: Directed by Ti West. With Ethan Hawke, John Travolta, Taissa Farmiga, James Ransone. A mysterious stranger and a random act of violence drag a town of misfits and nitwits into the bloody crosshairs of revenge.

title: Love Like Gold
synopsis: Directed by Kier Atherton. With Alexandra Henrikson, Christopher Innvar, Brick Patrick, Jeff Medley. Love Like Gold is a story of Gage and Lola. Gage, a wayward ranch hand in search of something different in his life, and Lola, a singer who wants to get away from the bad choices and hardships that have fallen on her. When these two meet they can't tell if they should trust each other to fall in love and start clean, or if there is no hope left for love and try to run away like they always have.

title: Gaucho del Norte
synopsis: Directed by Andres Caballero, Sofian Khan. Gaucho del Norte' tells the story of a Patagonian sheepherder recruited to work in Idaho. The nomadic two-year journey follows Eraldo Pacheco and his herd of more than a thousand sheep across a lonely, rugged landscape --- from the harsh beauty of wintry high desert, to the lush summer mountains. Living in isolation, Eraldo faces the ups and downs of a psychologically demanding job far away from his home and family, often questioning whether or not it's all worth it.

title: Oro del Diablo
synopsis: Directed by Robert Towne. With Baron Von Goghku, Stephanie Frias, Ray Niemira, Tito Arenal. His better days long gone, a former confederate soldier must choose between two gangs searching for the Lost Padre Mine in a quest of riches, revenge, and redemption.

title: Ditches
synopsis: Directed by Francisco Joaquín Paparella. With Diego Alonso Gómez, Augusto Brítez, Cuca Lubones, Eduardo Paulaza. A portrait of Zamora, a rural worker exiled in Patagonia in a town that suffers feminicides of teenagers thrown into ditches once dead. Through hard work, Zamora intends to expiate his guilt.

title: Fangs Vs. Spurs
synopsis: Directed by Patrick Love. With Joe Estevez, Colleen Elizabeth Miller, Walt Sloan, Helen Darras. When revengeful vampires attack, a group of self-centered cowboys must band together to save their town from utter destruction.

title: Kandiyohi
synopsis: Directed by Nicholas Engan. With Paul Cram, John Cromwell, Mitch Hansen, Ryan Harper. KANDIYOHI is an action packed modern-day western that brings the sleepy backdrop of rural Minnesota alive with violence and suspense. This breakout debut from writer and director Nicholas Engan tells the story of three down-on-their-luck friends drifting through life in their late-20s. After reconnecting during a visit to their hometown, a rapid spiral of drugs, shame, and betrayal will leave them with only one unbelievable option -- to rob the town's corrupt sheriff. When their plan goes fatally wrong, this group of friends will be pushed to the limit trying to outrun the law and its harsh brand of vengeance. It's all on the line in a cinematically stunning finale that will blow audiences away.

title: Reckless Abandon
synopsis: Directed by Christopher Martin. With R.K. Anderson, Greg Bronson, Jaron Druyon, Ron Ferguson. A story about responsibility, revenge and redemption

title: Akecheta
synopsis: Directed by Joey Orosco, Jose Orosco. With Veronica Pierce, Andy Andersen, Lupe Trejo, Russ Ives. A Native American Sioux Indian Akecheta is forced to become chief at the crooked hands of Sheriff Dan Brock when his village is slaughtered. He sets out on a journey to retrieve his one and only love Nahimana who was brutally taken by Sheriff Dan Brock and his right hand man Daroll McKintey. On Akecheta's journey he stumbles upon a man Job who is destituted and left to die and who was betrayed by his best friend Daroll McKintey. Job and Akecheta team up together to settle the score and get back what was rightfully theirs and causing havoc along the way.

title: Beaverland
synopsis: Directed by Antonio Luco, Nicolás Molina. Derek and Giorgia, a young couple of biologists, settles in the hostile Tierra del Fuego to study and combat the devastating beaver plague that destructs the area. This violent mission is a unique scenario for their love story.

title: Isle of Chimps
synopsis: With Melissa Exelberth. A colorful portrait of Uganda's Ngamba Island Chimpanzee Sanctuary, a place where orphaned and rescued chimpanzees - victims of the illegal exotic pet and bushmeat trades - are given a second chance at life in a community of chimps.

title: Abgetorft! Legen deutsche Unternehmer das Baltikum trocken?
synopsis: Directed by Susanne Brahms, Rainer Krause. With Kevin Behr, Robert Levin. Without peat no vegetables, plant production is not possible without peat. The world market leader is a company based in Emsland. This now obtains the raw material on a large scale from the Baltic States. In order to cover our demand for peat, they will eventually dry up intact moors there, warns moor expert Hans Joosten. This is a first-class environmental mess, because dry moors are a problem for climate protection, they emit enormous amounts of greenhouse gases. Hans Joosten therefore demands

title: Par monts et villages
synopsis: Directed by Lisa Sallustio.

title: Corona Extra TV Commercial Featuring Jon Gruden
synopsis: Directed by Dylan Verrechia. With Jon Gruden.

title: Droidema
synopsis: Directed by Jedd Lupoy. With Goo-Fed, Braigar, Alvin Lai. Dr Starns sends his daughter, Emma, to Lakewood Research Centre to show her a bleedingly-new discovery that could transform both of their lives. It all comes down to Dr Lionel as to whether the experiment will work or not.

title: Bad Blood
synopsis: Directed by Michael Yebba. With George Carroll, Evalena Marie, Michael Yebba.

title: Equinox
synopsis: Directed by Martin Sommerdag. With Rene Hansen. A documentary about a man and his spiritual journey. He is stuck in limbo, a place between heaven and earth.

title: My Uncle Hector
synopsis: Directed by Darlena Roberts. With Harrison Cade, Olivia Cade, Dom DeLuise, Susan Feniger. Uncle Hector is one of the most famous people in the world, but nobody knows he's real.

title: Pixel Theory: La Caja de Pandora
synopsis: La Caja de Pandora

title: Don't You Be Afraid
synopsis: Directed by John W. Mader. With Mike Muratore. Don't You Be Afraid was recorded in the middle of a heat wave in Los Angeles in 2010. Mike Muratore's style has earned him the moniker "The Serial Killer of Comedy". Find out why by watching this comedy special.

title: Lady Ganga: Nilza's Story
synopsis: Nilza's Story

title: The Walk Around the World
synopsis: Directed by Jordan Tappis. With Karl Bushby. Former British Paratrooper Karl Bushby embarks on a year-long journey to walk - one step at a time - 3,600 miles from the Pacific shores of Los Angeles to the steps of the Russian Embassy in Washington D.C. His goal

title: Sterling Silver
synopsis: Directed by Brian K. Palmer. With Brian K. Palmer, Paul Casali, Natasha Lahera, James Sjurson.

title: Bref, les 30 ans de Canal+
synopsis: Directed by Kyan Khojandi, Bruno Muschio. With Kyan Khojandi, Samuel Aouizerate, Solal Forte, Florence Fauquet.

title: The Hunt
synopsis: Directed by Oz Yilmaz. Peter's modus operandi is he works alone with a selection of classic music, preferably opera. On the very day of my visit, opera was the choice of music setting the tone of our interview. His various trinkets around the atelier indicated a life fully lived. Of course, this made me wonder why would a man who has had this joie de vivre return to the places that were remote. He indicated that his solitude was what allowed him to see nature's subtle play on colours. Brush stroke after brush stroke of laying colours until it took hues of golden rays caress on an autumn day made all the more sense. This was Peter's vision which he took as souvenirs from these lands and transplanted them in his studio. His diligent appliance of colours created a harmony in his paintings that is perhaps lost on today's art scene. Louder, bolder, more shocking seems to be the theme of the day. As jarring as this is, the world can do with some balancing of yin yang, how about some classic rendition of landscapes.

title: Amanda McKay
synopsis: Directed by Mark Haber. With Farrah Mackenzie, Andy Mackenzie, Sasha Alexander, Chris Yule. Autism isn't Amanda McKay's biggest problem - it's her own father.

title: Gander: America's Hero Dog
synopsis: America's Hero Dog

title: The Orange Tune
synopsis: Directed by Martin Sommerdag. With Inga Maria Eyjolfsdottir. An experimental story about the danger of daily routines and how hard it is to break free from once comfort zone.

title: Gilda Vomit
synopsis: Directed by Michael Patrick Rogers. With Chip Carriere, Becca Nicole Preston, Ronnie Hooks.

title: Maxxx
synopsis: Directed by O-T Fagbenle. With Helen Monks, Nonso Anozie, Ayesha Antoine, Hannah Arterton. A former star of a popular boyband longs for the life he once had before deciding to launch his solo career.

title: Searching for Anna May Wong
synopsis: Directed by Denise Chan, Z. Eric Yang. With Jake Choi, Jayden Ham, Amy Hill, James Hong. With the help of popular movie stars, this documentary tells the coming-of-age story of a young Chinese-American actress navigating the convoluted and narrow paths of Hollywood.

title: Lucky Me
synopsis: Directed by Thomas A. Morgan, Ibrahim Nada. With Guiseppe Pizano. 'Lucky Me' is a documentary profiling the life of Guiseppe Pizano, a young man abandoned by his mother at age 14. As a homeless youth, Guiseppe took up residence in bleachers of his high school and continued to attend class. He graduated with honors...and his story continues. He now has a TED talk in the works, a budding modeling career, and a story that will leave you cheering.

title: Pieces (2018)
synopsis: Directed by Avi Agarwal. With Avi Agarwal, David Light, Alex Lizotte. An intelligent guy with a simple life starts experiencing something inexplicable.

title: Deep Fried Gold: The Nashville Hot Chicken Movement
synopsis: The Nashville Hot Chicken Movement

title: Roofied 4: The Antidote
synopsis: The Antidote

title: The Sun's Gonna Shine
synopsis: Directed by Les Blank, Skip Gerson. With Lightnin Hopkins, Billy Bizor, Wendell Anderson. A lyrical recreation of Lightnin' Hopkins' decision at age eight to stop chopping cotton and start singing for a living. Folklorist/Ethnomusicologist Alan Lomax called Blank's stunning and elegiac short on Hopkins' reminiscences of his youth "one of the three most important films on the South." Color. 10 minutes. 1969.

title: Kokoa
synopsis: Directed by Moustapha Alassane.

title: Symphony 92.4 FM
synopsis: Directed by Eric Khoo. With Chiew Sung Ching. Story of the lonely old man who commits suicide on his birthday.

title: The History of the World Episode 16 the Invention of Writing and Its Destruction
synopsis: Directed by Phil Mulloy.

title: Everyday
synopsis: Directed by Hans Richter. With Sergei Eisenstein, Michael Hankinson, Basil Wright. An abstract look at daily life in London.

title: Landscape with the Fall of Icarus
synopsis: Directed by Chris Sullivan. In Pieter Bruegel's painting, "Landscape with the Fall of Icarus," the fall of the god, Icarus, passes unnoticed on earth. The farmers continue to work the land and the boats sail on. As William Carlos Williams later wrote in his poem of the same name, "a once mighty god becomes a little splash quite unnoticed." In Chris Sullivan's version, Icarus becomes Ray, an aging priest whose congregation is dwindling as fast as his sanity. As Ray's condition deteriorates, society fails to notice or care.

title: June Turmoil
synopsis: Directed by Zelimir Zilnik. With Dragoljub Micunovic, Dragoljub Vojnov, Stevo Zigon. The film is documenting student demonstrations in Belgrade in June 1968. It was shot for the most part in the court of Kapetan Misino Zdanje (Faculty of Philosophy building), where students gathered up and where famous artists participated thus showing solidarity with the students.

title: Here I Am
synopsis: Directed by Bruce Baillie. A sensitive, low-key portrait of the East Bay Activity Center, a school in Oakland, California, started in the 1950s to help emotionally disturbed children.

title: La maison aux images
synopsis: Directed by Jean Grémillon. At a Montmartre workshop, crafts people cut by hand, emboss,do various kinds of engraving, and make etchings.

title: The Way to Shadow Garden
synopsis: Directed by Stan Brakhage. With Walter Newcomb. This way madness - or experimental filmmaking - lies. A solitary man in coat and tie enters an apartment that may be a converted garage. It's midnight. He appears agitated and distraught. He throws a glass of water in his face and laughs. He takes off the coat and tie. His moods swing. He stares at a light bulb. He removes his shirt. He lights a cigarette. He looks at a book. He does something drastic and self-destructive. He opens doors to a garden that we see as a film's negative. We see his face as if peering around a plant. The garden doors close behind him.

title: Swingers' Serenade
synopsis: Directed by Danny Plotnick. With Chris Enright, Jay Hinman, Alison Faith Levy, Miles Montalbano.

title: Become an Artist
synopsis: Directed by William Farley, George Manupelli, Don Novello. With Don Novello. Satirizes television pitches, art schools, and the self-importance of artists.

title: Kindering
synopsis: Directed by Stan Brakhage. With Iona Bartek, Quay Bartek. Refracted images, not unlike those in a funhouse mirror, display two children playing in a backyard, a boy and a girl. There's a dog, a swing, a picket fence, a Big Wheels trike. The grass is green and lush. A soundtrack mixes a chorus, swelling strings, and a child vocalizing. The effect is to idealize the images.

title: Ice Cream Sundae
synopsis: Directed by Désirée Nosbusch. With Michael J. Sheridan, Tippi Hedren, Kat Ogden, Joe Rabl.

title: Edie: Girl on Fire
synopsis: Girl on Fire

title: Great Bear Rainforest
synopsis: Directed by Rebekah Jorgensen, Ian McAllister, Marc Griffith. With James Cromwell, Ian McAllister, Ryan Reynolds. Hidden from the outside world, the Great Bear Rain-forest is one of the wildest places left on earth. For the first time ever, experience this magical world in IMAX and giant screen theaters, and discover the land of the spirit bear.

title: Stella
synopsis: Directed by Sofia Sondervan. With Tamara Van Witzenburg, Baruch Schwartz, Richard Smolenaers, Roland de Jonge. During WWII a Jewish woman travels through Holland to find food for her starving husband and meets up with a German deserter.

title: The Devil's Work
synopsis: Directed by Zlatko Grgic. When a man is constantly punished for his good deeds, he proceeds to fight back with a potion.

title: Venice, Feeding the Pigeons in St. Mark's Square
synopsis: With William K.L. Dickson.

title: The Sexlife of a Chair
synopsis: Directed by Phil Mulloy.

title: Cowboys: Outrage!
synopsis: Outrage!

title: Cowboys: That's Nothin'
synopsis: That's Nothin'

title: Cowboys: The Conformist
synopsis: The Conformist

title: Death of a Nation
synopsis: Directed by Michael Pollak. With Jon Cohn, Brian Robinson, Kyle Riley, Daron Ross. A powerful film that examines the "progress" of our present day culture through the eyes of the oppressor.

title: Turning It Over

synopsis: Directed by Raman Turhan. With Raman Turhan. The film deals with themes such as immigration, cultural and religious diversity. The message of the film is not to do to others what you would not want done to yourself. And as the character says "be careful because one day you could be in my place."

title: Selflove
synopsis: Directed by Julian Reich. With Ainaz Azarhoush, Juan Hasan. If creativity was a person living inside of you, would it change the way you treat yourself?

synopsis: Directed by Raman Turhan. With Raman Turhan. A major arms dealer has had a luxurious life - thanks to his work. One evening while in a very exclusive place having dinner with his beautiful girlfriend, he loses his temper and yells at all the local customers that they too have great personalities of power and wealth. Finally, he vents by saying to them everything he wanted to say in an entire lifetime. But in the end he discovers a shocking truth that "nothing is as it seems ..."

When they come face-to-face in the small town of Bellingham, they fail to connect, and are left to wander the coastline-- basking in the luminosity of their shared despair.

According to the Sumerians, the alien Gods left a hidden DNA sequence within us - humans, and if we knew how to access it, we can unleash the power from within. Kai Quast (Eric Roberts) had a heart attack but somehow, he stopped his own death and ever since he is searching for answers. He gets visited in his dreams by the ancient Sumerian Serpent God - Enki, who comes down to earth, takes the physical form and shows Kai how to unleash the God's DNA and join Enki. Kai abandons his failing marriage and the chemical recreation of youth potion he is working on to explore the wondrous journey offered by Enki.

Then Mingtian orders Jin Ling, one of his disciples, to poison everyone on Kunlun Mountain. To save Yunqiao, Shen Gongbao sneaks into Motun Mountain with an invisibility cloak, and learns that Yunqiao knows how to destroy the universe. To stop Mingtian, Jiang Ziya and the others came to Motun Mountain and prevent a disaster from occurring in the human world.

The three of them, together with other demon-subduing masters, went to Yunzhan Cave to get rid of the culprit, a pig demon aged over 1,000 years. Along the way, they defeated a lot of demons and overcame all the difficulties in the way. In the end, Ashi let the others fight their way through the last pass at the cost of his own life, but the results were unexpected.

On the way of escape, Zhang Xiaozhi and Qian Yan'er save the heroine Bajiao accidentally. But unexpectedly, they fall into another trap delicately set by Wanyan. It's extremely dangerous in the tomb. By accident, Zhang Xiaozhi initiates the Holy Dragon Plate. The Holy Dragon is woken up, and large number of zombie throng out. Zhang Xiaozhi and Qian Yan'er are once again surrounded by crises.

The two monkeys carelessly fall from it, but saved by Long Ruyi, who mistakenly takes Monkey Ji as the Six-Eared Monkey, and falls in love with him. Out of jealousy, the Six-Eared Monkey is enticed by a snake demon, and kills the old monkey. The two monkey spirits become enemies and have a fight. The Heavenly Court punishes them and by following the Bodhisattva's advice, Monkey Ji protects Tang Sanzang on the journey westward. But when he is driven away by Tang Sanzang, the Six-Eared Monkey arrives.

Tianpeng met Bao'er, a monster hunter and her teammates in the mortal world. They go on journey to find the Five Finger Mountain. The journey is filled with twists and turns and Tianpeng gets to understand the great love, thus becoming a great man after experiencing all those hardships and difficulties.

Bai Yutan receives the news that there is the magic herb for treating internal injury in Tanzhou, so he heads for Tanzhou. On the way, he saves Qiaoqiao and Hong'er and the three people travel together. Bai Yutang and Qiaoqiao fall in love with each other. After they arrive in Tanzhou, Bai Yutang learns that Qiaoqiao is the fugitive of the theft of pearl. He chooses to believe Qiaoqiao and help her to redress the injustice. They sneak into the villa of Ren Zhuan to investigate the case, and find that Ren Zhuan is the mastermind of the theft. Bai Yutang hands over the evidence of the crime to the imperial government and Qiaoqiao's family are cleared.

He's considered as a "dangerous element" by the villagers and the head Hu. The Monster Nian, comes to the human world by accident and takes away the lion head, the village's heirloom. While trying to get the lion head back, Luo Chuan gets to know Axi, the Immortal Mouse, that comes to the mortal world to catch the Monster Nian. They gradually realize Nian is not scary at all and can make friends with humans, but Hu makes a plot against Nian after being possessed by the Spirit-Devouring Demon. In the end, Luo Chuan and Axi, together with other villagers, defeat the Spirit-Devouring Demon and awakens Hu.

King of Heng sends Chen Xuan to Yunlai Town to supervise Ye Celeng and find out the truth. They accidentally meet Yunshan and Ye Celeng pretends to have never met her before. There's blood demon in Yunlai Town and the faked Taoists Ji Chen and his master cheat the people there out of their money by pretending to kill the blood demon for them, and then get saved by Ye Celeng. Xie Rou's brother Xie Changsheng is attracted by the beauty of Bai Shanshui. He pretends to be an official Xuan Wu and goes to the inn to pursue Bai Shanshui. And Bai Shanshui mistakes Xie Changsheng as Xuan Wu who she wants to see. Two martial arts masters and Xie Rou also come to the inn. A battle-weary ex-Special Forces Operative buys a ranch in remote American West to flee from the world, and encounters a strange series of trespassers, including a beautiful elf princess and a Native American mystic and Orcs. When the Orcs invade his property, John must give up his isolation to become a hero, before the Orcs unleash their dragon god on our world.

title: Sins of the Dragon
synopsis: Directed by Joey Corpora. With Connor Corpora, Joey Corpora, Brennen Dickerson, Brandon Frankenfield. In a world of martial arts and magic, a dark assassin seeks the power of the four "Dragons," martial arts masters of supernatural strength. When his actions cause the death of a young man's family, his downfall becomes inevitable.

title: Devudu Chesina Manushulu
synopsis: Directed by Puri Jagannadh. With Ravi Teja, Ileana D'Cruz, Mohammad Ali, Brahmanandam. The gods get involved in mortal struggles, turning back time to rewrite small histories and spread happiness to mortals and immortals alike.

title: Dorothy and the Witches of Oz
synopsis: Directed by Leigh Scott. With Paulie Rojas, Eliza Swenson, Billy Boyd, Christopher Lloyd. Dorothy Gale discovers that her best selling novels are actually based on suppressed childhood memories of her time in Oz, and that she may be in danger of experiencing it all over again.

title: Orion
synopsis: Directed by Asiel Norton. With David Arquette, Lily Cole, Maren Lord, Goran Kostic. In a desolate, future world, after civilization has collapsed, a wanderer fights to save a virgin mother from a powerful magician and, with her, searches for a mythical city containing the world's last survivors.

title: The Mummy
synopsis: Directed by Alex Kurtzman. With Tom Cruise, Russell Crowe, Annabelle Wallis, Sofia Boutella. An ancient Egyptian princess is awakened from her crypt beneath the desert, bringing with her malevolence grown over millennia, and terrors that defy human comprehension.

title: Demon God
synopsis: Directed by Sean Klisiewecz. With Jennifer Brown, Shannon Brown, Aviane Herbst, Robb Herbst. A disillusioned detective struggles to uncover the sinister secret behind a mysterious cult and embarks on a journey of apocalyptic revelation and personal salvation.

synopsis: The Day the Old West Stood Still

title: Avenged

synopsis: Directed by Alex Proyas. With Brenton Thwaites, John Samaha, Courtney Eaton, Nikolaj Coster-Waldau. Mortal hero Bek teams with the god Horus in an alliance against Set, the merciless god of darkness, who has usurped Egypt's throne, plunging the once peaceful and prosperous empire into chaos and conflict.

title: Unearthly
synopsis: Directed by Robert McCallum. With Phil Andros, Danica Barker, Johnny Bobesich, Spencer Cagan. After his daughter disappears in search of a mystic medallion, Malcolm vows to get her back even if that means entering a zone full of unspeakable evils, horrific creatures and images that haunt his nightmares.

title: A Sweet and Vicious Beauty
synopsis: Directed by Eric Thornett. With Bette Cassatt, Sara Cole, Brenden McDougal, Omar Ott. In the town of Harbor Bridge, it is said that when someone dies, his last breath stays in his throat. When the head is severed, that last breath can be taken by another, and the recipient becomes stronger. Narcissa Sentinel (Bette Cassatt) has been robbing graves to cure her illness with these last breaths...but soon realizes that perhaps fresher specimens are in order. Shot locally, A SWEET AND VICIOUS BEAUTY is an epic Gothic Victorian movie that shows the journey of Sentinel from a sickly woman to a bloodthirsty mass murderer who terrorizes the town. From spooky old houses to headless zombies, this film has it all!

title: Young Blood: Evil Intentions
synopsis: Evil Intentions

Young children with special powers are recruited to lead the fight. 13 years later, 5 special people must come together as one to save the day for humanity.

title: Ultra Reinforcement
synopsis: Directed by Tze-Chung Lam. With Wallace Huo, Tian Jing, Dylan Kuo, Tze-Chung Lam. Er Dan (Wallace Huo) accidentally traveled to the past to Tang Dynasty. In Tang Dynasty he met Shi Ke Jin (Dylan Luo) whom his elder brother Shi Ke Yan wanted to kill him. Without a doubt he tried to save Shi Ke Jin and brought him back to the future. Because Shi Ke Jin knows so much about the future, he decided to go back to kill his brother and conquer the world. When ErDan discovered his intention, he intended to go back to Tang Dynasty to stop his plan.

synopsis: Directed by Alexi Reibman, Jessie Alperin, Tayler Stander. With Conrad Buys, Ava Caiola, Shawn Contois, Emma Corfman. This student production was produced, shot, and edited by Alexi Reibman. The script was written by Jessie Alperin and Tayler Stander. There have always been two sides in our world; the light and the dark. Our world has been slowly changing and transforming, but one thing has always stayed the same; Our land and our people have been split into two. One with light, while the other remains in the darkness. The founders, the people who made our world this way, created a box and called it the source. It contains all the power. Whichever side has the source, owns the power, whilst the other side remains without it - living in the shadows.

He has a crush on Nana, a popular girl who's also the object of desire of Trai, the college's chief bully. When Trai finds out that Guy is also in love with the girl of his dreams, he reveals himself as a wolf and hurts his love rival. To fight back, Guy enlists the help of a mysterious boy named Zen.

title: Throwback
synopsis: Directed by Travis Bain. With Shawn Brack, Anthony Ring, Melanie Serafin, Vernon Wells. Two treasure hunters, a park ranger and an unhinged ex-cop tangle with a Yowie, the Australian Bigfoot, deep in the jungles of Far North Queensland.

title: Kamen Rider Wizard in Magic Land
synopsis: Directed by Shôjirô Nakazawa. With Shun'ya Shiraishi, Makoto Okunaka, Junki Tozuka, Yûko Takayama. title: Destroyer Prince
synopsis: Directed by Curtis Everitt. With Heather Barnes, Amelia Blue, Aaron Brown, Dexter Brown. The Wanderer is the old king who is overthrown by his bodyguards, and he seeks vengeance for the murder of his queen while providing safety for the future of his comatose son.

title: Hemoglobin
synopsis: Directed by Eddie Frente. With Luke Massy, Tina Balthazar, Sandy Tejada, Pascal Yen-Pfister. In a future where humans, zombies and vampires inhabit the earth, peace is hard to come by. A battle weary vampire General tries to leave the fighting behind - but soon learns that the war is everywhere. After he loses his wife to a mysterious band of murderers, he begins a hunt that reveals more than he - or anyone else - expected.

title: Atomic Kingdom: Revolution
synopsis: Revolution

title: Daylight's End
synopsis: Directed by William Kaufman. With Johnny Strong, Lance Henriksen, Louis Mandylor, Hakeem Kae-Kazim. Years after a mysterious plague has turned most of humanity into blood-hungry creatures, a vengeful drifter takes up with a group of survivors in an abandoned police station.

title: Takao Dancer
synopsis: Directed by Wenshing Ho, Ouchul Hwang. With Kly Huang, Young Pan, Kun-Yi Teng. In this timeless portrait of love and friendship, directors Wen-Shing Ho and Hwang Ouchul tenderly observe the human condition. Yi, Chi and Kong have been inseparable since childhood. Growing up on the Taiwanese seaside, Chi and Kong promise to bring Yi sunken treasure from a nearby shipwreck, but get trapped under water. Nine years later, yearning to escape to the big city, Kong devises a plan -- rob his father for the cash. Again, the plan goes awry. Another nine years later finds Kong and Yi in the big city. Chi, now a fugitive, re-emerges on their wedding day. The men fight, causing Yi to fall from the wedding yacht into the water, where she encounters the still trapped boys and sets them free.

title: Mystic Blade
synopsis: Directed by David Ismalone. With Jawed El Berni, Don Ferguson, David Ismalone, Julaluck Ismalone. Sam is a killer by trade, one of a group of merciless men known as the Shadow Syndicate whose business is delivering fate for a price. But when Sam is asked to erase the line between honor and evil, he turns his back on the Shadows knowing this will make him a wanted man. After years of hiding in the hills of Thailand, Sam falls in love with a beautiful Thai girl (Mali) and fathers a son (Shiro). Sam and his family live a simple and happy life fishing and living off the land. But he can't run away from the past and soon finds out what happens when you cross the Shadow Syndicate. Sam and his wife are left for dead on a violent and bloody night . They think they have taken everything from him until cries from Shiro bring Sam back to the world of the living. Now with something worth fighting for and a thirst for vengeance ; Sam forges a mystical blade from the ashes of his one great love. Sam and Shiro embark on a journey across the globe to track down these evil men one by one to have their revenge.

title: Ninja Apocalypse
synopsis: Directed by Lloyd Lee Barnett. With Christian Oliver, Les Brandt, Cary-Hiroyuki Tagawa, Ernie Reyes Jr.. Framed for assassinating the Grandmaster, the Lost Ninja Clan must fight their way up an underground nuclear bunker filled with hordes of supernatural enemies, mutants, and flesh-eating zombies.

title: Irandam Ulagam
synopsis: Directed by K. Selvaraghavan. With Arya, Anushka Shetty, Jaya Bachchan, Venkatesh Harinathan. Madhu, a mathematician, becomes depressed after the unexpected deaths of his girlfriend and father. However, when he tries to commit suicide, his look-alike takes him to an unnamed exoplanet.

title: The Declassified
synopsis: Directed by Eric Edwards Abud. With Eric Edwards Abud, Heather Dorff, Erin Breen, Brandon Galatz. Four friends from different Worlds clash contrasting personalities in a perception of reality. This group of personalities sets out to document their lives and discover what it means to be real. Parallel story lines intertwine and develop towards one coming of life climax. Psychological mystery and suspense unravel in a society that has lost a grip on what reality is, causing the thin line between to bleed.

title: The Snow Queen
synopsis: Directed by Rene Perez. With Nadia Lanfranconi, Iren Levy, Aurelia Scheppers, David Reinprecht. A mysterious presence has threatened humanity for hundreds of years as it lurks in the frozen wastes people avoid. It takes two groups of adventurers, separated in time, to defeat her and the army of demons and monsters she can summon.

title: The Last One
synopsis: Directed by Lee Thongkham. With Jimmy Dempster, Luis Valladares, Benny Bernard Jr., Kim Santiago. A post-apocalyptic tale of Hope, Faith, Death, and the discovery of humanity last breath for survival.

title: The Demon's Odyssey

When a Shape-Shifting God is exiled to Earth to live out his life as a Demon, he discovers an unborn half-human, half-vampire baby that he thinks could be his ticket back to Godhood. The vampire, Alucard and his human bride, Brigit and their friends hire a Monster Hunter named Van Keizer to stop the Demon.

title: The Journey to Aresmore
synopsis:
Directed by Adam Starks. With Joshua Copeland, Adam Starks. The Journey to Aresmore follows the story of two 17 year old boys (Peter Townsend and Jack Cunningham) mysteriously taken into another world Known as Elithior. A world full of magic and mythical creatures, although they soon begin to realize that their story is unlike any fairytale. In order to get home, the two must make their way to the kingdom of Aresmore whilst hunted by the evil army of Falroar, a corrupt wizard with his mind set on ruling Elithior and enslaving its people.

After months of traveling through the harsh wastelands of Elithior, both Jack and Peter begin to understand that there is a greater power at work and they are faced with decisions that puts their morals to the test

title: Morning Star
synopsis: Directed by Luca Boni, Marco Ristori. With Adrian Bouchet, Mike Mitchell, Ivy Corbin, Daniel Vivian. In a battle a dying prince asks a warrior to relay news of his death to his father, the king. Now the Warrior must make his way to fulfill his promise.

title: The Wrath of Vajra
synopsis: Directed by Wing-Cheong Law. With Xing Yu, Sung-jun Yoo, Heon Jun Nam, Baocheng Jiang. Before the West entered World War II, a Japanese death cult called the Temple of Hades is ordered to aid in the spiritual destruction of China. Their method - abduct their enemies' children and train them as killers for the Emperor. Young Vajra was especially gifted, but swears a secret oath of revenge when his brother dies. Now the greatest assassin in the temple, Vajra escapes to China and begins his quest to protect the innocent, and destroy the ones responsible for making him a living weapon. A former Shaolin monk, martial arts action star Xing Yu (aka Shi Yanneng) stars as Vajra in his first leading role.

It ends fictionally in present-day Oakland, CA, addressing very real issues in the life of a present-day Black Man in the United States.

Kaia, after becoming an adult, decides to leave her gypsy community, and sets out alone on a journey to find and rescue Reka.

He knows that Yuri is condemned to die in a car accident. To save the woman, Chasuke goes down to this world.

Meanwhile a mysterious yet violent girl named Josephine (Paula Solinger) holds the box while on the run from the deranged cult she once belonged to. Hot on her trail are two crooked cops (Fred Doss and Stephen Brodie) and a psychotic bounty hunter named Coffin. Their paths ultimately collide in an explosion of blood soaked chaos, leaving our anti-heroes to decide whether this box is worth their lives.

title: Kamen Rider Gaim: Great Soccer Battle! Golden Fruits Cup!
synopsis: Directed by Osamu Kaneda. With Gaku Sano, Yutaka Kobayashi, Mahiro Takasugi, Yûmi Shida. Gaim is taken into a new Zawame City, where soccer is immensely popular and the teams aim to win the All Rider Cup where the reward is the golden fruit. Along with the City restored, he sees many things that different from his city before.

title: Angel of Death
synopsis: Directed by Taavi Peelo. With Katie Wood, Taavi Peelo, Mark Hindman Smith, Paul Cavendish. Nastja's father Constantine thought he has found the cure to save people from sickness and death but everything has a price in this world. It was a curse that turns people into who they are not - monsters, as we all know vampires. After Constantine realised the truth about the cure he decided to destroy it but he was betrayed by his apprentice Bastian. Blinded by the greed and power Bastian kills Constantine and steals the cure to become a vampire himself. Nastja, daughter of Constantine promised on her father's grave to find Bastian and make him suffer for everything he has done. Nastja knew she have no chance against the vampire so she decided to become one herself. But first, she had to die.

title: The Black Fables

With the anthological meeting between four of the most important names in the Brazilian horror

synopsis: Directed by Chimbudeven. With Joseph Vijay, Sridevi, Sudeep, Prabhu. A virtuous soldier tries to save people from an evil queen and a throne-seeking commander.

title: The Amazing Praybeyt Benjamin
synopsis: Directed by Wenn V. Deramas. With Vice Ganda, James Bimby Aquino, Richard Yap, Alex Gonzaga. A soldier who once saved the entire country is assigned to guard a genius child whose intellect is needed to foil the plans of an evil villain.

title: The Secret Flute: Garo Side-Story
synopsis: Tougen no fue

title: Tokyo Grand Guignol
synopsis: Directed by Nicolas Alberny, François Gaillard, Gilles Landucci, Yann Moreau. With Hiroyuki Amemiya, Akiko An, Rei Atsumi, Mina Chung. A man repeats the same day running from the Yakuza. A woman encounters her violent mirror image. A woman and her laser gun fight a shadow demon. And a man is cursed to become a werewolf pining for a prostitute.

title: In April
synopsis: Directed by Carlo Bruno. With Lily Blane, Carlo Bruno, Marina Bruno, Michael Earle Caza. A man drives away from home waiting for that moment to opt for suicide. On the verge of insanity, he discovers a strange travel companion. Catchphrase

title: Consciousness
synopsis: Directed by Emmanuel Fabiyi. With Rebecca-Clare Evans, Jason Redshaw, David Roy, Catherine Stobbs. The battle between two angelic warriors for the revelational seals that belong to the unknown prophets.

title: Velociraptor McQuade
synopsis: Directed by Peter Murfet. With Marcus Caballero, Sharif Elboushi, Toni Miles, Peter Murfet.

title: Baji
synopsis: Directed by Nikhil Mahajan. With Shreyas Talpade, Amruta Khanvilkar, Jitendra Joshi, Ila Bhate. It is an action-adventure laced superhero vigilante film that transcends both folklore and present day. It is based on the legend of a man who took upon himself to protect the common man against oppression and injustice.

title: Voice of the Vespers
synopsis: Directed by Matthew Van Howe. With Petro Andryvyz, Kyle Dal Santo, Kate Froehlich, Derek Garza. Reservoir Dogs meets Star Wars in a micro-budget, science fiction / action film full of intrigue, betrayal, and spirit. Join in the struggle of Salem as he desperately searches for his Vesper. His very soul is at stake as Dartagnon and his minions attempt to stop him at every turn. From dangerous experiments to the mind-bending reality of the Elder Flex, Voice of the Vespers is a unique world with extraordinary characters that keeps you questioning their loyalties until the end.

title: Yoddha the Warrior
synopsis: Directed by Raj Chakraborty. With Dev, Nigel Akkara, Mimi Chakraborty, Rajatabha Dutta. Yoddha The Warrior is a Bengali action historical-romance movie of 2014. The film is a remake of 2009 Telugu blockbuster movie Magadheera featuring Ram Charan Teja and Kajal Agarwal. The film is directed by Raj Chakraborty. In the film, Dev will be seen opposite Mimi Chakraborty for the first time. Shree Venkatesh Films is producing the film who also produce Chander Pahar which was the biggest earned film in tollywood, which was Starring by Dev.The film is releasing to break the previous record of Chander Pahar.

title: Hostile
synopsis: Directed by Nathan Ambrosioni. With Anatolia Allieis, Nathan Ambrosioni, Vanessa Azzopardi, Didier Beaumont. Anna and Emilie are 14 and 15. They are sisters and orphans. Hardly have they been in their new home when a strange event turns their world upside down.

title: Underworld
synopsis: Directed by Josef von Sternberg, Arthur Rosson. With George Bancroft, Evelyn Brent, Clive Brook, Fred Kohler. Boisterous gangster kingpin Bull Weed rehabilitates his former lawyer from his alcoholic haze, but complications arise when he falls for Weed's girlfriend.

title: The Docks of New York
synopsis: Directed by Josef von Sternberg. With George Bancroft, Betty Compson, Olga Baclanova, Clyde Cook. A blue-collar worker on New York's depressed waterfront finds his life changed after he saves a woman attempting suicide.

title: The Racket
